00:10:21.566 --> 00:10:24.660
We are supporting digital
inclusion and engaging

3971138521
00:10:24.661 --> 00:10:27.207
expert grassroots organisations

2318604088
00:10:27.208 --> 00:10:29.265
directly to help ensure that we get this

2689220411
00:10:29.266 --> 00:10:30.971
right and that they are included.

3869479892
00:10:30.972 --> 00:10:33.255
Josh Babarinde thank you, Mr.

85163131
00:10:33.256 --> 00:10:33.706
Speaker.

2958583219
00:10:33.707 --> 00:10:35.411
NHS Sussex found that Eastbourne,

992365603
00:10:35.412 --> 00:10:37.569
despite being the sunniest town in the UK,

1163912994
00:10:39.507 --> 00:10:42.366
is one of the most digitally
excluded patches of Sussex.

1019468860
00:10:42.367 --> 00:10:44.773
There are great organisations
like Tech Resort,

3803750258
00:10:44.774 --> 00:10:46.831
run by Liz Crew and Will Callaghan doing

1384324098
00:10:46.832 --> 00:10:48.838
work to help bridge the digital divide.

46144848
00:10:50.507 --> 00:10:52.863
However, they will be
scuppered by the closing

1227744312
00:10:52.865 --> 00:10:56.261
of the Digital Inclusion Innovation Fund,

2280763377
00:10:56.262 --> 00:10:58.861
whose last grants expired last month.

4223673755
00:10:58.862 --> 00:11:00.968
So will the Ministers commit to reviewing

389199025
00:11:00.968 --> 00:11:02.724
whether that fund will be reopened

2471359376
00:11:02.725 --> 00:11:08.117
and set out a timeline for that
so Tech Resort can benefit?

3603626562
00:11:08.118 --> 00:11:08.569
The hon.

3988779376
00:11:08.570 --> 00:11:10.625
Gentleman raises a very important point,

3334623378
00:11:10.626 --> 00:11:14.213
and I know he has excellent
record in this area.

401942988
00:11:14.214 --> 00:11:17.474
The Digital Inclusion Fund was
designed for a one year programme

3761332025
00:11:17.475 --> 00:11:21.183
to understand what works
in digital inclusion.

4043984103
00:11:21.184 --> 00:11:23.892
I share the member's concerns
and we remain committed

1547900975
00:11:23.892 --> 00:11:26.048
to building a digitally inclusive society,

985378244
00:11:26.049 --> 00:11:29.963
including our public services, which
we are making more personalised,

4046448848
00:11:30.507 --> 00:11:32.563
joining up and digital so that everybody

121974284
00:11:32.564 --> 00:11:35.161
is included and benefits from them,

2586335820
00:11:35.162 --> 00:11:38.724
as we all expect our
public services to be as

854846635
00:11:38.725 --> 00:11:41.312
adequate and as inclusive as they can be.

583505214
00:11:41.313 --> 00:11:42.767
Fred Thomas question for Mr.

4010048965
00:11:42.767 --> 00:11:43.218
Speaker.

3666927817
00:11:44.508 --> 00:11:44.909
>> Sir.

2646463677
00:11:44.910 --> 00:11:49.569
>> Making it as simple as possible
for parents and children to get

3340571777
00:11:49.570 --> 00:11:53.063
involved in our consultation is
really important to me personally,

1962414195
00:11:53.064 --> 00:11:55.072
because I know this is an issue so many

625489495
00:11:56.507 --> 00:11:58.512
families grapple with every single day.

3742194707
00:11:58.513 --> 00:12:03.466
We've got dedicated surveys for
parents and young people, almost 38,

2864082171
00:12:03.508 --> 00:12:07.972
000 parents and 12,700 young people
have completed the surveys so far.

2292967867
00:12:07.973 --> 00:12:11.367
Alongside all the events I
and my Ministers have taken part in.

110836275
00:12:11.368 --> 00:12:16.471
But there is still a week to go,
so anybody who watches DSIT questions,

3033761978
00:12:16.472 --> 00:12:17.524
please get involved.

3689866047
00:12:17.525 --> 00:12:19.883
Answer because we want
to know what you think.

1851102502
00:12:19.884 --> 00:12:23.368
We want your views because
we've got to get this right.

1317584365
00:12:23.369 --> 00:12:25.610
>> Fred Thomas thank you, Mr.

2485078204
00:12:25.611 --> 00:12:26.061
Speaker.

2572574317
00:12:26.062 --> 00:12:29.512
>> I speak to parents in Plymouth
about this topic regularly.

474979777
00:12:29.513 --> 00:12:32.861
92% of parents are concerned about
the impact of social media,

3873683460
00:12:32.862 --> 00:12:36.714
but many just don't have time to
complete a lengthy consultation.

2362133810
00:12:36.715 --> 00:12:39.720
I'm also noting concerns
raised about the framing

383336946
00:12:39.721 --> 00:12:42.028
of some of the questions
in the consultation,

4229733994
00:12:42.029 --> 00:12:45.037
including prompts to consider
the benefits of social media,

801870305
00:12:45.038 --> 00:12:47.395
the absence of any clear
mechanism to consider

3596828326
00:12:47.396 --> 00:12:48.899
evidence from medical experts

1007303436
00:12:48.900 --> 00:12:52.107
and frontline professionals
separately to submissions from tech

1734433871
00:12:52.108 --> 00:12:54.664
companies who obviously
have a commercial interest

4273145585
00:12:54.665 --> 00:12:56.669
in opposing any potential restrictions,

1635130822
00:12:56.670 --> 00:12:58.928
and also the use of AI
to analyse responses.

3213391167
00:12:58.929 --> 00:13:02.089
So can the Secretary of State
confirm that these concerns will

55039202
00:13:02.090 --> 00:13:05.247
be taken into account when assessing
the consultation results,

146222694
00:13:05.249 --> 00:13:08.222
and reiterate her commitment to taking

1151031103
00:13:08.223 --> 00:13:11.514
bold and decisive action this summer?

330085561
00:13:11.515 --> 00:13:15.613
>> Let me just reassure him
on some of those points.

2166560995
00:13:15.615 --> 00:13:15.814
We.

1603409833
00:13:15.816 --> 00:13:18.374
We have had 38,000 parents
respond to the surveys,

2724424242
00:13:18.375 --> 00:13:22.267
which I think is good,
but there's more to be done there.

3698945080
00:13:22.269 --> 00:13:24.985
In terms of medical professionals.

2076281709
00:13:24.986 --> 00:13:28.273
We've had a response from
the Royal College of Psychiatrists,

3042941757
00:13:28.274 --> 00:13:30.913
multiple individual medical doctors,

2394187463
00:13:30.914 --> 00:13:33.258
health professionals for safer screens,

207275535
00:13:33.259 --> 00:13:36.563
and local providers like
Cardiff Children's Services.

35226027
00:13:36.564 --> 00:13:41.168
And we also have an expert panel
that includes that is chaired by

3666586776
00:13:41.169 --> 00:13:44.965
the eminent paediatrician professor
Professor Russell Viner,

1657090125
00:13:44.966 --> 00:13:47.321
and also many psychologists
and psychiatrists.

2991576314
00:13:47.322 --> 00:13:48.811
On that.

1186371448
00:13:48.812 --> 00:13:53.863
We are actively seeking views of
medical professionals and parents.

1098785773
00:13:53.863 --> 00:13:55.269
There's still a week to go.

3842211995
00:13:55.270 --> 00:13:55.771
Many hon.

2040824386
00:13:55.772 --> 00:13:59.716
Members have actually fed in individual
views from their constituencies,

4229222702
00:13:59.717 --> 00:14:03.328
and I'd encourage everybody to
do so in the remaining six days.

924596030
00:14:03.329 --> 00:14:04.734
>> Thank you very much, Mr.

2494261674
00:14:04.735 --> 00:14:05.185
Speaker.

3077909345
00:14:05.186 --> 00:14:08.017
A considerable number of
parents in my constituency

3895208303
00:14:08.019 --> 00:14:09.872
of Edinburgh West have written

745499447
00:14:09.872 --> 00:14:13.283
to me concerned about the children's
safety and the online dangers.

3396118291
00:14:13.284 --> 00:14:15.488
They welcome
the government's consultation,

3806728957
00:14:15.488 --> 00:14:17.545
but they are concerned about the timing.

547055319
00:14:17.546 --> 00:14:19.501
You would like some reassurances about

3442321236
00:14:19.502 --> 00:14:21.258
how quickly it will be dealt with,

821455302
00:14:21.511 --> 00:14:24.522
and if the Ministers has any
advice for them in time being,

1632518782
00:14:24.523 --> 00:14:27.613
and how they can help
the children deal with the threat.

1585370218
00:14:27.615 --> 00:14:30.122
>> Come forward with
proposals before the summer.

1317106781
00:14:30.122 --> 00:14:33.965
We have already taken powers
in the Children's Act

1583460027
00:14:33.966 --> 00:14:36.512
to implement the results
of their consultation,

2877816959
00:14:36.513 --> 00:14:41.363
which I intend to do by
the end of the year.

1416116164
00:14:41.365 --> 00:14:43.421
And in the meanwhile, we aren't waiting.

2265270663
00:14:43.421 --> 00:14:45.908
I've taken a number of
steps to amend various

1626237895
00:14:45.909 --> 00:14:47.563
acts to give greater protection,

3691848821
00:14:47.564 --> 00:14:51.961
and also produced a really brilliant
set of advice for parents.

1183599004
00:14:51.962 --> 00:14:54.321
You don't know until you
ask about how to talk

4905528
00:14:54.512 --> 00:14:56.819
to kids about social
media at different ages.

1606807005
00:14:56.820 --> 00:15:01.667
It's available free online and I have
personally found it very helpful.

500351029
00:15:01.668 --> 00:15:02.570
>> Iqbal Mohamed.

2920137066
00:15:02.571 --> 00:15:04.066
>> Thank you.

1115411913
00:15:04.067 --> 00:15:04.267
Mr.

2654428271
00:15:04.267 --> 00:15:05.370
Question number five.

3991239876
00:15:05.371 --> 00:15:05.972
Mr Speaker.

4053436479
00:15:05.973 --> 00:15:06.523
Ministers.

2522517985
00:15:06.524 --> 00:15:07.677
Well, there are three.

1771509143
00:15:07.678 --> 00:15:11.188
>> Particular things this government
is doing to make sure artificial

2497875107
00:15:11.189 --> 00:15:13.843
intelligence is developed
responsibly and developed.

233531964
00:15:13.845 --> 00:15:14.145
Here.

724911491
00:15:14.146 --> 00:15:17.805
One builds deep capability in government
with the AI Security Institute.

783673336
00:15:17.807 --> 00:15:20.767
Two to develop a wider AI
assurance sector so that Britain

1037989869
00:15:20.767 --> 00:15:22.976
is on the frontier in
that context as well.

144030302
00:15:22.977 --> 00:15:25.819
And three, robust regulation
at the point of use.

576564631
00:15:25.820 --> 00:15:27.668
>> Iqbal Mohamed you, Mr.

2548744312
00:15:27.669 --> 00:15:31.216
Speaker, given the growing
warnings from leading scientists,

2297448974
00:15:31.217 --> 00:15:34.968
industry figures and Nobel laureates,

2045276428
00:15:34.968 --> 00:15:37.924
that advanced AI systems
could pose existential risks

3044843241
00:15:37.925 --> 00:15:41.066
on a par with nuclear
or biological threats?

1791291143
00:15:41.067 --> 00:15:43.514
Does the Secretary of State agree with me

3106341356
00:15:43.515 --> 00:15:46.012
that the current reliance on voluntary

2082701263
00:15:46.013 --> 00:15:49.170
commitments through the AI Security
Institute is insufficient,

3995716090
00:15:49.171 --> 00:15:53.968
and will she outline what concrete
steps the government will now take

1491273568
00:15:53.968 --> 00:15:57.769
to move beyond non-binding agreements
and to introduce enforceable,

771288810
00:15:57.770 --> 00:15:59.472
internationally agreed standards.

1817625286
00:16:00.512 --> 00:16:01.265
>> To the hon.

2437823371
00:16:01.266 --> 00:16:05.272
Member that there are a series
of regulations at the point

2948651191
00:16:05.273 --> 00:16:08.676
of use that apply to AI
algorithms and systems as well.

3926654052
00:16:08.677 --> 00:16:11.035
Second, that we have taken
powers in the Crime

3432495589
00:16:11.036 --> 00:16:13.822
and Policing Act to allow
us to bring unregulated

3710781427
00:16:13.823 --> 00:16:15.629
chatbots into the scope of that act

3929435348
00:16:15.630 --> 00:16:17.685
and its requirements on illegal content.

517434613
00:16:17.686 --> 00:16:19.992
And third, through
the AI Security Institute,

990464915
00:16:19.993 --> 00:16:22.449
Britain has been at
the frontier internationally

1289970340
00:16:22.450 --> 00:16:24.555
on both think about policies and thinking

3821209637
00:16:24.557 --> 00:16:26.262
about the best ways of developing

708935967
00:16:26.263 --> 00:16:28.819
our capability across of
both mandatory regulatory

701220729
00:16:28.820 --> 00:16:30.675
contexts that I have just mentioned,

645887184
00:16:30.676 --> 00:16:33.786
and of course, some voluntary
requirements on top of that to.

4172274833
00:16:33.787 --> 00:16:34.789
>> Anneliese Dodds.

4234089844
00:16:34.790 --> 00:16:39.376
>> Mr Speaker S's pre-release
analysis of AI models did not prevent

473814337
00:16:39.377 --> 00:16:43.767
the production by grok of over
3 million sexualised images.

1236122518
00:16:45.522 --> 00:16:47.980
Even Steve Bannon, of all
people, is now calling

4117166388
00:16:47.981 --> 00:16:50.717
for mandatory pre-release
vetting of AI models.

3973939102
00:16:50.718 --> 00:16:53.270
So can I ask if the time has come for

2569708071
00:16:53.271 --> 00:16:55.327
the UK to review our voluntary approach?

60737585
00:16:55.328 --> 00:16:55.779
>> Well.

749530260
00:16:55.780 --> 00:16:57.223
>> Can I thank my hon.

2466664729
00:16:57.224 --> 00:17:00.965
Friend for having raised this topic
with deep expertise as well.

3513146363
00:17:00.966 --> 00:17:02.771
On the particular question of grok,

426605634
00:17:02.772 --> 00:17:04.828
she'll be very aware that the regulatory

529317849
00:17:04.829 --> 00:17:07.838
and legal context made a number
of those instances illegal.

4129954228
00:17:07.839 --> 00:17:11.250
We will continue to enforce very
robust law on those questions and,

74941708
00:17:11.251 --> 00:17:14.459
of course, develop our ongoing
conversations on further policy.

22062874
00:17:14.459 --> 00:17:16.064
>> Oliver Dowden thank you, Mr.

142856584
00:17:16.066 --> 00:17:16.516
Speaker.

3290848257
00:17:16.517 --> 00:17:19.175
Given the rapid advances we
are seeing recently from

1312842806
00:17:19.515 --> 00:17:21.921
frontier AI models in
areas such as identifying

4049126555
00:17:23.517 --> 00:17:26.814
software vulnerabilities
and rapid testing for those

4220126862
00:17:26.816 --> 00:17:29.071
vulnerabilities in
a very sophisticated way.

4280133472
00:17:29.516 --> 00:17:35.818
What engagement is the government
having with those frontier companies,

1393603616
00:17:35.819 --> 00:17:37.773
particularly in relation to anthropic?

4246585370
00:17:37.774 --> 00:17:39.868
And is the government considering making

1833828199
00:17:39.869 --> 00:17:41.574
changes to the carried over cyber

1918600760
00:17:41.575 --> 00:17:46.275
security bill to address these
very, very real vulnerabilities?

3347788221
00:17:46.276 --> 00:17:46.575
Well.

3216503045
00:17:46.577 --> 00:17:48.584
>> Can I on the question of engagement,

3035813479
00:17:48.584 --> 00:17:51.997
can I first point out and pay tribute
to the AI Security Institute,

742890222
00:17:51.997 --> 00:17:55.060
one of the only labs in the world
which had engaged with all

498149276
00:17:55.061 --> 00:17:57.767
the frontier companies prior
to deployment of models,

1135879058
00:17:57.769 --> 00:18:00.276
in this case with anthropic
mythos model as well.

2455359597
00:18:00.278 --> 00:18:03.638
On the broader question of the Cyber
Security and Resilience Bill,

920556859
00:18:03.639 --> 00:18:07.151
a major reason for bringing data
centres and scope in the way that we

694189102
00:18:07.153 --> 00:18:10.613
have done is to appreciate
the particular cyber risks apply to them.

3648365856
00:18:10.615 --> 00:18:12.822
We will continue to
keep that under review.

920754844
00:18:12.823 --> 00:18:14.822
>> Emily Darlington thank you, Mr.

2839277349
00:18:14.823 --> 00:18:15.273
Speaker.

1996919064
00:18:15.274 --> 00:18:19.523
One of the best ways to make
sure that AI is developed,

1685503766
00:18:19.524 --> 00:18:21.880
both contributing to
innovation and to growth,

1316970459
00:18:21.881 --> 00:18:24.572
is to set very high standards.

18705332
00:18:24.573 --> 00:18:27.281
We are lucky to have
the British Standards Institute,

3317908269
00:18:27.282 --> 00:18:29.718
the oldest standards
institute in the world,

1601370828
00:18:29.720 --> 00:18:33.171
and I'm very lucky that they
are based in Milton Keynes.

287803502
00:18:33.171 --> 00:18:35.971
Will he join me in wishing
them a huge happy

4220590743
00:18:35.972 --> 00:18:38.726
birthday on this momentous year for them?

2722438525
00:18:38.727 --> 00:18:44.622
But also, can he say what kind of
engagement he's had on their work

2746826353
00:18:44.622 --> 00:18:49.168
to set high re-assuring standards
for A's development here?

376245243
00:18:49.517 --> 00:18:49.968
>> Well.

3804169981
00:18:49.968 --> 00:18:50.671
>> My my hon.

1388395445
00:18:50.673 --> 00:18:54.170
Friend has been a remarkable
champion for the BSI,

1864540297
00:18:54.171 --> 00:18:56.831
and I know this on this
and wider questions as well.

920180900
00:18:56.832 --> 00:19:00.495
I won't sing Happy Birthday, but
I will certainly wish them a very happy

259187465
00:19:00.496 --> 00:19:03.905
birthday and look forward to
continuing my conversations with them.

529366001
00:19:03.906 --> 00:19:06.562
>> Chorley of College Liberal
Democrat spokesperson.

1670811238
00:19:06.563 --> 00:19:07.466
>> Thank you, Mr.

691826395
00:19:07.467 --> 00:19:07.917
Speaker.

507579279
00:19:07.918 --> 00:19:11.177
Working across departments
and with my counterpart in the Lords,

4132798015
00:19:11.178 --> 00:19:13.233
we've published a comprehensive paper on

3774471509
00:19:13.234 --> 00:19:15.292
how Britain can thrive in the age of AI,

845915879
00:19:15.293 --> 00:19:18.251
calling for a digital sovereign
strategy and an integrated

2526495732
00:19:18.252 --> 00:19:20.509
approach to AI that is
bold and responsible.

3083396491
00:19:20.510 --> 00:19:22.765
Pro-innovation pro trust
and built alongside

1866702297
00:19:22.766 --> 00:19:24.269
industry and civic expertise.

3855960599
00:19:24.270 --> 00:19:25.524
I'd be happy to discuss.

4160117191
00:19:25.525 --> 00:19:28.486
What we see is Britain has
a leading place in AI services,

1453729797
00:19:28.487 --> 00:19:30.392
but we've squandered leads before and

2896752301
00:19:30.392 --> 00:19:32.497
the government hasn't offered a coherent,

2847539556
00:19:32.499 --> 00:19:34.655
joined up strategy to do this differently,

4008304752
00:19:34.656 --> 00:19:36.260
centred on trust and standards.

2342943089
00:19:36.261 --> 00:19:38.519
So I ask, where is
the government's AI bill,

2534738487
00:19:38.520 --> 00:19:41.128
and can we have guarantees
that the Labour's latest

3221102344
00:19:41.129 --> 00:19:43.937
internal drama will not cost
Britain its most important

1133968648
00:19:44.520 --> 00:19:46.424
economic opportunity in a generation?

402060621
00:19:46.425 --> 00:19:48.472
>> Well, can I can I just gently.

2997224393
00:19:48.473 --> 00:19:49.526
>> Point to the hon.

1489643861
00:19:49.528 --> 00:19:51.937
Lady that there is a very
clear strategy we set

2324510949
00:19:51.938 --> 00:19:54.295
out early on the AI
opportunities action plan.

3201740598
00:19:54.296 --> 00:19:55.801
We have then built in public.

1771678888
00:19:55.802 --> 00:19:57.106
It is a public dashboard.

1575084341
00:19:57.107 --> 00:20:01.382
You can follow progress right across
the country, 75% of it delivered.

3985894942
00:20:01.383 --> 00:20:04.828
And just this week we found
out that it and I have driven

2067312048
00:20:04.829 --> 00:20:07.235
productivity revivals for
this country as well.

3569517304
00:20:07.236 --> 00:20:11.180
We're firing on all cylinders
when it comes to UK AI.

1509669908
00:20:11.180 --> 00:20:13.519
>> We now come across Clive Jones.

2919195861
00:20:13.520 --> 00:20:14.924
>> Question number one, Mr.

1708400780
00:20:17.520 --> 00:20:18.322
Speaker, >> So.

