These are not outlets known to hyperbole.

3056906032
01:44:31.928 --> 01:44:37.016
Perhaps the government could issue
a correction to major media outlets.

843485964
01:44:37.017 --> 01:44:41.106
>> I'm trying to do it
here, now and in live.

1051318217
01:44:41.107 --> 01:44:44.671
And indeed, I went to see the BBC
earlier and gave them a clip.

2218404312
01:44:44.672 --> 01:44:48.508
But but I just to be absolutely clear,

882064426
01:44:48.509 --> 01:44:50.364
we are not suspending any sanctions.

2588376248
01:44:50.607 --> 01:44:55.011
The sanctions regime in the UK is
tougher today than it was yesterday

1065737398
01:44:55.012 --> 01:44:57.813
than it was a week ago,
and that it was a year ago.

2885846462
01:44:57.814 --> 01:45:00.473
And I am absolutely certain
that as my colleagues in

952623734
01:45:00.474 --> 01:45:04.313
the Foreign Office and I in
DBT progress with these,

2171614906
01:45:04.314 --> 01:45:07.064
looking at the constant
issues of diversion

201914180
01:45:07.065 --> 01:45:09.469
and subversion of our sanctions regime,

1007282492
01:45:09.469 --> 01:45:13.687
that the regime will get even tougher
as the months and years proceed.

2406220904
01:45:13.688 --> 01:45:18.714
>> That brings us to Jim
Shannon Mr Speaker.

3445010068
01:45:18.715 --> 01:45:20.621
>> I would hit him with the question.

3583307138
01:45:20.623 --> 01:45:21.877
Thank you very much, Mr.

2786712803
01:45:21.878 --> 01:45:22.328
Speaker.

795830896
01:45:22.329 --> 01:45:26.157
Can I thank you very
much for his, I believe,

3588525972
01:45:26.159 --> 01:45:27.612
sincere and helpful answers.

2114277289
01:45:27.612 --> 01:45:30.614
And instead of forcing.

2790080811
01:45:30.615 --> 01:45:33.325
But can I say this gently
to the Secretary instead of

243527929
01:45:33.326 --> 01:45:35.982
forcing British businesses
to navigate complex legal

3589691647
01:45:35.983 --> 01:45:39.270
loopholes to import foreign
energy and pressing ahead

48847369
01:45:39.271 --> 01:45:41.428
with a permanent ban on our own resources?

714670478
01:45:41.429 --> 01:45:44.067
Under the Energy
Independence Bill, there is,

2626629384
01:45:44.068 --> 01:45:45.573
I believe many of us believe,

3497150901
01:45:45.574 --> 01:45:47.530
a very clear solution to this problem.

1439817495
01:45:47.531 --> 01:45:49.813
So very kindly Secretary state,

1921949596
01:45:49.814 --> 01:45:52.711
if this government wants
a true energy security,

2435834989
01:45:52.712 --> 01:45:55.808
they must scrap
the ideological roadblocks,

1293545214
01:45:55.809 --> 01:45:59.760
approve the crucial domestic
projects like Rosebank

1243771229
01:45:59.761 --> 01:46:01.565
and Jackdaw oilfields, and unleash.

2493345085
01:46:01.566 --> 01:46:03.270
Because that's what would happen.

1004176694
01:46:03.271 --> 01:46:06.279
Unleash the full potential of
British North Sea production.

301794721
01:46:06.280 --> 01:46:08.137
So can I ask the Secretary of State,

4175309264
01:46:08.138 --> 01:46:11.347
please discuss with the Cabinet
members and demand common sense

28341418
01:46:11.348 --> 01:46:14.957
and energy security to be
prioritised over any single

1798767021
01:46:14.958 --> 01:46:17.164
government Ministers
on this point of view?

3776155046
01:46:18.591 --> 01:46:19.544
Thank you so much.

1845160844
01:46:19.545 --> 01:46:19.896
>> Mr.

953953028
01:46:19.897 --> 01:46:20.498
Mr Speaker.

3864397042
01:46:20.499 --> 01:46:24.112
All roads lead to Jim Shannon, I think,

1829658660
01:46:24.112 --> 01:46:27.719
and certainly all Urgent Questions
do I feel as if I might.

207811282
01:46:27.719 --> 01:46:31.211
I wasn't here for the debate yesterday
because I was in Strasbourg,

2473617811
01:46:31.212 --> 01:46:33.070
but I feel as if I'm hearing some of

477618376
01:46:33.071 --> 01:46:35.126
the debate that was rehearsed yesterday,

4121830331
01:46:35.127 --> 01:46:37.334
and I don't want to
repeat those arguments.

1565476332
01:46:37.335 --> 01:46:40.146
The only point I would make
to him and and I'm grateful

12453026
01:46:40.147 --> 01:46:42.404
for his comments about
my sincerity on this.

111921140
01:46:42.405 --> 01:46:45.063
I'm desperate to make sure
that the Ukrainian people

647212821
01:46:45.064 --> 01:46:47.621
are able to assert their
freedom and defeat Putin.

800102087
01:46:47.623 --> 01:46:52.166
And we will do everything in our
power to secure that outcome.

1796600904
01:46:52.607 --> 01:46:54.261
>> That completes the statement.

1802633253
01:46:54.262 --> 01:46:56.419
Can we not Urgent Question even coming out

267708942
01:46:56.420 --> 01:47:05.262
like the front benches change over.

1890437853
01:47:05.263 --> 01:47:06.918
Point of order Jeremy Corbyn Mr.

3931162240
01:47:07.567 --> 01:47:09.523
Speaker, the West Bank village of Khan

3242506483
01:47:09.523 --> 01:47:11.966
al-Ahmar is under threat at the moment

337925907
01:47:11.967 --> 01:47:16.121
and being forcibly evacuated by
Israeli forces and illegal settlers.

2894384642
01:47:16.121 --> 01:47:17.362
Can you advise me?

843978402
01:47:17.364 --> 01:47:20.660
Is there some way that we
can persuade the Foreign

906596326
01:47:20.661 --> 01:47:22.861
Office to come to this House and make

3685889339
01:47:22.862 --> 01:47:24.916
a statement about their attitude towards

3047259750
01:47:24.918 --> 01:47:27.314
these illegal forcible evacuations and,

967493276
01:47:27.315 --> 01:47:31.017
of course, the continued military
support for Israel, that is,

2851301528
01:47:31.612 --> 01:47:34.170
occasioning the ability of
Israel to do just that.

1024955375
01:47:34.615 --> 01:47:35.066
>> Yeah.

4036701225
01:47:35.067 --> 01:47:36.272
>> Can I thank the hon.

3633850582
01:47:36.273 --> 01:47:36.823
Gentleman?

1184675749
01:47:37.568 --> 01:47:40.578
Well, I would say is I've been
expecting a statement today.

1487835887
01:47:40.579 --> 01:47:43.213
I'm hoping for a statement
tomorrow, but if not,

2888094390
01:47:43.214 --> 01:47:47.816
I'm sure that somebody
might be able to put

1658534318
01:47:47.817 --> 01:47:50.076
a UQ in and who knows
what that might bring.

4251044999
01:47:50.077 --> 01:47:50.427
Right.

631850220
01:47:50.428 --> 01:47:53.564
The clerk will now proceed to
read the orders of the day.

3279507651
01:47:53.565 --> 01:47:54.818
>> King's Speech motion.

2659858968
01:47:54.819 --> 01:47:58.213
>> For an address.

2695776722
01:47:58.214 --> 01:47:58.764
Adjourned.

3483587406
01:47:58.764 --> 01:47:59.767
Debate on question.

203681071
01:47:59.768 --> 01:48:03.019
>> I inform the House that
I have selected amendment

3696555116
01:48:03.020 --> 01:48:05.873
o in the name of
the Leader of the Opposition,

2134860367
01:48:06.568 --> 01:48:11.212
which will be moved at the start
of the debate and amendments.

348298353
01:48:11.213 --> 01:48:12.217
L in the right hon.

3029358921
01:48:12.218 --> 01:48:16.120
Member for Kingston and Surbiton
and P in the name of the honourable,

1543501070
01:48:16.610 --> 01:48:19.018
which has been moved by
the Member for Clacton,

916281241
01:48:20.611 --> 01:48:22.920
which will be moved at
the end of the debate.

2089856923
01:48:22.921 --> 01:48:25.579
The question is that
the Humble Address be presented

2850992513
01:48:26.611 --> 01:48:28.518
to His Majesty as on the Order Paper.

2296486477
01:48:28.519 --> 01:48:32.767
I now call the Shadow Secretary
of State for defence.

273341464
01:48:32.768 --> 01:48:33.821
Oh, it shouldn't be.

2174139261
01:48:33.822 --> 01:48:36.731
It should be Secretary of State
for Defence or Ministers.

1670253617
01:48:36.732 --> 01:48:38.838
Sorry, the amendment's going to be moved.

887664175
01:48:38.839 --> 01:48:42.067
I was right, so it was the look
you gave me that worried me.

1443391702
01:48:42.068 --> 01:48:44.174
So shadow Secretary of State for defence.

2971784414
01:48:44.175 --> 01:48:44.927
>> Yeah, yeah.

4049121554
01:48:44.928 --> 01:48:45.831
>> Thank you, Mr.

2877423067
01:48:45.832 --> 01:48:46.282
Speaker.

2670322213
01:48:46.282 --> 01:48:49.616
>> I beg to move the amendment
as on the Order Paper,

940986334
01:48:49.617 --> 01:48:52.579
and it is an honour to open
the final debate on the King's

4056988144
01:48:52.580 --> 01:48:55.438
Speech on defence readiness
on behalf of the opposition.

2359545459
01:48:55.439 --> 01:48:57.263
But may I begin, Mr.

1299463918
01:48:57.264 --> 01:48:59.370
Speaker, by expressing how saddened I was

973082749
01:48:59.371 --> 01:49:01.478
to hear of the death of Lance Bombardier,

1579368161
01:49:01.612 --> 01:49:04.620
Kiera Sullivan from the King's
Troop Royal Horse Artillery.

2000987982
01:49:04.621 --> 01:49:07.028
My condolences and
the condolences of the whole

542657636
01:49:07.029 --> 01:49:08.985
of the opposition are with her family,

524659449
01:49:09.573 --> 01:49:11.076
both personal and regimental.

3573572246
01:49:11.077 --> 01:49:14.739
Now, before turning to the defence
related matters that were or were not

1158230063
01:49:14.740 --> 01:49:18.398
included in the government's programme
for the next legislative session,

1768703420
01:49:18.400 --> 01:49:20.709
I pay tribute to the men
and women serving in

641459925
01:49:20.710 --> 01:49:22.967
our armed forces right
now across the globe,

1871394819
01:49:22.968 --> 01:49:25.211
whether on board our nuclear submarines,

1611331390
01:49:25.212 --> 01:49:27.217
providing a continuous at sea deterrent

3184697737
01:49:27.218 --> 01:49:30.579
or those deployed in the Middle
East to defend our overseas bases,

4127929807
01:49:30.580 --> 01:49:34.013
I thank them for their service
and unwavering professionalism.

1585828819
01:49:34.014 --> 01:49:36.564
And I also want to pay tribute to our

4140928824
01:49:36.565 --> 01:49:38.369
brave Ukrainian allies who continue

3954942909
01:49:38.570 --> 01:49:42.462
to defy those original expectations
of an early Russian victory.

3772921501
01:49:42.463 --> 01:49:42.914
And, Mr.

4070960940
01:49:42.915 --> 01:49:48.020
Speaker, I do want to say, when we
take steps to publicly show our

3350471063
01:49:48.021 --> 01:49:51.564
sympathy for Ukraine's heroic
struggle, such as by wearing badges,

1456217567
01:49:51.565 --> 01:49:54.111
as I have done every day
since the invasion,

2292782697
01:49:54.112 --> 01:49:57.915
or by displaying Ukraine flags from local

351813626
01:49:57.916 --> 01:49:59.669
and national government buildings.

3775892133
01:49:59.670 --> 01:50:02.430
We do it not just to show
solidarity with a democratic

853430438
01:50:02.431 --> 01:50:04.737
nation under brutal
attack by a dictatorship,

1715789623
01:50:04.737 --> 01:50:08.628
but because it is firmly in
our national interest to

2027034061
01:50:08.629 --> 01:50:11.916
assist Ukraine in keeping
Putin's military in check.

1929428458
01:50:11.918 --> 01:50:14.566
So when newly newly elected councils make

745148409
01:50:14.567 --> 01:50:17.366
their first priority on entering office,

44138915
01:50:17.367 --> 01:50:21.311
pulling down the Ukraine flag,

562905550
01:50:21.312 --> 01:50:24.216
we are entitled to ask
if the party in question

3991002888
01:50:24.217 --> 01:50:26.023
cares about the fate of its people,

2034015833
01:50:26.615 --> 01:50:31.566
and understands the implications
for our own national security.

367145328
01:50:31.567 --> 01:50:32.921
If Russia were to triumph.

1072711958
01:50:32.922 --> 01:50:34.263
And finally, Mr.

3312266193
01:50:34.264 --> 01:50:37.230
Speaker, I want to pay tribute
to all those who served

3325564206
01:50:37.231 --> 01:50:40.073
our country in the past,
our brave veterans.

1845205273
01:50:40.074 --> 01:50:43.920
Which brings me to Labour's plans,
as set out in The King's Speech.

3411397876
01:50:43.921 --> 01:50:47.267
Now, of all Britain's
military capabilities,

913325761
01:50:47.268 --> 01:50:49.418
few are more important to our defence,

1848735223
01:50:49.419 --> 01:50:53.416
nor more widely admired, particularly by

2331771544
01:50:53.418 --> 01:50:55.574
the United States than our special forces.

1107135806
01:50:56.615 --> 01:50:58.674
And yet, at a time of war on two fronts,

152954950
01:50:58.675 --> 01:51:00.782
Labour are ploughing on with a Bill which

973215915
01:51:00.782 --> 01:51:05.317
will reopen vexatious legal actions
that not only threaten our veterans,

2593806481
01:51:05.318 --> 01:51:08.582
but would undermine the morale
of all who serve today,

3776657497
01:51:08.583 --> 01:51:13.327
in particular in the Special
Forces special forces like the SAS

1823469506
01:51:13.328 --> 01:51:16.568
and those of that regiment on
duty in Loch Gall in 1987.

3275520366
01:51:16.569 --> 01:51:16.769
Mr.

1791210208
01:51:16.770 --> 01:51:21.066
Speaker, who shot IRA terrorists
headed to a police station,

636097932
01:51:21.067 --> 01:51:23.275
driving a digger with
a bomb in its bucket,

760442247
01:51:23.616 --> 01:51:27.215
firing machine guns into
the building as they approached.

645866664
01:51:27.216 --> 01:51:30.467
I believe that those soldiers
were acting to defend

621359730
01:51:30.468 --> 01:51:34.770
our society from terrorists
intent on mass murder.

1440917158
01:51:34.771 --> 01:51:37.927
But whatever one's view, surely
going back almost 40 years

4011941145
01:51:37.928 --> 01:51:42.571
to events that took place in
split seconds makes no sense.

1779065305
01:51:42.572 --> 01:51:47.019
Now, crucially, in October 2023,

165401993
01:51:47.020 --> 01:51:51.171
coroner Justice McAlinden
declined to list a new inquest

3432792956
01:51:51.172 --> 01:51:53.666
into Loch Gall precisely because of

1562259457
01:51:53.668 --> 01:51:57.216
the cut off date set by our Legacy Act,

54949350
01:51:57.217 --> 01:52:00.567
an act which therefore did its
job in halting such cases

2538526482
01:52:00.568 --> 01:52:04.865
and genuinely protecting our
veterans from endless litigation.

4012465068
01:52:04.866 --> 01:52:08.175
However, in his comments,
Justice McAlinden did

2689520076
01:52:08.177 --> 01:52:10.416
add that preparatory work for the inquest

3075882397
01:52:10.418 --> 01:52:12.674
should continue because
he noted there would

929635621
01:52:12.675 --> 01:52:14.916
be a general election the following year,

997309889
01:52:14.916 --> 01:52:19.219
stating and I quote, that may affect
how the legislation is implemented.

1257207692
01:52:19.219 --> 01:52:19.420
Mr.

3464096499
01:52:19.421 --> 01:52:21.619
speaker, he had a point, didn't he,

3446221973
01:52:21.620 --> 01:52:26.321
because fast forward three years
and with war now facing us,

227059732
01:52:26.322 --> 01:52:28.530
not just in Ukraine
but in the Middle East,

3672652736
01:52:28.531 --> 01:52:31.318
the government of today
remains intent on repealing

2578291296
01:52:31.319 --> 01:52:34.371
the protections for veterans
that we put in place.

9936842
01:52:34.373 --> 01:52:36.969
It goes without saying that Labour's plans

1982707779
01:52:36.969 --> 01:52:38.725
will harm our veterans once again,

1728154271
01:52:38.726 --> 01:52:41.416
keeping them awake at night
with fear of whether

1757206788
01:52:41.418 --> 01:52:45.014
they will be hauled before our courts.

1353756320
01:52:45.016 --> 01:52:46.422
I give way to my friend Mr.

2371915197
01:52:46.423 --> 01:52:48.531
>> First of all, can I commend the Shadow

1685570076
01:52:48.532 --> 01:52:50.386
Ministers for bringing this forward?

706615908
01:52:50.387 --> 01:52:52.093
He's right to put this on record.

1622211913
01:52:52.094 --> 01:52:55.607
This is very much part of this debate,
but it goes further than that.

3455267344
01:52:55.608 --> 01:52:57.564
The veterans who can't sleep at night,

1307386756
01:52:57.565 --> 01:52:59.521
the families who are worried of what's

3136852768
01:52:59.522 --> 01:53:01.478
going to happen to their their father,

372693776
01:53:01.478 --> 01:53:04.338
their brother or their sister,
whatever the case may be.

1853426367
01:53:04.339 --> 01:53:05.393
But it does the hon.

2473713037
01:53:05.394 --> 01:53:06.898
Gentleman also agree with me.

2427782585
01:53:06.898 --> 01:53:08.251
It's affecting recruiting.

1755585085
01:53:08.252 --> 01:53:10.460
Those who want to join
the Army are saying,

3168775096
01:53:10.461 --> 01:53:13.874
if we join and we get involved in
a battle to protect this country,

3049962881
01:53:13.875 --> 01:53:17.085
we can find ourselves being being
persecuted or taken to court.

1084833963
01:53:17.086 --> 01:53:19.494
Does he feel for that
reason and other reasons?

2419349942
01:53:19.495 --> 01:53:22.404
Government must be fair when
it comes to the legislation,

2649367473
01:53:22.405 --> 01:53:25.816
and must follow the very points
that the Ministers has put forward?

2996977786
01:53:25.817 --> 01:53:28.326
>> Well, I'm always grateful
to him for his very,

3309311732
01:53:28.327 --> 01:53:31.337
very good interventions,
and he's hit the nail on the head.

1853239524
01:53:31.338 --> 01:53:32.942
This isn't just about veterans.

2096753378
01:53:32.943 --> 01:53:34.297
It's important as that is.

2535970871
01:53:34.298 --> 01:53:36.555
It is about the wider
impact on recruitment.

2706416607
01:53:36.556 --> 01:53:39.067
And we don't just take my
word for it or the hon.

4269816147
01:53:39.068 --> 01:53:40.370
Gentleman for Strangford.

2814296228
01:53:40.371 --> 01:53:43.430
In November last year, nine
former four star generals wrote,

1600934078
01:53:43.431 --> 01:53:47.072
and I quote this lawfare is
a direct threat to national security,

3965101554
01:53:47.073 --> 01:53:49.481
going on to say that
the troubles bill achieves

4106214944
01:53:49.615 --> 01:53:51.920
nothing and ongoing
lawfare risks everything.

222650515
01:53:51.921 --> 01:53:55.021
So I asked Labour MPs this
question when considering

3717844205
01:53:55.615 --> 01:53:57.822
the troubles Bill
and the issue of lawfare.

1499665240
01:53:58.620 --> 01:54:00.675
Surely the overriding factor to consider

1235737434
01:54:00.675 --> 01:54:03.976
is the threat we face as a nation

2694190755
01:54:03.977 --> 01:54:08.027
and the impact of this legislation
on our ability to defend ourselves?

2238599867
01:54:08.028 --> 01:54:10.983
Do they really think in
their heart of hearts that

3281271245
01:54:10.984 --> 01:54:13.090
this is what they should be prioritising?

1540895364
01:54:13.091 --> 01:54:17.723
Just when we need our
soldiers more than ever?

120501707
01:54:17.724 --> 01:54:21.529
I just want to make one more point
and then I'll give way to Mr.

1027592786
01:54:21.530 --> 01:54:21.980
Speaker.

2490869873
01:54:21.981 --> 01:54:24.239
I put this challenge to
all those who intend

4173821482
01:54:24.240 --> 01:54:26.295
to stand in Labour's leadership contest.

449903774
01:54:26.615 --> 01:54:28.620
Will those candidates seeking to become

1048746443
01:54:29.620 --> 01:54:31.324
our next Prime Minister recognise

1839177901
01:54:31.325 --> 01:54:34.286
that the first duty of any
leader is defence of the realm,

2237739082
01:54:34.287 --> 01:54:36.946
and that therefore it is in
the national interest to

232168461
01:54:38.576 --> 01:54:41.234
scrap the troubles bill
and back our brave veterans.

3492553337
01:54:41.235 --> 01:54:42.889
I give way to honourable leader.

900492729
01:54:42.891 --> 01:54:44.746
>> I thank the Shadow Ministers for.

1421906566
01:54:44.748 --> 01:54:45.500
>> Giving way.

1371922852
01:54:45.501 --> 01:54:48.912
Would he acknowledge that no party
and no victims group in Northern

277723275
01:54:48.913 --> 01:54:51.469
Ireland supports his party's
approach to the past,

2518109044
01:54:51.471 --> 01:54:53.477
and that even the Dillon judgement last

3079631147
01:54:56.620 --> 01:54:58.578
week did not in any way rule it legal.

721538685
01:54:58.579 --> 01:55:00.938
And would he not agree
with me that, you know,

776723146
01:55:00.939 --> 01:55:04.278
soldiers following the rule of
law is a matter of recruitment

1511931474
01:55:06.577 --> 01:55:08.986
and no soldier wants to
be painted with a brush

2697772426
01:55:08.987 --> 01:55:10.994
that they don't follow the rule of law.

4137545700
01:55:10.995 --> 01:55:13.303
And would he care to
articulate to the house?

3772054451
01:55:13.304 --> 01:55:15.360
Out of 300,000 soldiers who served under

2451809022
01:55:15.361 --> 01:55:17.516
Operation Banner in Northern Ireland,

3184377014
01:55:17.517 --> 01:55:20.921
how many actually have faced
any judicial proceedings?

991492835
01:55:20.922 --> 01:55:23.271
It's in the very low two figures.

2106543097
01:55:23.272 --> 01:55:23.572
Yeah.

1534514039
01:55:23.573 --> 01:55:24.978
>> Well, I respect the hon.

3263819107
01:55:26.620 --> 01:55:29.630
Lady and I respect the strength
of her view on this matter.

3371123807
01:55:29.632 --> 01:55:32.758
I would just say we have to
deal with what is certain here.

599631173
01:55:32.759 --> 01:55:33.562
In my view, Mr.

2580664340
01:55:33.563 --> 01:55:36.130
Speaker, it is extremely unlikely that any

46075435
01:55:36.132 --> 01:55:38.428
new cases would lead to prosecutions.

3541335355
01:55:38.429 --> 01:55:42.275
It is, however, certain that
were this process to recommence,

949566508
01:55:42.276 --> 01:55:45.823
it would damage the morale of our armed

1198256954
01:55:45.824 --> 01:55:47.782
forces at a time of war on two fronts,

1774805942
01:55:47.782 --> 01:55:50.571
and I think that is not
in the national interest.

945535659
01:55:50.572 --> 01:55:51.174
I give way.

217145800
01:55:51.175 --> 01:55:52.831
>> I'm grateful to my right hon.

4015164577
01:55:52.832 --> 01:55:55.187
Friend who's making
an excellent intervention.

3825818405
01:55:55.188 --> 01:55:57.950
Can I just say to him in
answer to that and to others,

1231622494
01:55:57.951 --> 01:56:01.073
having someone who served
in Northern Ireland,

690919631
01:56:01.074 --> 01:56:03.634
I have spoken to many
veterans that I was >> There

1523770219
01:56:03.635 --> 01:56:05.641
with and others that were there before.

3459156316
01:56:05.642 --> 01:56:07.548
There is a scintilla of real question

1855207723
01:56:07.549 --> 01:56:09.882
mark about how they will be treated.

2683602371
01:56:09.883 --> 01:56:12.791
The vexatious nature of these
complaints will, of course,

806224968
01:56:12.791 --> 01:56:15.273
drag them eventually back into the courts.

3440846702
01:56:15.273 --> 01:56:16.126
That's the fear.

1028024840
01:56:17.619 --> 01:56:19.525
They are sure that they are innocent,

2277120346
01:56:19.526 --> 01:56:22.135
but by the time the courts
have finished with them,

910163469
01:56:22.136 --> 01:56:25.696
innocent wouldn't matter at all because
they will have destroyed life.

868593932
01:56:25.697 --> 01:56:27.052
Does he not agree with me?

4009406554
01:56:27.053 --> 01:56:29.275
>> I don't need to add
a great deal because

2986452336
01:56:29.276 --> 01:56:31.181
my friend served on Operation Banner.

1245360620
01:56:31.182 --> 01:56:32.786
He speaks with great authority.

3682660706
01:56:32.787 --> 01:56:35.044
He has always been
passionate on this issue,

524820610
01:56:35.045 --> 01:56:37.305
and I do think he hits
the nail on the head,

3732108588
01:56:37.306 --> 01:56:38.761
as so many people have said.

3973374318
01:56:38.762 --> 01:56:40.468
So many veterans have said to me,

2324388879
01:56:40.469 --> 01:56:43.780
it is the process itself which is
so punishing with this lawfare.

50821065
01:56:43.781 --> 01:56:44.734
It is so damaging.

4037121727
01:56:44.735 --> 01:56:46.541
It is not in the national interest,

1226098234
01:56:46.541 --> 01:56:48.799
and it will damage
the British armed forces.

2311668029
01:56:48.800 --> 01:56:50.406
And I'll give way to my friend.

659703793
01:56:51.620 --> 01:56:52.323
>> As my hon.

3508423987
01:56:52.324 --> 01:56:53.025
Friend knows.

2348462762
01:56:53.026 --> 01:56:57.925
The then Defence Committee did
two reports into this question,

691041527
01:56:57.927 --> 01:57:00.173
and in the course of those inquiries,

3301453633
01:57:00.174 --> 01:57:04.224
we interviewed four eminent
professors of law,

1172566770
01:57:04.225 --> 01:57:07.374
including one particularly
famous left wing one.

3064870478
01:57:07.375 --> 01:57:11.233
We didn't ask them what
they wanted to happen.

4279435732
01:57:11.234 --> 01:57:16.528
We asked them what could legally be
done about a statute of limitation,

41149362
01:57:17.620 --> 01:57:19.725
and they all agreed, however reluctantly,

3105240684
01:57:19.726 --> 01:57:24.577
that it would be legal
to have a statute of

1131831480
01:57:25.619 --> 01:57:27.624
limitation provided it was coupled with

20899568
01:57:27.625 --> 01:57:32.323
a truth recovery process
which met the requirement

3937576236
01:57:32.324 --> 01:57:36.821
for an investigation to occur,

3994327374
01:57:36.822 --> 01:57:40.331
and that the other key
condition was it applied

982559416
01:57:40.332 --> 01:57:44.119
to all people involved in the conflict.

290940415
01:57:44.120 --> 01:57:46.175
Now the government could pursue the line

1886284001
01:57:47.620 --> 01:57:49.626
that these four professors of law took,

3945274934
01:57:49.627 --> 01:57:51.777
but it doesn't want to do so,

223110416
01:57:51.778 --> 01:57:54.822
and it's happy to shelter
behind court judgements

2421653696
01:57:54.823 --> 01:57:56.969
that it could appeal but won't.

4205874722
01:57:56.969 --> 01:57:58.675
>> Well, it's an excellent point.

2337695164
01:57:58.675 --> 01:58:00.330
My friend is absolutely correct.

2304992081
01:58:00.331 --> 01:58:03.227
Our legacy act was based
on what happened in South

3663178372
01:58:03.228 --> 01:58:05.925
Africa and which is where
we may not like it,

4246751004
01:58:05.925 --> 01:58:08.434
but if you want to have
peace and reconciliation,

1627379473
01:58:08.435 --> 01:58:11.178
any changes in the law
which favour those who may

234774052
01:58:11.179 --> 01:58:14.077
have been guilty have
to apply to both sides.

3710762885
01:58:14.078 --> 01:58:16.575
It is simply a statement of fact.

3328150334
01:58:16.576 --> 01:58:19.170
And as I think I just
showed with Loch Gall,

707109547
01:58:19.171 --> 01:58:21.871
how our Act of Parliament, the Legacy Act,

1818259434
01:58:21.871 --> 01:58:24.079
did indeed stop
an inquest which would have

2598097272
01:58:24.080 --> 01:58:25.835
been damaging to the armed forces,

2670976225
01:58:25.836 --> 01:58:31.320
but which I do not believe would
have led to any actual prosecutions.

2064722959
01:58:31.321 --> 01:58:34.782
So turning to what wasn't in
the King's Speech Madam Deputy Speaker,

1051881581
01:58:34.782 --> 01:58:37.526
the Strategic Defence Review
promised, and I quote,

2178973838
01:58:37.527 --> 01:58:39.883
a new defence readiness Bill to provide

330694351
01:58:39.884 --> 01:58:41.789
the government with powers in reserve

3928390560
01:58:41.790 --> 01:58:45.529
to mobilise reserves and industry
should crisis escalate into conflict.

3318358554
01:58:45.530 --> 01:58:49.931
Now, with war on two fronts,
surely such legislation should

3519862987
01:58:49.932 --> 01:58:52.389
be the absolute top priority
of this government.

2002816957
01:58:52.623 --> 01:58:56.374
But alas, there is no defence
readiness bill in the King's speech.

3410594903
01:58:56.375 --> 01:58:57.027
And why not?

1208545417
01:58:57.028 --> 01:59:00.587
Because, Madam Deputy Speaker,
the Defence Readiness Bill isn't ready.

2271261792
01:59:01.623 --> 01:59:03.028
And what else is not ready?

1831496774
01:59:03.029 --> 01:59:05.174
Madam Deputy Speaker, of course,

1984035962
01:59:05.175 --> 01:59:08.130
the Defence Investment
Plan and we know that.

3006022881
01:59:08.132 --> 01:59:12.074
We know they're working
flat out and and at pace.

3683675618
01:59:12.075 --> 01:59:13.228
But almost a year ago,

109364206
01:59:13.230 --> 01:59:16.478
the Secretary of State
promised from that Dispatch

2879745891
01:59:16.478 --> 01:59:20.023
Box that the Defence Investment Plan
would be published last autumn.

4050440187
01:59:20.025 --> 01:59:21.380
It is now ten months late.

2990529087
01:59:21.380 --> 01:59:23.624
So when the Ministers responds,

4179653191
01:59:23.625 --> 01:59:26.124
can he tell us exactly when we are going

2437830940
01:59:26.125 --> 01:59:27.930
to get the defence investment plan?

573475851
01:59:27.931 --> 01:59:30.189
Most importantly, we are
bound to ask why do

1838278146
01:59:30.190 --> 01:59:33.578
we still have no defence investment plan?

1599674106
01:59:33.579 --> 01:59:37.182
Now, of course, the dip is meant to
set out the detailed procurement

917483594
01:59:37.183 --> 01:59:41.925
decisions intended to implement
Labour's strategic defence review.

3003036174
01:59:41.925 --> 01:59:45.982
So what do the authors of Labour's
SDR, appointed by the Prime Minister,

275856472
01:59:46.623 --> 01:59:48.829
actually think about
the failure to publish

1263172512
01:59:48.830 --> 01:59:51.332
the dip and the impact
on delivering the SDR?

528622652
01:59:51.333 --> 01:59:54.579
Well, Madam Deputy Speaker,
the three key authors,

1906614664
01:59:54.580 --> 01:59:57.878
Doctor Fiona Hill, General Sir
Richard Barrons, Lord Robertson,

749080171
01:59:58.624 --> 02:00:01.432
every one of them has absolutely
slammed the government

3387070491
02:00:01.433 --> 02:00:04.174
for its failure to deliver
with Lord Robertson,

2843156132
02:00:04.175 --> 02:00:07.684
a former Labour defence secretary,
a former Labour defence secretary,

1546331376
02:00:07.685 --> 02:00:10.434
a former secretary general of NATO,

447575658
02:00:10.435 --> 02:00:13.023
stating and I quote, we
cannot defend Britain

402123380
02:00:13.023 --> 02:00:14.978
with an ever expanding welfare Budget.

2927967575
02:00:16.623 --> 02:00:17.375
We agree 100%.

4001471921
02:00:17.376 --> 02:00:21.474
The fact is, the current
Prime Minister bottled

1177554855
02:00:21.475 --> 02:00:25.224
it on welfare reform u-turning repeatedly,

404426979
02:00:25.225 --> 02:00:29.027
despite a majority of over 160
and failing to make even modest changes

4270359251
02:00:29.028 --> 02:00:33.231
to working age benefits whilst
removing the two child benefit cap.

617305037
02:00:33.232 --> 02:00:34.337
I give way to my hon.

2006279006
02:00:34.338 --> 02:00:34.737
Friend.

2133005303
02:00:34.739 --> 02:00:35.591
>> I'm grateful.

669012064
02:00:35.624 --> 02:00:39.182
>> To him giving way to be
charitable to the government.

2800090377
02:00:39.183 --> 02:00:40.286
Maybe they are given.

1745397517
02:00:40.287 --> 02:00:42.977
They had another U-turn
on the Chagos deal.

3093390314
02:00:42.978 --> 02:00:46.088
There is actually Â£34 billion
that could be spent in defence.

2825828802
02:00:46.089 --> 02:00:48.597
Maybe there's a delay in
the plan because they're

850839822
02:00:48.598 --> 02:00:50.705
trying to decide how to spend that money.

1688552539
02:00:50.706 --> 02:00:52.964
Or is there another
reason you can think of?

1857104371
02:00:52.965 --> 02:00:53.818
>> Well, my hon.

1289231911
02:00:53.819 --> 02:00:55.823
Friend has remarkable foresight because

2810456020
02:00:55.824 --> 02:00:58.677
I will be coming to the Chagos issue.

1631659585
02:00:58.678 --> 02:01:00.032
But this is the key point.

2989831862
02:01:00.034 --> 02:01:03.989
Had the Prime Minister held his nerve
and reformed the benefit system,

359874848
02:01:03.990 --> 02:01:06.224
including toughening rules for working age

32134461
02:01:06.225 --> 02:01:08.933
benefits and keeping the two child limit,

1523051243
02:01:08.934 --> 02:01:12.978
as was his previous position, he could
have found the billions to fund

660812210
02:01:12.980 --> 02:01:16.877
defence rather than entrenching
welfare dependency even further.

2117035067
02:01:16.878 --> 02:01:19.938
So with this total failure of
nerve from the Prime Minister,

178227798
02:01:19.939 --> 02:01:23.521
he had some brass neck using his
response to the King's speech

2481707836
02:01:23.522 --> 02:01:26.574
last Wednesday to accuse
us of defence austerity.

778216098
02:01:26.575 --> 02:01:27.879
Just to remind the House.

1442244131
02:01:28.623 --> 02:01:30.779
Last year, the government insisted on Â£2.6

4028315950
02:01:30.780 --> 02:01:33.638
billion of reductions to
the Ministry of Defence Budget.

2497035384
02:01:34.624 --> 02:01:36.982
This year they are insisting
on a further Â£3.5

3853842611
02:01:37.582 --> 02:01:39.287
billion of cuts are, they'll say,

1798618630
02:01:39.288 --> 02:01:41.696
but they were the last
government to spend 2.5%

4129314210
02:01:41.697 --> 02:01:44.478
defence on defence in 2010.

2308734884
02:01:44.480 --> 02:01:46.787
Always omitting
the caveat that when the same

897508090
02:01:46.788 --> 02:01:49.929
Labour government came to power in 1997,

1809924295
02:01:49.930 --> 02:01:52.287
they inherited defence
spending from us at 3%.

2793922265
02:01:52.633 --> 02:01:54.938
Indeed, in talking about
so-called austerity,

1542262869
02:01:55.628 --> 02:01:58.927
they conveniently forget
as well that the IFS found

218458129
02:01:58.928 --> 02:02:01.035
that had Labour won the election in 2010,

1370836008
02:02:01.036 --> 02:02:05.135
they were planning to cut 25%
from the defence Budget.

3650465185
02:02:05.136 --> 02:02:06.540
But at least they achieved.

2580972943
02:02:06.541 --> 02:02:09.840
Secretary to the Treasury at the time had

2952445579
02:02:09.841 --> 02:02:11.998
the good grace to leave a note confessing.

2951731182
02:02:11.999 --> 02:02:15.681
Inverted commas, I his
message said we all know it.

2801207597
02:02:15.682 --> 02:02:16.835
There's no money left.

2960359098
02:02:16.836 --> 02:02:20.539
And once again relying on us to
clear up the mess of a Labour

406772781
02:02:20.540 --> 02:02:23.198
government that had run out
of other people's money,

1155450378
02:02:23.199 --> 02:02:26.711
not for the first time in history,
but the worst thing about Labour's

72085398
02:02:26.712 --> 02:02:29.419
resort to history is that
it's completely irrelevant.

3379338443
02:02:29.420 --> 02:02:32.737
I have repeatedly accepted that
defence spending fell under

1143351319
02:02:32.739 --> 02:02:35.787
successive governments since
the end of the Cold War.

140471441
02:02:36.584 --> 02:02:37.234
Irrefutable.

1809862086
02:02:37.235 --> 02:02:39.594
But that was because
the the world we lived in

2923636587
02:02:39.594 --> 02:02:41.752
was one where we thought peace would last,

516760411
02:02:42.628 --> 02:02:45.184
whereas today the threat
is completely transformed

1572029302
02:02:45.185 --> 02:02:46.639
and instead of looking back,

2576685576
02:02:46.639 --> 02:02:48.947
the public want us to
confront the challenges

1968917776
02:02:48.948 --> 02:02:51.056
we face right now to be ready for battle.

2170261501
02:02:51.057 --> 02:02:53.430
And above all, they want
us to be honest about

310655354
02:02:53.431 --> 02:02:55.889
the choices needed to find
the cash for defence.

3324027418
02:02:55.889 --> 02:03:00.380
That's why we've started to
set out a a set of fully

2165850338
02:03:00.382 --> 02:03:02.539
funded steps towards 3% of GDP on defence,

292191762
02:03:02.540 --> 02:03:05.878
as was last achieved under
a conservative government.

3399634316
02:03:05.879 --> 02:03:07.184
So take Chagos as my hon.

87887457
02:03:07.185 --> 02:03:09.491
Friend said in a very
good intervention now,

319527512
02:03:09.492 --> 02:03:12.299
Madam Deputy Speaker Labour
may delude themselves that,

2545585650
02:03:12.300 --> 02:03:14.382
like the parrot in Monty Python sketch,

308678962
02:03:14.383 --> 02:03:19.184
their Chagos deal is merely resting
pining for the archipelago.

2847390576
02:03:21.628 --> 02:03:23.134
But we know the deal is dead.

3744376843
02:03:23.135 --> 02:03:27.183
It is an ex treaty,
and even if they disagree with

1587499184
02:03:27.184 --> 02:03:29.389
no treaty legislation
in the King's speech,

4002195283
02:03:29.391 --> 02:03:32.001
it must be clear, even to
them that the hundreds of

2905145801
02:03:32.002 --> 02:03:34.433
millions of pounds due
to be sent to Mauritius.

907633519
02:03:34.434 --> 02:03:37.182
This Parliament, primarily
from the MoD Budget,

4110871721
02:03:37.183 --> 02:03:40.241
must now be available
to be spent elsewhere.

2920461029
02:03:40.242 --> 02:03:42.498
That's why earlier this
month in Portsmouth,

1603088495
02:03:42.499 --> 02:03:45.585
the Leader of the Opposition
and I set out that we would

275139423
02:03:45.586 --> 02:03:48.337
use Labour's Chagos Cash
for a better purpose,

3907472140
02:03:48.338 --> 02:03:51.094
accelerating the construction
of the 13 frigates being

1118276201
02:03:51.096 --> 02:03:54.633
made in Scotland that we
ordered in government.

62323159
02:03:54.634 --> 02:03:57.938
The fact is, there is no other
way to address the shortage

1632061283
02:03:57.939 --> 02:04:00.934
of surface ships very
serious in the short term,

476842849
02:04:00.935 --> 02:04:04.329
than accelerating the build of
those 13 fantastic new warships.

4181408286
02:04:04.330 --> 02:04:07.337
Indeed, if you bear with
me, just a few days after

416067556
02:04:07.338 --> 02:04:11.328
we set out our policy to do exactly that.

607382567
02:04:11.329 --> 02:04:14.188
Lo and behold, HMS Iron Duke
was withdrawn from service,

1236910933
02:04:14.189 --> 02:04:16.947
confirming the urgent need
to act on defence readiness

2714338141
02:04:16.948 --> 02:04:19.155
and be willing to to
divert cash elsewhere.

3482346421
02:04:19.156 --> 02:04:20.110
I give way to hon.

2044155269
02:04:20.111 --> 02:04:20.411
Lady.

4283082901
02:04:20.412 --> 02:04:21.114
>> Thank you.

1168575281
02:04:21.115 --> 02:04:21.968
I thank the hon.

551343043
02:04:21.969 --> 02:04:22.369
Member.

1005283361
02:04:22.370 --> 02:04:22.620
Hon.

4017428915
02:04:22.621 --> 02:04:24.425
Member, for taking an intervention.

3355198999
02:04:24.425 --> 02:04:27.538
Would he agree with me that had
his government not got rid of

959686800
02:04:27.628 --> 02:04:30.588
shipbuilding in my city and had
put some plans into place,

3724751361
02:04:30.627 --> 02:04:32.584
we may well have been able to continue

586848874
02:04:32.585 --> 02:04:34.492
to build ships in my city rather than

4006959751
02:04:34.493 --> 02:04:37.903
decimate it and leave us with three
incompetent ports of Ministers.

2112734348
02:04:37.904 --> 02:04:39.911
>> Well, I'm very grateful for the hon.

2080961012
02:04:39.912 --> 02:04:42.685
Lady, but I think she
would be better focusing

2451173866
02:04:42.686 --> 02:04:45.084
on the type 45 destroyers in government.

864911206
02:04:45.085 --> 02:04:47.530
They were meant to order 12 type 45.

1162604972
02:04:47.531 --> 02:04:50.279
They slashed that order
in half to just six.

676451912
02:04:50.280 --> 02:04:52.388
And worse than that, in an act of genius,

2122195929
02:04:52.389 --> 02:04:54.929
they inserted an engine
that didn't even work.

2262410564
02:04:54.930 --> 02:04:56.887
And we've had to spend years trying to

3847317351
02:04:56.888 --> 02:04:58.642
replace through the PIP programme.

3617703294
02:04:58.643 --> 02:05:02.339
But, Madam Deputy Speaker, on
the issue of welfare and defence funding,

1931706783
02:05:02.340 --> 02:05:05.451
we've been the first party to
explicitly set out how we would

2775685130
02:05:05.452 --> 02:05:08.308
reduce benefit expenditure to
increase defence spending,

1891021731
02:05:08.309 --> 02:05:11.017
with confirmation that we
would restore the two child

1585870199
02:05:11.018 --> 02:05:13.930
benefit cap and use
the savings for our military.

4125221663
02:05:13.931 --> 02:05:16.541
We set out plans to move 2
billion a year from R&D,

2832356147
02:05:16.543 --> 02:05:18.648
from other government departments to fund

2511735214
02:05:18.648 --> 02:05:20.655
drones and drone tech across the board.

2247567040
02:05:20.656 --> 02:05:23.316
But if we are to become
the world leader in uncrewed

2158881384
02:05:23.317 --> 02:05:25.324
warfare that I still believe we can be,

697120650
02:05:25.325 --> 02:05:28.082
not least after our extraordinary
support for Ukraine.

3981534126
02:05:28.083 --> 02:05:31.496
We don't just need our services to
have the cash to test and train.

319825474
02:05:31.496 --> 02:05:34.004
We also need to invest
billions into transforming

2152025562
02:05:34.005 --> 02:05:35.458
our defence industrial base.

231380177
02:05:35.459 --> 02:05:38.620
I'll give way to my friend who's
an expert on industrial base.

539251162
02:05:38.621 --> 02:05:41.633
>> On the type 26 global combat
ship, and I welcome that.

1608190578
02:05:41.634 --> 02:05:44.834
That's a really important,
as I'm sure my right hon.

2700592766
02:05:47.630 --> 02:05:49.937
Friend will important
naval deal with Norway?

4193244986
02:05:49.938 --> 02:05:51.333
Is it not the case?

502243462
02:05:51.334 --> 02:05:55.383
The timeline of those
delivery will give the first

2399643625
02:05:55.384 --> 02:05:59.428
ships to Norway and not
to the United Kingdom.

21849110
02:05:59.429 --> 02:06:00.482
If I'm wrong, great.

1288694194
02:06:00.483 --> 02:06:04.885
And if that is the case, that
there must be a discussion

2780699735
02:06:04.886 --> 02:06:09.088
within the MoD about extending
the life of the existing.

4089289616
02:06:09.089 --> 02:06:09.891
Well and great.

4118834360
02:06:09.892 --> 02:06:10.945
If I'm wrong, great.

647836587
02:06:10.946 --> 02:06:13.555
Well, you know, I'm used
to being wrong many times,

2275418918
02:06:13.556 --> 02:06:16.618
but I'm happy to be wrong on
something we need to get right.

3610911921
02:06:16.619 --> 02:06:17.170
Thank you.

978286337
02:06:17.171 --> 02:06:20.332
>> I'm grateful to my friend,
and I'm aware that timelines are

257763330
02:06:20.333 --> 02:06:23.892
an issue in in a couple of dimensions
in this chamber at the moment.

484659046
02:06:23.893 --> 02:06:26.302
So I will I will come to
my conclusion shortly.

2738319872
02:06:26.303 --> 02:06:28.561
But to my friend, he
does make a fundamental

2649099913
02:06:28.562 --> 02:06:30.116
question about the Royal Navy.

2482260872
02:06:30.117 --> 02:06:32.325
Madam Deputy Speaker
at a time when we know

4158464355
02:06:32.326 --> 02:06:34.130
we have shortages of surface ships,

1086857939
02:06:34.132 --> 02:06:36.641
I do hope that the Ministers
will set out exactly

2255713538
02:06:36.642 --> 02:06:38.650
how many type 26 we are going to order,

1295216925
02:06:38.651 --> 02:06:40.305
irrespective of the Norway deal.

3624992866
02:06:40.306 --> 02:06:42.011
I support the Norway export deal.

2667488464
02:06:42.012 --> 02:06:44.521
How many will we be ordering
in addition to that?

4254952464
02:06:44.522 --> 02:06:48.084
Because the written answer he gave
me was very, very ambiguous indeed.

378824371
02:06:48.085 --> 02:06:50.484
So Madam Deputy Speaker, it's to get that

271989997
02:06:50.485 --> 02:06:52.189
extra money into industrial base,

97245553
02:06:52.190 --> 02:06:54.346
which is why our alternative King's Speech

2722346597
02:06:54.347 --> 02:06:56.102
has a sovereign Defence fund bill.

365583340
02:06:56.103 --> 02:06:58.159
But there is finally one other important

2008396560
02:06:58.160 --> 02:07:00.115
bill in our alternative King's Speech,

2506722288
02:07:00.116 --> 02:07:02.873
our promise to repeal Labour's
terrible troubles Bill.

2300836405
02:07:02.874 --> 02:07:05.532
It is not enough to
oppose Labour's lawfare.

2108673486
02:07:05.532 --> 02:07:08.491
We would restore full legal
protections for our veterans,

926653588
02:07:08.492 --> 02:07:11.000
boosting morale and sending
a signal that we will

899043669
02:07:11.001 --> 02:07:13.183
always have the back of those who serve.

836150995
02:07:13.184 --> 02:07:16.433
Madam Deputy Speaker,
the public know that it is

4138226402
02:07:16.434 --> 02:07:18.793
madness at a time of war
for the UK government

3430172228
02:07:18.794 --> 02:07:21.332
to be prioritising putting
our soldiers back

1119044915
02:07:21.333 --> 02:07:23.289
in the dock for serving their country.

259103764
02:07:23.290 --> 02:07:26.781
That's why our motion today
calls on this House to

3375216870
02:07:26.782 --> 02:07:29.339
reject Labour's plans
and scrap the troubles bill.

1447477979
02:07:29.632 --> 02:07:31.889
We will always defend
those who defended us.

2576232375
02:07:32.630 --> 02:07:32.931
Yeah.

4180736355
02:07:32.932 --> 02:07:35.540
>> The original question
was that an Humble Address

2769471544
02:07:35.541 --> 02:07:38.441
be presented to His Majesty
as on the Order Paper.

559555532
02:07:38.442 --> 02:07:40.548
Since when amendment O has been proposed?

1356071669
02:07:40.549 --> 02:07:41.703
As on the Order Paper.

1349110229
02:07:41.704 --> 02:07:45.035
The question is that
the amendment be made.

4096184104
02:07:45.036 --> 02:07:48.334
I now call the Ministers
Ministers Luke Pollard.

3750041327
02:07:48.335 --> 02:07:49.388
>> Thank you, Madam.

509626864
02:07:49.389 --> 02:07:51.646
>> Deputy Speaker,
and I know members across

2197591965
02:07:51.647 --> 02:07:54.005
the House will join me
and the Prime Minister,

2304382631
02:07:54.005 --> 02:07:56.362
who said earlier in sending
our condolences to

3341183232
02:07:56.364 --> 02:07:58.570
the family and friends
of Lance Bombardier.

1994276677
02:07:58.571 --> 02:08:01.938
Kiera O'Sullivan, a gifted soldier
horsewoman who died on Friday.

1592973440
02:08:01.939 --> 02:08:05.790
A young leader, a young
life taken too soon.

2029826138
02:08:05.791 --> 02:08:07.846
Madam Deputy Speaker, His Majesty opened

2230422726
02:08:07.847 --> 02:08:10.593
his gracious speech with a warning that

2048423734
02:08:10.594 --> 02:08:14.202
increasingly dangerous and volatile
world threatens the United Kingdom.

628135724
02:08:14.203 --> 02:08:16.638
And as we debate our
response in this chamber,

910263625
02:08:16.639 --> 02:08:18.294
our armed forces are on missions

395071072
02:08:18.295 --> 02:08:23.086
across the world facing down those
threats, strengthening our alliances,

1373263530
02:08:23.630 --> 02:08:26.588
defending our overseas bases
and our overseas territories,

1653279136
02:08:26.589 --> 02:08:28.896
and preparing for missions
to the High North,

1491953713
02:08:29.632 --> 02:08:32.189
the Strait of Hormuz and
a Post-ceasefire Ukraine.

4212559316
02:08:33.632 --> 02:08:35.989
Our armed forces are
working around the clock,

2838183638
02:08:35.990 --> 02:08:37.844
protecting our homeland, our allies,

1303647253
02:08:37.844 --> 02:08:39.700
our interests, equipped with some of

901786664
02:08:39.701 --> 02:08:43.984
the most advanced
capabilities in the world.

682904332
02:08:43.985 --> 02:08:48.035
The effective closure of
the Strait of Hormuz is hurting

3177104451
02:08:48.036 --> 02:08:50.985
all our constituents right
across this country.

3731553143
02:08:50.986 --> 02:08:53.181
They see it in their newsfeeds.

3512022773
02:08:53.182 --> 02:08:54.888
They feel it at the petrol pumps.

740982301
02:08:54.889 --> 02:08:57.286
They pay for it through rising bills.

428238699
02:08:57.287 --> 02:08:59.537
This government is determined to do all we

2179071253
02:08:59.538 --> 02:09:01.844
can to end that pain as soon as we can.

163796028
02:09:01.846 --> 02:09:04.504
We have stepped up to lead
a multinational response,

518385671
02:09:04.505 --> 02:09:06.511
with the Prime Minister and the Defence

3436850205
02:09:06.512 --> 02:09:08.264
Secretary building and co-chairing

3761158025
02:09:08.590 --> 02:09:11.500
a new 40 nation coalition
united in our mission to secure

1223163605
02:09:11.501 --> 02:09:15.185
the Strait of Hormuz as soon as
a lasting ceasefire is in place,

1505225904
02:09:15.186 --> 02:09:17.393
with the UK's armed
forces leading the way,

2866104069
02:09:17.394 --> 02:09:20.099
deploying advanced autonomous
mine hunting equipment,

2777113946
02:09:20.100 --> 02:09:22.233
new uncrewed boats and drones,

3072551542
02:09:22.234 --> 02:09:24.691
working alongside the heavy
metal of HMS Dragon.

3515632182
02:09:24.692 --> 02:09:27.036
Deploying to the Middle
East with its cutting

3902676798
02:09:27.037 --> 02:09:28.891
edge Sea Viper Counter-drone system.

757177365
02:09:28.892 --> 02:09:33.584
Because, Madam Deputy Speaker, innovation,
hard power and the ability to

336698280
02:09:33.585 --> 02:09:37.246
sustain it are the currency of our
more dangerous and unpredictable age.

702295872
02:09:37.246 --> 02:09:42.236
Hard power is the essential building
block of effective deterrence,

1524220070
02:09:42.237 --> 02:09:45.034
and deterrence is our
insurance policy against

3815869817
02:09:45.035 --> 02:09:47.343
the growing threats that
we face as a nation.

395424829
02:09:47.344 --> 02:09:51.236
That is why this government
is investing in hard power,

3772241726
02:09:51.237 --> 02:09:55.138
investing over Â£270 billion in
defence over this Parliament.

3463059292
02:09:55.139 --> 02:09:58.386
Defence innovation, working twice,

1268688943
02:09:58.387 --> 02:10:02.737
once for national security
and once for British industry.

3315690844
02:10:02.737 --> 02:10:03.942
That is the Labour way.

284550271
02:10:03.943 --> 02:10:04.343
Please.

2793658282
02:10:04.344 --> 02:10:06.841
>> I'm grateful to
the Ministers for giving way.

1782924099
02:10:06.842 --> 02:10:08.799
He makes a strong case for hard power,

2619606199
02:10:08.800 --> 02:10:10.856
and the investment in British defence is

3096708939
02:10:10.857 --> 02:10:12.763
one that we in these benches support.

2963338154
02:10:12.764 --> 02:10:14.770
However, he also knows that generals on

2233078932
02:10:14.771 --> 02:10:16.627
both sides of the Atlantic have made

640080670
02:10:16.628 --> 02:10:18.784
the case that investment in development is

1115219440
02:10:18.785 --> 02:10:20.891
necessary in order to prevent a conflict.

2609003705
02:10:20.892 --> 02:10:24.502
In fact, they say that prevention is
better than military intervention.

2369562967
02:10:24.503 --> 02:10:26.659
So can the Ministers take this opportunity

3340744894
02:10:26.660 --> 02:10:28.768
to assure the House that there will be no

831740146
02:10:28.769 --> 02:10:31.074
further cuts to
the international development

1312589196
02:10:31.075 --> 02:10:32.779
Budget in the forthcoming period?

178094923
02:10:32.780 --> 02:10:34.837
>> Can I thank him for his intervention?

3656144198
02:10:34.838 --> 02:10:38.904
He knows as well as I do that we have
a commitment to get back to 0.7%

1804680873
02:10:38.905 --> 02:10:41.537
of GDP on international aid when we can.

1636284940
02:10:41.538 --> 02:10:43.996
But I will also remember
the time when his party

4124827833
02:10:43.998 --> 02:10:46.690
in government cut defence
spending as well.

3984979026
02:10:46.691 --> 02:10:49.441
And so I appreciate what
he's trying to say.

1612537913
02:10:49.442 --> 02:10:52.990
But let's unite now in understanding
the threats we face today.

2266586560
02:10:52.991 --> 02:10:56.398
Require investment in defence,
requiring increasing defence Budget.

3436891521
02:10:56.398 --> 02:10:58.938
And that is what this
government is delivering,

3679785434
02:10:58.939 --> 02:11:02.501
investing more in our armed forces
and those who wield the hard power.

158821319
02:11:02.502 --> 02:11:05.109
Is this government's approach
investing more in our

4247991840
02:11:05.110 --> 02:11:07.516
defence industry that
develops and sustains it?

2346323801
02:11:07.517 --> 02:11:10.324
Is this Labour government's
approach and investing more

2983615264
02:11:10.325 --> 02:11:12.732
in our alliances that
multiply that hard power?

2460197382
02:11:12.733 --> 02:11:14.637
Is this Labour government's approach?

1253156999
02:11:14.638 --> 02:11:15.441
>> Will my hon.

3604618455
02:11:15.442 --> 02:11:16.093
Friend give.

1774278882
02:11:16.094 --> 02:11:16.896
>> Way, please?

3791184965
02:11:16.897 --> 02:11:18.303
>> I am grateful to my hon.

1582058857
02:11:18.304 --> 02:11:18.704
Friend.

231766469
02:11:18.705 --> 02:11:21.490
He's making a very powerful
case for how investing

4086617762
02:11:21.491 --> 02:11:23.639
in our armed forces and defence,

1376056681
02:11:23.639 --> 02:11:26.688
after 14 years of Tory
neglect is imperative to get

2901679250
02:11:26.689 --> 02:11:29.195
Britain growing and for
our defence preparedness.

2793538066
02:11:29.196 --> 02:11:31.987
But would he agree with me
that these capabilities

1535654685
02:11:31.989 --> 02:11:35.041
must always be exercised in the right way?

3440745344
02:11:35.041 --> 02:11:39.648
30 UK arms licences to Israel
were suspended in September 2024,

938229580
02:11:39.650 --> 02:11:43.487
but in light of the Iran war that he
mentioned and the fact that 72,000

914894430
02:11:43.487 --> 02:11:48.941
Palestinians have now been killed in
Gaza, could Ministers revisit this?

241815634
02:11:48.942 --> 02:11:51.750
I know that this worsening
means many constituents want

1248316941
02:11:51.751 --> 02:11:54.209
to end all arms sales with
the Netanyahu regime.

757154737
02:11:55.636 --> 02:11:55.886
Yes.

946277916
02:11:55.887 --> 02:12:00.335
>> Can I thank my friend
for her intervention?

1255610315
02:12:00.336 --> 02:12:02.593
This government has
called for a cease fire.

1512102790
02:12:02.594 --> 02:12:05.957
We have called for increased aid
to get to the people who need it.

1449986079
02:12:05.958 --> 02:12:08.365
We have introduced
an arms export against those

1610020836
02:12:08.366 --> 02:12:10.523
weapon systems that could be used in Gaza.

1124492470
02:12:10.523 --> 02:12:13.232
We keep, of course, all
export licences under review,

427252187
02:12:13.233 --> 02:12:14.688
but I think the whole house,

4147157016
02:12:14.689 --> 02:12:16.043
whichever party we are in,

2539729437
02:12:16.044 --> 02:12:20.240
want to see a lasting peace
and a two state solution.

2346508894
02:12:20.241 --> 02:12:22.599
So the people of Gaza,
Palestine can live side

2261918486
02:12:22.600 --> 02:12:25.389
by side alongside a secure Israel as well.

2419099458
02:12:25.391 --> 02:12:28.752
That is the effort that this
government is making on that respect.

3859156820
02:12:28.753 --> 02:12:32.887
Now, Madam Deputy Speaker,
the conservative equipment plan

3553669485
02:12:32.888 --> 02:12:36.385
that we inherited in July
2024 was overcommitted.

3813240254
02:12:36.386 --> 02:12:39.648
It was underfunded and unsuited
to the threats we now face.

3335408734
02:12:39.648 --> 02:12:43.439
This Labour government is rearming,
renewing our armed forces

1541754470
02:12:43.440 --> 02:12:47.392
and ending the Tory hollowing out
and underfunding that we inherited.

1120714576
02:12:47.639 --> 02:12:49.895
Our strategic defence
review and our Defence

3722661217
02:12:51.636 --> 02:12:53.491
Investment Plan will put that right.

3114164805
02:12:53.492 --> 02:12:54.044
And as we.

2727269201
02:12:54.045 --> 02:12:57.592
If you're listening to the Defence
Secretary speech last night,

2517992982
02:12:57.593 --> 02:12:59.986
you will heard him say,
it's getting close.

1882690144
02:12:59.987 --> 02:13:00.739
I'll give way.

2470627739
02:13:00.740 --> 02:13:03.398
>> Really grateful for
the Ministers for giving way.

3343299922
02:13:03.398 --> 02:13:05.492
But when is this going to happen?

350877098
02:13:05.493 --> 02:13:06.798
All we can see around us.

993712307
02:13:06.799 --> 02:13:09.005
I represent a constituency
with the highest

2940340016
02:13:09.005 --> 02:13:10.711
proportion of veterans in the UK.

867456229
02:13:10.712 --> 02:13:12.768
They take a really, really keen interest

747717218
02:13:12.769 --> 02:13:14.626
in what goes on in our armed forces.

1287076941
02:13:14.627 --> 02:13:17.334
We look across the harbour,
across Portsmouth harbour

2067262207
02:13:17.335 --> 02:13:19.341
to ships that are sat there stationary,

737836570
02:13:19.342 --> 02:13:21.648
not going anywhere,
and the defence industry,

2249110960
02:13:21.648 --> 02:13:24.240
which is being undermined at every step.

2075559051
02:13:24.241 --> 02:13:28.444
When is the government going to
actually put this word into action?

2360666969
02:13:28.445 --> 02:13:29.197
>> Yeah, yeah.

1429738688
02:13:29.198 --> 02:13:31.355
>> Well, I can thank her for intervention.

251188355
02:13:31.356 --> 02:13:33.715
She, like me, represents
an area with a lot of

265366228
02:13:33.716 --> 02:13:35.822
military personnel and a lot of veterans.

1556531455
02:13:35.823 --> 02:13:39.284
That's why she, I know, will welcome
the fact that veterans spending

3413651932
02:13:39.285 --> 02:13:41.994
is now at a record high under
this Labour government.

2323959646
02:13:41.995 --> 02:13:44.753
We are working to deliver
the defence investment plan,

3489472897
02:13:44.754 --> 02:13:47.914
but that has not stopped us from
investing in new capabilities

3739568395
02:13:47.915 --> 02:13:50.224
that I'll come to in
a moment in this speech,

1672492362
02:13:50.225 --> 02:13:53.285
but I will give away to Ministers
following these words, as.

311145467
02:13:53.286 --> 02:13:54.790
>> Always with much interest.

185245593
02:13:54.791 --> 02:13:57.450
>> Has he had a conversation
with the former Health.

1216499122
02:13:57.451 --> 02:13:58.189
>> Secretary.

1048856643
02:13:58.190 --> 02:14:01.990
>> Who last Thursday spoke
of dither and delay?

4052476015
02:14:01.991 --> 02:14:08.296
And does he relate that
to the extraordinary

1930982921
02:14:08.297 --> 02:14:10.202
delay in the Defence Investment Plan?

456692423
02:14:10.203 --> 02:14:12.760
>> Madam Deputy Speaker,
I always welcome recruits

937456937
02:14:12.761 --> 02:14:14.817
to our armed forces and defence debates,

200665134
02:14:14.818 --> 02:14:17.125
and the Member for Ilford
North is absolutely

2142340477
02:14:17.126 --> 02:14:19.231
welcoming our defence debates here today.

2662439191
02:14:19.232 --> 02:14:21.643
But may I say politely
to him, I focus a lot of

3646510927
02:14:21.644 --> 02:14:24.046
attention on the gentleman
opposite me here,

954447870
02:14:24.047 --> 02:14:26.655
who left an unfunded
and hollowed out armed forces.

