Majesty's gracious speech to this House.

2637033873
02:23:50.703 --> 02:23:54.052
>> I call the Liberal Democrat
spokesperson, James MacCleary.

82419339
02:23:54.053 --> 02:23:55.106
>> Thank you, Madam.

886439852
02:23:55.107 --> 02:23:56.059
>> Deputy Speaker.

377546630
02:23:56.060 --> 02:23:57.112
>> If His Majesty's.

1689008539
02:23:57.114 --> 02:23:59.221
>> Most gracious speech was meant to show

1990759014
02:23:59.222 --> 02:24:00.876
that this government has grasped

1095053375
02:24:00.877 --> 02:24:04.440
the scale of the danger facing Britain,
then it fell a long way short.

3079883359
02:24:04.441 --> 02:24:06.549
We live in a more dangerous world than at

126351005
02:24:06.550 --> 02:24:08.608
any point since the end of the Cold War.

1390723529
02:24:08.609 --> 02:24:10.615
Vladimir Putin is waging war in Europe.

1520921422
02:24:10.616 --> 02:24:13.224
Ukraine is fighting not
just for its very survival.

3110914685
02:24:13.225 --> 02:24:15.331
But the security of our entire continent.

1916963186
02:24:15.332 --> 02:24:17.987
Across Europe, we're seeing
sabotage, cyber attacks,

1322704156
02:24:18.647 --> 02:24:21.101
disinformation, intimidation
and hybrid warfare.

2883584891
02:24:21.102 --> 02:24:24.614
Further afield, the world order is
being tested by the rise of China,

913568314
02:24:24.615 --> 02:24:28.148
by instability in the Middle East
and by authoritarian regimes.

3968811926
02:24:28.150 --> 02:24:31.505
Are watching very carefully
to see whether democracies

3587496654
02:24:31.507 --> 02:24:33.713
still have the resolve
to defend ourselves.

2123000946
02:24:33.714 --> 02:24:36.152
And at the same time,
we can no longer assume

3516933834
02:24:36.153 --> 02:24:38.058
that old certainties will still hold.

2584038526
02:24:38.059 --> 02:24:41.245
The United States remains a vital ally,

4154952029
02:24:41.246 --> 02:24:44.047
but President Trump has
shown just how quickly

2281054390
02:24:44.048 --> 02:24:46.103
long standing alliances can be weakened,

390559982
02:24:46.103 --> 02:24:47.758
questioned or taken for granted.

4230994461
02:24:47.759 --> 02:24:49.853
This is the reality facing Britain.

1433692290
02:24:49.853 --> 02:24:52.357
So this should have been a king's speech

3954644611
02:24:52.358 --> 02:24:54.414
that put national security at its heart.

1116823210
02:24:54.647 --> 02:24:58.344
It should have been a moment of
seriousness, urgency and ambition.

3053969249
02:24:58.344 --> 02:25:01.657
Instead, once again, we
got more delay and more

3980934988
02:25:01.657 --> 02:25:03.916
warm words that are not
backed up by action.

3942899019
02:25:03.916 --> 02:25:08.160
Now, we all know the Conservatives
hollowed out our armed forces,

2972898020
02:25:08.161 --> 02:25:11.356
but this Labour government
cannot simply point to

310934007
02:25:11.357 --> 02:25:14.016
the failures of the past
and pretend that is enough.

4275556092
02:25:14.017 --> 02:25:15.823
It now has a responsibility to act,

105308483
02:25:15.824 --> 02:25:18.255
but so far it is moving far too slowly.

1119545767
02:25:18.257 --> 02:25:19.110
I will give way.

370205980
02:25:19.111 --> 02:25:19.862
>> Giving way.

3640147196
02:25:19.864 --> 02:25:22.273
>> And he is right to
point out the devastating

2500391886
02:25:22.648 --> 02:25:24.152
record of the party opposite.

3619263002
02:25:24.153 --> 02:25:27.364
But will he share my sadness
and frustration of the role played

943964860
02:25:27.365 --> 02:25:31.011
by the Liberal Democrats in
hollowing out the size of

4109216484
02:25:31.012 --> 02:25:34.522
our armed forces and waving through
Budget after Budget after Budget,

2205714349
02:25:34.523 --> 02:25:36.728
which cut defence
spending in this country.

3085904949
02:25:36.730 --> 02:25:39.005
And will he own up to that sorry record?

465242656
02:25:39.005 --> 02:25:39.407
>> Yes.

2246468361
02:25:39.407 --> 02:25:40.361
>> Thank you, hon.

3198340878
02:25:40.362 --> 02:25:41.865
Member, for his intervention.

682193180
02:25:41.866 --> 02:25:45.226
As has already been pointed out,
defence spending has been reduced

2354031321
02:25:45.227 --> 02:25:48.186
by successive governments over
a very long period of time.

1175127156
02:25:48.187 --> 02:25:50.846
So I think I think focusing
on the Liberal Democrats

4056711481
02:25:50.847 --> 02:25:53.405
record alone is somewhat
unfair, to say the least.

2036668153
02:25:53.406 --> 02:25:55.062
I certainly give way to the hon.

3398794678
02:25:55.063 --> 02:25:55.612
Gentleman.

2300177928
02:25:55.614 --> 02:25:56.216
>> Can you.

2178248752
02:25:56.217 --> 02:25:57.270
>> Remind the House.

353573270
02:25:57.271 --> 02:25:58.073
>> Which party.

4292215031
02:25:58.648 --> 02:25:59.603
>> It was, who in.

513576809
02:25:59.603 --> 02:26:04.253
>> Coalition insisted that we
delay cas d replacement by two.

2570478041
02:26:04.254 --> 02:26:09.291
Full years as a condition
of the coalition?

370206466
02:26:09.293 --> 02:26:09.895
>> The hon.

488997009
02:26:10.651 --> 02:26:13.108
Member enjoys raising
the coalition quite a lot.

1656919485
02:26:13.109 --> 02:26:13.359
The.

2155499713
02:26:13.360 --> 02:26:16.166
You're talking about
the nuclear submarines, won't you?

3574536716
02:26:16.168 --> 02:26:17.071
Is that what you.

286595990
02:26:17.072 --> 02:26:18.526
That's what you asked about.

2586201489
02:26:18.647 --> 02:26:19.800
>> Order on your feet.

1644127034
02:26:19.802 --> 02:26:20.605
I'm on my feet.

4148881976
02:26:20.606 --> 02:26:21.157
Excuse me.

186089757
02:26:21.648 --> 02:26:23.302
I wasn't talking about anything.

294892604
02:26:23.303 --> 02:26:26.758
So please don't use the word
you or your James MacCleary.

2230109231
02:26:26.759 --> 02:26:29.566
>> The Liberal Democrats have
reaffirmed our commitment

1736150763
02:26:29.567 --> 02:26:31.421
to our nuclear deterrent repeatedly,

1380521059
02:26:31.422 --> 02:26:32.978
and we will continue to do so.

1438132973
02:26:32.978 --> 02:26:35.586
The Defence Investment plan
is still not published.

274902588
02:26:35.587 --> 02:26:37.759
Industry is still waiting for certainty.

69347996
02:26:37.760 --> 02:26:40.299
Our allies are still waiting for clarity.

2048508402
02:26:40.300 --> 02:26:43.950
Our armed forces are still waiting
for the investment they need.

410335422
02:26:43.951 --> 02:26:47.159
It was therefore deeply disappointing
that the promised Defence

1088937767
02:26:47.160 --> 02:26:49.868
Readiness Bill was not
included in the King's Speech.

1900390147
02:26:49.869 --> 02:26:52.025
It speaks volume that the government's own

3105934371
02:26:52.026 --> 02:26:54.103
bill on readiness is itself delayed.

919028434
02:26:54.105 --> 02:26:57.213
That matters because defence
cannot be switched on overnight.

4087316113
02:26:57.214 --> 02:27:01.097
You cannot rebuild capacity in
industry at the flick of a switch.

3728878406
02:27:01.098 --> 02:27:04.455
You cannot train personnel, repair
readiness, modernise equipment,

3300433700
02:27:04.456 --> 02:27:08.111
strengthen supply chains
and restore deterrence

2087372245
02:27:08.112 --> 02:27:10.855
with vague promises
or indeed working at pace.

3703639170
02:27:10.856 --> 02:27:11.356
Secondly.

2396278808
02:27:11.357 --> 02:27:13.800
>> One of the things that we we need

4124961280
02:27:13.802 --> 02:27:17.352
the government needs to improve upon.

128359448
02:27:17.353 --> 02:27:18.808
There needs to be better at.

3885005770
02:27:18.809 --> 02:27:20.252
Is drone technology.

2323857723
02:27:20.253 --> 02:27:25.108
Understand that for every one
Ukrainian soldier is killed,

2218628113
02:27:25.109 --> 02:27:26.262
they kill 14 Russians.

1965503583
02:27:26.263 --> 02:27:28.168
With that massive move in technology,

1713474210
02:27:28.169 --> 02:27:30.226
does he feel it's time for this country,

2001730914
02:27:30.227 --> 02:27:32.884
United Kingdom of Great
Britain or Northern Ireland,

2652408918
02:27:32.885 --> 02:27:34.690
to have a partnership with Ukraine?

2681010187
02:27:34.691 --> 02:27:37.261
So the technological advances that they're

397784764
02:27:37.262 --> 02:27:38.918
they're doing can be part of us.

955292043
02:27:38.919 --> 02:27:40.505
>> I think the hon.

1879384184
02:27:40.505 --> 02:27:44.116
Member and yes, obviously, learning
from Ukraine can be very important.

1853165400
02:27:44.117 --> 02:27:46.174
And the government, to be fair, I think,

1016042705
02:27:46.175 --> 02:27:48.181
have made some steps in this direction.

1452618368
02:27:48.182 --> 02:27:51.445
But we can always do more to learn
from our our friends who are,

2031616248
02:27:51.446 --> 02:27:54.657
you know, testing this technology
in the field day in, day out.

1149082116
02:27:54.657 --> 02:27:57.768
So I think it's very important
point, but defence takes time.

4265747683
02:27:57.769 --> 02:27:59.373
Industry needs a demand signal.

3059830567
02:27:59.374 --> 02:28:00.777
Our allies need confidence.

4274064813
02:28:00.778 --> 02:28:02.633
Our adversaries need to see resolve.

3922591028
02:28:02.634 --> 02:28:06.045
That is why the Liberal Democrats
are calling for the government to

3836388086
02:28:06.046 --> 02:28:09.208
commit to spending 3% of GDP on
defence by 2030 at the latest,

3196319876
02:28:09.209 --> 02:28:11.016
not as a slogan or a press release,

1627604820
02:28:11.017 --> 02:28:13.275
but as a serious plan
to make Britain safer.

3689305300
02:28:13.276 --> 02:28:15.632
We must also understand
that Britain's defence

892796273
02:28:15.633 --> 02:28:17.540
does not begin and end at our border.

2799646907
02:28:17.541 --> 02:28:20.400
That is why forcing a choice
between spending on defence

1968957438
02:28:20.401 --> 02:28:23.452
and international development
is entirely false.

2596572224
02:28:23.453 --> 02:28:27.056
Just yesterday, former senior
British officers wrote in The Times

4226067207
02:28:27.057 --> 02:28:30.317
about the danger that cuts to
development posed to our security.

3899541025
02:28:30.318 --> 02:28:33.361
They described it as the first
line of defence for the UK.

763524778
02:28:33.362 --> 02:28:36.862
The government must urgently reverse
course on these cuts that only

4049151541
02:28:36.862 --> 02:28:41.219
undermine this country's security
and soft power around the world.

501221758
02:28:41.221 --> 02:28:44.128
Last year's Strategic Defence
Review highlighted the need

3182904955
02:28:44.129 --> 02:28:46.888
for an urgent injection of
cash into our armed forces.

1572039156
02:28:46.889 --> 02:28:49.196
That is why Liberal
Democrats are calling for

2206045380
02:28:49.197 --> 02:28:51.152
the immediate launch of defence bonds,

1360350529
02:28:51.153 --> 02:28:54.155
raising G20 billion over two
years to support immediate

3288385698
02:28:54.156 --> 02:28:56.059
capital intensive defence investment.

2039031691
02:28:56.060 --> 02:28:57.414
I certainly will, the hon.

2810803459
02:28:57.415 --> 02:28:57.815
Member.

2525021975
02:28:57.816 --> 02:28:59.671
>> Always very generous, giving way.

1807528030
02:28:59.672 --> 02:29:01.127
I have to say that, speaker.

2041340187
02:29:01.128 --> 02:29:04.590
He says that issue war bonds for
the for the extra defence spending,

4120329274
02:29:04.591 --> 02:29:06.697
which is of course, just other borrowing.

518317541
02:29:06.698 --> 02:29:10.009
But he's also said he would maintain
aid spending at 0.7 percent.

2159286107
02:29:10.010 --> 02:29:11.815
That's a huge increase in spending.

1580987404
02:29:11.816 --> 02:29:13.120
How would that be funded.

4267528242
02:29:13.121 --> 02:29:14.174
So it's quite right.

3244724220
02:29:14.175 --> 02:29:17.536
>> Of course defence bonds, as with
all bonds, would be borrowing.

1999664211
02:29:17.537 --> 02:29:20.094
And we've spoken before
about the need to increase

4092345414
02:29:20.096 --> 02:29:22.300
defence spending through
cross-party talks.

3331745502
02:29:22.300 --> 02:29:25.215
And the reversal in aid
spending is part of an overall

1843667878
02:29:25.216 --> 02:29:27.675
package of of how we would
Budget in the future.

350599729
02:29:27.675 --> 02:29:29.734
I mean, one of the ways we've looked at,

1914435941
02:29:29.735 --> 02:29:31.641
and we will be proposing later today,

916797810
02:29:31.642 --> 02:29:34.350
is rejoining a customs union
with the European Union,

3386065422
02:29:34.351 --> 02:29:36.606
which would generate
increased spending that

4232088691
02:29:36.607 --> 02:29:38.562
would help modernise our armed forces.

2925198777
02:29:38.563 --> 02:29:40.968
It would strengthen our
sovereign capabilities.

845246975
02:29:40.969 --> 02:29:42.974
It would support British defence firms,

2778476761
02:29:42.975 --> 02:29:45.632
including the small
and medium sized businesses that

953608
02:29:45.633 --> 02:29:48.041
are so often at the cutting
edge of innovation.

1916118350
02:29:48.041 --> 02:29:50.250
It would give the
the public a direct stake

1674578589
02:29:50.251 --> 02:29:52.458
in the defence
and security of our country.

841589475
02:29:52.459 --> 02:29:55.317
This is about spending better,
not simply spending more.

3833496305
02:29:55.318 --> 02:29:57.775
For too long, defence
procurement has been slow,

3494571010
02:29:57.776 --> 02:29:59.128
bureaucratic and wasteful.

3799659556
02:29:59.129 --> 02:30:01.084
Too many programmes have been delayed.

526192974
02:30:01.085 --> 02:30:02.639
Too many costs have spiralled.

1369042514
02:30:02.639 --> 02:30:05.097
Too often British industry
has been left without

3673420944
02:30:05.098 --> 02:30:07.907
the certainty it needs to
invest, hire, train and grow.

3518058917
02:30:07.907 --> 02:30:10.013
If we're serious about national security,

2690709261
02:30:10.014 --> 02:30:12.571
we must also be serious
about industrial security.

1358576638
02:30:12.572 --> 02:30:14.675
That means backing British manufacturing.

1690433037
02:30:14.677 --> 02:30:17.083
It means investing in
research and development.

3484321540
02:30:17.084 --> 02:30:19.790
It means supporting
apprenticeships and skilled jobs.

1363484130
02:30:19.791 --> 02:30:22.548
It means making sure that
defence spending strengthens

874881549
02:30:22.549 --> 02:30:24.202
communities across this country,

2007467577
02:30:24.203 --> 02:30:27.757
not just the balance sheets of
a handful of prime contractors.

1644803807
02:30:27.758 --> 02:30:30.366
It also means recognising
that in the modern world,

2982566170
02:30:30.367 --> 02:30:32.725
defence is not just about
the number of tanks,

4235232307
02:30:32.726 --> 02:30:34.314
ships and aircraft we possess.

3771868825
02:30:34.315 --> 02:30:37.264
Important though they are, it
is also about cyber space,

1354836436
02:30:37.266 --> 02:30:38.969
drones, AI, secure supply chains,

1657038184
02:30:38.971 --> 02:30:42.531
energy resilience and the ability to
move quickly when threats change.

834696926
02:30:42.532 --> 02:30:45.656
Climate change is causing
global instability.

854564861
02:30:45.657 --> 02:30:48.264
Melting ice opens up new
flashpoints in the Arctic.

291666847
02:30:48.266 --> 02:30:52.859
Stress on food and water resources
drives displacement and conflict.

2003153202
02:30:52.860 --> 02:30:56.121
Our armed forces need the tools
to fight the wars of the future,

627344590
02:30:56.123 --> 02:30:58.382
not just patch up
the gaps left by the past.

4269317999
02:30:58.655 --> 02:31:00.360
But Britain cannot do this alone.

15713590
02:31:00.361 --> 02:31:02.568
If the last century has
taught us anything,

2125771766
02:31:02.569 --> 02:31:04.826
and if recent years have
taught us anything,

1085148855
02:31:04.827 --> 02:31:08.241
it is that our security is bound
up with that of our of our allies.

556669255
02:31:08.655 --> 02:31:12.267
That is why we must be unwavering in
our continued support for Ukraine.

1886012170
02:31:12.268 --> 02:31:13.521
We must strengthen NATO.

2559953955
02:31:13.522 --> 02:31:15.777
We must deepen cooperation
with Commonwealth

802268491
02:31:15.778 --> 02:31:18.009
allies like Canada and Australia,

4005730546
02:31:18.010 --> 02:31:21.763
and we must rebuild a serious
defence relationship with Europe.

3609459490
02:31:21.764 --> 02:31:25.914
The Liberal Democrats have called
for a new European rearmament bank

1390063732
02:31:25.915 --> 02:31:29.123
and for UK participation in
Europe's Safe Rearmament programme.

1111644685
02:31:29.124 --> 02:31:31.331
These would allow Britain
and our allies to

2455127167
02:31:31.332 --> 02:31:33.437
mobilise investment at the scale required

4039800378
02:31:33.438 --> 02:31:37.098
to ensure our defence industries lead
the next generation of technology,

4279236221
02:31:37.099 --> 02:31:39.355
while also generating
the economies of scale

1248440169
02:31:39.356 --> 02:31:41.513
needed to reduce costs over the long term.

881454441
02:31:41.514 --> 02:31:44.509
This isn't about choosing
between Britain and Europe,

2398883004
02:31:44.510 --> 02:31:48.171
it's about recognising the obvious
truth that Britain is safer when the.

747063150
02:31:48.172 --> 02:31:53.108
When Europe is stronger and Europe
is stronger when Britain leads.

4044393262
02:31:53.109 --> 02:31:56.761
National security should not be subject
to short term political gains.

1345390607
02:31:56.762 --> 02:31:59.621
That is why we have called on
the government to urgently

2033071429
02:31:59.623 --> 02:32:03.111
convene cross-party talks
on how we reach 3% by 2030.

3604659274
02:32:03.112 --> 02:32:06.323
Our adversaries are not waiting
for us to get our act together.

1810303961
02:32:06.324 --> 02:32:08.782
Our armed forces should
not have to wait either.

837615365
02:32:08.782 --> 02:32:11.858
Defence requires all of
society to be involved.

1089016156
02:32:11.859 --> 02:32:14.314
Being ready to defend our nation means

287009270
02:32:14.315 --> 02:32:16.269
also building our national resilience.

3707271869
02:32:16.655 --> 02:32:20.909
The government must move faster
and show far more ambition to involve

386192452
02:32:20.910 --> 02:32:24.665
the public in defence and security,
should the worst ever happen,

746980118
02:32:24.666 --> 02:32:27.627
than having 70 million of us
ready to come to our nation's

3227678615
02:32:27.656 --> 02:32:29.862
defence is the most
powerful weapon of all.

2081441888
02:32:29.864 --> 02:32:32.069
But it requires leadership
from government,

871202740
02:32:32.070 --> 02:32:35.114
and that has so far been absent,

3182993554
02:32:35.115 --> 02:32:37.370
despite promises of
a national conversation.

3975143780
02:32:37.371 --> 02:32:39.929
This means learning from
our friends in the Baltic

4217931029
02:32:39.930 --> 02:32:41.886
and elsewhere about how we can harness

2250508427
02:32:41.887 --> 02:32:44.161
the talents of
the British people to become

3418630976
02:32:44.162 --> 02:32:46.016
more resilient and prepared country.

3171511567
02:32:46.017 --> 02:32:49.069
The best way to prevent
a war is to prepare for it.

457990990
02:32:49.070 --> 02:32:51.378
The choice before us is
clear we can continue

3817902657
02:32:51.379 --> 02:32:53.267
with managed decline, delayed plans,

1698099285
02:32:53.268 --> 02:32:56.810
underpowered commitments,
or we can choose seriousness.

1836782521
02:32:56.811 --> 02:33:00.460
We can publish the Defence Investment
Plan and Defence Readiness Bill.

2769103651
02:33:00.461 --> 02:33:01.916
We can commit to 3% by 2030.

1804470244
02:33:01.918 --> 02:33:05.468
We can launch defence bonds,
we can back British industry.

1536816259
02:33:05.660 --> 02:33:09.920
We can rebuild our armed forces,
we can strengthen our alliances,

592157790
02:33:09.921 --> 02:33:13.109
and we can send a clear
and unambiguous message to Putin

3591571300
02:33:13.110 --> 02:33:16.358
and to every other authoritarian
regime watching us.

1552021291
02:33:16.359 --> 02:33:20.272
Britain will defend itself, its allies,
its values and its way of life.

1104010989
02:33:20.273 --> 02:33:23.611
That is the ambition that this
King's Speech should have shown,

3012382368
02:33:23.612 --> 02:33:25.769
and that is the action this country needs.

463224496
02:33:25.770 --> 02:33:31.211
And that is why Liberal Democrats
will continue fighting for it.

2251982980
02:33:31.212 --> 02:33:33.718
>> Select Committee Chair
Tanmanjeet Singh Dhesi.

330228265
02:33:33.719 --> 02:33:36.058
>> Thank you very much,
Madam Deputy Speaker.

2243894103
02:33:36.059 --> 02:33:40.227
His Majesty the King opened his
speech by noting that, and I quote,

1084430188
02:33:41.657 --> 02:33:43.611
an increasingly dangerous and volatile

3206692046
02:33:43.612 --> 02:33:46.162
world threatens the United Kingdom.

738512718
02:33:46.163 --> 02:33:49.161
We have seen unprecedented military action

3797816194
02:33:49.162 --> 02:33:50.814
and instability internationally,

2968809964
02:33:50.815 --> 02:33:55.159
with the conflict in the Middle East
being only the most recent example.

3747438413
02:33:55.160 --> 02:34:00.017
Closer to home, we have the continued
concerns about the security

448062559
02:34:00.018 --> 02:34:04.109
of Ukraine deterring further
Russian action on the European

1160848590
02:34:04.110 --> 02:34:08.871
continent and creating a resilient
society ready to support

760063690
02:34:08.873 --> 02:34:12.164
our government and armed
forces if we have to respond.

4170471908
02:34:12.165 --> 02:34:15.714
As I have previously noted in this House,

3965647896
02:34:15.715 --> 02:34:19.612
our once dependable ally,
the United States,

1849986619
02:34:19.614 --> 02:34:22.507
is withdrawing from its historic role as

3108387358
02:34:22.508 --> 02:34:24.413
the protector of democracy in Europe.

1900766725
02:34:25.663 --> 02:34:30.059
It has become increasingly
clear to us on the defence

3317534595
02:34:30.060 --> 02:34:34.111
Committee that there is
an overreliance on the USA,

778550019
02:34:34.112 --> 02:34:37.870
both militarily and for access
to its defence industrial base.

3485350408
02:34:37.871 --> 02:34:41.990
When we see, as a result of the Iran war,

2378487960
02:34:41.991 --> 02:34:45.624
the US delaying deliveries
and increasing the cost

3087060811
02:34:45.625 --> 02:34:49.669
of Patriot missiles already
sold to Switzerland,

749389776
02:34:49.670 --> 02:34:53.360
we must examine our own dependencies.

3411886868
02:34:53.361 --> 02:34:55.216
That is, it is becoming increasingly

1548987505
02:34:56.659 --> 02:34:58.514
unclear how far that is sustainable,

90542801
02:34:58.514 --> 02:35:00.571
I warned in March, Madam Deputy Speaker,

3031542300
02:35:00.572 --> 02:35:05.219
that Russia is already operating
in the grey zone against the UK,

121291630
02:35:07.619 --> 02:35:10.075
notably in sabotage
and cyber operations against

3291268739
02:35:10.660 --> 02:35:13.115
the infrastructure that
supports our prosperity.

1763420718
02:35:14.659 --> 02:35:19.514
Furthermore, we know that Russia
and others and China are arming

2098700773
02:35:19.514 --> 02:35:23.611
at pace and are increasing
their readiness for war.

2748148961
02:35:23.612 --> 02:35:28.712
And yet many UK capability
targets are measured

1009567522
02:35:28.713 --> 02:35:31.059
in years and decades rather than months.

2791213649
02:35:31.060 --> 02:35:35.112
Neither the government, our military
nor our society are yet prepared

1025769672
02:35:35.114 --> 02:35:40.474
or resilient enough to cope
with a large scale conflict.

2938955725
02:35:40.475 --> 02:35:45.164
As His Majesty warned us a week ago,

3332596378
02:35:45.165 --> 02:35:51.264
and I quote every defence
and element of the nation's energy,

1175276530
02:35:51.264 --> 02:35:54.624
defence and economic security will
be tested Madam Deputy Speaker.

2281879326
02:35:54.625 --> 02:35:58.560
The UK's armed forces need to both
improve their current readiness

4207505340
02:35:58.561 --> 02:36:02.612
and adopt new technologies
at pace and at scale.

734777905
02:36:02.614 --> 02:36:04.768
The government has consistently recognised

2786597299
02:36:04.769 --> 02:36:06.775
that our armed forces are hollowed out.

3407181431
02:36:07.620 --> 02:36:09.525
Both the Strategic Defence Review and

3728379144
02:36:09.526 --> 02:36:11.580
the National Security Strategy committed

2233153136
02:36:11.581 --> 02:36:14.763
the government to improving
the UK's warfighting readiness.

1625444426
02:36:16.661 --> 02:36:21.059
However, our credibility has
been harmed in recent months.

2437155279
02:36:21.060 --> 02:36:24.862
The lack of available frigates
and destroyers to carry out

1740708038
02:36:24.862 --> 02:36:30.065
the tasks which we have set ourselves
and often agreed with NATO,

3651224162
02:36:30.066 --> 02:36:34.373
is merely one example of
the difficulties faced.

2789453677
02:36:34.374 --> 02:36:39.379
The US is carrying out a NATO audit
and it's looking hard at us.

2348044495
02:36:40.664 --> 02:36:42.969
Our European partners
are questioning whether

3243217791
02:36:42.969 --> 02:36:45.062
we can deliver the commitments

2388812872
02:36:45.063 --> 02:36:50.865
which we have made to NATO under
the defence planning process,

302071849
02:36:50.866 --> 02:36:57.914
and indeed, whether we continue to
deserve our leadership role in NATO.

2613912756
02:36:57.915 --> 02:37:01.066
Madam Deputy Speaker, in
the Defence Committee's report,

2037666396
02:37:01.067 --> 02:37:04.413
looking at the UK's contribution
to European security,

784714770
02:37:04.414 --> 02:37:07.466
we warned that time is
short, given the urgency of

4240573776
02:37:07.467 --> 02:37:11.864
the threat and the work required
to respond appropriately.

2034160315
02:37:11.865 --> 02:37:18.464
We raise questions both about
the sufficiency of capabilities we

1621412827
02:37:18.465 --> 02:37:23.066
provide to NATO and those which
we could protect our homeland.

2272660214
02:37:23.067 --> 02:37:26.425
We questioned the government's
progress on engaging the population

2445148932
02:37:27.660 --> 02:37:30.069
about both the threat
and how we respond to it.

2909035258
02:37:30.070 --> 02:37:34.259
We have also looked at long
term procurement programmes,

587739729
02:37:34.260 --> 02:37:36.314
completing the previous committee's work

3499175607
02:37:36.315 --> 02:37:39.273
on the Global Combat Air programme,

4575622
02:37:39.275 --> 02:37:42.569
along with undertaking
a new inquiry into Aukus.

1277597699
02:37:42.570 --> 02:37:46.367
We are well aware that
decisions taken today,

2934696424
02:37:46.368 --> 02:37:49.916
particularly those which
delay programme or

1098539149
02:37:49.916 --> 02:37:52.760
lead to the loss of sovereign capability,

4074846444
02:37:52.761 --> 02:37:56.561
have a huge impact on
our future ability to

1785548823
02:37:56.562 --> 02:38:00.313
defend our nation and deter adversaries.

3551400040
02:38:00.314 --> 02:38:04.916
And so, Madam Deputy Speaker, we
await the Defence Investment Plan.

1285976617
02:38:04.916 --> 02:38:08.973
We know that the delay is
damaging both our domestic

3720459657
02:38:08.974 --> 02:38:12.014
industry and our
international credibility.

3632578038
02:38:12.014 --> 02:38:15.163
We don't have empty factories,
spare components or a surplus

1944618622
02:38:15.164 --> 02:38:19.468
of welders sitting around
waiting to jump into action.

1494345506
02:38:19.469 --> 02:38:22.367
Once the government decides what it wants.

279408994
02:38:22.368 --> 02:38:24.824
Companies don't have
warehouses full of supplies

2819716975
02:38:24.825 --> 02:38:27.364
waiting for government
to put their order in.

2657088964
02:38:27.365 --> 02:38:30.766
Defence industry needs
to increase capacity.

920821381
02:38:30.767 --> 02:38:35.166
That means building
production lines and training

994077687
02:38:35.168 --> 02:38:37.375
people so that they can
build the products.

42927211
02:38:37.376 --> 02:38:38.929
That is particularly relevant.

89210448
02:38:39.621 --> 02:38:41.877
Madam Deputy Speaker,
if allies and partners

1771347084
02:38:41.878 --> 02:38:45.722
are buying the same
things at the same time,

1211950799
02:38:45.723 --> 02:38:50.826
as we have seen as a result of
the war in Ukraine, most importantly,

1421008039
02:38:50.827 --> 02:38:55.213
we don't know at what rate the government

2923552040
02:38:55.214 --> 02:38:56.668
intends to reach the targets

1893190609
02:38:56.669 --> 02:38:59.728
of 3% GDP on defence spending,
hopefully in this Parliament.

4277323377
02:39:03.663 --> 02:39:07.921
Madam Deputy Speaker or
the NATO 3.5% target by 2035,

3719743039
02:39:07.922 --> 02:39:12.064
and all the various
defence financing options

2761678057
02:39:12.065 --> 02:39:13.619
need to be rapidly considered,

4031305791
02:39:13.620 --> 02:39:16.564
with some implemented ASAP.

3688100522
02:39:16.565 --> 02:39:19.163
Also, I have asked the Prime Minister.

3040835967
02:39:19.164 --> 02:39:21.270
Madam Deputy Speaker, if he would publish

4294903824
02:39:21.271 --> 02:39:24.569
a timeline so that industry could plan,

3558978665
02:39:24.570 --> 02:39:28.572
based on when this additional
funding would arrive.

3454627318
02:39:28.573 --> 02:39:32.268
He refused to give
the certainty beyond 2027,

444647565
02:39:32.269 --> 02:39:35.464
and we need that certainty.

388292222
02:39:35.465 --> 02:39:39.775
The US and the EU are looking
at our defence industrial

2055059584
02:39:39.776 --> 02:39:43.668
base and working out how
best they can tempt

1691389572
02:39:43.669 --> 02:39:47.617
our companies to move out
to their countries so

3774637115
02:39:47.618 --> 02:39:50.264
that they can benefit
from British innovation.

2971998426
02:39:50.264 --> 02:39:54.365
Whilst we fail to provide
a reason to stay here.

3325373796
02:39:54.366 --> 02:39:56.922
Madam Deputy Speaker,
the defence Committee warned

2557630053
02:39:56.923 --> 02:39:59.568
in our European Security
Report that establishing

3924018873
02:39:59.569 --> 02:40:02.869
this takes time and if
the government just decides

3555100958
02:40:02.870 --> 02:40:07.022
to turn on the tap at the last minute,

667419901
02:40:07.023 --> 02:40:10.617
a lot of taxpayers money will
be lost to defence inflation,

3889880148
02:40:10.618 --> 02:40:13.820
leaving the MoD with very
little to show for it.

92482549
02:40:13.821 --> 02:40:16.865
Let me now move on to
the Defence Readiness Bill,

3482941809
02:40:16.866 --> 02:40:20.368
which should have featured
prominently in the King's Speech.

935261980
02:40:20.369 --> 02:40:23.121
But alas, the government has not included.

4141279733
02:40:23.123 --> 02:40:26.369
The purpose of the Defence
Readiness Bill is to give

3050029149
02:40:26.370 --> 02:40:28.767
the government powers
in reserve to respond

2808051424
02:40:28.768 --> 02:40:32.068
effectively in the event
of escalation towards

3094629716
02:40:32.069 --> 02:40:35.264
a war involving the UK or its allies,

113200235
02:40:35.264 --> 02:40:38.072
and facilitate external security scrutiny

492878468
02:40:38.073 --> 02:40:39.978
of the UK's ability to defend itself.

4015840962
02:40:39.980 --> 02:40:42.821
The government is determining
which additional

3330457953
02:40:42.822 --> 02:40:46.071
legal powers it needs and looking

3511494678
02:40:46.072 --> 02:40:50.967
at measures to better protect our
critical national infrastructure,

3359183943
02:40:50.968 --> 02:40:56.717
providing for the mobilisation of
wider defence capability in crisis

2235955082
02:40:56.718 --> 02:41:00.175
and ensure Parliament's ability to
scrutinise warfighting readiness.

1158629197
02:41:00.175 --> 02:41:03.371
We were told that this work would include

59739626
02:41:03.373 --> 02:41:05.076
engagement with key stakeholders,

3715243193
02:41:05.077 --> 02:41:08.177
including other government
departments and the committee,

3308971030
02:41:08.178 --> 02:41:10.869
during 2026 as specific
measures are developed.

3239373819
02:41:10.870 --> 02:41:14.871
Drafting Madam Deputy Speaker
will then, and I quote,

1553873910
02:41:14.873 --> 02:41:19.172
take place following robust evidence
gathering and policy development.

1316829709
02:41:20.663 --> 02:41:23.072
All of this is welcome,
but we need a timeline.

2133863965
02:41:23.073 --> 02:41:26.025
In conclusion, Madam
Speaker, it is now more than

3871939414
02:41:27.666 --> 02:41:30.075
two years since the end
of the last Parliament.

2606478777
02:41:30.076 --> 02:41:32.370
The government has demonstrated again

323772218
02:41:32.371 --> 02:41:36.120
and again that it
understands the problems.

3311414446
02:41:36.121 --> 02:41:39.932
What it has failed to do is to
implement a transformative solution.

2101473617
02:41:41.666 --> 02:41:46.568
We need to fund defence properly,
with a timetable showing precisely

1076249397
02:41:46.569 --> 02:41:51.423
how and when we will reach
the agreed 3.5% NATO target.

76799522
02:41:51.424 --> 02:41:54.870
We urgently need a defence investment plan

363959507
02:41:54.871 --> 02:41:58.419
published before the summer recess,

1133941154
02:41:58.420 --> 02:42:00.526
which shows what is being invested where,

2536970346
02:42:02.666 --> 02:42:06.669
crucially, also where the investments
are and what the subsequent

3911329101
02:42:06.670 --> 02:42:11.923
changes to the structure of
the UK armed forces are.

467577095
02:42:11.924 --> 02:42:15.235
We need a Defence Readiness Bill
to be published in this session,

2426526920
02:42:15.236 --> 02:42:19.968
and we need a commitment that it will
undergo pre-legislative scrutiny.

1842388739
02:42:19.969 --> 02:42:22.778
We need to engage the public
in a national conversation

4229368264
02:42:22.779 --> 02:42:24.885
that the Prime Minister has talked about,

1740372482
02:42:24.886 --> 02:42:27.118
about spending more on defence and what

3290996658
02:42:27.119 --> 02:42:30.166
the public's role is in
our nation's security.

1558309299
02:42:30.168 --> 02:42:30.619
We know.

136763610
02:42:30.620 --> 02:42:33.620
Madam Deputy Speaker, that
the government is wary

3505471787
02:42:33.621 --> 02:42:37.224
of panicking the public, and rightly so.

1508696750
02:42:37.225 --> 02:42:41.473
But the best way to avoid that is by
ensuring that the public understand

10072101
02:42:41.474 --> 02:42:44.673
what is required of them as
individuals and communities,

3452425470
02:42:44.674 --> 02:42:48.576
and also to ensure that
our brave armed forces

3880408611
02:42:48.577 --> 02:42:52.521
have the necessary
capabilities to defend us.

3196842948
02:42:52.522 --> 02:42:54.963
Thank you very much.

3813688251
02:42:54.964 --> 02:42:55.365
>> Sir.

4149176210
02:42:55.366 --> 02:42:58.669
>> Iain Duncan Smith
Deputy Speaker It's always

2233629910
02:42:58.670 --> 02:43:00.918
a pleasure to follow the right hon.

1261991224
02:43:00.919 --> 02:43:04.080
Gentleman who I voted for for his
position, as he will recall,

4113352931
02:43:04.081 --> 02:43:05.887
and I'll come for payback later on.

796565455
02:43:05.888 --> 02:43:07.844
Can I also say, while I'm making this,

699077584
02:43:07.846 --> 02:43:12.225
it's very good to see my right hon.

2677377704
02:43:12.226 --> 02:43:14.670
Neighbour in my area sitting there,

3714715937
02:43:14.671 --> 02:43:18.273
and I will listen with great
interest to what he has to say,

2010877372
02:43:18.275 --> 02:43:20.633
and I hope that the Labour
Party finds another

1384336450
02:43:20.634 --> 02:43:24.925
use for him in its own talent spotting.

1839171450
02:43:24.925 --> 02:43:26.130
Can I put it like that?

3525186282
02:43:26.132 --> 02:43:29.675
Can I say, can I say,
Madam Deputy Speaker,

239752700
02:43:29.675 --> 02:43:32.185
I just want to touch on
before coming to defence.

1434949344
02:43:32.186 --> 02:43:36.675
After all, this is about
the the the address.

1896574388
02:43:36.675 --> 02:43:39.737
I just want to touch on
an issue that has arisen

274502155
02:43:39.739 --> 02:43:44.127
and my my assistant Britain
assistant Alice Stuttaford,

3584036755
02:43:44.668 --> 02:43:47.225
spotted yesterday something
which tells me that we

1134162720
02:43:47.226 --> 02:43:49.784
are in a slight problem
here with the government's

688462589
02:43:51.672 --> 02:43:54.532
commitment to the legal position
now of the use of slave

4083443752
02:43:54.532 --> 02:43:58.596
made products through
the Great British Energy Company,

3069651888
02:43:58.597 --> 02:44:01.578
and in answer to a question
we discovered through

309280173
02:44:01.579 --> 02:44:03.384
which was raised by Politico, that.

3533285426
02:44:03.385 --> 02:44:05.791
What was their position
with regards to whether

3479472179
02:44:05.793 --> 02:44:07.648
they were implementing what was law?

515665104
02:44:07.648 --> 02:44:10.409
Thanks to many on the back
benches of the Labour Party

3804766978
02:44:10.410 --> 02:44:13.280
and many of us here and my
amendment passed became law.

2708065113
02:44:13.673 --> 02:44:17.623
A spokesman for the government,
when asked about whether they

643819502
02:44:17.624 --> 02:44:21.829
were applying that to
the producers as well, said this he.

4235808562
02:44:21.830 --> 02:44:25.326
I think he or she said, we
have strict procurement

1520515500
02:44:25.327 --> 02:44:28.323
controls in place to ensure
that any solar panels.

3780799076
02:44:28.324 --> 02:44:31.373
It's not just solar panels.

1178886649
02:44:31.374 --> 02:44:35.125
It's all elements to do with net
zero are free from forced labour.

2948444813
02:44:35.126 --> 02:44:42.184
And then they added this
as far as possible.

3938447559
02:44:42.185 --> 02:44:43.239
That is not the law.

2198272837
02:44:44.672 --> 02:44:46.228
There is no caveat to the law.

2712766944
02:44:46.228 --> 02:44:48.536
Everybody rebelled on
that side and we passed

261209329
02:44:48.537 --> 02:44:50.423
it through as well at the same time.

2034908283
02:44:50.424 --> 02:44:52.983
And we implemented
an absolute which it is not for

703883154
02:44:52.984 --> 02:44:58.625
the Great British Energy
Company to use any

327041306
02:44:58.626 --> 02:45:01.032
products that contain any
kind of forced labour

258676116
02:45:01.034 --> 02:45:03.339
procurement or rather
production within them.

4080797805
02:45:03.340 --> 02:45:05.197
And I want to say to the government,

198287547
02:45:05.198 --> 02:45:07.757
I know this is not their
speciality at this point,

2672513055
02:45:07.758 --> 02:45:11.272
but I want to say, well, they will
raise it with the government,

1908407613
02:45:11.273 --> 02:45:15.021
because I then saw that
in the Gracious Speech

3185410940
02:45:15.022 --> 02:45:16.876
there were very peculiar commitments

2798081039
02:45:16.877 --> 02:45:20.128
using immigration as a way
for tackling forced labour,

4224310360
02:45:20.671 --> 02:45:21.975
but it's not good enough.

4032100885
02:45:21.976 --> 02:45:27.222
I want to make the point here
that we need to reinforce

504345420
02:45:27.223 --> 02:45:31.430
the Modern Slavery Act
and make it an offence

1369114103
02:45:31.431 --> 02:45:37.277
for any company to be
importing or using any items

1234102845
02:45:37.278 --> 02:45:42.081
or goods that contain slave forced labour.

862267177
02:45:42.082 --> 02:45:46.921
This should be a unifying factor on
these benches, but I don't know why.

3426719862
02:45:46.922 --> 02:45:49.480
The government has now
watered down what was meant

1722067232
02:45:49.481 --> 02:45:51.588
to be their intention in the first place,

2783295593
02:45:52.671 --> 02:45:54.677
and Deputy Speaker will know full well,

2662641909
02:45:54.678 --> 02:45:56.879
because she has been party to this,

3690396003
02:45:56.880 --> 02:46:00.177
that this is a real cause,
because it comes to the roots

3598376068
02:46:00.178 --> 02:46:02.487
of one of the issues I'm
going to come on to,

3341472839
02:46:02.489 --> 02:46:05.523
which is the threat that we
face from places like China.

1393223286
02:46:05.525 --> 02:46:09.230
If we go on strengthening them by
buying their slave made goods,

1621394848
02:46:09.231 --> 02:46:11.924
then we do our own
defence, no good at all.

4203390957
02:46:11.925 --> 02:46:15.473
And so I would ask the government
to raise this with them,

1638821557
02:46:15.474 --> 02:46:17.380
that what is needed is a wide ranging

1359673090
02:46:17.382 --> 02:46:19.487
commitment through the Modern Slavery Act

2263827876
02:46:20.671 --> 02:46:22.778
to ban all products made by slave labour.

3834204471
02:46:22.779 --> 02:46:29.125
And I want to return to the debate
today, which is on defence.

780507183
02:46:29.126 --> 02:46:30.880
The fact is, Madam Deputy Speaker,

3273989634
02:46:30.882 --> 02:46:34.179
we are now facing the greatest
threat to our freedom

1820955295
02:46:34.672 --> 02:46:38.932
across the Western world that we have
faced, I believe, since the 1930s.

1928864322
02:46:38.933 --> 02:46:41.894
I don't even believe that they
are less than the Cold War.

3518323991
02:46:41.895 --> 02:46:44.629
I believe this is greater
in a way than the Cold War,

2617693164
02:46:44.630 --> 02:46:47.025
because at least during the Cold War,

1228632335
02:46:47.026 --> 02:46:49.584
we already knew and recognised
what war was about,

638175658
02:46:49.585 --> 02:46:53.928
why we had to be prepared for
it, and what we were defending.

1680024700
02:46:53.929 --> 02:46:55.183
We've lost lots of that.

1420794381
02:46:55.184 --> 02:46:59.522
Many people out there
don't fully understand

3708439451
02:46:59.523 --> 02:47:01.478
how that threat has changed and grown.

719289349
02:47:02.672 --> 02:47:08.584
And the reality is that China
today, one shipyard in China,

82878114
02:47:08.585 --> 02:47:13.075
makes more naval ships than
the whole of the United States.

326874271
02:47:13.076 --> 02:47:19.685
In one year, they have over 130
times the capacity to be build

1442024654
02:47:19.686 --> 02:47:24.137
naval ships than Europe
and America are doing at the moment.

746930975
02:47:24.675 --> 02:47:24.975
Yeah.

3702110746
02:47:24.976 --> 02:47:27.083
If people don't think that it's a threat,

799825395
02:47:27.671 --> 02:47:32.422
I always say don't listen
necessarily even to what they say,

3331726009
02:47:32.423 --> 02:47:37.230
go and have a look what these
totalitarian states are doing.

2777096826
02:47:37.231 --> 02:47:41.582
They are producing and preparing for war.

1090490749
02:47:41.583 --> 02:47:46.090
I'm not, I hope, scaremongering,
I believe this to be a reality.

896163665
02:47:46.091 --> 02:47:48.375
China is reinforcing and supporting Russia

1297949558
02:47:48.376 --> 02:47:52.725
in its brutal invasion of Ukraine,

3103172960
02:47:52.726 --> 02:47:55.835
that without China, Russia could
not have continued this war.

419594220
02:47:55.836 --> 02:47:58.028
They were running out of ammunition.

1806352256
02:47:58.029 --> 02:48:02.478
But China brokered an arrangement
with the North Koreans,

643348658
02:48:02.480 --> 02:48:05.439
who now produce millions of
rounds of ammunition for them,

1829262741
02:48:05.440 --> 02:48:07.647
and even soldiers that
they used and abused

3193032650
02:48:07.648 --> 02:48:11.385
on the battlefield who once wounded, etc.

3232887275
02:48:11.386 --> 02:48:13.943
were then assassinated
so they wouldn't be ashamed

2682301029
02:48:13.944 --> 02:48:16.728
when they went back to North Korea.

3601749713
02:48:16.728 --> 02:48:18.483
This is about totalitarian states.

757788865
02:48:18.484 --> 02:48:20.692
And I question and
I say to the government,

1243572095
02:48:21.675 --> 02:48:23.882
do not use the phrase
authoritarian states.

918053770
02:48:23.883 --> 02:48:25.035
They are totalitarian.

2736448418
02:48:25.036 --> 02:48:26.540
There is a difference, right?

4014894244
02:48:26.541 --> 02:48:29.599
Authoritarian states are about
dictators and others that are

4036629460
02:48:29.600 --> 02:48:32.511
risen to power and at some
stage have to be brought down.

3591657789
02:48:32.512 --> 02:48:35.529
Totalitarian states are
where every element of

2378560108
02:48:35.530 --> 02:48:40.685
the way that people live
their lives is controlled,

19717132
02:48:40.686 --> 02:48:44.678
run, spied upon and arrested
by the state organs

2200104820
02:48:44.679 --> 02:48:48.076
regardless of whoever is in charge.

2728120479
02:48:48.077 --> 02:48:51.875
Communism is the key, and these states are

3737473780
02:48:51.876 --> 02:48:53.880
communist and other extremist versions.

3155895389
02:48:53.880 --> 02:48:56.231
After all, Iran is part of this alliance.

4049358467
02:48:56.232 --> 02:48:58.876
They are an extremist organisation.

3081099554
02:48:58.877 --> 02:49:02.428
I still don't understand
why the government

688346062
02:49:02.429 --> 02:49:04.976
has failed to proscribe the Iranian IRGC.

549982172
02:49:04.977 --> 02:49:05.779
It's high time.

2023698682
02:49:05.780 --> 02:49:10.539
It really is high time they're
here, present in our country,

954965570
02:49:10.540 --> 02:49:12.645
stirring up violence, stirring up hatred.

475106065
02:49:12.646 --> 02:49:14.830
We should deal with them and say it's

3394726151
02:49:14.831 --> 02:49:17.478
a criminal act to be here to that extent.

1024125687
02:49:17.478 --> 02:49:20.938
Therefore, how the government responds
in defence terms is critical.

4205124458
02:49:20.939 --> 02:49:23.197
Now, I'm one of those
people that has argued

524628153
02:49:23.198 --> 02:49:24.904
since the ending of the Cold War.

2098876409
02:49:24.905 --> 02:49:27.576
We've made a mistake in reducing defence.

359724547
02:49:27.577 --> 02:49:28.981
Nobody listened to me then,

4046934777
02:49:28.982 --> 02:49:31.892
and there's no reason why they
should listen to me today.

3058805068
02:49:31.893 --> 02:49:35.377
But I have to tell the Ministers
I'm going to keep on saying it,

3788271937
02:49:35.378 --> 02:49:37.435
and I think others around should ask it,

1327542720
02:49:37.436 --> 02:49:40.797
and I hope members on the benches
opposite will ask this question.

1187065379
02:49:40.798 --> 02:49:42.503
I know what the restrictions are.

931841455
02:49:42.504 --> 02:49:44.761
I know that when you're
facing the Treasury,

53840510
02:49:44.762 --> 02:49:46.566
when government faces the Treasury,

2588255543
02:49:46.567 --> 02:49:48.824
they then dictate to
the Department and say,

4056286527
02:49:48.825 --> 02:49:51.780
we can't afford this, we won't do it.

3170703914
02:49:51.781 --> 02:49:54.741
Treasury is the last people in
the world ever to recognise

156928604
02:49:54.742 --> 02:49:58.030
a threat to anybody at
any time, for anything,

2784849924
02:49:58.031 --> 02:50:00.489
and they continue as though
it was all sweetness

96192294
02:50:00.490 --> 02:50:03.249
and light because they don't
want to make any changes.

3365044066
02:50:03.250 --> 02:50:08.384
But it's for the defence Ministers
to make the point about the threat.

2858367685
02:50:08.635 --> 02:50:14.080
Why, in heaven's name, have we not
published the Defence Readiness Bill?

1393675048
02:50:14.081 --> 02:50:14.733
That is the.

3948265803
02:50:14.734 --> 02:50:17.190
That is the Defence
Department's greatest weapon

177598241
02:50:17.191 --> 02:50:19.430
in the fight with the Treasury over this.

3261599713
02:50:19.431 --> 02:50:22.730
Every other department knows
what I'm talking about,

536020372
02:50:22.731 --> 02:50:24.385
whether it's health or whatever.

3093372310
02:50:24.386 --> 02:50:25.439
It's always a fight.

2489066065
02:50:25.440 --> 02:50:28.977
But it has to be because we are
facing what is likely to be

308051705
02:50:28.978 --> 02:50:32.226
the greatest threat that we
have faced since the 1930s.

801645411
02:50:32.227 --> 02:50:35.582
And to do that, they need
to make it clear to them,

2143902300
02:50:35.583 --> 02:50:37.389
we can't go around this any longer.

738685682
02:50:37.389 --> 02:50:39.749
We have to spend that
money we have to commit.

1909738635
02:50:39.750 --> 02:50:41.957
Now, I know the government
has talked about

935301638
02:50:41.958 --> 02:50:43.814
being committed to 3% in due course,

2015631244
02:50:43.815 --> 02:50:45.974
but I say to them that will not be enough.

4266646314
02:50:45.975 --> 02:50:49.125
During my time when I was serving,

3522324123
02:50:49.126 --> 02:50:52.828
we were committed to 5% of GDP
to face down the Soviet Union.

2976036135
02:50:52.829 --> 02:50:55.628
We will need to have to do the same again,

2943985675
02:50:55.629 --> 02:50:58.328
because I believe this is an even greater

2532315559
02:50:58.329 --> 02:51:00.035
threat that we are about to face,

3296119746
02:51:00.675 --> 02:51:03.436
and the Ministers will know
that we will give them all

785265886
02:51:03.437 --> 02:51:05.945
support if they are prepared
to fight about that.

4262345995
02:51:05.946 --> 02:51:09.736
Let's get the Defence Investment
Plan published right away.

2065823019
02:51:09.737 --> 02:51:12.680
It's really important
these totalitarian states

1788073482
02:51:12.681 --> 02:51:14.787
don't face these restrictions that we do,

2090032428
02:51:14.788 --> 02:51:16.895
and we have those restrictions for a good

781857128
02:51:16.896 --> 02:51:18.901
reason because we believe in democracy.

886515956
02:51:18.902 --> 02:51:24.278
But freedom is the most expensive
thing that we will ever try to own,

271301885
02:51:24.279 --> 02:51:28.076
and it can be taken away in just a wish.

534356089
02:51:28.077 --> 02:51:32.582
And our job and their job as
the government is to stand firm,

126943045
02:51:32.583 --> 02:51:36.983
even in government and say the number
one priority of all things that we

88637375
02:51:36.984 --> 02:51:43.832
must do is to defend the realm from
threats, internal and external.

601486842
02:51:43.833 --> 02:51:47.326
And if we don't do that,
we will have failed.

4267724947
02:51:47.327 --> 02:51:49.031
Failed in our obligations, failed

949631812
02:51:50.681 --> 02:51:52.737
the British people and failed our allies

391627446
02:51:52.737 --> 02:51:55.849
and our friends who look to us
for leadership in this matter.

941593715
02:51:55.850 --> 02:51:58.159
But we can only lead
if we have the equipment

3757882719
02:51:58.679 --> 02:52:00.736
to show them that we have the endeavour.

14966022
02:52:00.737 --> 02:52:04.531
When we took the Falkland
Islands, we had 53

3776089532
02:52:04.532 --> 02:52:07.286
frigates and destroyers available to us.

1271005415
02:52:07.287 --> 02:52:08.987
We couldn't do that today.

2817304963
02:52:08.989 --> 02:52:11.398
That is the measure of
how far we've gone under

4053907880
02:52:11.398 --> 02:52:13.252
Labour and Conservative governments.

560533208
02:52:13.253 --> 02:52:15.888
And I simply say to
the government, please now,

789153075
02:52:15.889 --> 02:52:19.286
as the Defence Department
tell them, enough is enough.

364129872
02:52:19.684 --> 02:52:22.193
We are going to publish
this bill and we're going

3282488740
02:52:22.194 --> 02:52:24.199
to publish the Defence Investment Plan.

2837736689
02:52:24.200 --> 02:52:26.586
And by the way, where is the China audit?

3755020134
02:52:26.587 --> 02:52:29.181
Let's publish that too.

3757450624
02:52:29.182 --> 02:52:29.633
>> Yeah.

638652862
02:52:29.634 --> 02:52:30.486
>> Yeah, indeed.

581830108
02:52:30.487 --> 02:52:33.226
>> Wes Streeting.

3178851119
02:52:33.227 --> 02:52:33.628
>> Yes.

4059545873
02:52:33.629 --> 02:52:35.434
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

1647196040
02:52:35.435 --> 02:52:36.237
>> Can I begin.

435480217
02:52:36.239 --> 02:52:37.342
>> By joining others.

392710185
02:52:37.637 --> 02:52:42.580
In expressing my condolences to
the family of Lance Bombardier,

683272156
02:52:42.581 --> 02:52:45.205
Kiera Sullivan and Madam Deputy Speaker.

3999923112
02:52:45.206 --> 02:52:47.817
Can I also begin by saying
what a pleasure it is to

3394664760
02:52:47.818 --> 02:52:50.324
follow my parliamentary
neighbour, the right hon.

3457204582
02:52:50.325 --> 02:52:52.380
Member for Chingford and Woodford Green,

516036730
02:52:52.380 --> 02:52:54.337
despite our best efforts to retire him

1935758340
02:52:54.338 --> 02:52:57.083
at the last general election, the.

3415428170
02:52:57.084 --> 02:52:59.481
The test of any of us in politics is.

3982849232
02:52:59.482 --> 02:53:02.393
Did we leave things in a better
place than we found them?

1360517604
02:53:02.394 --> 02:53:05.284
Thanks to the choices made
by this Labour government,

804002792
02:53:05.285 --> 02:53:08.539
the NHS is on the road to recovery.

2963306733
02:53:08.540 --> 02:53:11.181
Waiting lists fell by 110 000 in March,

1906460645
02:53:11.182 --> 02:53:18.233
the single biggest fall in a single
month outside of the pandemic.

2781361885
02:53:18.234 --> 02:53:18.936
For 17 years.

3824057271
02:53:18.937 --> 02:53:21.243
The ambulance response
times for heart attack

1176378552
02:53:21.244 --> 02:53:23.837
and strokes are now
the fastest in five years.

3708563230
02:53:23.838 --> 02:53:26.043
Patient satisfaction
with access to general

1982473136
02:53:26.044 --> 02:53:30.782
practice has gone from 60% to 75%.

809273658
02:53:30.784 --> 02:53:33.544
And at a time when public
trust in politicians is low,

228216055
02:53:33.545 --> 02:53:37.945
we hit our target of recruiting
8500 more mental health

4140377015
02:53:37.946 --> 02:53:42.544
workers three years early
and on social care.

1104099548
02:53:42.545 --> 02:53:46.787
I'm proud that we're putting
in an extra Â£4 billion

3297332448
02:53:46.788 --> 02:53:48.843
worth of investment that we've delivered

3934650092
02:53:48.844 --> 02:53:53.232
the biggest expansion of Carer's Allowance

951353590
02:53:53.233 --> 02:53:54.989
since the 1970s, that the >> Â£150.

2233774832
02:53:54.990 --> 02:53:55.892
>> Million extra.

1077841073
02:53:55.893 --> 02:53:57.447
>> In the disabled facilities.

20483988
02:53:57.448 --> 02:53:58.852
>> Grant is providing more.

2198164022
02:53:58.853 --> 02:53:59.454
>> Dignity.

2124927357
02:53:59.455 --> 02:54:00.907
>> Freedom and independence.

3887045388
02:54:00.909 --> 02:54:02.012
>> To thousands more.

2921360009
02:54:02.013 --> 02:54:02.864
Disabled people.

1524994707
02:54:02.865 --> 02:54:03.868
And that the first.

2415853535
02:54:03.869 --> 02:54:05.323
>> Ever fair pay agreements.

933020819
02:54:05.324 --> 02:54:06.929
>> Will be delivered in social.

1783032289
02:54:06.930 --> 02:54:07.230
Care.

3205966154
02:54:07.231 --> 02:54:09.592
Because the people who
care for our loved ones

1301535372
02:54:09.593 --> 02:54:14.483
should never struggle to care their own.

3509391663
02:54:14.484 --> 02:54:19.075
All made possible thanks to the efforts

2142481544
02:54:19.076 --> 02:54:21.083
of the entire NHS and social care team.

1559712200
02:54:21.679 --> 02:54:23.587
In the four and a half years I've led

4200106339
02:54:23.588 --> 02:54:25.494
for Labour on health and social care.

1652577002
02:54:25.495 --> 02:54:28.585
I've met the best of them,
the ones who ran towards danger

2488111133
02:54:28.586 --> 02:54:32.434
in Southport and fought
to save those children,

718601705
02:54:32.435 --> 02:54:34.894
the ones who scrubbed up
and went to work during

2687918450
02:54:34.895 --> 02:54:38.746
the pandemic while the rest
of us retreated to safety.

263153588
02:54:38.748 --> 02:54:42.440
The ones who bring new
life into the world,

10088022
02:54:42.441 --> 02:54:44.632
and the ones who hold our hands

44655634
02:54:44.633 --> 02:54:48.385
at the end leading that team has
been the greatest joy of my life,

1292152742
02:54:48.386 --> 02:54:51.636
and the depth of love
and gratitude I have for

2846641029
02:54:51.637 --> 02:54:54.378
the people I've worked
with is beyond words.

681663084
02:54:54.379 --> 02:54:57.284
The brilliant team of
Ministers and officials

3309695875
02:54:57.285 --> 02:55:00.034
at the Department of
Health and Social Care,

167358549
02:55:00.035 --> 02:55:02.883
particularly my private
office and NHS England,

3840961605
02:55:02.884 --> 02:55:06.433
and the best team of special
advisers in government and

3169587339
02:55:06.434 --> 02:55:10.994
the leaders and frontline staff
across this remarkable system.

439183350
02:55:10.995 --> 02:55:14.987
I am rooting for all of
them and for my successor,

4149739013
02:55:15.679 --> 02:55:17.585
who has my wholehearted support as he

15111303
02:55:17.586 --> 02:55:19.882
takes on the best job in government.

2667611789
02:55:19.883 --> 02:55:20.334
>> Yeah.

144219008
02:55:20.335 --> 02:55:23.587
>> I won't pretend that leaving government

2444069909
02:55:23.588 --> 02:55:25.585
hasn't been an emotional wrench.

1034970680
02:55:25.586 --> 02:55:28.597
The scars I bear on my abdomen
from my cancer treatment are

2861118671
02:55:28.598 --> 02:55:32.642
a daily reminder to me of a time
in my life, not so long ago,

3087803170
02:55:32.643 --> 02:55:37.039
when I wasn't thinking about
politics, only survival,

1483193404
02:55:37.040 --> 02:55:40.799
and the NHS was there for
me when I needed it.

1002026480
02:55:41.683 --> 02:55:45.234
Walking through the doors of my
department every day as the person

1756959206
02:55:45.235 --> 02:55:49.088
entrusted with protecting
the very service that saved my life,

2149471360
02:55:49.089 --> 02:55:53.084
has been a massive responsibility
and the most enormous privilege,

2422877712
02:55:53.085 --> 02:55:58.592
and not one I gave up lightly or hastily.

3270754158
02:55:58.593 --> 02:56:00.600
I left the government because we are in

567370906
02:56:00.601 --> 02:56:03.053
the fight of our lives
against nationalism,

3981470728
02:56:03.054 --> 02:56:07.224
and it is a fight that
we are currently losing.

3152873172
02:56:07.225 --> 02:56:08.478
Unless we change course,

1432469877
02:56:08.637 --> 02:56:13.083
we risk handing the keys
of number ten to reform,

3051808327
02:56:13.084 --> 02:56:15.242
and I do not want that on our conferences.

3478384137
02:56:15.683 --> 02:56:16.084
>> Yes.

2331539033
02:56:16.085 --> 02:56:17.992
>> For the first time in our history,

1095636807
02:56:19.684 --> 02:56:23.484
nationalists are in power in every
corner of the United Kingdom.

1162715623
02:56:23.485 --> 02:56:26.985
Scottish and Welsh nationalism
represents an existential

1918618519
02:56:26.986 --> 02:56:32.337
threat to the future integrity
of the United Kingdom,

4231210602
02:56:32.338 --> 02:56:35.339
and reform UK represent
a threat to the values

4091264145
02:56:35.340 --> 02:56:39.896
and ideals that have
made this country great.

179413639
02:56:39.897 --> 02:56:42.535
Values and ideals that are written into

988211800
02:56:42.536 --> 02:56:44.541
the DNA of the National Health Service.

2135553503
02:56:44.543 --> 02:56:45.946
They were dismantled given.

1062515817
02:56:45.947 --> 02:56:48.085
>> The chance.

1291606015
02:56:48.086 --> 02:56:49.239
>> Its very existence.

3241691743
02:56:49.240 --> 02:56:51.782
An act of courage as well as conviction

639135095
02:56:51.784 --> 02:56:54.134
that healthcare should be provided

3141473920
02:56:54.135 --> 02:56:58.788
based on what each of us need,
not what any of us can afford.

1806983992
02:56:58.789 --> 02:57:02.436
A reminder that even in our darkest hours,

3236974251
02:57:02.437 --> 02:57:07.241
this country is capable
of doing big things.

2936801368
02:57:07.242 --> 02:57:09.936
It is our responsibility to defend that

546760923
02:57:09.937 --> 02:57:11.842
promise and the values it represents,

3557528104
02:57:11.843 --> 02:57:17.543
not just for the NHS or even for
the survival of this government,

361229016
02:57:17.544 --> 02:57:21.184
but to win the battles we
thought that were long

2629238754
02:57:21.185 --> 02:57:24.437
since won of progressives
against reactionaries,

905500208
02:57:24.438 --> 02:57:29.235
of patriots versus nationalists,
of hope over hate.

1483678214
02:57:29.236 --> 02:57:30.189
That is our fight.

2282832231
02:57:30.190 --> 02:57:33.236
It's Andy Burnham's fight in Makerfield,

1694303201
02:57:33.237 --> 02:57:37.439
and it is Labour's fight for
the soul of our country.

2583322378
02:57:37.440 --> 02:57:40.594
Yet for too long and for too often,

379006387
02:57:40.594 --> 02:57:43.937
patriotism in Britain has
been left to the loudest

1656778713
02:57:43.938 --> 02:57:46.233
voices and the narrowest arguments,

3868360950
02:57:46.234 --> 02:57:50.234
as though love of country
belongs to one tribe,

136538566
02:57:50.235 --> 02:57:51.891
one party, or one point of view.

1590398042
02:57:51.892 --> 02:57:54.995
But the Britain I believe
in is bigger than that.

3957107857
02:57:56.683 --> 02:57:59.139
Because patriotism is not
about who you exclude,

2192106520
02:57:59.141 --> 02:58:02.237
it is about who you stand beside.

3199654663
02:58:02.239 --> 02:58:07.341
It is not rooted in fear of change
or suspicion of difference.

511680929
02:58:07.342 --> 02:58:12.992
It is rooted in solidarity, in
the belief that we rise or fall together.

1724508604
02:58:12.993 --> 02:58:15.530
That is the best of our country's story.

281070084
02:58:15.531 --> 02:58:18.989
A Britain where people from different
backgrounds, different faiths,

3087686600
02:58:18.990 --> 02:58:25.134
different nations and regions still
see themselves in one another.

2317077504
02:58:25.135 --> 02:58:31.338
A country where the son of Indian
pharmacists can become our first

1510079559
02:58:31.339 --> 02:58:35.839
Hindu Prime Minister without
having his Englishness questioned.

3326573684
02:58:35.840 --> 02:58:40.752
A patriotism built not on blood
and soil, but on shared values,

735178677
02:58:41.684 --> 02:58:44.138
shared institutions
and shared responsibilities.

2000973140
02:58:46.683 --> 02:58:50.786
I understand that the SNP implied
Comrie will not see themselves in

3940205152
02:58:50.787 --> 02:58:54.940
the English nationalist politics of
the party that sits behind them.

639616130
02:58:54.941 --> 02:58:59.038
But nationalism is not
progressive and nationalism

1354921396
02:58:59.039 --> 02:59:03.344
and patriotism are not
the same things nationalism says.

1404052259
02:59:03.688 --> 02:59:05.242
Look inward, protect your own.

892469063
02:59:05.243 --> 02:59:08.244
Turn away from the others.

3445760540
02:59:08.245 --> 02:59:11.438
Patriotism says this
country is strongest when

3742958471
02:59:11.439 --> 02:59:16.137
we are confident enough
to be outward looking,

4021295328
02:59:16.138 --> 02:59:20.535
generous and united, united,
but not always the same.

3603191941
02:59:20.536 --> 02:59:24.588
On these benches we believe
in a stronger Scotland

3482712942
02:59:24.589 --> 02:59:28.839
and a stronger Wales as part
of a fairer United Kingdom.

3443737815
02:59:28.840 --> 02:59:32.789
And 28 years ago this week,
the people of Northern Ireland took

3379163730
02:59:32.790 --> 02:59:39.194
a leap of faith and voted to
endorse the Good Friday Agreement.

1467893923
02:59:39.195 --> 02:59:42.456
The triumph of hope over bitter
enmity, a reminder that a bigger

2697771824
02:59:42.457 --> 02:59:46.437
and better politics is possible
when people have courage.

2179677279
02:59:46.438 --> 02:59:50.195
That is why we must reject
the politics that tries to divide us,

3687594164
02:59:50.683 --> 02:59:54.438
whether it's dividing
the countries of the United Kingdom

3486180308
02:59:54.439 --> 02:59:58.019
or the people who call Britain their home.

1113723309
02:59:58.020 --> 03:00:00.027
The nurse from Nigeria is not the enemy

1380557327
03:00:00.028 --> 03:00:03.298
of the factory worker in Newcastle.

2272234381
03:00:03.299 --> 03:00:08.045
The family fleeing war is not responsible
for the cost of living crisis.

733644444
03:00:08.046 --> 03:00:10.102
Division is the oldest trick in politics

3946166607
03:00:11.687 --> 03:00:13.642
and Britain deserves better than that.

2600295109
03:00:13.643 --> 03:00:14.094
>> Here.

16227106
03:00:14.094 --> 03:00:16.603
>> Because the future of
this country will not be

1070799038
03:00:16.688 --> 03:00:18.993
built by setting neighbour
against neighbour,

507000769
03:00:18.994 --> 03:00:24.340
it will be built by renewing
the bonds between us decent jobs,

1807780624
03:00:24.341 --> 03:00:28.645
strong public services, safe
communities, a place we can call home,

3984483115
03:00:28.646 --> 03:00:31.844
and a sense that everyone has
a stake in Britain's success.

1924421364
03:00:31.844 --> 03:00:35.343
That is the patriotism we need today,

2105899233
03:00:35.344 --> 03:00:39.153
not a brittle nationalism built
on grievance, but a confidence.

2151970697
03:00:41.689 --> 03:00:46.587
British patriotism, decent,
fair minded, internationalist,

734619348
03:00:46.588 --> 03:00:49.596
bound together in common endeavour
with the conviction that

2617469816
03:00:49.597 --> 03:00:52.942
our greatest strength has
always been one another.

2427758068
03:00:52.943 --> 03:00:57.643
We need to mobilise that spirit
as we face the gathering storm.

2618502735
03:00:57.644 --> 03:00:59.992
The war in Iraq may be over for now,

3903551467
03:00:59.993 --> 03:01:02.541
but this fragile peace has not resolved

1873789087
03:01:02.543 --> 03:01:05.087
the crisis in the Strait of Hormuz.

2655364934
03:01:05.088 --> 03:01:06.843
Even if it were resolved tomorrow,

3113309495
03:01:06.844 --> 03:01:09.700
the long tail consequences
for the global economy

1852945365
03:01:09.701 --> 03:01:12.191
and the British people will be stark.

3645388854
03:01:12.192 --> 03:01:15.589
And the tragedy for this
government is that my right hon.

1920637682
03:01:15.590 --> 03:01:18.240
Friend the Chancellor has been delivering

3507998659
03:01:18.241 --> 03:01:21.636
the fastest growing economy in the G7.

3814911387
03:01:21.637 --> 03:01:25.484
Falling inflation
and lower interest rates.

1790491624
03:01:25.485 --> 03:01:28.342
Her hard work undermined
by the consequences

663556870
03:01:28.343 --> 03:01:29.749
of a war we did not choose.

3291168328
03:01:29.750 --> 03:01:35.040
And I paid tribute to the Prime
Minister for keeping us out of it.

3799107163
03:01:35.041 --> 03:01:37.148
It will be painful for the British people

4029380274
03:01:39.646 --> 03:01:41.651
who have weathered crisis after crisis.

2690106689
03:01:41.652 --> 03:01:49.387
Some imposed on us, like the wars in
Iran and Ukraine and the pandemic.

3816929258
03:01:49.388 --> 03:01:52.346
Others like austerity, Brexit
and Liz Truss's joyride with

265042132
03:01:52.347 --> 03:01:57.537
the British economy the result
of poor political leadership.

3918937434
03:01:57.538 --> 03:02:00.244
When I gave my maiden speech 11 years ago,

3966079769
03:02:00.245 --> 03:02:02.743
I argued that none of the problems

3348283212
03:02:02.744 --> 03:02:07.593
facing our country would be solved
by leaving the European Union.

198859507
03:02:07.594 --> 03:02:11.203
Today, in the dangerous and volatile
world we find ourselves in,

3767322771
03:02:11.688 --> 03:02:16.937
dominated by an unpredictable
superpower in the USA,

2705925250
03:02:16.938 --> 03:02:20.789
a rising superpower in China
and a failed superpower in Russia.

3052890427
03:02:20.790 --> 03:02:23.987
It is even more clear that
we would have been better

3287899566
03:02:23.987 --> 03:02:28.349
off leading Europe than
leaving the European Union.

1633950775
03:02:28.350 --> 03:02:33.144
Not despite our sovereignty
and the need to control our borders,

4020947834
03:02:33.145 --> 03:02:34.889
but to enable those things.

3371147494
03:02:34.891 --> 03:02:39.048
This is why I argue for
a new special relationship.

1724202752
03:02:39.049 --> 03:02:41.839
It is also why I welcome the insurance,

3264768676
03:02:41.840 --> 03:02:46.586
the assurances that the government
is strengthening sanctions

2158203199
03:02:46.587 --> 03:02:49.341
on Russia to underline
our rock solid support

319067748
03:02:49.342 --> 03:02:51.646
that we have given President Zelensky

2679661947
03:02:51.647 --> 03:02:54.795
and the Ukrainian people
the front line in Ukraine

1534505089
03:02:54.796 --> 03:02:57.840
is the front line for our
freedom and democracy,

2002820320
03:02:57.841 --> 03:03:03.796
and we are meant to be the party of
internationalism and solidarity.

2922097835
03:03:03.797 --> 03:03:06.295
It is only too disappointing to see reform

1668349637
03:03:06.296 --> 03:03:08.401
councillors taking down the Ukraine flag.

1343290784
03:03:08.402 --> 03:03:13.397
When the British people
want to fly in solidarity.

28301094
03:03:13.398 --> 03:03:14.201
>> It is truly.

904338886
03:03:14.692 --> 03:03:15.644
>> Truly shameful.

2981265963
03:03:15.645 --> 03:03:16.197
>> No, no.

2861442073
03:03:16.198 --> 03:03:20.191
>> And of course, Madam Deputy Speaker.

2292717928
03:03:20.192 --> 03:03:24.494
NATO's Secretary General is
right to warn today that

3192663470
03:03:24.495 --> 03:03:28.448
our alliance has an unhealthy
reliance on one ally.

2513240186
03:03:28.449 --> 03:03:32.999
We need to invest more heavily
in our defence and more rapidly.

1600383601
03:03:33.000 --> 03:03:34.639
I know my right hon.

2449241447
03:03:34.641 --> 03:03:37.049
Friend the Defence Secretary and his

2511195422
03:03:37.050 --> 03:03:38.906
team do not need persuading on this,

985326170
03:03:39.687 --> 03:03:45.841
nor do they need lectures from
the Conservative Party who ran down our

2539448904
03:03:45.842 --> 03:03:49.202
capability and now have the audacity
to heckle from the sidelines,

1490870309
03:03:49.203 --> 03:03:51.445
like the arsonist
complaining that the fire

3462341113
03:03:51.446 --> 03:03:53.351
brigade hasn't turned up fast enough?

883663713
03:03:53.352 --> 03:03:57.393
I'm with the Secretary of State and his

962683550
03:03:57.394 --> 03:03:59.991
team all the way, but we also, he says,

2748350705
03:03:59.992 --> 03:04:03.543
the Shadow Secretary of State
says bankrupting the the country.

1572951936
03:04:03.544 --> 03:04:05.651
I think he's thinking about Liz Truss and

12785899
03:04:05.652 --> 03:04:09.296
the joyride that no doubt
he was cheering on.

3667546502
03:04:09.297 --> 03:04:12.309
I think I think a period of
silence, or at least an apology

424788612
03:04:12.310 --> 03:04:14.994
might be welcome from
the conservative front bench.

1751645195
03:04:14.995 --> 03:04:17.694
But we also need to recognise
that a nation draws

681037298
03:04:17.695 --> 03:04:22.062
its strength from
the condition of its people.

1548241818
03:04:22.063 --> 03:04:25.677
A recent survey of 16 to 29 year olds
suggested that around half of all

643386435
03:04:26.691 --> 03:04:31.395
young people in this country wouldn't
be prepared to fight for it.

3770310288
03:04:31.396 --> 03:04:32.800
I'm not so sure about that.

2229584892
03:04:32.802 --> 03:04:37.951
I think they would be every bit as
brave and self-sacrificing as their

2542894384
03:04:37.952 --> 03:04:41.460
grandparents and great grandparents
were, or as their contemporaries.

763833174
03:04:41.461 --> 03:04:44.446
Holding back the Russians
in Ukraine have been.

731054957
03:04:44.447 --> 03:04:48.602
When the cause is just
and the need is urgent,

3233788192
03:04:48.603 --> 03:04:51.045
they will step up regardless of what they

2253757934
03:04:51.046 --> 03:04:54.648
might have told opinion pollsters.

1845907193
03:04:54.650 --> 03:04:58.092
I know this because when this country

482068060
03:04:58.093 --> 03:04:59.949
was facing a dire threat from Covid,

1568691419
03:04:59.950 --> 03:05:02.696
young people did step up.

2055878831
03:05:02.697 --> 03:05:04.251
The generation, least at risk,

1251977545
03:05:05.691 --> 03:05:11.204
gave up the most to help
the rest of us keep safe here.

2997515976
03:05:11.205 --> 03:05:12.810
And how did Britain repay them,

356463108
03:05:13.691 --> 03:05:16.548
shortchanging them on their
education, layering on debt,

3626528358
03:05:16.691 --> 03:05:19.049
making it harder to get
on the housing ladder,

13159447
03:05:19.691 --> 03:05:21.798
failing to protect them from the AI jobs.

915723459
03:05:21.799 --> 03:05:22.398
Apocalypse.

1695552059
03:05:23.691 --> 03:05:27.242
This generation is the first
left totally exposed to

1170232765
03:05:27.243 --> 03:05:30.388
the time sucking algorithms
and perils of social media.

3378294633
03:05:30.389 --> 03:05:35.000
The Education Secretary and
I have raised our concerns about

2284194190
03:05:35.001 --> 03:05:37.910
the impact of this on their
learning and their wellbeing,

2400062984
03:05:37.911 --> 03:05:40.608
but I also wonder what it
is doing to their sense

2320648591
03:05:40.609 --> 03:05:44.094
of connection with community and country.

2011960916
03:05:44.096 --> 03:05:49.698
But patriotism isn't a lecture
the old deliver to the young.

1100932487
03:05:49.699 --> 03:05:50.751
It's a relationship.

1065488897
03:05:50.752 --> 03:05:52.755
And for generations, Britain understood

857741829
03:05:53.696 --> 03:05:55.701
that relationship as a social contract.

1870246386
03:05:55.702 --> 03:06:00.442
You work hard, you play by the rules,
you contribute to society and in

399087777
03:06:00.443 --> 03:06:05.603
return you can build a decent life,
a secure job, home of your own,

2595752489
03:06:05.605 --> 03:06:10.941
a family if you want one, and
the hope and conviction that your

1638009552
03:06:10.942 --> 03:06:14.492
children will do better than
you did a generation ago.

2837093270
03:06:14.493 --> 03:06:18.893
The average home cost around
four times average earnings.

2464564105
03:06:18.894 --> 03:06:20.198
In many parts of Britain.

1599157372
03:06:22.691 --> 03:06:25.099
Today it is eight, ten,
even 12 times earnings.

2941858503
03:06:25.691 --> 03:06:28.698
Private rents consume vast
proportions of household income.

3448553525
03:06:28.699 --> 03:06:31.043
Millions of young people
who work hard and do

4092344539
03:06:31.044 --> 03:06:36.205
the right thing cannot
see a path to Today,

822498034
03:06:36.853 --> 03:06:40.310
nearly a million young people are
not home ownership or security.

3570336695
03:06:40.311 --> 03:06:43.270
Today, nearly a million young
people are not in education,

1759136953
03:06:43.271 --> 03:06:44.473
employment or training.

166630009
03:06:44.474 --> 03:06:47.347
Many are trapped in insecure
work, unable to move out,

2875026121
03:06:47.348 --> 03:06:51.147
delaying starting their families,
postponing adulthood itself.

2678529143
03:06:51.148 --> 03:06:54.142
And layered on top of this,

3292752495
03:06:54.143 --> 03:06:57.838
economic insecurity is
a new technological anxiety.

1047591022
03:06:57.839 --> 03:06:59.994
For generations, people believed there was

604292751
03:06:59.995 --> 03:07:02.252
a ladder of advancement,
an entry level job,

116352202
03:07:03.692 --> 03:07:07.152
skills acquired over time,
promotion, security, progress.

2095063767
03:07:07.153 --> 03:07:10.896
Now, many young people fear
that artificial intelligence

3552047780
03:07:10.897 --> 03:07:14.647
may remove the lower rungs
of that ladder altogether.

4205313079
03:07:14.648 --> 03:07:17.639
They ask, what skills will still matter?

1304970771
03:07:17.639 --> 03:07:20.094
Will there still be routes into stable,

2097752279
03:07:20.096 --> 03:07:24.999
middle class lives for kids from
working class families like mine?

3809291217
03:07:25.000 --> 03:07:28.548
Will deindustrialisation be
replaced with reindustrialisation

877871568
03:07:28.549 --> 03:07:31.698
and the jobs of the future?

1143142994
03:07:31.699 --> 03:07:36.603
Will opportunities extend to our
towns, rural and coastal communities,

1744007692
03:07:36.605 --> 03:07:39.155
or will inequality become entrenched?

1989313963
03:07:39.156 --> 03:07:43.597
These are not irrational fears.

1170878810
03:07:43.598 --> 03:07:46.094
They are rooted in real economic change.

3608756816
03:07:46.096 --> 03:07:50.098
And unless mainstream democratic
politics can answer these questions,

1590245657
03:07:50.099 --> 03:07:53.347
others will exploit that vacuum.

2439040271
03:07:53.348 --> 03:07:54.250
They already are.

2961637426
03:07:54.251 --> 03:07:54.652
>> Yes.

3380842502
03:07:54.653 --> 03:07:58.001
>> Defence is about hard
power and capabilities,

2009926974
03:07:58.002 --> 03:08:01.502
but it is underpinned by the soft power

1566011856
03:08:01.503 --> 03:08:03.901
that binds the country together pride,

1723075696
03:08:03.902 --> 03:08:08.356
belonging, shared activities
and institutions hope.

857988404
03:08:08.357 --> 03:08:11.848
We need to rebuild them for modern times.

4028890471
03:08:11.849 --> 03:08:14.597
This is the calling of the Labour Party,

2292613111
03:08:14.598 --> 03:08:17.397
brought into existence to
champion the interests

4137895115
03:08:17.398 --> 03:08:18.903
of the working man and woman,

1856225847
03:08:18.904 --> 03:08:21.450
the many, not just the privileged few.

3565099279
03:08:21.451 --> 03:08:25.153
It gave this kid from a council
estate in Stepney in east London,

1726740113
03:08:25.696 --> 03:08:28.995
the chance to realise my
potential to go to a great

1351371901
03:08:28.996 --> 03:08:31.753
university and spend my career
tackling the injustices

2034346269
03:08:31.754 --> 03:08:35.499
that hold other kids from
backgrounds like mine back.

3384512253
03:08:35.500 --> 03:08:39.409
The greatest tragedy of Britain
today is that the next generation,

3736796404
03:08:39.410 --> 03:08:41.848
for the first time in our modern history,

3527450562
03:08:41.849 --> 03:08:45.447
face worse prospects than the last.

3670204783
03:08:45.448 --> 03:08:48.043
So the question isn't whether young people

1501049327
03:08:48.044 --> 03:08:49.598
would fight for their country,

294576730
03:08:49.599 --> 03:08:54.802
but when their country is
going to fight for them.

2141659615
03:08:54.803 --> 03:08:57.901
This is our generational
challenge to not only deal

2048605137
03:08:57.902 --> 03:09:00.448
with the immediate
issues of affordability,

3543010716
03:09:00.449 --> 03:09:03.850
small boats and NHS waiting lists,

709287343
03:09:03.851 --> 03:09:08.053
but also to face up to a turbulent
world being remade by climate change

3765829267
03:09:08.054 --> 03:09:10.959
and the biggest and fastest
industrial revolution

28687902
03:09:10.960 --> 03:09:12.415
in the history of the world.

4256685557
03:09:12.416 --> 03:09:16.904
To make sure that no one is left
behind and no one is held back.

854718322
03:09:16.905 --> 03:09:22.091
That's our job now, as the old
economy of the 20th century

3469471717
03:09:22.092 --> 03:09:25.991
finally gives way to
the AI revolution of the 21st,

737753830
03:09:25.992 --> 03:09:31.099
and to tackle the crisis facing
the next generation as an emergency,

1383122724
03:09:31.100 --> 03:09:34.746
with the urgency that the moment requires.

1815949402
03:09:34.748 --> 03:09:35.851
Never waste a minute.

1281244440
03:09:36.654 --> 03:09:40.099
That's been my mantra in government,
and it's why I don't believe

1041433220
03:09:40.100 --> 03:09:44.048
our party has time to waste
in government treading water.

4077914649
03:09:44.049 --> 03:09:46.699
Because the thing about
emergencies is that

1786460125
03:09:46.700 --> 03:09:48.454
they make the impossible possible.

4099619081
03:09:48.695 --> 03:09:50.800
Look back at the crises we've confronted.

1812378198
03:09:50.802 --> 03:09:55.044
We couldn't vaccinate against
the deadly virus until we could.

4166063524
03:09:55.045 --> 03:09:58.849
We couldn't nationalise
the banking system until we could.

2113667208
03:09:58.850 --> 03:10:02.002
We couldn't reorient our
entire manufacturing base

1889442168
03:10:02.003 --> 03:10:04.494
towards building aircraft until we could.

1218938012
03:10:04.495 --> 03:10:07.152
We couldn't build hundreds of thousands

3816043842
03:10:07.153 --> 03:10:09.160
of homes fit for heroes until we could.

1547309101
03:10:10.696 --> 03:10:12.100
In times of greatest peril,

3793833384
03:10:12.101 --> 03:10:17.547
our country has been capable
of doing big things.

3147861221
03:10:17.548 --> 03:10:18.250
We still can.

2146281371
03:10:18.251 --> 03:10:20.910
Britain used to punch above
its weight in the world.

453397981
03:10:21.696 --> 03:10:22.398
We still can.

199341838
03:10:22.398 --> 03:10:27.208
Each generation used to provide
a better future for the next.

4201373598
03:10:27.209 --> 03:10:27.911
We still can.

2786881217
03:10:28.696 --> 03:10:33.249
Another member of the cancer
club, the late, great Bowelbabe.

2736668114
03:10:33.250 --> 03:10:37.657
Dame Deborah James, famously
said, take risks, love deeply.

2258776190
03:10:37.657 --> 03:10:42.153
Have no regrets and always,
always have rebellious hope.

3514756677
03:10:42.154 --> 03:10:45.945
It is with that in mind
and with the belief

3534573107
03:10:45.946 --> 03:10:47.552
that we can and must do better.

879481790
03:10:47.553 --> 03:10:51.253
With deep love for my
party and my country.

727577602
03:10:51.254 --> 03:10:53.310
With no regrets and with rebellious hope

2889160170
03:10:53.692 --> 03:10:55.347
that I have left the government,

3518265539
03:10:55.348 --> 03:10:59.800
the Labour Party was elected
to deliver real change.

4092057014
03:10:59.802 --> 03:11:03.945
We still can.

1969365111
03:11:03.946 --> 03:11:05.500
>> And Doctor Andrew Murrison,

1064124881
03:11:05.501 --> 03:11:09.415
after which we will go to
a speaking limit of seven minutes.

2145068089
03:11:09.699 --> 03:11:10.901
Doctor Andrew Murrison.

248382801
03:11:10.902 --> 03:11:11.353
>> Here.

1183785508
03:11:11.353 --> 03:11:16.603
And can I genuinely
congratulate the right hon.

1520397738
03:11:16.605 --> 03:11:19.246
Gentleman for a remarkable speech and wish

3449787638
03:11:19.248 --> 03:11:23.556
him well in his future ambitions?

388221275
03:11:23.557 --> 03:11:27.602
But his speech and its
content were, I'm afraid,

2874471536
03:11:27.603 --> 03:11:29.961
not as germane as
the contribution of the hon.

3256435980
03:11:29.962 --> 03:11:32.600
Gentleman who chairs
the Defence Select Committee.

540995340
03:11:32.601 --> 03:11:36.907
I agree with everything he had to say.

3003638014
03:11:36.909 --> 03:11:44.455
I only regret I couldn't put it as
elegantly as he did the right hon.

2123127910
03:11:44.456 --> 03:11:47.153
Gentleman, the Member for
Ilford North resignation

413086386
03:11:47.154 --> 03:11:51.052
letter on Thursday is worth reading,

2208651676
03:11:51.053 --> 03:11:53.411
and I'm very sure that
members of the Treasury

1249590679
03:11:53.412 --> 03:11:56.147
benches will have read it closely.

123459130
03:11:56.148 --> 03:11:58.005
He talked of where we need a vision.

1756897724
03:11:58.005 --> 03:12:03.413
We have a vacuum where we need
direction, we have drift,

3743979711
03:12:04.699 --> 03:12:06.603
and that should worry the government.

3467927789
03:12:06.605 --> 03:12:11.066
And I agree with him,
and I'm particularly mindful of

3956798006
03:12:11.067 --> 03:12:14.107
the Defence Investment plan,
which we haven't seen.

1562926495
03:12:14.699 --> 03:12:17.306
And I'm very conscious that
Defence Readiness Bill,

149754636
03:12:18.703 --> 03:12:24.898
which we were expecting in this King's
speech, has yet to materialise.

926036822
03:12:24.898 --> 03:12:30.257
That's of deep and profound
concern in the 1930s,

195503230
03:12:30.258 --> 03:12:33.703
where arguably we faced
a similar situation

767761899
03:12:33.704 --> 03:12:35.949
to that which we are up against now,

2177431110
03:12:35.950 --> 03:12:39.360
the government of the day
decided about five years in

1893755109
03:12:39.361 --> 03:12:42.250
advance of the outbreak
of the Second World War,

3672565262
03:12:42.251 --> 03:12:50.605
that it must gear up our defence
industrial base to tackle the future.

1831836372
03:12:50.606 --> 03:12:53.606
And it created things
like shadow factories,

2087037946
03:12:53.607 --> 03:12:58.148
initially with the opposition of
industry and centred very largely,

2003500063
03:12:58.150 --> 03:13:00.205
at least initially around the automotive

2289734567
03:13:01.699 --> 03:13:03.754
industry and the production of aircraft,

201208358
03:13:03.755 --> 03:13:05.903
but extending much further than that.

1248087770
03:13:05.904 --> 03:13:11.066
And it was truly a cooperative
venture that led eventually to this

1497714341
03:13:11.699 --> 03:13:17.209
country being able to turn out
in those early years, to do.

1656704289
03:13:17.705 --> 03:13:19.862
more aircraft than Germany was able to do.

3174045500
03:13:19.862 --> 03:13:23.261
And I would have thought that
this government would have

4093700954
03:13:23.262 --> 03:13:28.600
learnt those lessons and would
now be bringing forward,

3957269048
03:13:28.601 --> 03:13:31.897
as a matter of urgency, its
own defence readiness Bill.

940167660
03:13:31.898 --> 03:13:36.305
It has missed an opportunity
and I am very sorry about that,

2089680396
03:13:36.306 --> 03:13:41.199
because there is no question of a doubt
that industry is being held back

3342792835
03:13:41.200 --> 03:13:47.259
as as has has already been mentioned
this afternoon in its ambition

763627660
03:13:47.260 --> 03:13:55.049
to partner with the Ministry of
Defence with Ministers and get things

2182934198
03:13:55.050 --> 03:13:59.555
going in terms of reprovisioning
what we have sent to Ukraine,

1259585700
03:13:59.556 --> 03:14:02.565
quite rightly, and fitting our
armed forces for the future.

3271312363
03:14:02.566 --> 03:14:04.972
Now, some have already
mentioned hollowing out.

3114761887
03:14:04.973 --> 03:14:10.259
I think it's worthwhile
saying that in 1989,

4094204519
03:14:10.260 --> 03:14:13.469
every country in the Western world
was taking a peace dividend.

1412554632
03:14:13.471 --> 03:14:16.609
It would have been
extraordinary had they not,

602534420
03:14:16.610 --> 03:14:20.709
and they would have been
punished by the voters.

3699583710
03:14:20.710 --> 03:14:25.904
But that was then the big
lesson I learned from what

2615118956
03:14:25.905 --> 03:14:30.010
has happened in the years
since 1989 is actually,

366053642
03:14:30.011 --> 03:14:32.655
you can afford to titrate what you provide

4080409218
03:14:32.656 --> 03:14:35.910
in order to defend this country,

1354641412
03:14:35.911 --> 03:14:42.111
which is never popular electorally
with the threat that is facing you.

2689624035
03:14:42.112 --> 03:14:45.760
But you must do nothing
to reduce your armed

2393951421
03:14:45.761 --> 03:14:48.206
forces below an irreducible minimum,

544339656
03:14:48.207 --> 03:14:54.108
so that you can regrow at pace rapidly,

3682026578
03:14:54.109 --> 03:14:59.060
as happened before in the years
immediately preceding 1914 and 1939.

2537153590
03:14:59.704 --> 03:15:03.454
And you must do nothing that
will damage long term projects,

1015030979
03:15:03.455 --> 03:15:07.310
because procurement isn't something
you can turn on and off like a tap.

228085383
03:15:07.311 --> 03:15:11.411
Procurement takes decades.

178469372
03:15:11.412 --> 03:15:15.313
I think we've learnt that mistake,
and one of the mistakes I think

480013766
03:15:15.314 --> 03:15:21.309
the previous government made was
delaying the dreadnought class.

279890293
03:15:22.703 --> 03:15:23.957
And the reason for that,

2089202266
03:15:23.958 --> 03:15:26.567
as I referred to in
the intervention, that the hon.

2388979690
03:15:26.568 --> 03:15:29.257
Gentleman very generously
allowed me to make,

3428490409
03:15:29.258 --> 03:15:32.901
was the coalition government and pressure

1045390841
03:15:32.902 --> 03:15:34.556
from our then coalition partner.

161686192
03:15:34.703 --> 03:15:40.656
Now, right now we're facing our
principal ally, the United States,

4222770660
03:15:40.657 --> 03:15:44.306
backing off in terms of its support for

3167432355
03:15:44.307 --> 03:15:46.061
ourselves and our European allies.

3527062748
03:15:46.062 --> 03:15:49.810
We can no longer entirely
rely on that which

4133392116
03:15:49.811 --> 03:15:55.306
we had previously heavily relied upon.

1657805311
03:15:55.307 --> 03:16:03.609
We will be the only provider
of a nuclear deterrent.

3613048826
03:16:03.610 --> 03:16:07.308
If it's as it seems likely the US proceeds

259831610
03:16:07.309 --> 03:16:09.164
on this particular course of action,

2632335612
03:16:09.165 --> 03:16:12.507
and that is to say, a nuclear
deterrent declared to NATO.

2693262163
03:16:12.508 --> 03:16:17.511
It is therefore important that
in the Defence Readiness Bill,

2633104717
03:16:17.512 --> 03:16:20.255
when we see it,

1048887473
03:16:20.256 --> 03:16:27.006
we have a reaffirmed commitment
to reprovisioning cas de.

1232388837
03:16:27.007 --> 03:16:27.458
At pace.

1062578090
03:16:27.459 --> 03:16:30.012
Now, much work has been done in terms of

2656253157
03:16:30.013 --> 03:16:34.956
infrastructure and at a facing w e,

3571856253
03:16:34.957 --> 03:16:39.250
but we are still facing
a rundown Vanguard class that

3430122824
03:16:39.251 --> 03:16:44.756
is obliged to go on patrol
for upwards of 200 days,

1011788029
03:16:44.757 --> 03:16:48.109
with consequent impact on the men and now

98766521
03:16:48.110 --> 03:16:50.116
women who man up the submarine service.

659188410
03:16:50.117 --> 03:16:54.099
And of all the pinch point
trades in our armed forces,

1347059127
03:16:54.100 --> 03:16:58.105
it is those that exist
within the submarine service

2582296446
03:16:58.106 --> 03:17:00.113
that should keep us all awake at night.

2262195492
03:17:01.704 --> 03:17:04.311
It is imperative that we
accelerate that programme.

4030243350
03:17:06.662 --> 03:17:08.770
And I would also ask Ministers to look at

2244369611
03:17:08.771 --> 03:17:14.559
the F 35 alpha provision and agree with me

2462695759
03:17:14.560 --> 03:17:18.960
that providing 12 airframes
is hardly sufficient,

1297639735
03:17:18.961 --> 03:17:21.953
given the threat that we now face.

1972461886
03:17:21.954 --> 03:17:22.757
I need to know.

2354776109
03:17:22.758 --> 03:17:24.161
I'd like to know.

1726034687
03:17:24.162 --> 03:17:26.370
I'm sure the whole House
would like to know

4233838598
03:17:27.707 --> 03:17:29.814
when the F 35 alphas will be operational,

3068291107
03:17:30.707 --> 03:17:32.912
as opposed to providing
training airframes.

1367425805
03:17:32.913 --> 03:17:37.214
Is it the intention of the government
to expedite that programme?

3336853019
03:17:37.215 --> 03:17:40.911
Is it the intention of the government
to exploit the option that

2955161855
03:17:40.912 --> 03:17:44.613
it has kept open to have more
than 12 of those airframes?

1958115919
03:17:44.614 --> 03:17:50.364
And will Ministers confirm that
they will be nuclear enabled?

2027788050
03:17:54.861 --> 03:17:58.807
Speaker, I would Madam Deputy Speaker,

3255032804
03:17:58.808 --> 03:18:02.459
I would strongly urge that Ministers

3845538490
03:18:02.460 --> 03:18:05.953
look at the Sovereign Defence Fund Bill

1689242296
03:18:05.954 --> 03:18:07.658
in the alternative King's Speech.

3135312422
03:18:07.659 --> 03:18:10.568
It would repurpose
the National Wealth Fund to

3014575638
03:18:10.569 --> 03:18:13.461
overhaul our vital
defence industrial base.

396188302
03:18:13.462 --> 03:18:16.711
Yeah, now, governing is
about difficult decisions,

1470317090
03:18:16.712 --> 03:18:20.514
and it seems to me that
defence is a more urgent

307740718
03:18:20.515 --> 03:18:23.112
priority right now than using the fund to,

4061110678
03:18:23.113 --> 03:18:28.711
in the words of government,
help tackle climate change,

2266065710
03:18:28.712 --> 03:18:30.558
a more urgent priority indeed,

1730297938
03:18:30.559 --> 03:18:35.512
than ramping up welfare, as Lord
Robertson has made very clear.

3019979824
03:18:35.513 --> 03:18:38.621
Now, the defence industrial
base is going to be

1241083067
03:18:38.622 --> 03:18:42.160
pretty useless if it's
not populated by men

1566779704
03:18:42.161 --> 03:18:47.361
and women with the skills
necessary to deliver what

487578503
03:18:47.362 --> 03:18:50.363
is needed in order to
keep this country safe.

502352383
03:18:50.364 --> 03:18:53.962
The Youth Opportunities Bill
in the alternative King's

3205366137
03:18:53.963 --> 03:18:56.370
Speech has the kind of
imaginative content that

1803765993
03:18:56.371 --> 03:18:59.562
I would have expected from
an incoming government

3341435501
03:18:59.563 --> 03:19:02.463
that had 14 years to think
about these things,

2104070723
03:19:02.464 --> 03:19:06.366
but unfortunately not all we
had from the Prime Minister

636038538
03:19:06.367 --> 03:19:09.771
on young people on Wednesday
was a load of waffle.

2532964101
03:19:09.772 --> 03:19:13.016
Time and again, it's as
if he's a passive observer

4047638488
03:19:14.707 --> 03:19:16.461
rather than an active participant.

2651788844
03:19:16.462 --> 03:19:20.263
The Youth Opportunities Bill
sets out how genuine investment

4037633037
03:19:20.264 --> 03:19:25.215
in our young people will
power and grow the economy,

752296206
03:19:26.704 --> 03:19:29.661
delivering a virtuous circle
from which everyone benefits.

3216369389
03:19:29.662 --> 03:19:33.109
It will cap state funding for
pointless work, irrelevant,

1910459223
03:19:33.110 --> 03:19:35.616
badly taught degrees from
third rate institutions

3497002529
03:19:35.617 --> 03:19:39.861
that are perpetrating
a fraud on a generation.

1378484074
03:19:39.862 --> 03:19:43.059
It will grow well focussed
apprenticeships like those

4246474401
03:19:43.060 --> 03:19:49.112
offered by Wiltshire College
in my constituency.

1900095806
03:19:49.113 --> 03:19:50.466
Now, Madam Deputy Speaker,

564199524
03:19:52.708 --> 03:19:57.559
I would just want to say a few
words in conclusion about

4235255262
03:19:57.560 --> 03:20:02.007
Special forces and we
have to approach these

2967325653
03:20:02.008 --> 03:20:03.714
issues with a great deal of care.

2525782010
03:20:03.715 --> 03:20:09.166
I am extremely concerned by
the messaging that has gone out from this

3221581468
03:20:09.167 --> 03:20:15.310
government in relation to
the Northern Ireland Troubles Bill.

1331022348
03:20:15.311 --> 03:20:17.961
It isn't so much the case
that has been put before

1978738677
03:20:17.962 --> 03:20:20.068
the House by the Northern Ireland Office,

2016537131
03:20:20.069 --> 03:20:22.158
Secretary of State for Northern Ireland,

352405164
03:20:22.159 --> 03:20:24.167
but it is the way it has been received.

422276658
03:20:24.711 --> 03:20:25.162
The hon.

2761225859
03:20:25.163 --> 03:20:27.319
Gentleman sitting next to the Secretary of

1980033717
03:20:27.320 --> 03:20:29.325
State for defence will know absolutely,

3744208331
03:20:29.326 --> 03:20:31.933
because his contacts are
probably better than mine,

3025394945
03:20:31.934 --> 03:20:34.091
that this has caused a degree of disquiet,

1784968389
03:20:35.712 --> 03:20:38.368
particularly among units
that are absolutely crucial

3281005561
03:20:38.369 --> 03:20:41.561
to this country's defence and security,

464176472
03:20:41.562 --> 03:20:44.313
and they will perceive
that in years to come,

2992083424
03:20:44.314 --> 03:20:50.164
a future government may decide
that what is happening now

2271221103
03:20:50.165 --> 03:20:58.308
and what is acceptable right
now is no longer acceptable.

3251812630
03:20:58.309 --> 03:20:59.914
Well, of course I'll give them.

4041109846
03:20:59.915 --> 03:21:04.157
>> He this business about what's
going on over Northern Ireland.

2925431899
03:21:04.158 --> 03:21:08.168
It's not alone because it builds
on a perception and the gratuitous

2674885088
03:21:08.169 --> 03:21:12.412
pursuit of soldiers involved
in Afghanistan and Iraq,

1665465010
03:21:12.413 --> 03:21:14.871
partly by the Prime Minister
in a previous life,

3718818460
03:21:14.872 --> 03:21:17.769
but by the lawyers knowing
full well that what they

1709342961
03:21:17.770 --> 03:21:20.311
were pursuing were in
fact complete untruths.

1879404880
03:21:20.312 --> 03:21:23.211
And that has made them
wonder what's the point?

2794413833
03:21:23.212 --> 03:21:26.614
If politicians will not stand
up for them, then who will?

2915125829
03:21:26.615 --> 03:21:28.069
>> Yeah, I absolutely agree.

192167927
03:21:28.070 --> 03:21:29.123
Agreed my right hon.

379125186
03:21:29.124 --> 03:21:29.524
Friend.

2868089426
03:21:30.708 --> 03:21:32.665
He won't be surprised to hear from me.

1298191493
03:21:32.666 --> 03:21:34.873
I would say it's more
the Northern Ireland,

2211953496
03:21:34.874 --> 03:21:37.965
because Northern Ireland has
read across to a number

1506842390
03:21:37.966 --> 03:21:40.424
of theatres where our men
and women are actively

4065580275
03:21:40.425 --> 03:21:43.911
engaged or could be in the future.

2386354969
03:21:43.912 --> 03:21:48.912
And it seems to me that
the exodus from some of

1864172879
03:21:48.913 --> 03:21:52.863
these units is going
to cause irretrievable

2110206329
03:21:52.864 --> 03:21:55.459
and irrecoverable damage to our ability to

2995212714
03:21:55.460 --> 03:21:57.617
protect the men and women of this country.

971384674
03:21:57.618 --> 03:22:02.964
So I would urge Ministers, I have
no doubt that they're doing this.

692943495
03:22:02.965 --> 03:22:06.126
With all the best of intentions,
to look at the messaging that

484320003
03:22:06.127 --> 03:22:08.988
is being given to the men
and women of our armed forces,

153803594
03:22:08.989 --> 03:22:15.214
many of which I have the honour
and privilege to represent

1642197070
03:22:15.215 --> 03:22:19.467
and decide what they can do in
order to address this legislation.

2097839635
03:22:19.468 --> 03:22:22.012
And I would say, scrap it and start again.

4208219714
03:22:22.013 --> 03:22:23.368
But if they can't do that,

4272434803
03:22:24.711 --> 03:22:29.012
what they can do to prevent
this idea, get this idea,

2204810568
03:22:29.013 --> 03:22:30.917
getting penetrance among those units,

108569479
03:22:30.918 --> 03:22:34.313
particularly that the government
is simply not on their side.

3471984168
03:22:34.314 --> 03:22:36.171
And in any event, even if they were,

736580166
03:22:37.669 --> 03:22:41.773
that government's in the future
may, by the standards of the day,

3642457875
03:22:41.774 --> 03:22:44.765
decide that what is being done
in the name of the state at

4096052193
03:22:44.766 --> 03:22:50.616
the moment in the King's name
was no longer acceptable.

2853233547
03:22:50.617 --> 03:22:52.674
Lawfare is a real and present danger for

2485528569
03:22:52.675 --> 03:22:55.613
the men and women of our armed forces,

92857143
03:22:55.614 --> 03:22:58.713
and I feel certain that
the Secretary of State,

767410440
03:22:58.714 --> 03:23:03.167
knowing him as I do, is cognisant
of the threat that it faces.

438811359
03:23:03.168 --> 03:23:07.618
Madam Deputy Speaker, conscious
of the frog in your throat,

2927443171
03:23:07.619 --> 03:23:12.771
I shall end my remarks there.

1309989545
03:23:12.772 --> 03:23:13.974
>> Catherine McKinnell.

3379299891
03:23:13.975 --> 03:23:14.526
Thank you.

1020075178
03:23:14.527 --> 03:23:19.113
>> Madam Deputy Speaker,
and it's an honour.

3496657975
03:23:19.114 --> 03:23:22.124
>> To follow the Member for
South West South West Wiltshire

2008065077
03:23:22.125 --> 03:23:26.321
and it's very clear that when
it comes to defence readiness,

4243348832
03:23:26.322 --> 03:23:29.124
there is much upon which we can all agree.

2065373347
03:23:29.125 --> 03:23:31.864
And I wanted also, before
he leaves the chamber,

675972117
03:23:31.865 --> 03:23:35.763
to pay tribute to the Member for Chingford

1224273792
03:23:35.764 --> 03:23:38.572
and Woodford Green as
well, and my right hon.

851790637
03:23:38.573 --> 03:23:40.378
Friend the Member for Ilford North.

2038105126
03:23:41.711 --> 03:23:47.011
I think the former set out
in very powerful terms

1100047036
03:23:47.012 --> 03:23:49.119
the challenges that we face as a country.

350970685
03:23:49.712 --> 03:23:51.217
However, it was my right hon.

3540842130
03:23:51.218 --> 03:23:54.961
Friend who set out in
very powerful terms also

3087778273
03:23:54.962 --> 03:23:57.813
the hope and the determination that we

3046920163
03:23:57.814 --> 03:24:01.414
must show in government
in order to meet those

758184247
03:24:01.415 --> 03:24:05.161
challenges in a way that they deserve.

112356791
03:24:05.162 --> 03:24:06.968
And as ever, he shows great courage

919332547
03:24:06.969 --> 03:24:10.474
and strength in leading from the front,

3246032282
03:24:10.475 --> 03:24:14.465
because the debate today
quite rightly focuses

2336794994
03:24:14.466 --> 03:24:16.170
on defence and national security.

2074792542
03:24:16.171 --> 03:24:18.127
And it clearly couldn't be more timely

4129235902
03:24:18.128 --> 03:24:19.883
given the challenges that we face.

276944448
03:24:19.884 --> 03:24:24.770
But that sense of security comes not
just from investment in defence,

622127742
03:24:24.771 --> 03:24:29.367
although clearly that is important,
and I will come to that shortly.

3182747928
03:24:29.368 --> 03:24:32.365
But also that investment
in the broadest sense

329389545
03:24:32.366 --> 03:24:37.064
possible in our people in creating strong,

4082110157
03:24:37.065 --> 03:24:41.013
resilient, enterprising
and cohesive communities.

243239372
03:24:41.014 --> 03:24:43.964
And that is what will
ultimately keep us safe.

1015131398
03:24:43.965 --> 03:24:46.813
The Armed Forces Bill
and the National Security

501070363
03:24:46.814 --> 03:24:51.162
Bill are important steps forward,

228733625
03:24:51.163 --> 03:24:55.113
and with the disgusting and horrifying
extremism and anti-Semitism

1689423223
03:24:55.114 --> 03:24:58.915
that we have seen rising here in Britain,

416669068
03:24:58.916 --> 03:25:02.568
the Tackling State Threats Bill
will also be a welcome response

3486214835
03:25:02.569 --> 03:25:05.622
to those threats that we
face on our own soil,

3696218770
03:25:05.623 --> 03:25:11.061
including from Iran and the Islamic
State Revolutionary Guard Corps.

1412634622
03:25:11.062 --> 03:25:14.573
And having called for this, I welcome
the legislation that is coming,

1986105085
03:25:14.574 --> 03:25:17.867
and I will be following
developments on it very closely.

664965419
03:25:17.868 --> 03:25:18.319
>> Yeah.

1178034076
03:25:18.712 --> 03:25:19.313
Hear, hear.

2512328287
03:25:19.314 --> 03:25:23.312
>> But we cannot make
meaningful progress on

2385003098
03:25:23.313 --> 03:25:25.568
defence without
the Defence Investment plan.

3546081090
03:25:26.712 --> 03:25:31.417
And whilst I know that
the Secretary of State and his

2304459795
03:25:31.418 --> 03:25:36.513
team are working incredibly
hard on producing this,

322487386
03:25:36.514 --> 03:25:39.923
the delay is and does risk
having real world consequences.

3897522885
03:25:39.924 --> 03:25:45.850
And we need it to maintain our
international credibility.

556056865
03:25:45.851 --> 03:25:48.478
For example, in my role as
UK trade envoy to Italy,

232858451
03:25:48.479 --> 03:25:54.211
I know how important the collaboration
is for our GCap programme

2954969162
03:25:54.212 --> 03:25:56.965
and the opportunities
and the defence investment that

52196666
03:25:56.966 --> 03:26:01.337
will be unleashed in my
region, the North East.

3335698606
03:26:01.338 --> 03:26:05.373
Our defence sector is a major employer,
supporting thousands of jobs and

3366480175
03:26:05.374 --> 03:26:08.173
a wide network of small
and medium enterprises,

1269241349
03:26:08.174 --> 03:26:10.267
and we could do even more.

4007257438
03:26:10.268 --> 03:26:13.161
But we do need that
certainty and that security

3092516923
03:26:13.162 --> 03:26:15.018
about what is coming down the track.

1174656810
03:26:16.715 --> 03:26:21.013
And that is as much to protect
our supply chains as those

3723586344
03:26:21.014 --> 03:26:24.161
big contractors that we
know are still waiting,

849366054
03:26:24.162 --> 03:26:27.766
because without the investment
plan, we risk undermining defence,

2848384395
03:26:27.767 --> 03:26:30.917
manufacturing and sovereign capabilities.

3638420887
03:26:30.918 --> 03:26:33.165
Both in my region and across the country.

26790146
03:26:33.166 --> 03:26:37.220
And domestic production is not
something we can gamble with.

3554120941
03:26:37.221 --> 03:26:39.774
We have such a strong story
to tell in Newcastle,

1832347006
03:26:39.775 --> 03:26:42.684
the opening of the North East
Space Skills and Technology

3921145679
03:26:42.685 --> 03:26:45.369
Centre at Northumbria University has added

926488079
03:26:45.370 --> 03:26:47.866
a new dimension to our
regional capabilities,

1270835900
03:26:47.867 --> 03:26:51.520
supporting apprenticeships
and graduate programmes and helping

1918034780
03:26:51.521 --> 03:26:53.978
to build the next generation
of skilled workers.

3714022293
03:26:53.979 --> 03:26:56.967
And we know that defence investment,

2990503250
03:26:56.968 --> 03:26:59.726
it doesn't just impact one
industry, it boosts skills,

2753414663
03:26:59.727 --> 03:27:02.968
innovation and opportunities across our

322853397
03:27:02.969 --> 03:27:04.965
whole economy and that's why we need

2805554277
03:27:04.966 --> 03:27:06.974
to know the details of the plan so that

3518285339
03:27:06.975 --> 03:27:08.679
businesses can provide that real,

1355226166
03:27:08.680 --> 03:27:12.423
tangible support for our
young people so that they

2138104482
03:27:12.424 --> 03:27:15.368
can access high quality
training and employment.

1088119757
03:27:15.369 --> 03:27:18.921
And as a northerner, I'm
pleased to see the Northern

4187806256
03:27:19.716 --> 03:27:22.323
Powerhouse Bill also included
in The King's Speech.

3698560443
03:27:22.324 --> 03:27:24.681
And that must be backed
by genuine investment.

352957524
03:27:24.682 --> 03:27:30.570
The North cannot possibly endure yet
another round of broken promises,

1624407915
03:27:30.571 --> 03:27:33.468
especially after
the catastrophic HS2 management

761999269
03:27:33.469 --> 03:27:34.872
of the previous government.

2897722011
03:27:34.873 --> 03:27:38.123
The Small Business Protections
Bill is also long overdue.

2796404291
03:27:38.675 --> 03:27:42.033
Protection for sole traders,
freelancers and family run businesses

1306987610
03:27:42.034 --> 03:27:45.572
who we know have been ignored by
large companies for far too long.

1295493077
03:27:45.573 --> 03:27:49.921
And I know that so many small
businesses will welcome this,

1346494343
03:27:50.711 --> 03:27:52.716
as it could genuinely save livelihoods,

1098384771
03:27:52.717 --> 03:27:56.068
particularly in retail and hospitality.

2779195246
03:27:56.069 --> 03:27:58.376
And on the subject of
retail and hospitality,

3488620843
03:27:58.377 --> 03:28:01.775
the North East is home
to some of the best.

3382399464
03:28:01.776 --> 03:28:05.671
Newcastle North is the home of
the Greggs sausage roll, after all.

2612277979
03:28:05.672 --> 03:28:08.930
But many in the sector are
concerned about the impact

1935483209
03:28:08.931 --> 03:28:11.821
of the overnight visiting
visitor Levy bill,

2052722768
03:28:11.822 --> 03:28:15.965
so I do urge Ministers to keep
an eye and keep an open mind

1005012506
03:28:15.966 --> 03:28:20.618
on how it emerges and
the evidence that comes through it,

781675173
03:28:20.619 --> 03:28:25.222
because we do need to ensure our
hospitality industry thrives.

3925378279
03:28:25.223 --> 03:28:26.628
And for many at the moment,

1124045418
03:28:26.629 --> 03:28:29.570
it's too often a question
of whether they'll survive.

2656052714
03:28:29.571 --> 03:28:32.265
So I urge the Chancellor to do everything

1134333773
03:28:32.266 --> 03:28:34.070
possible to support our businesses,

2003356047
03:28:34.071 --> 03:28:36.426
especially in retail,
leisure and hospitality,

2471051234
03:28:36.427 --> 03:28:39.137
because they are the sectors
that give so many of our

2124855966
03:28:39.138 --> 03:28:41.746
young people their first
foot on the career ladder,

1205686054
03:28:41.747 --> 03:28:45.015
and without them, we know
that costs to the state

4002193909
03:28:45.016 --> 03:28:47.474
and to those individuals
will be so much higher.

1868917323
03:28:47.716 --> 03:28:51.261
But too often the government
doesn't fear the businesses

385669192
03:28:51.262 --> 03:28:54.412
feel like the odds are
stacking up against them.

3498069367
03:28:54.413 --> 03:28:57.625
But as a government, we just need
to pull all in one direction.

1108475985
03:28:57.626 --> 03:29:00.420
It's in all of our interests
to make sure that those

2955025951
03:29:00.421 --> 03:29:03.321
opportunities reach us
far and wide for jobs,

176061889
03:29:03.322 --> 03:29:07.033
for investment, and for
community cohesion,

2429645893
03:29:07.034 --> 03:29:09.642
because that is as much
about our national security

1676591369
03:29:09.643 --> 03:29:13.268
as investment in rotary
blades and electronics.

2180344355
03:29:13.269 --> 03:29:16.723
So I will continue to monitor
this and call for it in my role

757042088
03:29:16.724 --> 03:29:20.423
as the co-chair of the Youth
Employment All party group.

246170937
03:29:20.711 --> 03:29:24.716
And finally, the government's work
through the Energy Independence

2221997038
03:29:24.717 --> 03:29:27.274
Bill and Nuclear Regulation
Bill are both welcome.

2589867525
03:29:27.275 --> 03:29:30.583
They'll strengthen our energy
security and our national security,

1181255050
03:29:30.584 --> 03:29:33.291
and they will accelerate
home grown renewable energy.

4014743736
03:29:33.292 --> 03:29:36.126
And as the chair of the all
party group on warm homes,

905718058
03:29:36.127 --> 03:29:39.183
I want to see a really
ambitious energy production,

1237270370
03:29:39.184 --> 03:29:43.116
and I will continue to
monitor the impact both on

2134354157
03:29:43.117 --> 03:29:45.625
warm homes and
the retrofitting of homes as well,

3229643708
03:29:45.626 --> 03:29:47.833
because that is how we
will help households

777509533
03:29:48.720 --> 03:29:50.475
manage the rising costs of living.

1264423381
03:29:50.476 --> 03:29:52.684
There's so much in this
King's speech to be

1642087305
03:29:52.685 --> 03:29:55.063
welcomed by my constituents in Newcastle,

4023530415
03:29:55.064 --> 03:29:57.570
North from the Commonhold
and Leaseholders Rights

660001373
03:29:57.571 --> 03:30:00.420
Bill to the Social Housing Renewal Bill.

297002491
03:30:00.421 --> 03:30:04.424
But we have to ensure that they
feel it, that they understand it,

3574796848
03:30:04.425 --> 03:30:06.769
that they come with us and they see

2232194703
03:30:06.770 --> 03:30:10.276
the vision so that we can help people

1534698839
03:30:10.277 --> 03:30:15.373
to build better lives and stronger
communities right across the UK.

989097805
03:30:15.374 --> 03:30:17.423
>> Julian Lewis Sir Julian Lewis.

274056211
03:30:17.424 --> 03:30:19.229
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

2707337778
03:30:21.721 --> 03:30:22.172
The hon.

3593624846
03:30:22.173 --> 03:30:25.132
Lady for Newcastle North has
such a sunny personality that

3041452057
03:30:25.133 --> 03:30:28.323
I always feel cheered up after
listening to her contributions,

1590828128
03:30:28.324 --> 03:30:32.570
even when she's the bearer
of somewhat disappointing

2372993997
03:30:32.571 --> 03:30:38.329
news about impressed the economy.

36387000
03:30:38.330 --> 03:30:40.387
Also, I was impressed with the speech of

2084370631
03:30:40.388 --> 03:30:42.494
the former Secretary of State for health,

943830020
03:30:42.495 --> 03:30:45.676
who's just about to
escape from the chamber,

1846835540
03:30:45.677 --> 03:30:49.829
but it did leave me wondering, had
I been a parliamentary sketch writer,

1670223862
03:30:49.830 --> 03:30:51.535
what my headline would have been?

271139469
03:30:51.720 --> 03:30:56.773
And I think the headline would have
been why on earth did he resign?

1737948068
03:30:56.774 --> 03:31:00.019
It sounded much more like
a manifesto in a leadership

244340582
03:31:00.020 --> 03:31:02.969
campaign than a trigger for calling one.

2156335241
03:31:02.970 --> 03:31:03.873
But there we are.

2730030380
03:31:03.874 --> 03:31:06.568
We all have our own motives.

3299272572
03:31:06.569 --> 03:31:10.131
And he did say one particular point
of great relevance to this debate,

2076771505
03:31:10.132 --> 03:31:12.417
which I have already,

3073619553
03:31:12.418 --> 03:31:14.072
I promise, Madam Deputy Speaker,

3138358419
03:31:15.715 --> 03:31:17.772
written down before I heard him make it,

3229486333
03:31:17.773 --> 03:31:23.165
which was the comparison between
the terrible experience of the pandemic

314014059
03:31:23.166 --> 03:31:29.621
and the terrible experience of
a country involved in a full scale war.

2481540761
03:31:29.622 --> 03:31:32.917
There were, of course, the casualties.

3712455389
03:31:32.918 --> 03:31:37.319
There was the determination
to learn from it.

4178461053
03:31:37.320 --> 03:31:38.473
There was the outcome.

2719060989
03:31:38.474 --> 03:31:44.316
That means that we are a lot
better prepared for the future.

2734769989
03:31:44.317 --> 03:31:47.015
Should another deadly
virus attack us, we will,

2401257559
03:31:47.016 --> 03:31:50.817
as a result of the lessons
learned during that pandemic,

1930854152
03:31:50.818 --> 03:31:55.771
be in a much better position
to develop vaccines.

1350045953
03:31:55.772 --> 03:31:59.165
Effective vaccines, far more quickly.

3160950996
03:31:59.166 --> 03:32:02.518
But the real parallel, I'm
afraid, is not a very happy one.

1618135167
03:32:02.519 --> 03:32:04.928
It is the fact that
if someone had said before,

4067177280
03:32:04.929 --> 03:32:09.432
we knew we were going
to have that pandemic,

1177557107
03:32:09.433 --> 03:32:13.822
you need to invest a considerable
sum of money into developing

2419673964
03:32:13.823 --> 03:32:19.768
a system to enable you
to develop vaccines.

650586698
03:32:19.769 --> 03:32:25.376
In quick response to
the emergence of a new deadly virus.

4115659117
03:32:25.377 --> 03:32:27.417
We probably would not have done it.

1450443545
03:32:27.418 --> 03:32:31.968
And that is where the parallel
lies with wartime situations,

1745262366
03:32:31.969 --> 03:32:35.965
because for many years now,

4111888851
03:32:35.966 --> 03:32:37.972
defence minded members on both sides of

3557437261
03:32:37.973 --> 03:32:40.380
the House have been urging successive

3071188960
03:32:40.381 --> 03:32:45.576
governments that we need to
spend a lot more on defence.

747367343
03:32:45.577 --> 03:32:50.122
And if those warnings go unheeded,

3031199158
03:32:50.123 --> 03:32:55.677
and if this country
ends up in a full scale

2343004262
03:32:55.678 --> 03:32:58.266
armed conflict with a peer adversary,

2422619368
03:32:58.267 --> 03:33:05.522
we will not be talking about
spending 3 or 4% on defence of GDP.

2896541845
03:33:05.523 --> 03:33:08.232
We will be talking about,
and we will actually be

291170365
03:33:08.233 --> 03:33:14.483
having to spend 30
or 40% of GDP on defence,

2928492976
03:33:14.484 --> 03:33:18.822
and we do not wish to get to
that situation because not

2351609831
03:33:18.823 --> 03:33:23.926
only is it economic loss,
but think of the human cost,

281733322
03:33:25.715 --> 03:33:28.172
because if by investing
in defence in peacetime,

2572594863
03:33:28.173 --> 03:33:34.969
you can actually deter a potential
enemy from starting a war,

4020080312
03:33:34.970 --> 03:33:36.826
you then not only save the treasure,

3808869826
03:33:36.827 --> 03:33:44.275
you save the blood that
otherwise is shed so copiously.

4030959594
03:33:44.276 --> 03:33:47.768
So Russia, as we know, is spending
something of the order of between

1374020872
03:33:47.769 --> 03:33:55.824
a third and a half of its gross
domestic product on military power,

676036460
03:33:55.825 --> 03:34:01.180
and the Defence Committee
in the past has looked at

1617117499
03:34:01.181 --> 03:34:10.029
the question of what this
country has historically spent,

1973448430
03:34:10.030 --> 03:34:14.425
and in both, both a report
entitled Shifting the Goalposts

293558338
03:34:14.426 --> 03:34:20.022
and in a second report, Shifting
the Goalposts, an update.

4072138535
03:34:20.023 --> 03:34:20.273
The.

2116217349
03:34:20.274 --> 03:34:24.877
The figures were spelt out,
which showed that my right hon.

2580335169
03:34:24.878 --> 03:34:31.471
Friend the Member for Chingford was
completely correct in the mid 1980s,

2885188590
03:34:31.472 --> 03:34:36.624
he said when he was serving
that we were spending.

1495138892
03:34:36.625 --> 03:34:37.729
Of the order of 5.3%.

1318179131
03:34:37.730 --> 03:34:47.021
In fact, in 1983 to 4, the figure
given at the time was 4.4%.

1496090009
03:34:47.022 --> 03:34:48.930
And in 1984 to 5 the figure was 4.5%.

1357053201
03:34:48.931 --> 03:34:57.625
But in reality, that was because
we held higher criteria for what

2363786181
03:34:57.626 --> 03:35:01.130
counted as defence expenditure
than the other NATO powers.

3035992980
03:35:01.131 --> 03:35:03.972
And later on we adopted their standards.

3901428950
03:35:03.973 --> 03:35:07.384
So looking back now, when we are
talking in these percentage terms,

29467952
03:35:07.385 --> 03:35:12.785
we can see that those
figures were actually 5.3%

1665246441
03:35:12.786 --> 03:35:18.482
in 1983 to 4 and 5.5% in 1984 to 5.

1791820783
03:35:18.483 --> 03:35:20.331
Now, these are very big figures,

1525966593
03:35:20.332 --> 03:35:26.528
and people talk about the way in
which the peace dividend was taken.

662774014
03:35:26.529 --> 03:35:27.282
But as my hon.

1347313425
03:35:27.283 --> 03:35:29.640
Friend on the front bench,
as shadow Secretary

2606740916
03:35:32.719 --> 03:35:34.476
of State pointed out in 1996 to 7,

3089561674
03:35:34.477 --> 03:35:40.319
the year in which Tony Blair took over
from the conservative government,

2025722785
03:35:40.320 --> 03:35:42.176
that was already half a dozen years,

1252565369
03:35:42.723 --> 03:35:44.731
at least since the end of the Cold War.

1251160783
03:35:44.732 --> 03:35:47.730
If we count that as as
1991 rather than 1989,

482809537
03:35:47.731 --> 03:35:53.880
with the fall of the Berlin
Wall, and at that time,

122864945
03:35:53.881 --> 03:35:57.234
1996 to 7, six years after
the ending of the Cold War,

3195099085
03:35:57.235 --> 03:36:00.927
we were still spending 3%.

1004610967
03:36:00.928 --> 03:36:05.027
When you consider that
that was the figure then,

654332357
03:36:05.028 --> 03:36:07.584
and when you consider, as quite rightly,

2021107200
03:36:07.585 --> 03:36:11.620
the chairman of the current
day defence Committee

1874722786
03:36:11.621 --> 03:36:15.073
said in a admirably objective speech

3070127761
03:36:15.074 --> 03:36:17.230
that Russia is preparing for conflict now,

2708020102
03:36:17.719 --> 03:36:19.424
but we are responding too slowly.

3150244710
03:36:19.425 --> 03:36:24.030
He said time is short, given
the urgency of the situation.

1157586914
03:36:24.031 --> 03:36:27.428
He's exactly right when we are talking

2775034077
03:36:27.429 --> 03:36:31.878
about achieving figures of 3% in a few

2494451497
03:36:31.879 --> 03:36:37.979
years time and 5% in a few more years
time, I just put it to the house.

2269473868
03:36:37.980 --> 03:36:44.274
Does the killer in the Kremlin
intend to give us that time?

2966784013
03:36:44.275 --> 03:36:49.026
And if we want to deter
him from taking a step,

582635125
03:36:49.027 --> 03:36:53.074
which would be to
the detriment of the world,

941027800
03:36:53.075 --> 03:36:54.480
then we need to invest now.

187983829
03:36:54.481 --> 03:37:01.973
And as in the case of the pandemic,
we need to find the money now.

1059352569
03:37:01.974 --> 03:37:06.726
And if a war broke out tomorrow,
we would find the money now.

783342040
03:37:06.727 --> 03:37:10.085
So let's find it today
and diminish the chance of that

1982334478
03:37:10.086 --> 03:37:15.127
terrible conflict happening
on the day after.

579144621
03:37:15.128 --> 03:37:17.173
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

1851393093
03:37:17.174 --> 03:37:20.234
>> I welcome any debate which,
as the collective security of

581295032
03:37:20.235 --> 03:37:23.444
the British people at its heart,
because, Madam Deputy Speaker,

855098513
03:37:23.445 --> 03:37:26.729
I believe one of
the greatest threats of security

3597587820
03:37:26.730 --> 03:37:29.086
is the economic system
governing this country,

759992193
03:37:29.087 --> 03:37:32.630
which has consistently failed working
class people and communities,

1669394496
03:37:32.723 --> 03:37:36.324
an issue which undoubtedly
will be made worse still

827921913
03:37:36.325 --> 03:37:38.533
by the illegal and ill
planned war in Iran.

2023829613
03:37:38.680 --> 03:37:42.423
So now more than ever, we
need a radical restructuring

2085448577
03:37:42.424 --> 03:37:44.078
of both priorities and policies.

4204856899
03:37:44.079 --> 03:37:47.580
More council housing, a total enterita by

1187132653
03:37:47.581 --> 03:37:51.476
the nationalisation of our industries,

229861064
03:37:51.477 --> 03:37:54.777
sold off and gutted by Thatcher,
including water and energy.

950000986
03:37:54.778 --> 03:37:58.482
No one in Britain should be going hungry,

4167147146
03:37:58.483 --> 03:38:00.640
so I welcome the recognition in the King's

2779432844
03:38:00.641 --> 03:38:04.537
Speech from the government that
a food poverty crisis exists in the UK.

1779554644
03:38:04.724 --> 03:38:08.383
However, redistribution of
surplus food won't begin to end.

3682792642
03:38:08.384 --> 03:38:11.877
The insecurity food insecurity faced by

3271501380
03:38:11.878 --> 03:38:13.884
over 14 million people in this country.

3115405164
03:38:13.885 --> 03:38:16.833
It's a sticking plaster
over the gaping wound.

1296667856
03:38:16.834 --> 03:38:19.980
We need a solution that
acknowledges the sheer scale

1787864256
03:38:19.981 --> 03:38:22.540
of hunger across the UK
over the last five months.

310837733
03:38:22.724 --> 03:38:24.228
The Right to Food Commission.

1916578720
03:38:24.229 --> 03:38:26.276
I am proud to be part of a.

4002442262
03:38:26.277 --> 03:38:29.273
I travelled across these
islands from Liverpool,

2455468226
03:38:29.274 --> 03:38:31.227
Knowsley to Newcastle, Northumberland,

1412994751
03:38:31.228 --> 03:38:33.133
from Cardiff and Aberdeen to Belfast,

997824845
03:38:33.134 --> 03:38:35.341
with Glasgow and London
to come next month.

188725174
03:38:35.342 --> 03:38:36.394
Listening to people.

946722591
03:38:37.680 --> 03:38:41.327
This country too often ignores
not economists in boardrooms,

2585547378
03:38:41.328 --> 03:38:42.580
not corporate lobbyists,

2768807786
03:38:42.581 --> 03:38:45.833
but working class people in
working class communities

3364434460
03:38:45.834 --> 03:38:49.137
who understand better than
anyone the scale of food

1946950990
03:38:49.138 --> 03:38:51.696
insecurity in this country
and how it is impacting

258079643
03:38:51.697 --> 03:38:55.579
the lives and health of the very people,

2761448135
03:38:55.580 --> 03:39:00.980
the people living every day
in hunger every single day,

3779799865
03:39:00.981 --> 03:39:02.735
and living with this consequences.

3789472682
03:39:02.736 --> 03:39:05.393
The Commission have gathered
evidence what I believe

2310497656
03:39:05.394 --> 03:39:08.489
will be a defining report
for our generation,

1439240293
03:39:08.490 --> 03:39:11.903
a roadmap to finally making
the right to food, the law of the land.

3918833147
03:39:11.904 --> 03:39:15.565
Because, Madam Deputy Speaker, in one
of the richest countries on earth,

318493461
03:39:15.566 --> 03:39:17.622
millions of our people are going hungry,

500584490
03:39:17.623 --> 03:39:20.634
and that should shame every
single one of us in this place.

2078642586
03:39:20.635 --> 03:39:23.444
And I say this truthfully,
because what I've heard over

2259612180
03:39:23.445 --> 03:39:26.203
the last few months has left
me absolutely devastated.

416579074
03:39:26.204 --> 03:39:29.164
I set, prepared and skipping
meals for their kids can eat.

849526401
03:39:29.165 --> 03:39:31.070
I've listened to disabled people tell

2937003540
03:39:31.071 --> 03:39:32.976
us they're sitting in freezing homes,

3765170035
03:39:32.977 --> 03:39:36.329
deciding whether to put
the heating on or buy food,

210028911
03:39:36.330 --> 03:39:39.237
let alone a treat a day or,
God forbid, a holiday.

2525671945
03:39:39.238 --> 03:39:42.528
I've met with workers,
workers in full time jobs,

770227079
03:39:42.529 --> 03:39:44.324
relying on food banks to survive.

2295007904
03:39:44.325 --> 03:39:48.281
And that, Madam Deputy Speaker,
is the scandal of modern Britain.

431918168
03:39:48.282 --> 03:39:50.580
Because these people are not failing.

4259686851
03:39:50.581 --> 03:39:51.834
Britain is failing them.

588630054
03:39:51.835 --> 03:39:55.384
We have heard evidence from
union members outlining how

678374139
03:39:55.385 --> 03:39:58.329
civil servants are using food
banks because of low pay.

190935150
03:39:58.330 --> 03:40:01.190
The Bakers Union report on how
the very workers who make

1836685776
03:40:01.191 --> 03:40:05.132
our food cannot afford to
put it on their own tables.

2255912598
03:40:05.133 --> 03:40:07.538
Think about how obscene that is.

2431940755
03:40:07.539 --> 03:40:10.077
Think about how flawed our economic system

2631108562
03:40:10.078 --> 03:40:11.634
must be if it results in this.

742696956
03:40:11.635 --> 03:40:14.745
And let us not stop pretending
that this happens by accident.

957934944
03:40:15.727 --> 03:40:16.329
It did not.

1411727519
03:40:16.330 --> 03:40:20.278
This is the result of political decisions.

1428296517
03:40:20.279 --> 03:40:23.488
40 years of neoliberal economic
economics that have seen people

1233545361
03:40:23.489 --> 03:40:27.332
and communities disempowered
and left behind, industries destroyed,

800332433
03:40:27.333 --> 03:40:29.732
trade union power,
weakened, public services,

2826061014
03:40:30.728 --> 03:40:34.479
hollowed out wages and incomes driven
down while wealth flows upwards.

601423932
03:40:34.480 --> 03:40:39.342
And then after that, people are
told to be grateful for charity.

3755365234
03:40:39.343 --> 03:40:41.549
Madam Deputy Speaker,
food banks were never

3254636881
03:40:41.550 --> 03:40:43.431
supposed to be part of British life.

2875187420
03:40:43.432 --> 03:40:47.680
They declared a sign our
economy and society is broken.

1489220898
03:40:47.681 --> 03:40:49.938
But an entire generation
of children are now

2113187241
03:40:49.939 --> 03:40:53.333
growing up believing
food banks are normal.

40925789
03:40:53.334 --> 03:40:54.337
That is not normal.

1881016696
03:40:54.338 --> 03:40:56.331
It is not acceptable.

2473876219
03:40:56.332 --> 03:40:58.538
And also it's not
inevitable because hunger

3482094495
03:40:58.539 --> 03:41:00.748
in Britain is not caused
by a lack of food.

1908296038
03:41:00.749 --> 03:41:01.952
It's caused by poverty.

2077185668
03:41:01.953 --> 03:41:05.533
That is the truth of the heart
of this debate, not scarcity,

2890321794
03:41:05.534 --> 03:41:09.592
poverty, low wages, insecure
work, sky high rents,

3768404197
03:41:09.593 --> 03:41:12.934
broken security system
and an economic system that

1575288434
03:41:12.935 --> 03:41:15.385
pretends wealth while punishing the poor.

1094375721
03:41:15.386 --> 03:41:18.882
That's why I say gently to
the government Ministers surplus

4091665622
03:41:18.883 --> 03:41:21.933
food redistribution is not
a solution to hunger.

1847848794
03:41:21.934 --> 03:41:24.440
Yes, any support for
struggling families matters?

578517771
03:41:24.441 --> 03:41:26.529
Of course it does.

1940061615
03:41:26.530 --> 03:41:30.480
But we do not, cannot build a just
system, just society on leftovers.

1361184879
03:41:30.481 --> 03:41:34.738
We cannot normalise the emergency
charity as permanent public policy,

4153825430
03:41:34.739 --> 03:41:36.796
and we cannot allow food banks to become

760709401
03:41:36.797 --> 03:41:39.155
the for the maid service
of the British state.

3309757041
03:41:39.733 --> 03:41:40.485
Because we do.

3511598053
03:41:40.486 --> 03:41:43.834
We are accepting managed
poverty instead of ending it,

250993692
03:41:43.835 --> 03:41:45.339
and I reject that completely.

1001406694
03:41:45.733 --> 03:41:48.892
Earlier this week, the Mayor of
Greater Manchester spoke about

460312955
03:41:48.893 --> 03:41:51.832
the damage done by 40 years
of neoliberal economics,

1946382384
03:41:51.833 --> 03:41:55.192
and he was spot on because everywhere
the commissioners travelled,

3608035273
03:41:55.193 --> 03:41:59.282
there was a sense deep in communities
that people have been abandoned.

1844843034
03:41:59.283 --> 03:42:03.591
In Northumberland, one woman said
something I will never, ever forget.

4116472262
03:42:03.592 --> 03:42:07.787
She said, don't you dare call
us disadvantaged, call us.

318618656
03:42:07.788 --> 03:42:10.844
Asset stripped and my God,
Madam Deputy Speaker.

3897760295
03:42:10.845 --> 03:42:11.597
She was right.

2167264708
03:42:11.598 --> 03:42:15.072
That is exactly what has happened
to working class Britain.

1138077625
03:42:15.073 --> 03:42:17.640
Asset stripped hope stripped,
industry stripped,

1965031842
03:42:17.641 --> 03:42:20.283
security stripped and then those very

4041452373
03:42:20.284 --> 03:42:22.389
communities that blamed and demonised for

254579789
03:42:22.390 --> 03:42:24.344
the consequences of political choices.

4245962133
03:42:24.345 --> 03:42:27.036
But despite everything,
despite all the hardship,

710451649
03:42:27.037 --> 03:42:29.786
those communities still
fight for one another.

1717824680
03:42:29.787 --> 03:42:32.896
That was the beautiful thing we
witnessed everywhere we went.

2461574702
03:42:32.897 --> 03:42:35.053
Solidarity is still alive in this country.

2145058687
03:42:35.054 --> 03:42:38.714
Working class people still feeding
each other, looking after each other,

3815653450
03:42:38.715 --> 03:42:42.736
organising together show more humanity
and church halls and community

447881235
03:42:42.737 --> 03:42:45.594
centres than many have ever
experienced from government.

1019348335
03:42:45.727 --> 03:42:46.931
And that is the spirit.

384656306
03:42:46.932 --> 03:42:49.893
And that is what the Right to
Food campaign is built upon.

3693185806
03:42:49.894 --> 03:42:52.535
Because people do not
want charity forever.

2995413456
03:42:52.536 --> 03:42:54.491
They want dignity, they want security.

3121941381
03:42:54.492 --> 03:42:57.552
They want to know they can feed
their families without fear.

1803884873
03:42:57.553 --> 03:42:59.834
Madam Deputy Speaker,
hunger is a political

1931048256
03:42:59.835 --> 03:43:01.992
choice and a hunger is a political choice.

1365088376
03:43:01.993 --> 03:43:04.833
And ending hunger must
become a political priority.

1903442279
03:43:04.834 --> 03:43:06.839
That means universal free school meals.

569083506
03:43:06.840 --> 03:43:09.141
It means wages people
can actually live on.

2663106727
03:43:09.142 --> 03:43:11.398
It means secure work,
stronger trade unions.

1508399065
03:43:11.399 --> 03:43:14.182
It means proper enforcement
of a legal right to food,

4064069429
03:43:14.183 --> 03:43:16.088
and it means investments in community

2915434776
03:43:16.732 --> 03:43:18.536
kitchens and local food programmes.

1536109088
03:43:18.537 --> 03:43:21.044
And it means finally
rebuilding the welfare state

4061110590
03:43:21.045 --> 03:43:23.451
that protects people
instead of punishing them.

1551881184
03:43:23.452 --> 03:43:25.985
And yes, price caps on essential items.

1461076815
03:43:25.986 --> 03:43:27.540
These are not extreme demands.

2133592536
03:43:27.541 --> 03:43:31.682
They're the bare minimum
standards for civilised society,

3548008619
03:43:31.683 --> 03:43:33.337
because in 21st century Britain,

713906066
03:43:33.731 --> 03:43:38.542
nobody should be going hungry in
the community we have visited.

3481393127
03:43:38.543 --> 03:43:41.936
Everybody agreed food is our
most basic human right,

3485910602
03:43:41.937 --> 03:43:45.385
and good food should be
a fundamental human right for all.

908790895
03:43:45.386 --> 03:43:47.876
And right to food will place this at

3689432853
03:43:47.877 --> 03:43:50.488
the very heart of
government decision making

3552187528
03:43:50.489 --> 03:43:53.952
and history will ask all of us in
this House a very simple question.

2831281618
03:43:53.953 --> 03:43:57.465
When millions of children are going
hungry, what did you do about it?

1371540166
03:43:58.731 --> 03:43:59.986
I know what side I'm on.

854168225
03:43:59.987 --> 03:44:03.938
>> My constituency neighbour, Mike Martin.

3399068570
03:44:03.939 --> 03:44:07.349
>> Madam Deputy Speaker, you don't
normally introduce me like that.

1243350511
03:44:07.350 --> 03:44:10.752
So thank you very much.

3285130548
03:44:10.753 --> 03:44:13.985
And it's a an honour to
share a border with you,

1833649460
03:44:13.986 --> 03:44:16.243
Madam Deputy Speaker,
and to follow the hon.

1972484280
03:44:16.244 --> 03:44:19.081
Member from Liverpool, West Derby,

1675681946
03:44:19.082 --> 03:44:24.687
for clearly a heartfelt
and and powerful Wars are speech.

1044943489
03:44:24.688 --> 03:44:29.286
Madam Deputy Speaker, Wars are raging
in Europe and in the Middle East,

3080208296
03:44:29.287 --> 03:44:32.882
and extreme tensions
exist in the Far East.

3410631320
03:44:32.883 --> 03:44:37.237
And moreover, these regional conflicts
are starting to knit together.

2871510060
03:44:38.690 --> 03:44:41.298
Russia and China supported
Iran in the Middle East,

1888377923
03:44:42.731 --> 03:44:44.786
North Korea supported Ukraine in Europe,

4134000606
03:44:44.787 --> 03:44:48.917
and this knitting together of
regional conflicts is is what we

2316014564
03:44:48.918 --> 03:44:52.593
saw in the 1930s in the foothills
of the Second World War.

1556867699
03:44:52.594 --> 03:44:55.735
And so there is an argument
to be made that we are

1066420996
03:44:55.736 --> 03:44:59.738
in the foothills now
of another global war.

2527389945
03:44:59.739 --> 03:45:03.587
It's undoubtedly true that
the threats that we face are increasing.

2576979058
03:45:03.588 --> 03:45:05.885
Yet at the same time, day by day,

2234809179
03:45:05.886 --> 03:45:10.741
UK military capability
is actually decreasing.

362298506
03:45:10.742 --> 03:45:14.691
Madam Deputy Speaker, we must
rapidly rearm to narrow this gap.

87461833
03:45:14.692 --> 03:45:19.336
It is the only way that
we can deter conflict.

3203456550
03:45:19.337 --> 03:45:22.088
Yet despite this,
the King's Speech contains

1483939445
03:45:22.089 --> 03:45:24.331
no programme for rearmament.

2946483866
03:45:24.332 --> 03:45:27.181
The government speaks
the language of urgency,

2008004023
03:45:27.182 --> 03:45:30.934
yet refuses even to introduce
the necessary policy and legislation.

3785949624
03:45:30.935 --> 03:45:34.691
As has already been mentioned
from all sides of the House,

3748538028
03:45:34.692 --> 03:45:38.202
we've been waiting for the Defence
Investment Plan since last autumn,

3549375209
03:45:38.203 --> 03:45:43.141
and we were promised a defence
readiness Bill in this King's speech.

4116566608
03:45:43.142 --> 03:45:46.590
Where is it, Madam Deputy
Speaker, as an island nation,

1678761200
03:45:46.591 --> 03:45:52.085
our navy is of the utmost importance,
but it is also on its knees.

3323782624
03:45:52.086 --> 03:45:55.687
While HMS Dragon took a week to
deploy to the Mediterranean,

3078290720
03:45:55.688 --> 03:45:59.134
the French sent an entire carrier
group, an aircraft carrier,

3070342411
03:45:59.135 --> 03:46:02.486
eight frigates and submarine.

1967900194
03:46:02.487 --> 03:46:03.591
How did they do that?

3694253930
03:46:03.592 --> 03:46:07.264
Well, on paper, France
and the United Kingdom

3844246816
03:46:07.265 --> 03:46:10.945
have comparable fleets, but in practice,

1747419623
03:46:10.946 --> 03:46:14.154
France achieves around 80%
availability for its escort vessels,

1548483456
03:46:14.155 --> 03:46:17.637
while we only achieve 50%.

7798722
03:46:17.638 --> 03:46:19.442
So through better maintenance, the.

2511499887
03:46:19.735 --> 03:46:21.690
That France achieves a better outcome.

1266577852
03:46:23.735 --> 03:46:26.393
Capability on paper is
worthless if it can't deploy.

4174843927
03:46:26.394 --> 03:46:28.493
And it gets worse.

1970485254
03:46:28.494 --> 03:46:31.532
We started this year with seven frigates.

4243154740
03:46:31.533 --> 03:46:34.285
HMS Richmond will be
decommissioned this year,

2483561527
03:46:34.286 --> 03:46:37.699
and HMS Iron Duke was withdrawn
from service this month.

2585279953
03:46:37.700 --> 03:46:41.236
This leaves us with five frigates.

2370912842
03:46:41.237 --> 03:46:43.793
Furthermore, three build
slots in Glasgow intended

3363160269
03:46:43.794 --> 03:46:46.086
for new frigates have been ceded to Norway

919939310
03:46:46.087 --> 03:46:48.544
because of the lack of
guaranteed investment due

2026393108
03:46:48.545 --> 03:46:50.651
to delays in the Defence Investment Plan.

3133068276
03:46:50.652 --> 03:46:53.643
This is a real world example of government

1688461700
03:46:53.644 --> 03:46:56.888
inertia affecting our defence.

843925157
03:46:56.889 --> 03:47:01.190
Putin exploits weakness
and he shies away from strength.

1407116551
03:47:01.191 --> 03:47:05.693
It pains me to say it, but our
Navy does not project strength

2154168711
03:47:05.694 --> 03:47:08.501
and Putin will continue
to mount increasingly

1711342346
03:47:08.502 --> 03:47:11.108
flagrant violations of our
territorial waters until

2617125091
03:47:11.109 --> 03:47:13.790
our navy is strong enough
to make him feel twice.

4282523786
03:47:14.736 --> 03:47:27.134
Will it take the severing of
a data cable to cause us to act?

1846121534
03:47:27.135 --> 03:47:28.237
Madam Deputy Speaker.

4224401484
03:47:28.238 --> 03:47:31.033
Dry mouth is real.

2635345018
03:47:31.034 --> 03:47:32.339
From the sea to the land.

1792632015
03:47:32.340 --> 03:47:35.993
Madam Deputy Speaker, the MoD was
unable to confirm to the Defence

3060610422
03:47:36.694 --> 03:47:39.803
Select Committee whether it was
able to deploy a battlegroup.

4085143593
03:47:39.804 --> 03:47:42.362
So a thousand soldiers to
the continent of Europe.

3058027189
03:47:42.363 --> 03:47:45.791
And this comes back to my point
about projecting strength.

327642029
03:47:45.792 --> 03:47:49.692
Putin knows that if he
were to test article five,

1576342604
03:47:49.693 --> 03:47:53.441
the 900 British soldiers in
Estonia would be in extreme risk.

1378922361
03:47:53.442 --> 03:47:57.434
We have no ability to
deploy reinforcements.

495221564
03:47:57.435 --> 03:48:00.541
The King's Speech doesn't
do anything to change that.

2389658054
03:48:00.542 --> 03:48:02.890
There is a gaping hole in our deterrence

839637811
03:48:02.891 --> 03:48:05.389
every day that goes unaddressed.

2391015338
03:48:05.390 --> 03:48:10.140
The risks to our forces
who are already deployed

1854589549
03:48:10.141 --> 03:48:11.797
and to our nation at home, grow.

3075115825
03:48:11.798 --> 03:48:16.338
Our artillery systems have
halved in number since 1997.

2778056053
03:48:16.339 --> 03:48:20.085
Our precision DfE capability
has been cut by a third.

858044056
03:48:20.086 --> 03:48:22.042
We have just 14 155 artillery systems.

422903245
03:48:22.735 --> 03:48:27.889
Although I know the government has
just recently announced a new order.

3589314469
03:48:27.890 --> 03:48:31.790
Poland donated 100 systems to Ukraine
and rebuilt their own inventory.

736881932
03:48:31.791 --> 03:48:35.590
At the same time they
donated and replaced.

4011327495
03:48:35.591 --> 03:48:39.555
We just donated, which is why we
have 14 artillery systems left.

2212072233
03:48:39.740 --> 03:48:44.353
And meanwhile, warfare has changed
and the UK has not adapted.

231678664
03:48:44.354 --> 03:48:46.359
During a recent NATO training exercise,

1567906807
03:48:46.735 --> 03:48:48.740
a British brigade was effectively wiped

1205696308
03:48:48.741 --> 03:48:51.338
out by four Ukrainian drone operators.

2935374675
03:48:51.339 --> 03:48:54.142
This is not an indictment of our soldiers,

3545027273
03:48:54.143 --> 03:48:56.537
but a reflection of modern warfare.

1094885401
03:48:56.538 --> 03:49:00.638
We cannot allow that situation
to become a reality.

2847740070
03:49:00.639 --> 03:49:04.290
The picture I've painted
is one of systematic

3059114655
03:49:04.291 --> 03:49:05.944
underfunding across all domains,

1828764057
03:49:06.691 --> 03:49:10.589
and unless we rapidly rearm, we
are going to be unable to deter.

4260074270
03:49:10.590 --> 03:49:13.137
And if we want to deter,
if we want to lead

2237622733
03:49:13.138 --> 03:49:17.040
in the security of the Euro-Atlantic area,

1076403695
03:49:17.041 --> 03:49:20.792
we probably need an army of about
100 000 with reserves of 50,

3644461827
03:49:20.793 --> 03:49:27.048
a fleet of 50 ships, and about 250
combat aircraft with crewed systems

1696823520
03:49:27.737 --> 03:49:30.544
surrounded by autonomous
systems and one way effectors.

2129379223
03:49:30.744 --> 03:49:35.491
That is the sort of capability
that we're talking about.

1768741819
03:49:35.492 --> 03:49:39.295
If we want to lead and deter in
the Euro-Atlantic, I will give way.

631594531
03:49:39.296 --> 03:49:44.240
>> For giving way, following his
remarks with a great deal of interest.

2583850270
03:49:44.241 --> 03:49:45.795
And he mentioned the reserves.

3394427277
03:49:45.796 --> 03:49:47.000
Well, I am a reservist.

1591802635
03:49:47.001 --> 03:49:49.893
And would you give the government
credit where it's due?

2281851579
03:49:49.894 --> 03:49:52.894
And that is in carrying
over the Armed Forces Bill,

1849800271
03:49:52.895 --> 03:49:56.846
advancing the age of retirement
for reserves to the age of 65,

561115228
03:49:56.847 --> 03:50:02.141
and agree with me that we can
probably go further in looking

4058418484
03:50:02.142 --> 03:50:04.499
at people who are skilled
in particular areas,

943530259
03:50:04.500 --> 03:50:06.958
especially the reserves,
who may be able to help

3222275554
03:50:06.959 --> 03:50:09.015
us address the challenges of the future.

1842142809
03:50:09.016 --> 03:50:12.680
Bath the UQ Mike Martin.

2403244533
03:50:12.706 --> 03:50:13.006
past.

1024260916
03:50:13.007 --> 03:50:14.111
>> Using the term UQ.

1588770393
03:50:14.112 --> 03:50:16.842
>> Mike Martin Kim for his intervention,

1526796465
03:50:16.843 --> 03:50:21.348
I served on the Bill Committee for
the Armed Forces Bill and absolutely,

3778455589
03:50:21.349 --> 03:50:24.445
as well as increasing the scope
of who can be called up.

1321179275
03:50:24.446 --> 03:50:26.702
It also creates
a consolidation of different

2789337870
03:50:26.740 --> 03:50:28.194
types of reserves and allows

1374783531
03:50:28.195 --> 03:50:33.186
zigzag pathways for specialists who
can come in and out of the reserve.

828388669
03:50:33.187 --> 03:50:37.242
So this is absolutely a step
in the right direction.

1141856735
03:50:37.243 --> 03:50:40.906
So the one thing that is missing at
the moment that might perhaps create

1791556625
03:50:40.907 --> 03:50:45.042
some of this political space >> For
an increase in defence spending.

4003329191
03:50:45.743 --> 03:50:48.704
And I should have said I was
slightly waylaid by my friend

880728577
03:50:48.705 --> 03:50:51.665
there who who intervened
but to create, to lead and deter.

541103994
03:50:51.666 --> 03:50:53.972
In the Euro-Atlantic
area we're talking about

3549883321
03:50:53.973 --> 03:50:57.389
a 50% increase in defence expenditure,

3882469695
03:50:57.390 --> 03:50:58.645
not 1 or 2 billion here.

3303893289
03:50:58.646 --> 03:51:01.003
We're talking about a 50%
increase in defence.

2571939976
03:51:01.004 --> 03:51:01.957
That is the scale.

2241284407
03:51:01.958 --> 03:51:05.148
I won't if that's OK because
we're short on time.

897014873
03:51:05.149 --> 03:51:09.058
That is the sort of scale
that we're talking about.

1615917313
03:51:09.059 --> 03:51:11.644
And perhaps to create the political space

431161696
03:51:11.645 --> 03:51:13.351
to make some of those trade offs,

1175018314
03:51:13.352 --> 03:51:16.593
because that is a huge amount of money.

36590722
03:51:16.594 --> 03:51:19.391
That's Â£30 billion extra
every single year.

3380203051
03:51:19.392 --> 03:51:23.053
We need to have this national conversation
on defence that was announced

1982401038
03:51:23.054 --> 03:51:28.190
in the Strategic Defence Review,
but has been notable by its absence.

1963634567
03:51:28.191 --> 03:51:30.097
So that's why, together with the hon.

347500637
03:51:30.098 --> 03:51:32.253
Member for Macclesfield and for Spelthorne

464051519
03:51:32.254 --> 03:51:34.896
and for Field Marshal
Richards in the other place,

1448842694
03:51:34.897 --> 03:51:38.202
we have formed the APPG on rearmament

2570554514
03:51:38.203 --> 03:51:40.941
and we hope to raise public awareness,

2082980246
03:51:40.942 --> 03:51:42.999
not just of the threats, because I think

282225738
03:51:43.000 --> 03:51:46.186
the public understand
the threats that we face,

1320733552
03:51:46.187 --> 03:51:48.194
but of the the diminishing, the lack of

937156323
03:51:48.740 --> 03:51:51.096
and diminishing capability
in the UK military.

740276135
03:51:51.097 --> 03:51:55.595
I recently went to a school in my
constituency and I was talking with

3243918808
03:51:55.596 --> 03:51:58.956
sixth formers and and I've asked
this question in several schools,

3230385823
03:51:58.957 --> 03:52:02.400
since they all assume we have
a fleet of about 50 or 100 ships,

2641100876
03:52:02.401 --> 03:52:05.990
when I tell them that we
have, what is it now?

3125959118
03:52:05.991 --> 03:52:08.396
14 frigates and destroyers,
surface combatants.

843832838
03:52:08.699 --> 03:52:09.601
They are shocked.

1331884873
03:52:09.602 --> 03:52:13.750
The general public does not know
the state of the British military,

2894269097
03:52:13.751 --> 03:52:17.346
and it is entirely commensurate
with the threat that we face.

3267365939
03:52:18.735 --> 03:52:20.589
Madam Deputy Speaker, in conclusion,

1914624389
03:52:20.590 --> 03:52:25.298
because time is very short, our
military is a paper tiger.

133566818
03:52:25.299 --> 03:52:27.557
Sooner or later we're
going to be found out.

1578899934
03:52:27.737 --> 03:52:31.687
And when we're found out and
the battlegroup in Estonia is overrun

2266273297
03:52:31.688 --> 03:52:36.447
or an aircraft carrier is sunk,
Suez will pale in insignificance.

122099773
03:52:36.448 --> 03:52:41.404
This King's Speech falls far
short of what required.

823890516
03:52:41.405 --> 03:52:41.906
>> Order!

2720755545
03:52:43.743 --> 03:52:44.093
Order!

1090143781
03:52:44.094 --> 03:52:45.899
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

1192035700
03:52:46.740 --> 03:52:50.738
My belief in the importance of national
defence is rooted in a single,

474716920
03:52:50.739 --> 03:52:52.695
simple idea that the United Kingdom is

553128404
03:52:52.696 --> 03:52:55.285
a nation inherently worth defending,

3283436966
03:52:55.286 --> 03:52:57.241
not because of tradition or nostalgia,

666025424
03:52:57.242 --> 03:53:02.742
but because of the values of decency,
respect, hard work and community,

2027701127
03:53:02.743 --> 03:53:05.296
which continue to define our society

3065618533
03:53:05.297 --> 03:53:07.404
and which can never be taken for granted.

3335193096
03:53:07.703 --> 03:53:10.009
Sadly, these values are
not universally held,

1541117377
03:53:10.010 --> 03:53:11.866
and when we look beyond our borders,

3641217741
03:53:11.867 --> 03:53:14.339
we see a world that is
increasingly dangerous,

2248189876
03:53:14.340 --> 03:53:19.401
worryingly unpredictable,
and more divided than I can remember.

1221054151
03:53:19.402 --> 03:53:19.802
That's.

1091803959
03:53:19.803 --> 03:53:22.861
That is why I welcome this
government's steadfast commitment

2581987001
03:53:22.862 --> 03:53:24.966
to improving Britain's defence readiness,

1971075236
03:53:24.967 --> 03:53:29.394
both through its pledge to increase
defence spending to 2.5% of GDP,

1348169544
03:53:29.395 --> 03:53:32.041
and through the various measures outlined

1725211784
03:53:32.042 --> 03:53:33.696
in the Strategic Defence Review.

1034483810
03:53:34.739 --> 03:53:38.602
But, Madam Deputy Speaker,
the scale of the of the challenges

4123615284
03:53:38.603 --> 03:53:43.199
we face today is unprecedented
and our job is to meet them.

2927014538
03:53:43.200 --> 03:53:45.906
Our approach to boosting
Britain's defence readiness,

3943233841
03:53:45.907 --> 03:53:49.297
however, cannot be focussed
on spending alone.

609429876
03:53:49.298 --> 03:53:51.806
Instead, we need to think
about how we strengthen

383934134
03:53:51.807 --> 03:53:54.643
the industries that support
our military capability,

2287213586
03:53:54.644 --> 03:53:57.145
whether that's by streamlining procurement

1759781409
03:53:57.146 --> 03:54:00.189
or empowering defence focussed

139705513
03:54:00.190 --> 03:54:06.334
SMEs to better respond to global
Apologies, I will conflicts.

1020611475
03:54:06.335 --> 03:54:08.993
Apologies, I will not give
way because I'm conscious

3280870379
03:54:08.994 --> 03:54:11.152
that I want colleagues to sort of come in.

4221721724
03:54:11.153 --> 03:54:11.704
Very good.

90645533
03:54:11.705 --> 03:54:15.742
All too often we hear
from SMEs in the defence

3864835413
03:54:15.743 --> 03:54:18.189
sector that access to funding is limited,

618731877
03:54:18.190 --> 03:54:20.045
slow moving and difficult to secure.

4093401476
03:54:20.046 --> 03:54:22.253
And all too often we
see innovative British

1408193998
03:54:24.743 --> 03:54:26.949
companies set up
or even relocate overseas.

2905302174
03:54:26.950 --> 03:54:29.396
Take Ballistic Dynamics, for example.

3797312804
03:54:29.397 --> 03:54:32.895
An SME that is passionate about
boosting the UK's defence

3282612870
03:54:32.896 --> 03:54:35.748
capability but whose founders
report facing structural

3128522920
03:54:35.749 --> 03:54:40.258
barriers such as a lack of
consistent funding opportunities

3640340540
03:54:41.739 --> 03:54:43.893
and frustratingly opaque tender processes.

1357260803
03:54:43.894 --> 03:54:45.544
In these troubled.

2940091292
03:54:45.545 --> 03:54:48.703
In these troubling times when our
adversaries are increasingly

2437848646
03:54:48.704 --> 03:54:52.199
bold in their challenges to our stability,

1272933848
03:54:52.200 --> 03:54:54.944
Home-grown industries
will be a key component

3072762451
03:54:54.945 --> 03:54:57.494
of what we are calling our pre-war phase,

3674553673
03:54:57.495 --> 03:54:59.151
or in some cases, our grey zone.

2716617008
03:55:00.745 --> 03:55:04.738
That pre-war phase must include
the full utilisation of our

2000613006
03:55:04.739 --> 03:55:07.500
highly trained and highly
disciplined reserve forces,

1800510641
03:55:07.501 --> 03:55:10.641
who are too often undervalued
in defence planning.

1981619101
03:55:10.642 --> 03:55:13.696
I'm glad to see this
government's efforts to improve

605434355
03:55:13.697 --> 03:55:16.347
the recruitment process for reservists,

1340919288
03:55:16.348 --> 03:55:20.244
and would encourage even greater
investment in the facilities,

2545070203
03:55:20.245 --> 03:55:23.745
institutions and training
that supports them.

3606538931
03:55:23.746 --> 03:55:27.056
I also appreciate the focus on
the reserve forces more generally,

1578015244
03:55:27.057 --> 03:55:29.953
but it has to be noted that
the very limited reference

2500687984
03:55:29.954 --> 03:55:35.140
to the active reserve forces
within the SDR is causing concern

3242297385
03:55:35.141 --> 03:55:38.247
among some sections of
the Armed Forces community.

2591933121
03:55:38.248 --> 03:55:41.239
The strategic reserves as
a concept is seductive

1080612562
03:55:41.240 --> 03:55:44.394
but relies upon many
optimistic assumptions.

1821031556
03:55:44.395 --> 03:55:48.047
But to be realistically relied
upon as part of any defence plan.

1339037628
03:55:48.048 --> 03:55:53.197
Whereas the active reserves
exist now preparing

2496827789
03:55:53.198 --> 03:55:55.645
preparing the United
Kingdom for the potential

443085932
03:55:55.646 --> 03:55:59.996
future conflict is
a monumental task and will

2712862758
03:55:59.997 --> 03:56:02.352
require collaboration
throughout Parliament.

1033741066
03:56:02.353 --> 03:56:05.848
I urge members across all
benches of this House to work

3299193135
03:56:05.849 --> 03:56:08.954
together to protect
the security of the country,

2108741389
03:56:08.955 --> 03:56:12.145
its citizens and our shared values.

955441027
03:56:12.146 --> 03:56:12.998
Thank you again.

3670454841
03:56:12.999 --> 03:56:14.202
>> For Alec Shelbrooke.

974754177
03:56:14.747 --> 03:56:16.552
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

4004473508
03:56:16.553 --> 03:56:19.614
And may I say it's a real pleasure
to follow the honourable,

3456399671
03:56:20.743 --> 03:56:23.299
gallant gentleman from
Southend East and Rochford.

3433946596
03:56:24.744 --> 03:56:26.800
He made some very important points there

597227684
03:56:26.801 --> 03:56:28.806
about being prepared and the importance

1915111430
03:56:28.807 --> 03:56:31.995
of the reserve and and that
actually, Madam Deputy Speaker,

1368947929
03:56:31.996 --> 03:56:36.097
what I wanted to focus on this
afternoon is what the actual

13875354
03:56:36.098 --> 03:56:38.707
threats are to this country
as we stand here today,

3542476212
03:56:38.708 --> 03:56:41.146
because I think that it,
to a certain extent,

2189442024
03:56:41.147 --> 03:56:45.748
gets overlooked at the threats
we face on a day to day basis.

859407772
03:56:45.749 --> 03:56:49.800
I think a lot of people think
a Russian invasion of this country

1394026383
03:56:49.801 --> 03:56:53.201
would look like any sort of
war, missile bombs coming down.

109751306
03:56:53.202 --> 03:56:55.800
I think there's a long, long way that goes

3241470403
03:56:55.801 --> 03:56:58.248
forward before you get to that space.

3556983592
03:56:58.249 --> 03:57:05.143
And in fact, I think we are in many
ways already at war with Russia.

2271335538
03:57:05.144 --> 03:57:06.699
Let's not forget that in 2017,

4279736748
03:57:06.700 --> 03:57:10.261
Russia launched a chemical
weapon attack on this country.

4038223736
03:57:10.262 --> 03:57:13.401
And if it hadn't been for
favourable weather conditions,

3668061938
03:57:13.402 --> 03:57:17.148
it had the potential to
kill thousands of people.

49866691
03:57:17.149 --> 03:57:20.493
And we must ask ourselves
in those circumstances,

2026723342
03:57:20.494 --> 03:57:22.499
would that have triggered article five?

2068955572
03:57:23.743 --> 03:57:26.452
Because conversations I've
had in my role in the NATO

1754424762
03:57:26.453 --> 03:57:29.143
parliamentary assembly at
the North Atlantic Council

90406821
03:57:29.144 --> 03:57:33.200
is that the general thought is that
would have triggered article five,

1333089502
03:57:33.201 --> 03:57:34.906
whether it was accidental or not.

3878309931
03:57:34.907 --> 03:57:38.067
A chemical weapon attack of one
of the most deadliest chemical

576567475
03:57:38.068 --> 03:57:40.626
weapons in the world was
launched on this country.

4229060757
03:57:40.627 --> 03:57:44.255
And these are often wrapped up
in things called hybrid warfare.

4085529781
03:57:44.743 --> 03:57:47.502
And let me just outline really
what hybrid warfare is.

4009509929
03:57:47.503 --> 03:57:52.147
I mean, yes, there are cyber attacks,
which I'll come back to sabotage,

4158048491
03:57:52.148 --> 03:57:55.608
which we see across Europe,
arson, vandalism, terrorism.

1901084850
03:57:55.609 --> 03:57:58.749
When we see these destructive
acts which are taking

1769203050
03:57:58.750 --> 03:58:01.005
place on railway networks
throughout Europe,

3240829306
03:58:01.006 --> 03:58:03.698
that almost certainly is
coming from the Russians.

3104437116
03:58:03.699 --> 03:58:06.657
And of course, I've mentioned
the chemical weapon attacks.

1437686965
03:58:06.658 --> 03:58:09.403
And it's not the only example
of the assassination

822315776
03:58:09.404 --> 03:58:11.611
attempts that take place
on this very soil.

3069496619
03:58:11.612 --> 03:58:14.218
And despite efforts of
government, all governments,

2838792399
03:58:14.219 --> 03:58:17.947
and all to be praised for trying
to crack down on malign finance,

1043075625
03:58:17.948 --> 03:58:19.152
we know it takes place.

3506124726
03:58:19.153 --> 03:58:23.649
But perhaps one of the things which
people don't realise is taking

3743623471
03:58:23.650 --> 03:58:28.199
place in a day to day basis
is information manipulation,

3935138785
03:58:28.200 --> 03:58:31.158
cognitive warfare, that
the Russians are brilliant at this

2363400170
03:58:31.159 --> 03:58:35.106
and they are well embedded in
this as well are the Chinese.

4009976257
03:58:35.748 --> 03:58:38.055
And it starts when we've
all described people

1112224566
03:58:38.056 --> 03:58:41.160
who go down the rabbit holes of,

2945142150
03:58:41.161 --> 03:58:42.816
of social media or the internet,

1128412522
03:58:42.817 --> 03:58:47.555
but that's where it starts, that
they're monitoring people's clicks.

4153905360
03:58:47.556 --> 03:58:49.900
They're monitoring what it is.

2623101480
03:58:49.901 --> 03:58:51.256
You first of all, look at,

419750705
03:58:51.257 --> 03:58:54.251
they're building a psychological
profile of what you are.

1824802700
03:58:55.743 --> 03:58:59.593
And then they're identifying your
psychological vulnerabilities.

2661794866
03:58:59.594 --> 03:59:02.655
They then feed that line and why
are they feeding that line?

375645227
03:59:02.656 --> 03:59:05.301
They're feeding that line
because they're trying to

167954699
03:59:05.302 --> 03:59:08.958
get this country amongst
lots of other countries,

3570088144
03:59:08.959 --> 03:59:12.448
to not really see the need
for us to invest in defence.

3712051172
03:59:12.450 --> 03:59:15.548
And therefore, and I'm sure most people

2920395699
03:59:15.549 --> 03:59:17.548
in this chamber will have first hand

144576385
03:59:17.549 --> 03:59:21.248
experience of people saying to them that

183563955
03:59:21.249 --> 03:59:23.054
the war in Ukraine is NATO's fault,

2017591841
03:59:25.748 --> 03:59:28.155
and it is Ukraine's fault
that they represented

3720487332
03:59:28.748 --> 03:59:31.055
a threat to Russia,
and Russia had no choice.

730651038
03:59:31.057 --> 03:59:32.311
Let me remind the House.

1042596114
03:59:32.312 --> 03:59:35.147
And to the wider public,
the only threat that Russia

2442182280
03:59:35.148 --> 03:59:39.911
felt was when the people of Ukraine said,

872668115
03:59:39.912 --> 03:59:42.700
we don't want a dictatorial
president anymore.

4137042193
03:59:42.701 --> 03:59:44.857
In the Purple Revolution in February 2014.

389552655
03:59:44.858 --> 03:59:46.564
And they booted him out and said,

2706344466
03:59:46.565 --> 03:59:49.608
we don't want to look to Moscow,
we want to look to Europe,

975554452
03:59:49.608 --> 03:59:52.197
because that's where
they have the freedoms

1432995625
03:59:52.197 --> 03:59:53.804
of choice that we want to have.

176986246
03:59:53.804 --> 03:59:56.951
That is where Russia saw
that as a threat that they

3911177896
03:59:56.952 --> 03:59:59.899
couldn't let happen
and immediately invaded Crimea.

2350201688
03:59:59.900 --> 04:00:02.703
And it is the shame to all of us that that

2183993739
04:00:02.704 --> 04:00:07.448
wasn't taken at the warning at the time.

1408907668
04:00:07.450 --> 04:00:09.258
And indeed, my right hon.

667663648
04:00:09.259 --> 04:00:11.215
Friend the Member for New Forest East,

3875902397
04:00:11.215 --> 04:00:14.427
who I'm once again very pleased
that he spoke before me because

1114139778
04:00:14.428 --> 04:00:16.835
he brings such wide
experience to these issues,

2908436215
04:00:16.836 --> 04:00:20.249
spoke very widely on
that issue at the time.

1810106056
04:00:20.250 --> 04:00:24.448
But he also makes the point
that the money we were

3688228166
04:00:24.450 --> 04:00:27.197
spending back in the 80s are huge figures,

1860591099
04:00:27.197 --> 04:00:29.206
and that's the point we have to get to.

13460081
04:00:29.744 --> 04:00:31.802
This is what we have to tell the public,

3453785098
04:00:31.803 --> 04:00:35.155
recognise the threats we are
under, recognise that today.

2549474083
04:00:37.704 --> 04:00:39.760
Marks and Spencers have announced a Â£131

3911440656
04:00:39.761 --> 04:00:42.151
million loss on their cyber attack.

841290980
04:00:42.152 --> 04:00:45.105
People can see things
but they can't see things.

2674856589
04:00:45.106 --> 04:00:48.606
They could see the empty
shelves of Marks and Spencers,

2886169626
04:00:48.607 --> 04:00:51.201
so they went to Sainsbury's or Morrisons.

1748767183
04:00:51.202 --> 04:00:56.108
They didn't see that a cyber
attack had emptied their shelves.

526043962
04:00:56.108 --> 04:01:02.450
They don't see that we make
a mistake in the NHS on an upgrade of

3682991198
04:01:02.451 --> 04:01:05.800
software and knock it out for
24 hours a couple of years ago.

2738130278
04:01:05.801 --> 04:01:07.656
These are the threats it represents.

2820040424
04:01:07.657 --> 04:01:11.197
So when we look at
and we say we are going to

2768115101
04:01:11.198 --> 04:01:13.507
have to cut other budgets
to pay for defence,

2319630185
04:01:13.508 --> 04:01:18.001
that is probably the most unpopular
thing you can say to a public.

1725666163
04:01:18.003 --> 04:01:23.054
But the services that people want
that money spent on will be gone.

2832564896
04:01:23.055 --> 04:01:25.504
They will not work.

1512972847
04:01:25.505 --> 04:01:27.360
And probably the biggest threat that

588172251
04:01:27.361 --> 04:01:29.218
will happen in the first 24 hours of

3734507558
04:01:29.219 --> 04:01:31.376
any attack is knocking out the power grid,

3047771166
04:01:31.376 --> 04:01:33.650
knocking out the power system.

693513014
04:01:33.651 --> 04:01:37.256
There is embedded cyber
technology in a lot of areas,

1648835685
04:01:37.257 --> 04:01:39.968
and we have to make sure
that we can deal with these.

4237074287
04:01:39.969 --> 04:01:43.712
Now, cyber warfare has to be
a whole of society approach.

4039198832
04:01:43.713 --> 04:01:47.108
Governments cannot do it on their own.

2708707917
04:01:47.108 --> 04:01:51.104
They need companies like JCB, like
sorry, like Jaguar, Land Rover,

2090609631
04:01:51.105 --> 04:01:53.807
like co-op to be able
to protect those areas.

1344610279
04:01:54.751 --> 04:01:57.260
But the point I wanted to
really get across today

1465031195
04:01:57.261 --> 04:01:59.704
is this cost an enormous amount of money.

307371549
04:01:59.705 --> 04:02:04.504
And the best way, and we know this,
and the phrase is old and well used,

4112681061
04:02:04.505 --> 04:02:07.317
but the best way to have
a peace is to prepare for war,

2923558960
04:02:07.318 --> 04:02:09.652
and you have to have the credible threats.

147714422
04:02:09.653 --> 04:02:14.403
And we have to spend huge
amounts of money now at

3185347384
04:02:14.404 --> 04:02:18.604
the very slightest
deviation from our policy.

813073760
04:02:18.605 --> 04:02:20.260
I don't like percentages of GDP.

215121600
04:02:20.261 --> 04:02:21.665
I think they're a nonsense.

3506001274
04:02:21.666 --> 04:02:22.919
I think it's ridiculous.

3425319129
04:02:22.920 --> 04:02:27.804
When NATO went there, we talk about
what we were spending in the 80s.

2579314171
04:02:27.804 --> 04:02:30.264
I remind people that
the 2% of GDP was something

1494421294
04:02:30.265 --> 04:02:32.197
that came about in this century.

1936594901
04:02:32.198 --> 04:02:34.458
When we look at the GDP
figures of the past,

3846162001
04:02:35.932 --> 04:02:37.688
it's because that is what it cost.

3582301571
04:02:37.689 --> 04:02:40.409
So I urge the government
look carefully at what

694602563
04:02:40.410 --> 04:02:44.406
we're saying about
reducing the welfare bill.

1121108050
04:02:44.407 --> 04:02:47.702
Look what Lord Robertson
said about the welfare bill.

2531367257
04:02:47.703 --> 04:02:50.251
These threats are real.

78215680
04:02:50.253 --> 04:02:51.005
They are real.

971511080
04:02:51.006 --> 04:02:53.954
Today, we have to have
the deterrents in place

393389285
04:02:53.955 --> 04:02:56.753
that just simply doesn't
make it worthwhile.

744071483
04:02:56.754 --> 04:02:58.861
But it costs an enormous amount of money.

329360715
04:02:58.862 --> 04:03:02.103
And that cognitive warfare that is taking

4149242270
04:03:02.104 --> 04:03:03.760
place on a daily basis is making

4103115910
04:03:03.761 --> 04:03:08.007
the citizens of this country not
recognise why we need to do that.

4061549695
04:03:08.008 --> 04:03:11.101
It's a brave decision,
but as we've made clear,

4169265604
04:03:11.102 --> 04:03:17.054
we would support the government
if they take that brave decision.

2748452710
04:03:17.054 --> 04:03:17.304
Yes.

833231732
04:03:17.305 --> 04:03:20.117
>> And on a six minute time
limit, I call David Taylor.

220954006
04:03:20.118 --> 04:03:21.923
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker,

1656404275
04:03:21.924 --> 04:03:24.202
and it's a pleasure to follow the hon.

4069665159
04:03:24.203 --> 04:03:26.007
Member for Wetherby and Shelbrooke,

1260668483
04:03:26.008 --> 04:03:28.917
who I know is a vocal champion
of tackling anti-Semitism,

1604001066
04:03:28.918 --> 04:03:31.829
and that is a topic that I'm
turning to in these remarks.

691958541
04:03:31.830 --> 04:03:34.804
In Tower Hamlets last week,
a young man was filmed

1151610351
04:03:34.805 --> 04:03:38.160
saying most chilling
anti-Semitic words The Jews,

616820507
04:03:38.161 --> 04:03:41.156
you're going to be beheaded
one by one, you dirty Jews!

3112863160
04:03:41.157 --> 04:03:43.213
Now he has been identified and arrested,

1797558676
04:03:43.214 --> 04:03:45.652
and I thank the Met
Police for their action.

3838784228
04:03:45.653 --> 04:03:48.302
And I pick that as just one example of

1904170502
04:03:48.303 --> 04:03:50.158
the crisis we face on anti-Semitism.

3375092909
04:03:50.751 --> 04:03:55.053
From the Golders Green terrorist attack
to the Hatzolah ambulance arson.

2165822667
04:03:55.054 --> 04:03:57.051
These incidents continue to rise.

2762563004
04:03:57.052 --> 04:03:59.007
And what is behind this anti-Semitism?

1697014955
04:03:59.751 --> 04:04:02.208
What radicalises individuals
to act in this way?

1878242604
04:04:02.209 --> 04:04:04.656
And who is responsible for these attacks?

1532624612
04:04:04.657 --> 04:04:04.907
Now?

101721864
04:04:04.908 --> 04:04:08.207
It should not need saying,
but I will spell it out.

1757068330
04:04:08.755 --> 04:04:11.162
Jewish people in the UK
are not responsible for

3391206959
04:04:11.164 --> 04:04:13.605
the actions of the Netanyahu government,

2226461496
04:04:13.606 --> 04:04:19.313
and anti-Semitism did not
start on the 7th of October.

4118864266
04:04:19.314 --> 04:04:21.406
Israel had not yet begun its operations

1310664524
04:04:21.407 --> 04:04:23.263
in Gaza in response to Hamas attack.

3409902493
04:04:23.264 --> 04:04:26.726
When the deputy leader of the Green
Party filmed a video saying that

3746944233
04:04:26.727 --> 04:04:32.060
people should support the right of
indigenous people to fight back.

343586237
04:04:32.061 --> 04:04:36.157
Anti-Semitism is often
called the oldest hatred.

1760352846
04:04:36.158 --> 04:04:38.365
Now I welcome His Majesty
the King specific

2884424991
04:04:38.366 --> 04:04:40.371
mention of anti-Semitism in the speech,

3836849890
04:04:40.372 --> 04:04:43.983
and the need to take urgent action
to ensure all communities feel safe.

2442534346
04:04:43.985 --> 04:04:46.442
I welcome the commitment
that the Prime Minister

481412479
04:04:46.443 --> 04:04:49.452
himself has shown in
tackling antisemitism,

2080303246
04:04:49.453 --> 04:04:51.661
both in my own party
but in government too,

3634280174
04:04:51.661 --> 04:04:55.322
including the recent summit in Downing
Street with the Jewish community.

1984010090
04:04:55.322 --> 04:04:57.730
I further welcome the Â£25
million of additional

1228014393
04:04:57.731 --> 04:05:00.751
funding to help protect
Jewish communities,

1855434057
04:05:00.753 --> 04:05:02.809
bringing the total to nearly 60 million.

1809829782
04:05:02.810 --> 04:05:05.858
Now, I agree with the Board
of Deputies who call for

761581777
04:05:05.858 --> 04:05:09.057
an end to the incitement at
pro-Palestinian protests,

4201686391
04:05:09.058 --> 04:05:12.510
where anti-Semitic hate speech
is frequently taking place,

4080530164
04:05:12.511 --> 04:05:16.256
including the use of
public order powers to

416554069
04:05:16.257 --> 04:05:18.362
restrict and ban marches where necessary.

3344988404
04:05:18.363 --> 04:05:20.958
If we look at the last
weekend as one example,

3191920763
04:05:20.959 --> 04:05:24.355
speakers from one of the March organisers,

1491410056
04:05:24.356 --> 04:05:28.664
Palestinian Forum in Britain, told
the crowd Israel is a Zionist cancer.

703142241
04:05:28.665 --> 04:05:31.473
Meanwhile, across London, at
the other far right march,

742365283
04:05:31.474 --> 04:05:33.710
a banner was proudly displayed that said

1672287320
04:05:33.711 --> 04:05:35.906
end the Zionist occupation of Britain.

1124825515
04:05:35.907 --> 04:05:39.118
Perhaps they could have
saved the taxpayer the Â£4.5

3637005467
04:05:39.119 --> 04:05:42.860
million policing Bill by combining
their marches together.

1158297602
04:05:42.861 --> 04:05:44.968
But let's be clear there is another major

2228280451
04:05:44.969 --> 04:05:47.254
driver of antisemitism in this country,

3619741756
04:05:47.255 --> 04:05:51.553
and that is the Islamist regime in Iran.

1542453932
04:05:51.554 --> 04:05:53.960
The group HIYIYI has
claimed responsibility for

35665884
04:05:53.961 --> 04:05:56.166
the ambulance arson
attack, amongst others.

785865605
04:05:56.167 --> 04:05:58.273
The US Department of Justice now believes

1852705486
04:05:58.274 --> 04:05:59.880
that it was a front designed to

1189738438
04:05:59.881 --> 04:06:05.205
carry out terrorist attacks at
the behest of the IRGC and its proxies.

708576434
04:06:05.206 --> 04:06:07.011
Meanwhile, we have Iran's press TV,

1091856213
04:06:07.012 --> 04:06:09.561
as well as their Spanish
mouthpiece Hispan TV.

4281804477
04:06:09.562 --> 04:06:12.660
Their UK based show
Palestine Declassified,

3948594221
04:06:12.661 --> 04:06:15.567
has regularly platformed
conspiracy theories and targeted

4281562203
04:06:15.759 --> 04:06:18.616
Jewish schools in Britain
and charities and individuals.

1164548130
04:06:18.617 --> 04:06:21.979
And I repeat my call for financial
sanctions to be placed on them.

4154895931
04:06:21.980 --> 04:06:24.996
As the US, Australia, Canada
and the EU have as this

2765170672
04:06:24.997 --> 04:06:27.912
would close a legal
loophole that currently

611880309
04:06:27.914 --> 04:06:30.121
allows them to pay UK
nationals and operate

3611175653
04:06:30.122 --> 04:06:32.325
through intermediaries
without restriction.

167270687
04:06:32.326 --> 04:06:34.433
Now connected to them is Red Media World,

1571886254
04:06:34.434 --> 04:06:36.692
a company with links to
Iran that the Sunday

2046257319
04:06:36.693 --> 04:06:38.948
Telegraph just reported
is using the skilled

1051221439
04:06:38.950 --> 04:06:40.904
worker visa scheme completely legally,

3570233657
04:06:40.905 --> 04:06:44.165
and I hope that the Foreign Office
will revoke this immediately,

3945461347
04:06:44.166 --> 04:06:47.427
as well as track an individual
that came through on that scheme.

3315728309
04:06:47.428 --> 04:06:49.535
Then there is the issue of charities that

941939387
04:06:49.536 --> 04:06:51.592
the Shawcross review has linked to Iran.

3315047805
04:06:51.593 --> 04:06:52.847
In the interest of time.

41455613
04:06:52.848 --> 04:06:56.362
I will not repeat what I've said
before, but I do agree with the hon.

2751997122
04:06:56.363 --> 04:06:59.924
Member for Bristol North East in
calling for the Charity Commission to

1673782547
04:06:59.925 --> 04:07:03.386
have extra resource to go after these
charities and close them down.

2316998783
04:07:03.387 --> 04:07:06.346
Now I have, along with other
colleagues across this House,

1190047745
04:07:06.347 --> 04:07:09.155
been campaigning for
the prescribing IRGC for some time

1917327379
04:07:09.156 --> 04:07:12.265
and therefore delighted to see
the announcement in the King's

2395244194
04:07:12.266 --> 04:07:14.523
Speech of the Tackling
State Threats Bill to

2675499107
04:07:14.524 --> 04:07:16.731
give the Home Secretary
new powers to clamp

1821527219
04:07:16.732 --> 04:07:18.887
on foreign states and organisations posing

4190320211
04:07:18.888 --> 04:07:20.643
a threat to our national security.

3086584891
04:07:20.644 --> 04:07:23.503
And I hope that goes alongside
further and faster action

3605355642
04:07:23.504 --> 04:07:25.813
to tackle the Iranian
threat to us in the UK,

904780930
04:07:25.814 --> 04:07:27.972
just as we have tried to do against Putin,

3460873916
04:07:27.973 --> 04:07:30.360
against their vast
property empire in London,

3950865056
04:07:30.361 --> 04:07:33.067
against their spreading of
hatred and disinformation,

4281200537
04:07:33.068 --> 04:07:36.009
on social, on social media designed to

2706792478
04:07:36.010 --> 04:07:39.119
sow discord and division in the UK.

1127084416
04:07:39.120 --> 04:07:42.054
And are we robustly
analysing companies House

1967584996
04:07:42.055 --> 04:07:43.861
register to ensure that Bank Melli.

2645375199
04:07:43.862 --> 04:07:48.919
I hope I pronounce this wrong and its
many subsidiaries are not dodging

4213139623
04:07:48.920 --> 04:07:52.908
sanctions simply by changing
their name at company House.

2919691391
04:07:52.909 --> 04:07:56.113
And should we also be
talking more about the VA?

4144623874
04:07:56.114 --> 04:08:00.611
J a Iran's intelligence agency
and its activities in the UK?

2076077969
04:08:00.612 --> 04:08:02.717
Now, in conclusion, Madam Deputy Speaker,

3048749119
04:08:02.718 --> 04:08:05.062
I also urge my government to ensure that

2022500595
04:08:05.063 --> 04:08:08.179
as soon as this new law is passed,

4030064476
04:08:08.179 --> 04:08:10.486
this new legislation is
immediately acted on.

2245318675
04:08:11.760 --> 04:08:14.117
By which I mean that our
intelligence officers

3115530605
04:08:14.118 --> 04:08:16.474
fully understand
the powers available to them,

3483397781
04:08:16.755 --> 04:08:21.205
not only by this new
legislation, but by existing

3063300095
04:08:21.206 --> 04:08:23.511
legislation that we've
always already passed.

767524927
04:08:23.755 --> 04:08:28.657
I had the pleasure this week
of hosting Jonathan Hackett,

69000588
04:08:28.658 --> 04:08:31.415
a marine veteran and an expert
on counterintelligence,

2755547292
04:08:31.416 --> 04:08:34.010
counterintelligence,
and intelligence operations,

1756877186
04:08:34.011 --> 04:08:36.820
who made the point that often,
sometimes on the ground,

313786548
04:08:36.821 --> 04:08:39.228
some of our intelligence
officers are not fully

1495680803
04:08:39.229 --> 04:08:41.185
aware of the powers available to them,

1897287720
04:08:41.186 --> 04:08:43.444
and it's crucial that
they are both aware of

1908508174
04:08:43.445 --> 04:08:45.753
the powers that they can
take to take action,

4218887509
04:08:45.755 --> 04:08:50.258
and also have the resources
and capabilities to do so.

3596744219
04:08:50.259 --> 04:08:52.064
Thank you very much, Max Wilkinson.

3104547189
04:08:52.065 --> 04:08:55.108
Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

4038772065
04:08:55.108 --> 04:08:58.670
I represent the constituency of
Cheltenham, which is the home of Gchq,

188378713
04:08:58.759 --> 04:09:02.210
where thousands of people work
every day to keep us safe.

2892639744
04:09:02.211 --> 04:09:03.162
They work quietly.

1852688963
04:09:03.164 --> 04:09:05.155
They never ask for our thanks.

1704333010
04:09:05.156 --> 04:09:09.418
And in this House, it is right that
we acknowledge that whenever we can.

3300340215
04:09:09.419 --> 04:09:13.565
I strongly agree with
the points that have been made

422813401
04:09:13.566 --> 04:09:16.664
earlier about the urgency
of investment in defence.

2454429834
04:09:16.665 --> 04:09:21.510
And as a member of
the APPG for rearmament,

3451380743
04:09:21.511 --> 04:09:24.363
I would commend
the comments made by my friend,

2403582076
04:09:24.364 --> 04:09:27.267
the Member for Tunbridge
Wells, and I would.

451785286
04:09:27.268 --> 04:09:32.267
I would echo the comments made by
my friend, the Member for Lewes,

2194535111
04:09:32.268 --> 04:09:38.719
about the need to reintegrate with
Europe as soon as we possibly can,

3996301818
04:09:38.720 --> 04:09:42.907
if not on the economy, on
defence reasons alone,

2441065508
04:09:42.908 --> 04:09:46.406
because almost ten years ago this country

3036616458
04:09:46.407 --> 04:09:48.161
voted to leave the European Union.

2131915706
04:09:48.844 --> 04:09:50.751
But it is now clear a decade on that,

1746519371
04:09:50.753 --> 04:09:53.411
whether you voted leave
or whether you voted remain,

2302499725
04:09:53.411 --> 04:09:56.160
you did not get what you voted for.

722506742
04:09:56.161 --> 04:10:00.304
Has Brexit made us wealthier?

900002066
04:10:00.305 --> 04:10:00.506
No.

3931042820
04:10:00.507 --> 04:10:01.811
Has it made us healthier?

2336350786
04:10:01.812 --> 04:10:02.012
No.

306847269
04:10:02.013 --> 04:10:04.321
Has it made it easier
for businesses to grow?

172847590
04:10:04.322 --> 04:10:06.363
As we were told by the Conservatives?

843879006
04:10:06.364 --> 04:10:06.564
No.

2150110098
04:10:06.565 --> 04:10:10.711
Has it lowered our taxes?

933646911
04:10:10.712 --> 04:10:10.911
No.

3769751188
04:10:10.912 --> 04:10:13.409
Has it helped us protect our environment?

827051917
04:10:13.410 --> 04:10:13.610
No.

3615167474
04:10:13.611 --> 04:10:16.555
And the faeces flowing
into our rivers suggests

1623843969
04:10:16.557 --> 04:10:18.763
it strongly has not
helped our environment.

98214587
04:10:18.764 --> 04:10:23.313
Has it helped us run a more effective
immigration and asylum system?

3233359430
04:10:23.314 --> 04:10:23.514
No.

3403734909
04:10:23.515 --> 04:10:25.620
The gangsters, profiting from small boats

2495426389
04:10:25.621 --> 04:10:27.528
are laughing all the way to the bank.

1064939473
04:10:27.529 --> 04:10:31.760
On the subject of today's
debate, has it made us more

138756051
04:10:31.761 --> 04:10:35.810
secure and has it boosted
national resilience?

632172928
04:10:35.811 --> 04:10:36.011
No.

754149014
04:10:36.012 --> 04:10:39.372
And we are now reliant on
an unstable United States run by

3531050152
04:10:39.373 --> 04:10:43.718
an unpredictable leader who many
people now think is mad with

918676172
04:10:44.759 --> 04:10:49.406
a deputy who is intent on fomenting
discontent on our streets,

2644142187
04:10:49.407 --> 04:10:53.064
and who is responsible for
the abject failure of Brexit.

2987647019
04:10:53.065 --> 04:10:56.962
It is certainly not
the people of this country.

431910702
04:10:56.963 --> 04:11:00.576
We all know in this House who is
responsible for the failure of Brexit,

2678106878
04:11:00.577 --> 04:11:03.963
and we all know that they are
currently getting away with it.

2572998287
04:11:03.964 --> 04:11:07.721
But while the rest of us are undeniably
poorer as a result of Brexit,

2290773116
04:11:07.722 --> 04:11:11.464
there are 5 million reasons
why the Reform Party must

1429261956
04:11:11.465 --> 04:11:14.064
keep claiming that it's
been a huge success.

466553365
04:11:14.065 --> 04:11:17.410
We all know what those reasons are.

2717753692
04:11:17.411 --> 04:11:19.416
They are deluded, Madam Deputy Speaker,

1296311145
04:11:19.759 --> 04:11:23.108
and so are their pals in
the Conservative Party.

1594890501
04:11:23.110 --> 04:11:26.772
They must en masse take responsibility
for the fact that this country is

2079952703
04:11:26.773 --> 04:11:32.161
now poorer and it is less secure as
a result of their disastrous Brexit.

696915810
04:11:32.162 --> 04:11:37.662
Now on to the government that our
government today has a responsibility

2942475611
04:11:37.664 --> 04:11:41.476
to be so much bolder in reversing
the damage caused to this country.

3095665219
04:11:41.477 --> 04:11:43.732
Every Labour backbencher
and Ministers knows

1470571042
04:11:43.733 --> 04:11:45.637
that rapid re-integration with Europe

41745923
04:11:45.638 --> 04:11:50.460
is the only way to increase prosperity,
security and boost business too.

1276043776
04:11:50.461 --> 04:11:52.616
Apparently the mayor of Greater Manchester

1392449920
04:11:52.761 --> 04:11:54.568
used to know it, but he's not sure.

1471170893
04:11:54.569 --> 04:11:57.779
For the next few weeks while he
fights that awkward byelection.

3923858100
04:11:57.780 --> 04:11:59.635
The good news, Madam Deputy Speaker,

2250884286
04:11:59.636 --> 04:12:03.246
is that the departed Health secretary
is now wildly pro-European again,

4010861939
04:12:03.247 --> 04:12:05.606
which may or may not have
something to do with

3428420367
04:12:05.607 --> 04:12:07.661
the Manchester mayor's current travails.

1984172315
04:12:07.718 --> 04:12:08.269
Who knows?

281006308
04:12:08.269 --> 04:12:11.278
This moment of national challenge
demanded a King's speech,

2476556279
04:12:11.279 --> 04:12:13.761
offering significant
change to reintegrate with

938215153
04:12:13.762 --> 04:12:16.170
Europe for the sake of
our economy and defence.

148579313
04:12:16.171 --> 04:12:19.871
But regrettably, the Prime Minister
has offered us more of the same.

117876727
04:12:19.872 --> 04:12:21.861
Politics, Madam Deputy Speaker,

2066368197
04:12:21.862 --> 04:12:24.616
is about ideas and
the ideas that inspire me,

296455379
04:12:24.617 --> 04:12:27.025
and those of us on these
benches are liberalism

3513101678
04:12:27.026 --> 04:12:30.162
and internationalism that will not change.

3382272698
04:12:30.164 --> 04:12:35.115
The challenge facing our nation today
can only be met by those ends.

2287851290
04:12:35.116 --> 04:12:39.172
Now at home, communities are
crying out for real empowerment.

991553473
04:12:39.173 --> 04:12:43.566
Yet this government's devolution
agenda delivers only the illusion of

4203540099
04:12:43.567 --> 04:12:47.418
local control to achieve growth,
including in our defence sector,

3671008015
04:12:47.419 --> 04:12:51.213
Whitehall's grip must be loosened
to devolve real power and funding,

4088102106
04:12:51.214 --> 04:12:54.423
not just to distant regional
centres away from our communities,

4139224572
04:12:54.424 --> 04:12:55.678
but to towns and cities.

4172727057
04:12:55.759 --> 04:12:59.517
Towns like my constituency Cheltenham,
which stands ready to help,

2452199437
04:12:59.518 --> 04:13:01.573
supporting the work of Gchq and building

3402383651
04:13:01.575 --> 04:13:03.532
on it at the Golden Valley Cyber Park,

1120615589
04:13:03.533 --> 04:13:05.488
which is supported by this government.

3287158316
04:13:05.489 --> 04:13:08.951
And I welcome that and I commend
the government's decision to do so.

109330522
04:13:08.952 --> 04:13:12.362
The King's speech also ignores
the new reality in British politics.

1622869928
04:13:12.363 --> 04:13:14.873
The two party system of
the red team and the blue

3035185013
04:13:14.874 --> 04:13:16.930
team shouting at each other is now over.

1808446037
04:13:16.932 --> 04:13:20.016
That undermines our ability
to have a thriving economy.

2862698650
04:13:20.017 --> 04:13:23.027
It undermines our ability to
make long term plans to invest

3574022153
04:13:23.028 --> 04:13:26.874
in the long term defence
and security of our country.

4075360046
04:13:26.875 --> 04:13:31.575
And it is a pity that Andy Burnham
has changed his mind on PR.

3103399123
04:13:31.576 --> 04:13:35.087
That makes at least two U-turns
before he's even rejoined this House,

142891229
04:13:35.088 --> 04:13:38.929
but let's hope he does a full
360 when he gets back here now.

1541165268
04:13:38.929 --> 04:13:41.568
This government now faces a stark choice

1374994465
04:13:41.569 --> 04:13:43.371
embrace proportional representation

4272604439
04:13:43.372 --> 04:13:46.031
or usher in a future reform
government propped up by

2708564617
04:13:46.032 --> 04:13:48.590
the Conservatives to give
us more of the same that

406767300
04:13:48.592 --> 04:13:50.749
they gave us before the failure of Brexit,

1425000050
04:13:50.750 --> 04:13:52.906
the lack of security, the failing economy.

3768266707
04:13:52.907 --> 04:13:55.364
Sadly, this King's speech
won't do what's needed

1840181163
04:13:55.365 --> 04:13:57.220
to fix our relationship with Europe,

232501852
04:13:57.221 --> 04:13:59.428
to make us safer or to
empower communities.

94638197
04:13:59.429 --> 04:14:01.967
And it will not change
politics for the better.

1281924796
04:14:01.968 --> 04:14:05.170
It is a crying shame that
with this massive majority,

61731726
04:14:07.727 --> 04:14:10.235
the government has a massive
lack of ambition to.

3475413272
04:14:10.763 --> 04:14:12.568
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

4165329885
04:14:12.569 --> 04:14:16.622
National security should be
the primary duty of every government,

1489149616
04:14:16.759 --> 04:14:18.968
and so I have been
pleased to be present in

2742163590
04:14:19.763 --> 04:14:23.013
this House whilst listening
to the contributions made

3981652759
04:14:23.014 --> 04:14:25.572
on defence readiness as
part of the King's Speech.

2609656370
04:14:25.572 --> 04:14:29.664
The King's Speech highlighted
this government's plan

1170858968
04:14:29.665 --> 04:14:32.564
to create a stronger,
safer and fairer Britain,

644011211
04:14:32.565 --> 04:14:34.571
where the world today is more dangerous

3874833746
04:14:34.572 --> 04:14:36.279
than it has been for a long time,

1700118483
04:14:36.280 --> 04:14:40.063
where too many people are struggling
with the cost of living and young

4023496209
04:14:40.064 --> 04:14:43.965
people are finding employment
prospects particularly difficult.

3710295080
04:14:43.965 --> 04:14:47.464
Last week I had
the privilege of presenting

1113755321
04:14:47.465 --> 04:14:49.269
the award for Overall Apprentice of

81062846
04:14:49.763 --> 04:14:51.920
the year at the Juniper Training Awards in

3929071934
04:14:51.921 --> 04:14:53.875
my constituency of Wolverhampton West.

3423342432
04:14:53.876 --> 04:14:59.063
What struck me at this event was
not simply the talent in the room,

2733457568
04:14:59.064 --> 04:15:00.767
but the determination, resilience

521057941
04:15:00.768 --> 04:15:04.672
and ambition shown by these young people.

2428132112
04:15:04.673 --> 04:15:08.034
They are proof of the potential
that lies within our young people,

722909207
04:15:08.035 --> 04:15:10.394
and we have a duty to
invest in their futures.

641683711
04:15:10.763 --> 04:15:14.414
Juniper training is
an example of an organisation

2039407002
04:15:14.415 --> 04:15:15.667
which provides credible,

4058226059
04:15:15.668 --> 04:15:17.865
credible alternative to traditional school

3731479669
04:15:17.866 --> 04:15:20.622
or college pathways for young people who

2529244312
04:15:20.623 --> 04:15:23.816
would otherwise be at risk
of not being in employment,

113182384
04:15:23.817 --> 04:15:24.969
education or training.

1283838109
04:15:26.763 --> 04:15:30.468
Their programs offer not only
qualifications for young people,

559361717
04:15:30.469 --> 04:15:33.364
but confidence, resilience
and a sense of purpose.

3934151632
04:15:33.365 --> 04:15:37.322
Providing a route into secure employment.

1863543567
04:15:37.323 --> 04:15:39.480
Our young people deserve our full support,

1286422637
04:15:39.481 --> 04:15:41.338
which is why I am pleased to welcome

3146369656
04:15:41.339 --> 04:15:43.722
the Government's New Deal for young people

259069234
04:15:43.723 --> 04:15:45.914
as part of our wider Youth Guarantee.

624782633
04:15:45.915 --> 04:15:49.664
I'm especially proud that
my constituency sits

3441690508
04:15:49.665 --> 04:15:52.021
within the new West
Midlands Trailblazer area,

306596774
04:15:52.022 --> 04:15:54.263
where young people are already beginning

1577242722
04:15:54.264 --> 04:15:55.968
to benefit from these initiatives

496739491
04:15:55.969 --> 04:16:01.319
through funding provided by
the Get Britain Working programme,

2969989578
04:16:01.320 --> 04:16:04.464
more than 800 young people
across the West Midlands have

219460295
04:16:04.465 --> 04:16:07.273
already taken their first
steps onto the career ladder,

889619930
04:16:07.274 --> 04:16:10.565
with a further 1200
expected to benefit from

3400841304
04:16:10.566 --> 04:16:15.771
the Â£10 million committed
so far by the end of 2027.

650828152
04:16:15.772 --> 04:16:19.129
In Wolverhampton itself, our youth
guaranteed trailblazer proposal

332556228
04:16:19.130 --> 04:16:24.214
is focussed on structured work
experience and transition support,

434167687
04:16:24.215 --> 04:16:29.213
intervening early to provide
that crucial support.

2991028742
04:16:29.214 --> 04:16:32.217
The Wolves at Work Open
Door programme supports

1721337665
04:16:32.218 --> 04:16:33.871
the Youth Trailblazer initiative

426788801
04:16:33.872 --> 04:16:39.323
and has placed more than 135
residents into work experience,

1336991937
04:16:39.325 --> 04:16:41.482
and more than 50 of these individuals have

3970593300
04:16:41.767 --> 04:16:43.923
already gone on to secure paid employment.

491277652
04:16:46.768 --> 04:16:49.124
Madam Deputy Speaker,
behind these figures lie

4294698773
04:16:49.125 --> 04:16:51.572
a young person whose
life has been changed,

1864324526
04:16:51.572 --> 04:16:58.167
someone who has gained confidence,
stability and hope for the future.

1951110961
04:16:58.168 --> 04:17:02.317
This is an achievement that my City
of Wolverhampton can be proud of.

2708872083
04:17:02.318 --> 04:17:05.875
More broadly, I am proud of
the work that this government is

3920110726
04:17:06.722 --> 04:17:12.070
undertaking nationally to
support young people into work.

4051866418
04:17:12.071 --> 04:17:17.220
The expanded Jobs Guarantee, now set
to support an additional 35,000

4005906642
04:17:17.221 --> 04:17:17.922
young people,

899199720
04:17:17.923 --> 04:17:22.167
will provide vital opportunities
to those on Universal Credit,

1641452027
04:17:22.168 --> 04:17:26.317
whilst helping people to
get back into employment

2093762953
04:17:26.318 --> 04:17:32.764
and thereby reducing the long
term welfare dependency.

560934988
04:17:32.765 --> 04:17:35.019
Moreover, this government
is expanding youth

3210079931
04:17:35.021 --> 04:17:37.278
hubs across the country
to ensure that young

2354948666
04:17:37.279 --> 04:17:42.113
people looking for work
can access that advice

429532934
04:17:42.114 --> 04:17:44.220
and support they need to find employment.

3902470381
04:17:44.221 --> 04:17:51.613
And through a Â£725 million
investment in apprenticeships,

4138315484
04:17:51.614 --> 04:17:53.420
we are backing our small and medium

1035772057
04:17:53.421 --> 04:17:58.516
sized businesses by covering
their full apprenticeship

1850435825
04:17:58.517 --> 04:18:00.171
costs for eligible young people.

381165023
04:18:00.172 --> 04:18:03.232
In doing so, we are also supporting
our businesses to create

1994117167
04:18:04.767 --> 04:18:07.323
the wealth that this country
so desperately needs.

563975078
04:18:07.730 --> 04:18:11.267
Madam Deputy Speaker, this
Labour government is providing

1106183519
04:18:11.268 --> 04:18:13.273
security and control to working people,

45301680
04:18:16.767 --> 04:18:18.774
and I am proud to support that mission.

3994672829
04:18:18.775 --> 04:18:25.314
>> Mark Pritchard.

372366152
04:18:25.315 --> 04:18:27.120
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

1445631679
04:18:27.767 --> 04:18:28.067
What?

1599530904
04:18:28.068 --> 04:18:28.769
Oh thank you.

776113324
04:18:28.771 --> 04:18:33.120
Are you get cheering at the end
rather than the beginning.

816485144
04:18:33.121 --> 04:18:34.174
But I appreciate it.

3775913279
04:18:34.175 --> 04:18:40.576
So, Madam Speaker, can I thank you
for calling me a lovely surprise.

754968056
04:18:40.577 --> 04:18:42.485
Can I pay a tribute to the right hon.

828373258
04:18:42.486 --> 04:18:45.821
Gentleman for Ilford North, who's
not in his place right now,

2451802077
04:18:45.822 --> 04:18:49.619
but I have notified him
that I will be possibly

2741062526
04:18:49.620 --> 04:18:51.173
condemning his leadership bid.

2927212030
04:18:51.771 --> 04:18:55.368
But I want to say I think it
was in 21 years in this House.

153781937
04:18:55.369 --> 04:18:58.820
I think it was one of
the best speeches I've heard.

4181365272
04:18:58.821 --> 04:19:00.829
And we need to hear more from all sides

680814571
04:19:00.830 --> 04:19:02.836
of the House about uniting this nation,

2899036770
04:19:02.837 --> 04:19:05.043
whether the speech
unites the Labour Party,

1584812939
04:19:05.044 --> 04:19:07.300
I'll leave that for
the Labour backbenchers.

947319778
04:19:07.301 --> 04:19:10.110
But certainly at a time of
nationalist talk and extreme

364655285
04:19:10.111 --> 04:19:12.974
talk on the left and
the right of British politics,

4207107115
04:19:12.975 --> 04:19:19.422
we need more people in all parties
to stand up for the common good,

2469346638
04:19:19.423 --> 04:19:23.821
for common purpose, and for
those things that unite us

464022894
04:19:23.822 --> 04:19:27.222
as a country rather than
those who seek to divide us.

3541357430
04:19:27.223 --> 04:19:28.126
I agree with him.

4016270222
04:19:28.126 --> 04:19:31.927
It is the British values that whether
you're from the left or right,

3985329672
04:19:31.928 --> 04:19:35.575
whether you're gay or straight,
whether you're Muslim or Christian,

2183881076
04:19:35.576 --> 04:19:39.727
whether you're enlightened,

2907515711
04:19:39.728 --> 04:19:42.572
educated or some on
certain benches suggest

3643886497
04:19:42.572 --> 04:19:44.227
because you have British values,

1966449650
04:19:44.228 --> 04:19:47.622
that you are not enlightened or educated,

1521408983
04:19:47.623 --> 04:19:51.178
but it is those values that
unite us, whatever our party.

1153229619
04:19:51.179 --> 04:19:54.677
And we all have a responsibility to stand

3497220196
04:19:54.678 --> 04:19:58.076
up and be heard on these issues.

2040001112
04:19:58.077 --> 04:20:00.221
May I also pay tribute?

2813554786
04:20:00.222 --> 04:20:04.372
And he's not again in his
place, but I have emailed his

334976902
04:20:04.373 --> 04:20:07.630
office to pay tribute to
the former health Ministers.

2717377440
04:20:07.631 --> 04:20:09.085
The Member for Ilford North.

3812239446
04:20:09.086 --> 04:20:11.971
Forgive me.

1150736164
04:20:11.972 --> 04:20:12.423
The hon.

2677761352
04:20:12.424 --> 04:20:13.978
Member for Glasgow South West,

757227867
04:20:13.979 --> 04:20:16.880
who has answered more
questions more quickly,

556999902
04:20:16.881 --> 04:20:20.776
more substantively than
any other Ministers.

1695104291
04:20:20.777 --> 04:20:24.794
Again, in the period that I've spent
in this House apart from one other

3215640675
04:20:24.795 --> 04:20:27.925
who went on to be Prime Minister,
and that is the right hon.

1607699936
04:20:27.926 --> 04:20:32.769
Member for Richmond
and wherever it is now.

200225871
04:20:32.771 --> 04:20:35.317
So not Richard Foord, not
Richmond, Yorkshire.

2427212615
04:20:35.318 --> 04:20:38.632
Just to be clear, in
Richmond, Surrey or London,

3489769586
04:20:38.633 --> 04:20:40.971
it's 54 Lib Dem councillors that we.

3332879502
04:20:40.972 --> 04:20:45.318
We know that it's not
the case in Richmond, Yorkshire.

2468760224
04:20:45.319 --> 04:20:46.170
Hopefully never.

1192539327
04:20:46.171 --> 04:20:50.925
But I think my speech has already
gone out of the window, but I.

3677877141
04:20:50.926 --> 04:20:54.928
I know it very well comes
as great, great relief,

1330105358
04:20:54.929 --> 04:20:59.078
but I want to pay tribute to all
of our armed forces on this.

2719405506
04:20:59.079 --> 04:21:03.523
What is today a defence day
for the King's Speech?

303223188
04:21:03.524 --> 04:21:07.123
All of those at RAF Cosford in
my constituency, the largest,

486262016
04:21:07.124 --> 04:21:09.429
second largest RAF base in the world,

4141076149
04:21:09.430 --> 04:21:13.129
all of those at the Royal Irish
Regiment in Clive Barracks

3363146471
04:21:13.130 --> 04:21:18.224
at Ternhill and all of those
within MoD Donnington,

1267959855
04:21:18.225 --> 04:21:22.725
all of them contributing
to our national security.

3503774269
04:21:22.726 --> 04:21:25.985
But as I mentioned earlier, yes,
it's about defence procurement.

2405831388
04:21:25.986 --> 04:21:30.171
Yes, it's about kit and equipment,
but without defence people,

3689296712
04:21:30.172 --> 04:21:31.123
without personnel,

2198169186
