democracy, destabilise the world.

3497035452
04:32:59.780 --> 04:33:02.389
And we've just heard a great
speech before me about

3569628133
04:33:02.390 --> 04:33:06.189
how that's impacting
the streets here in the UK.

1396055804
04:33:06.190 --> 04:33:10.745
So when we're seeing that,
what do they see of the UK?

1990879044
04:33:10.746 --> 04:33:12.301
And I'll back this comment up.

914426386
04:33:13.799 --> 04:33:17.694
They believe many countries
believe we are leaving the room.

1470882686
04:33:17.695 --> 04:33:19.934
We are not standing up anywhere near on

864277979
04:33:19.935 --> 04:33:21.941
the international stage as what we did.

679896116
04:33:21.942 --> 04:33:25.251
And one of my proudest moments on
the NATO parliamentary Assembly

1340666654
04:33:25.253 --> 04:33:29.440
was in 2022 in the Latvian
Parliament cross party.

1300671911
04:33:29.441 --> 04:33:33.641
And I stood there when the defence
Ministers said to the UK and the US,

1070450368
04:33:33.642 --> 04:33:35.894
hold your head up high, you have led

1186885315
04:33:35.896 --> 04:33:38.695
the world in this and we need to follow.

3014747582
04:33:38.696 --> 04:33:40.301
You have funded and you've led.

2240789468
04:33:40.784 --> 04:33:43.394
And that was a real proud
moment in the last month.

462965101
04:33:43.394 --> 04:33:46.154
And I've said this direct
into the Secretary of State.

248209628
04:33:46.155 --> 04:33:50.592
I won't say the country, but a NATO
defence Ministers in the same forum

2790611190
04:33:50.593 --> 04:33:55.444
sat there when I asked the question,
he said, with all due respect,

633270788
04:33:55.445 --> 04:33:58.237
the UK are not leading, they
are not even in the room

2859693228
04:33:58.238 --> 04:34:00.946
and they are not funding
where they were cross-party.

3876471452
04:34:00.947 --> 04:34:04.189
I couldn't disagree with him
and that was one of the saddest

2217574458
04:34:04.190 --> 04:34:09.748
days on NATO parliamentary
assembly of where we sat.

1476864116
04:34:09.749 --> 04:34:10.300
With that.

1336467130
04:34:10.301 --> 04:34:12.638
We need this investment within defence.

3553943000
04:34:12.639 --> 04:34:16.940
We need to clearly chart
a course where we can ensure

384393926
04:34:16.941 --> 04:34:18.999
that we are funding where we need to be,

1478499303
04:34:19.000 --> 04:34:24.141
and I'm doing this out of respect
for the defence Ministers.

4130172279
04:34:24.142 --> 04:34:28.333
I believe there's a credible
set of defence Ministers,

740204471
04:34:28.334 --> 04:34:31.294
but the argument is not currently
being won at the moment.

2404925359
04:34:31.295 --> 04:34:34.303
And where we've dropped in those rankings,

2471273990
04:34:34.304 --> 04:34:37.644
the NATO average is around about
2.76% for defence spending.

2888407785
04:34:37.646 --> 04:34:40.786
And we're arguing around
about 2.4%, give or take.

2779467963
04:34:40.786 --> 04:34:43.036
And actually the argument that it's

2602497795
04:34:43.037 --> 04:34:45.243
the largest sustained
defence funding since

3378605778
04:34:45.787 --> 04:34:49.988
the end of the Cold War is actually
a bit of a mockery, that sentence,

1035598364
04:34:49.989 --> 04:34:55.840
because we're comparing a peacetime
situation to the most unstable

920730800
04:34:55.840 --> 04:34:59.143
geopolitical situation of our
time, they're not comparable.

396765575
04:35:00.787 --> 04:35:04.237
And if you want to look at
the actual facts, in 2019 to 2020,

2750353363
04:35:04.238 --> 04:35:05.994
it went up 0.2%, which is similar.

2877701694
04:35:05.995 --> 04:35:06.245
Now.

2658170000
04:35:06.246 --> 04:35:07.099
I call that out.

412686719
04:35:07.100 --> 04:35:10.043
Then we were united in
the defence Select Committee,

67897296
04:35:10.044 --> 04:35:13.305
where we said that we needed to
fund in the last Parliament six,

2941927502
04:35:13.307 --> 04:35:17.983
seven years ago or six and
a half years ago, when of 3%.

4087707001
04:35:17.985 --> 04:35:19.739
That was the cross-party position.

2076330482
04:35:19.740 --> 04:35:22.493
Then we need to get to that position now.

927810263
04:35:22.494 --> 04:35:24.489
We need our ships funded.

3062144206
04:35:24.490 --> 04:35:25.543
We need more troops.

3260502431
04:35:25.544 --> 04:35:28.704
We need drone warfare, as we've
seen what's happening in Iran,

1094479161
04:35:29.786 --> 04:35:34.304
we must expand our technological
approach to defence,

2525739283
04:35:34.305 --> 04:35:35.911
defence and how we how that is.

2363495984
04:35:35.912 --> 04:35:39.204
Shape is changing and we need
to look at this on a really

3103978815
04:35:39.786 --> 04:35:42.497
serious level to be able to
stand on the world stage.

2914536367
04:35:42.789 --> 04:35:44.894
And our military strength has always been

75246460
04:35:44.896 --> 04:35:47.492
the bedrock of our global soft power.

815723039
04:35:47.493 --> 04:35:52.187
It has given us authority and a platform
to stand up for British values.

755102961
04:35:52.188 --> 04:35:55.790
But on the world stage at
the moment, that is, that is waning.

1799927343
04:35:55.791 --> 04:35:58.184
It is shaking at the moment.

975324540
04:35:58.185 --> 04:36:03.102
And what we're looking at with that,
and I think as we look at this,

3316203961
04:36:03.103 --> 04:36:09.153
as we chart this course, we have to
have a serious response to this now,

984355303
04:36:09.154 --> 04:36:12.340
today, and I'm not interested
what's happened in ten years,

497930347
04:36:12.340 --> 04:36:15.590
20 years, 40 years, because
as we've heard from hon.

1886534728
04:36:15.592 --> 04:36:18.388
Members on all sides, defence funding was

2694586782
04:36:18.389 --> 04:36:20.243
significantly higher many years ago.

642389374
04:36:20.786 --> 04:36:23.447
And it's very hard to put
that across to the public.

1221530688
04:36:23.790 --> 04:36:26.097
That conversation is
getting easier to be had

178128767
04:36:26.784 --> 04:36:28.941
when they see the impact from fuel prices,

787043335
04:36:28.942 --> 04:36:31.542
what's happening over in the Middle East?

2900106196
04:36:31.543 --> 04:36:34.555
Will I be able to fly away
and go on holiday in the summer?

1813264995
04:36:34.557 --> 04:36:36.694
All these type of equations are coming to

2923586464
04:36:36.695 --> 04:36:38.550
the forefront and people are asking.

1375657729
04:36:38.551 --> 04:36:41.242
And when I speak at different
dinners or events,

3888596041
04:36:41.243 --> 04:36:44.096
every so often someone
would talk about defence.

4285850374
04:36:44.097 --> 04:36:46.203
Now it's almost every single question can

876924726
04:36:46.204 --> 04:36:50.291
we defend ourselves and can we rearm?

3658387994
04:36:50.292 --> 04:36:53.251
And I I'm pleading with
the Ministers to win the argument,

3212680167
04:36:53.253 --> 04:36:55.260
because I know every single one of them

2754428430
04:36:55.261 --> 04:36:57.116
would want more funding for defence.

2784998265
04:36:57.117 --> 04:37:00.630
And I'm pleading to win this argument,
to do whatever it takes to see

533128803
04:37:00.631 --> 04:37:04.596
that we can rearm and we can have
the armed forces that we need,

1707778584
04:37:04.597 --> 04:37:07.659
and we can stand on the world
stage with our head held high.

3429069564
04:37:08.742 --> 04:37:10.396
Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

2448978051
04:37:10.397 --> 04:37:13.042
>> Graeme Downie hey.

3703889649
04:37:13.043 --> 04:37:16.237
>> Thank you very much,
Madam Deputy Speaker,

2017523114
04:37:16.238 --> 04:37:18.245
and it's a privilege to follow the hon.

955731270
04:37:18.246 --> 04:37:20.503
Member for South Shropshire
and what I think

1816265465
04:37:20.504 --> 04:37:22.358
has been a very constructive debate,

140222954
04:37:22.360 --> 04:37:25.939
with a lot of cross-party consensus.

3195377957
04:37:25.940 --> 04:37:29.500
Can I begin by welcoming the speeches
and contributions from Ministers

865622667
04:37:29.501 --> 04:37:32.760
earlier on regarding the measures
included in the King's Speech,

2635040732
04:37:32.761 --> 04:37:35.219
such as the Armed Forces
Bill and the commitment

1934184194
04:37:35.220 --> 04:37:36.923
towards supporting drone testing.

1870306606
04:37:36.924 --> 04:37:41.289
Something, again, I think we see across
the House is very much required.

294433446
04:37:41.290 --> 04:37:43.849
There are three points
I would like to make during

3003181697
04:37:43.850 --> 04:37:45.804
this speech around defence priorities,

1329276933
04:37:45.804 --> 04:37:47.711
around about the threats that we face

1835290590
04:37:47.712 --> 04:37:50.843
and some of the need for
long term thinking.

1847383789
04:37:50.844 --> 04:37:54.296
First of all, looking at some
of the threats that we face,

3536463535
04:37:54.786 --> 04:37:56.845
and we heard this earlier on by the hon.

2586643806
04:37:56.846 --> 04:38:00.338
Member for Wetherby and Easingwold,
who is no longer in his place.

30874082
04:38:00.339 --> 04:38:03.849
Regarding the British people need
to understand the threats that this

3977913628
04:38:03.850 --> 04:38:08.747
country does face and what warfare
looks like in a modern context.

3320996161
04:38:08.748 --> 04:38:12.092
I am one of the ones who believe
we already are in a conflict

745151459
04:38:12.093 --> 04:38:15.092
with Russia and should take
action along those lines.

3652413445
04:38:15.093 --> 04:38:18.546
And indeed, I believe in
the High North we actually are.

471672619
04:38:18.547 --> 04:38:22.648
Not only that, we are a front line
nation in that conflict with Russia,

3391919932
04:38:22.649 --> 04:38:26.440
and we have only seen just this week
of the threat we faced from reports

3855157914
04:38:26.441 --> 04:38:29.445
of Russian submarines
in the North Atlantic

620653897
04:38:29.446 --> 04:38:31.935
and attacks on energy infrastructure,

2106609283
04:38:31.936 --> 04:38:34.567
and indeed, the threat we
face on subsea cables.

1704303527
04:38:34.568 --> 04:38:36.876
This is something I see
in here all the time.

4017986058
04:38:36.878 --> 04:38:40.491
As chair of the All-Party
parliamentary Group on Estonia,

978579398
04:38:40.492 --> 04:38:43.201
where I was privileged to
visit earlier on this year,

2756667311
04:38:43.202 --> 04:38:45.411
to see some of the work
that they are doing

4230937477
04:38:45.411 --> 04:38:47.292
to prepare not only their military,

2714009805
04:38:47.293 --> 04:38:48.647
but their society as well.

1006654381
04:38:48.648 --> 04:38:50.955
There was an article
I would highly recommend

2344111673
04:38:50.956 --> 04:38:54.945
anyone to read this Week in Foreign Policy

2752590844
04:38:54.946 --> 04:38:58.894
by Franz Stefan Gadi regarding the threats

3979880005
04:38:58.894 --> 04:39:01.403
and indeed the weaknesses that NATO faces,

327738077
04:39:01.404 --> 04:39:05.196
not only on the military front,
but on political decision making.

2817103252
04:39:05.197 --> 04:39:06.947
And in that article, Mr.

2082916894
04:39:06.948 --> 04:39:09.908
describes how he, while playing
a war game, defeated NATO.

1018872863
04:39:09.909 --> 04:39:12.366
And it was not actually
about military strength.

1015512955
04:39:12.367 --> 04:39:15.947
It was about the need for
quick decision making.

1025389051
04:39:15.947 --> 04:39:18.744
And in that he describes
the UK forces in Estonia,

3627631935
04:39:18.745 --> 04:39:21.492
as well as other NATO forces in Lithuania.

3595325982
04:39:21.493 --> 04:39:25.551
So in sum, I can ask the Ministers
to provide some reassurance around

2010212994
04:39:25.552 --> 04:39:29.249
Kibrit and the fantastic British
forces that we have in Estonia,

2408468643
04:39:29.250 --> 04:39:32.108
the speed of their response
and the operational decision

1786064914
04:39:32.108 --> 04:39:35.340
making is in place to
make sure that we are not

892654195
04:39:35.340 --> 04:39:37.948
delayed by political stasis
in the event of Russian

264033686
04:39:37.950 --> 04:39:40.592
aggression coming forward
through hybrid warfare,

1661624719
04:39:40.593 --> 04:39:44.695
because we know that Russia's
experience in Ukraine already points,

3992699596
04:39:44.696 --> 04:39:47.043
that once they control the battlefield,

3884198402
04:39:47.044 --> 04:39:51.596
they make it very hard for a NATO
or any other counter-attack.

2996677660
04:39:51.597 --> 04:39:53.355
I am happy to give way to the hon.

621991286
04:39:53.356 --> 04:39:53.756
Friend.

3820434512
04:39:53.757 --> 04:39:54.711
>> I thank my hon.

2530733585
04:39:54.712 --> 04:39:55.865
Friend for giving way.

287447093
04:39:55.866 --> 04:39:58.204
And he speaks passionately about Estonia.

532049325
04:39:58.205 --> 04:40:01.464
Britain has got troops deployed
in Estonia providing a tripwire,

2671218799
04:40:01.465 --> 04:40:04.927
as he well knows, having no doubt
spent some time with him recently.

2235813600
04:40:04.928 --> 04:40:07.235
Will he join me in
encouraging the government

1574937833
04:40:09.750 --> 04:40:11.155
to make every effort to arm

3700316007
04:40:11.156 --> 04:40:14.094
and equip those troops with the necessary

3271248697
04:40:14.095 --> 04:40:16.237
capabilities merely to survive?

3040736346
04:40:16.238 --> 04:40:18.748
And does he agree with me
that at the moment they

3936523798
04:40:18.749 --> 04:40:21.257
provide not much deterrence
force at all until we

4140339128
04:40:21.258 --> 04:40:24.492
give them the technologies
we know have been standard

4225172943
04:40:24.493 --> 04:40:26.599
in modern warfare for multiple years now.

1243677109
04:40:27.791 --> 04:40:28.745
>> I thank my hon.

2847298025
04:40:28.746 --> 04:40:30.492
Friend for his intervention.

2633169035
04:40:30.493 --> 04:40:31.797
I totally agree with him.

1345797471
04:40:31.798 --> 04:40:35.211
We have to if we are to have
an effective deterrent in the Baltics,

1287296141
04:40:35.212 --> 04:40:37.570
it must make sure it is
an effective deterrent

1496822034
04:40:37.571 --> 04:40:40.079
and not just something
which looks good on paper,

3180766373
04:40:40.080 --> 04:40:42.136
but must be operationally ready to fight

558677144
04:40:42.137 --> 04:40:44.143
exactly that threat that he points out.

131827390
04:40:44.144 --> 04:40:47.206
I would like to move on to
the role of information and where

1562997889
04:40:47.207 --> 04:40:49.765
we are informing the British
public of the threat.

3587701874
04:40:49.766 --> 04:40:52.476
This is the point that
I have made many times before,

4256411096
04:40:52.477 --> 04:40:55.136
that I believe we must trust
the British people with

3071264408
04:40:55.137 --> 04:40:57.644
more information about
the threat that they face,

131181450
04:40:57.644 --> 04:40:59.448
whether that is from cybersecurity,

2255863321
04:40:59.450 --> 04:41:02.207
the threat to subsea cables
and energy infrastructure,

3640741105
04:41:02.208 --> 04:41:04.213
because unless the British people fully

1670551167
04:41:04.214 --> 04:41:06.119
understand the threat that they face,

951364654
04:41:06.120 --> 04:41:09.229
they will not be providing
the necessary pressure and indeed,

1119138038
04:41:09.230 --> 04:41:11.386
licence for government to act more quickly

3847607323
04:41:11.387 --> 04:41:13.346
and to act in the way that we all know

2137314644
04:41:13.347 --> 04:41:15.405
in this House that we must act to defend

4250133494
04:41:15.406 --> 04:41:17.210
ourselves from the current threats.

2632084403
04:41:17.211 --> 04:41:19.870
I am very much of the belief
that information breeds

2518694536
04:41:19.871 --> 04:41:22.128
teamwork and togetherness,
and a lack of it,

2535244003
04:41:22.129 --> 04:41:25.996
and a void creates speculation
and misinformation

2542233116
04:41:25.997 --> 04:41:27.693
from our from our enemies,

1494128611
04:41:27.694 --> 04:41:30.142
and indeed from some in this House.

840391123
04:41:30.143 --> 04:41:33.104
And we must make sure that
the British people are the ones

3437959884
04:41:33.105 --> 04:41:36.146
keeping us on our toes
and making sure that they are,

2580944929
04:41:36.147 --> 04:41:39.103
that we are defending them
in the way that we should.

697666523
04:41:39.104 --> 04:41:43.400
And I would point to recent cyber
attacks on cyber on Jaguar Land Rover,

653444397
04:41:43.401 --> 04:41:47.008
as was mentioned by a colleague,
are no longer in place in retail.

2426766342
04:41:47.009 --> 04:41:50.348
These are all threats
that the UK is facing,

345335356
04:41:50.349 --> 04:41:52.106
and we must be much more up front,

1749508309
04:41:52.107 --> 04:41:57.246
straightforward and trusting of
the British people with the information.

4218203418
04:41:57.247 --> 04:42:00.732
Finally, Madam Deputy Speaker,
I would like to move on to talk about

1162190195
04:42:00.733 --> 04:42:04.800
some of the priorities for long
term defence of the United Kingdom,

2595980630
04:42:04.801 --> 04:42:11.457
and that does, I am afraid, require
uttering the initials D, I and P.

4205132584
04:42:11.458 --> 04:42:15.600
I do not want to revisit some of
the arguments we've already had so far,

1137416789
04:42:15.601 --> 04:42:17.858
but I would like to urge
Ministers that when

1741402086
04:42:17.860 --> 04:42:19.865
looking at the Defence Investment Plan,

1313068744
04:42:19.866 --> 04:42:22.898
we are looking at the long
term planning as well

458341270
04:42:22.899 --> 04:42:25.005
and that when that document is published,

1191961716
04:42:25.006 --> 04:42:28.603
we do not focus just on
some of the things that are

1989480213
04:42:28.604 --> 04:42:31.495
maybe more immediate in
my own constituency.

3062244651
04:42:31.496 --> 04:42:33.552
And again, this was mentioned earlier on

3922532056
04:42:33.553 --> 04:42:35.596
by the Member for South West Wiltshire.

2226908116
04:42:35.597 --> 04:42:37.906
We are looking at some
of the work that needs

1263140673
04:42:37.907 --> 04:42:39.863
to be done around our submarine fleet.

3284206513
04:42:39.864 --> 04:42:43.192
First, around contingent
docking facilities at Rosyth,

1483996824
04:42:43.193 --> 04:42:46.683
which will ensure that
a lack of infrastructure

1799148070
04:42:46.684 --> 04:42:49.442
does not delay or curtail
the operation of dreadnought

565409609
04:42:49.443 --> 04:42:51.047
class submarines in the future.

2867066654
04:42:51.048 --> 04:42:55.605
I know the Defence Ministers,
Ministers are well aware of

2924089018
04:42:55.606 --> 04:42:58.546
the threat that poses that
when we get to that position,

3586180559
04:42:58.547 --> 04:43:01.304
dreadnought must be able to
enter service immediately,

3951884213
04:43:01.304 --> 04:43:04.515
fully and quickly to take
the pressure off the Vanguard service

2306630297
04:43:04.516 --> 04:43:08.506
that has already been
referred to earlier on today.

2292818887
04:43:08.507 --> 04:43:11.168
And the second, I am happy
to give way to my friend.

315980260
04:43:11.169 --> 04:43:12.046
>> Thank you.

3563584726
04:43:12.047 --> 04:43:14.354
And might you allow me,
Madam Deputy Speaker,

459722473
04:43:14.355 --> 04:43:16.713
to put on record my support
and recognition of

3739225034
04:43:16.714 --> 04:43:19.382
the bold and principled
speech by the right hon.

1404167489
04:43:19.383 --> 04:43:21.338
Member for Ilford North earlier today.

3912341767
04:43:21.339 --> 04:43:22.343
Can I thank my hon.

2944135009
04:43:22.797 --> 04:43:24.803
Friend for his support for this agenda?

1541305999
04:43:24.804 --> 04:43:29.196
Does he share my deep disappointment
about the news that British

2356263351
04:43:29.197 --> 04:43:32.596
manufacturing scale up has
gone into administration?

3382845906
04:43:32.597 --> 04:43:36.198
Alas, we are about to create
or potentially create the UK's

1874185784
04:43:36.200 --> 04:43:39.608
replacement to a Red arrows
Hawk jet and with their loss,

1318367944
04:43:39.610 --> 04:43:43.241
we may in fact see our beloved Red
arrows no longer being British.

281087149
04:43:43.242 --> 04:43:44.397
>> Can I thank my hon.

3254476120
04:43:44.398 --> 04:43:45.901
Friend for that contribution?

4193971929
04:43:45.902 --> 04:43:48.612
I know how closely he worked
with the company to make

2284395101
04:43:48.613 --> 04:43:51.092
sure that they were being
considered as well.

2195988121
04:43:51.093 --> 04:43:54.102
And indeed, having visited RAF
Valley earlier on this year,

2698509928
04:43:54.103 --> 04:43:57.703
seeing the need to replace
the Hawk as a trainer aircraft is one

1923142995
04:43:57.704 --> 04:44:01.366
that is pressing and one I think
must be met very quickly.

3448057221
04:44:01.367 --> 04:44:01.918
Just very.

2327148160
04:44:01.919 --> 04:44:04.176
Finally, Madam Deputy,
be aware I have taken

4229532173
04:44:04.177 --> 04:44:06.131
more interventions and perhaps others.

3380686218
04:44:06.132 --> 04:44:07.455
So my apologies.

2487333480
04:44:07.456 --> 04:44:10.567
The other thing I would like to
urge Ministers to consider in

2063373896
04:44:10.568 --> 04:44:13.727
the dip and more generally is
the submarine recycling project,

1750724320
04:44:13.728 --> 04:44:16.303
which I know is one that the Ministers for

2732127027
04:44:16.304 --> 04:44:20.086
Defence Procurement is very well aware of,

288182652
04:44:20.087 --> 04:44:22.255
making sure that we have the space to,

633441211
04:44:22.256 --> 04:44:24.160
as submarines continue through, that,

3068485574
04:44:24.161 --> 04:44:26.419
we have the space to
make sure they're being

2795876054
04:44:26.420 --> 04:44:28.675
managed and recycled
effectively and safely.

2103812992
04:44:28.676 --> 04:44:32.856
And indeed, at Rosyth
we have the HMS van or

3314313875
04:44:32.857 --> 04:44:35.937
the HMS Swiftsure pilot
project coming to an end,

1838701622
04:44:35.938 --> 04:44:39.148
which has seen the dismantling
of one submarine and that steel,

3464022146
04:44:39.149 --> 04:44:42.258
in fact being recycled and used
in the dreadnought programme.

593664054
04:44:42.259 --> 04:44:44.658
An incredible way of
making sure that we are

2155699607
04:44:44.659 --> 04:44:47.297
actually reusing materials where possible,

228779725
04:44:47.298 --> 04:44:52.247
holding down costs and as
well as securing hundreds

1081158241
04:44:52.248 --> 04:44:54.054
of jobs in my constituency as well.

1988924959
04:44:54.054 --> 04:44:56.312
Madam Deputy Speaker,
these are the kinds of

1005939216
04:44:56.313 --> 04:44:58.570
projects we must be
focusing on for defence.

1715629411
04:44:58.571 --> 04:45:02.135
We must be making sure we are aware
of the threats that we are facing,

1488553439
04:45:02.136 --> 04:45:05.045
informing the British people
of the threats we are facing

885474856
04:45:05.046 --> 04:45:08.357
and planning for the long term
so that this country remains safe.

755540133
04:45:08.358 --> 04:45:09.661
I will give very quickly.

3516382879
04:45:09.662 --> 04:45:11.069
I will give way to the hon.

1709578605
04:45:11.070 --> 04:45:11.370
Lady.

2148178399
04:45:11.792 --> 04:45:12.996
>> Thank you very much.

667035676
04:45:12.997 --> 04:45:16.496
Thank you for your contribution.

1243924370
04:45:16.497 --> 04:45:17.248
Very powerful.

2151998044
04:45:17.249 --> 04:45:19.853
Some of the work that we do on the Defence

2914948498
04:45:19.854 --> 04:45:23.254
Select Committee actually involves

668924993
04:45:23.255 --> 04:45:26.916
an awful lot of private briefings that
maybe members within the chamber,

2466813245
04:45:26.917 --> 04:45:30.128
the members of the public, do not
have the privilege of seeing.

3372274319
04:45:30.129 --> 04:45:34.704
When I asked the CDs recently why
we don't tell the public more,

1186736070
04:45:34.705 --> 04:45:37.455
his words were, we don't
want to alarm people.

463798432
04:45:37.456 --> 04:45:41.499
Now, would you agree that
the public are grown up?

4266922604
04:45:41.500 --> 04:45:42.503
We should maybe be.

703664820
04:45:42.504 --> 04:45:44.361
Let them know a bit more about this.

2089976185
04:45:44.362 --> 04:45:47.822
They should probably be a little
more alarmed than they already are,

958685483
04:45:47.823 --> 04:45:50.635
and they would come with us
on this journey to say yes,

2928390515
04:45:50.636 --> 04:45:52.140
please spend more on defence.

329563837
04:45:52.141 --> 04:45:53.296
>> Can I thank my hon.

3629989136
04:45:53.297 --> 04:45:54.750
Friend for her contribution?

1997832302
04:45:54.751 --> 04:45:56.356
I couldn't agree with her more.

1027662332
04:45:56.357 --> 04:45:58.967
I think we must bring
the British people with us on

4079843571
04:45:58.968 --> 04:46:01.525
this journey and trust them
with that information.

2055264532
04:46:01.526 --> 04:46:04.085
Only by moving together as
a country can we defend

1516984615
04:46:04.086 --> 04:46:06.292
ourselves against
the threats that we face.

1336462022
04:46:06.293 --> 04:46:07.947
Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

3519348818
04:46:07.947 --> 04:46:10.655
>> Graham Leadbitter thank
you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

4146284389
04:46:10.800 --> 04:46:14.304
Less than two weeks ago,
the SNP secured a landslide

1654642799
04:46:14.305 --> 04:46:16.460
record breaking Scottish election victory,

4110595642
04:46:16.797 --> 04:46:19.303
including securing two
constituency MSPs who have

1037797936
04:46:19.304 --> 04:46:21.459
left this place for Scotland's Parliament.

2078275723
04:46:21.460 --> 04:46:24.067
And I know that regardless
of political difference,

4097576195
04:46:24.068 --> 04:46:26.325
there is a significant
level of respect from

3160480723
04:46:26.326 --> 04:46:28.682
across parties for their
contributions in this

1424801721
04:46:28.683 --> 04:46:30.940
chamber and to the wider
work of Parliament.

3028477557
04:46:30.941 --> 04:46:32.947
That experience will stand them in good

3957818016
04:46:32.947 --> 04:46:34.904
stead for what lies ahead in Holyrood.

430832749
04:46:34.905 --> 04:46:37.562
Madam Deputy Speaker, much
more respect for Scottish

99490210
04:46:37.563 --> 04:46:39.719
voters is required from the UK government.

3431551157
04:46:39.720 --> 04:46:42.427
When the Labour government
in Westminster is founded.

2120744324
04:46:42.428 --> 04:46:44.959
Month after month, failing
to address the cost of

337844989
04:46:44.960 --> 04:46:47.650
living crisis affecting
all of my constituents,

4090268314
04:46:47.651 --> 04:46:51.656
the SNP offered a message of hope
for Scotland can and should be.

2772109731
04:46:51.657 --> 04:46:55.451
With the vast natural resources it
strategically important geographical

1357556308
04:46:55.452 --> 04:46:58.661
position in the world and
the incredible talents of its people.

742120098
04:46:58.662 --> 04:47:01.107
It is particularly notable
that in Scotland,

1173208547
04:47:01.108 --> 04:47:04.754
support for independence is now
consistently polling above 50%,

2366338296
04:47:04.755 --> 04:47:07.661
and Scotland's voters have
elected a significant majority

1111020782
04:47:07.662 --> 04:47:10.471
of MSPs who support independence
more than ever before,

477376986
04:47:10.795 --> 04:47:14.346
and a clear mandate from
the Scottish electorate

3099823857
04:47:14.347 --> 04:47:16.251
to pursue an independence referendum.

2778106401
04:47:16.251 --> 04:47:18.458
Madam Deputy Speaker,
the theme for today's

1847336533
04:47:18.459 --> 04:47:21.251
King's Speech debate is defence readiness.

2103267135
04:47:21.253 --> 04:47:24.010
Many will focus on defence
spend, defence procurement,

960111108
04:47:24.011 --> 04:47:26.968
national security threats
and other direct defence issues.

665396088
04:47:26.969 --> 04:47:30.197
And I agree with many of
the points that have been made by hon.

810381013
04:47:30.197 --> 04:47:32.153
Members in this debate this afternoon.

2296537843
04:47:33.844 --> 04:47:35.750
Many of them are extremely well made,

1169924735
04:47:35.751 --> 04:47:37.960
but I would contend that for around

1049468130
04:47:37.961 --> 04:47:41.269
4500 personnel across three
significant bases in my constituency,

4168169624
04:47:41.799 --> 04:47:44.305
probably the same number
again in family members,

2776914224
04:47:44.799 --> 04:47:48.600
around 1000 permanent defence
contractor jobs and their families,

801487706
04:47:48.601 --> 04:47:51.800
and an estimated 12,000
veterans and their families.

284549731
04:47:51.801 --> 04:47:54.459
A total of over 3000 people
with defence connection.

2215535507
04:47:54.460 --> 04:47:59.054
There are many, many issues that
contribute to defence readiness.

1747115818
04:47:59.054 --> 04:48:01.262
Turning first to
the cost of living crisis.

3169918935
04:48:01.263 --> 04:48:04.271
Like every other resident in
Moray, West Tyrone Strathspey,

1465175277
04:48:04.272 --> 04:48:08.058
our defence community are also
struggling to cover bills

1237039563
04:48:08.059 --> 04:48:10.668
having to cope with more
month than there is money.

445433732
04:48:10.669 --> 04:48:12.573
Defence personnel posted to the north

3919886700
04:48:12.575 --> 04:48:14.550
of Scotland from elsewhere in the UK,

2180423319
04:48:14.551 --> 04:48:17.108
will experience an amazing
place to live and work,

2207870167
04:48:17.110 --> 04:48:19.015
but they will also experience amongst

3101345797
04:48:19.016 --> 04:48:20.871
the highest energy prices in Europe,

17387231
04:48:20.872 --> 04:48:23.304
caused by a regulatory
system that is hugely

2163513040
04:48:23.305 --> 04:48:25.361
discriminatory to the north of Scotland.

4139041094
04:48:25.362 --> 04:48:27.468
Labour MPs promised that people would see

2965602987
04:48:27.469 --> 04:48:29.353
a Â£ 300 reduction in energy bills,

1928178385
04:48:29.354 --> 04:48:34.358
but they are projected to see
a more than Â£400 a year increase.

3371321841
04:48:34.360 --> 04:48:37.772
There is little to nothing in this
King's Speech that both seeks to

3132596742
04:48:37.773 --> 04:48:40.981
reverse that Â£700 plus difference
from their manifesto promise,

4020502610
04:48:40.982 --> 04:48:43.804
and that would also remove
the discrimination faced by

3960014055
04:48:43.805 --> 04:48:46.412
households and businesses
in the North of Scotland.

919041133
04:48:46.803 --> 04:48:49.260
Discrimination that has
gone on for decades with

2463397978
04:48:49.261 --> 04:48:51.668
no action to address this
by the Conservatives,

2432546694
04:48:51.669 --> 04:48:54.103
Liberal Democrats and New Labour.

2954538110
04:48:54.104 --> 04:48:57.614
Up until yesterday, there was no
plan from the Westminster government

1620924877
04:48:57.615 --> 04:49:01.126
to address growing food costs,
something the SNP is tackling head on.

1699632927
04:49:01.126 --> 04:49:04.687
Seemingly, the Chancellor is now
looking to do similar but critically,

1800320620
04:49:04.688 --> 04:49:05.942
not in a compulsory way.

1313244196
04:49:05.943 --> 04:49:08.600
I very much welcome
the government's late acceptance

1177932598
04:49:08.601 --> 04:49:10.407
of the SNP's wisdom in this matter,

1488116760
04:49:10.408 --> 04:49:12.715
but I would strongly
urge the government that

457349494
04:49:12.715 --> 04:49:15.303
if they are going to do
it, to do it properly.

3353475688
04:49:15.304 --> 04:49:17.111
There is no plan to cut fuel costs.

3351551319
04:49:17.112 --> 04:49:21.350
I promise not to increase tax
further, but no plan to reduce it.

2322389672
04:49:21.351 --> 04:49:22.804
In constituencies like mine,

3350741415
04:49:22.804 --> 04:49:26.305
where Carlisle is a necessity
to access basic services,

2030386676
04:49:26.307 --> 04:49:30.106
to access education, leisure and to
access employment opportunities.

298814227
04:49:30.107 --> 04:49:32.550
That is especially disappointing.

164123474
04:49:32.551 --> 04:49:35.461
People in the north of Scotland
deserve better than to be

1974192143
04:49:35.462 --> 04:49:38.611
punished by Westminster just
for living where they live.

419919735
04:49:38.612 --> 04:49:41.720
Defence personnel, often hundreds
of miles from their family,

1860654726
04:49:41.721 --> 04:49:44.353
also deserve better than
incurring the substantial

49779856
04:49:44.354 --> 04:49:47.910
costs that they have to pay to drive home.

343678464
04:49:47.911 --> 04:49:49.818
When it comes to energy and net zero,

263855427
04:49:49.819 --> 04:49:53.762
a sector that has always been a strong
destination for retiring forces

686755386
04:49:53.763 --> 04:49:56.221
personnel and which is
very suited to many skill

3521115920
04:49:56.222 --> 04:49:58.679
sets of those coming from
a military background.

2751749114
04:49:58.679 --> 04:50:02.305
The current government is intent on
repeating the mistakes of the past,

3866011759
04:50:02.307 --> 04:50:04.463
of accelerating the decline of one sector,

3423829183
04:50:04.464 --> 04:50:07.626
in this case oil and gas, at
a rate that does not match either

3757330013
04:50:07.628 --> 04:50:11.129
demand changes or the growth
of the renewables sector.

2090055164
04:50:11.130 --> 04:50:13.186
It is simply Thatcherism all over again,

2906661455
04:50:13.187 --> 04:50:16.748
which saw the tearing apart of coal
and steel communities in Scotland.

1082068471
04:50:16.749 --> 04:50:18.857
It is a betrayal of North Sea workers and

480648905
04:50:18.858 --> 04:50:21.508
the vast supply chain
associated with those jobs,

2507824676
04:50:21.509 --> 04:50:24.366
from skilled parts manufacturing
jobs to the hospitality

745068574
04:50:24.367 --> 04:50:26.172
staff across the north of Scotland.

4183522265
04:50:26.173 --> 04:50:29.203
Taxi drivers, cafes
and corner shops that have seen

3235051856
04:50:29.204 --> 04:50:32.006
their revenues eroded to
an unsustainable level.

2807777150
04:50:32.007 --> 04:50:37.510
It erodes the opportunities available
to defence personnel as well.

2170858423
04:50:37.803 --> 04:50:39.708
The Conservative Party are no better.

4101476076
04:50:39.709 --> 04:50:42.418
Their answer is simply to
push the cliff edge further

2793054067
04:50:42.419 --> 04:50:44.775
away rather than embrace
a managed transition,

2047964374
04:50:44.776 --> 04:50:46.833
which is what the industry wants to see.

142549934
04:50:46.834 --> 04:50:49.541
Neither of those scenarios
is acceptable to Scotland,

965185313
04:50:49.542 --> 04:50:54.503
and neither of those scenarios is
acceptable to my constituents.

1652463951
04:50:54.504 --> 04:50:57.754
This brings me back to the theme
of today defence readiness.

2916864759
04:50:57.755 --> 04:51:00.715
It is not attractive to people
to join a military when key

3523172520
04:51:00.717 --> 04:51:03.625
bases are seeing jobs
and opportunity eroded around them.

383541900
04:51:03.626 --> 04:51:05.730
That stifles transition opportunities for

2532461631
04:51:05.731 --> 04:51:07.836
personnel leaving the services and erodes

3795546408
04:51:07.837 --> 04:51:10.610
the vitality of the communities that

2507665451
04:51:10.611 --> 04:51:12.467
those bases are an integral part of.

1650311097
04:51:12.468 --> 04:51:15.353
Defence spending needs to
be significantly increased.

1834717858
04:51:15.354 --> 04:51:17.563
Yes, we need to have
a better offer for new

3485850077
04:51:17.564 --> 04:51:19.568
military personnel and absolutely, yes,

186064788
04:51:19.569 --> 04:51:22.278
we need to have a much
stronger defence resilience in

1537600792
04:51:22.279 --> 04:51:24.886
a more challenging world
with dictators like Putin,

2633994035
04:51:24.887 --> 04:51:27.144
who are prepared to risk
peace on a shocking

906004485
04:51:27.146 --> 04:51:29.050
scale and threaten the infrastructure

2002002633
04:51:29.051 --> 04:51:31.858
that is critical to our
economic and social well-being.

4090257672
04:51:31.860 --> 04:51:34.909
However, at the heart of
this are defence communities

2356985711
04:51:34.910 --> 04:51:36.915
that are embedded in wider communities.

3179364244
04:51:36.916 --> 04:51:39.909
Defence communities that
have the same aspiration

2234077080
04:51:39.910 --> 04:51:42.018
for the regions they live in and who want

2473430017
04:51:42.019 --> 04:51:43.923
the same opportunities for themselves

1462881648
04:51:43.924 --> 04:51:46.179
and the whole community
that surrounds them.

4036748289
04:51:46.180 --> 04:51:49.453
Madam Deputy Speaker
getting these fundamentals

3146927715
04:51:49.454 --> 04:51:51.559
right supports that bigger community age,

1304262737
04:51:51.560 --> 04:51:54.669
>> Recruitment and retention in
the armed forces and provides

3414918008
04:51:54.670 --> 04:51:58.411
the opportunities that our veterans
deserve when they exit service.

1965029369
04:51:58.411 --> 04:52:01.184
>> Gill German thank.

3123215432
04:52:01.185 --> 04:52:02.689
>> You, Madam Deputy Speaker.

2019401120
04:52:02.690 --> 04:52:05.890
Madam Deputy Speaker, things
feel insecure right now,

4228745480
04:52:05.891 --> 04:52:09.257
be it the war in Iran, the cost
of living pressure on families,

1500675013
04:52:09.258 --> 04:52:11.164
or the sense that systems just aren't

2291204295
04:52:12.803 --> 04:52:14.608
working quite right in Clwyd North.

2630667871
04:52:14.608 --> 04:52:17.218
I hear it all the time when
families are struggling

73494330
04:52:17.219 --> 04:52:20.311
and young people don't feel
that they've got a fair chance,

1965106677
04:52:20.805 --> 04:52:26.554
it erodes trust in the belief
that things can actually start

263609369
04:52:26.554 --> 04:52:29.406
getting better and creates
a feeling of insecurity.

357341544
04:52:29.407 --> 04:52:33.906
Building up this trust starts
with clearly defining what

3154103335
04:52:33.907 --> 04:52:37.060
we put in place in our first
two years of government,

2515175176
04:52:37.061 --> 04:52:42.657
and how our future actions
will improve people's lives.

2472020678
04:52:42.658 --> 04:52:47.059
I know from speaking to people
in the community in real,

487655154
04:52:47.060 --> 04:52:50.309
in Colwyn Bay, in Abergele, in Denbigh,

2208398370
04:52:50.310 --> 04:52:54.358
across Clwyd North, that
that it is full of decent

2436866671
04:52:54.360 --> 04:52:58.510
people trying to do
the right thing day by day.

3710126124
04:52:58.511 --> 04:53:01.715
I want to make sure that
these people know that they

3828307136
04:53:01.715 --> 04:53:06.201
are heard and that things
can and will get better.

3374126977
04:53:06.202 --> 04:53:09.367
We must be honest about the challenges,

1246427163
04:53:09.368 --> 04:53:12.509
but also focus on what
really matters to people.

3643797433
04:53:12.510 --> 04:53:17.256
Building something that works better.

3731349293
04:53:17.257 --> 04:53:17.758
In Wales.

2236381076
04:53:17.759 --> 04:53:22.207
This means a relentless focus on
building a stronger and fairer future.

1901623008
04:53:22.208 --> 04:53:24.314
Helping families with the cost of living.

1380136426
04:53:24.807 --> 04:53:25.207
Living.

291683408
04:53:25.208 --> 04:53:27.111
Strengthening our communities through

4061282342
04:53:27.807 --> 04:53:29.710
better connections and opportunities,

3585405909
04:53:29.711 --> 04:53:34.662
and improving both energy and,
crucially, national security.

4223139616
04:53:35.808 --> 04:53:39.554
It's about making sure progress
is felt in everyday life,

3405283756
04:53:39.554 --> 04:53:44.361
especially in communities that have
been historically left behind.

268922011
04:53:44.362 --> 04:53:51.207
And it's about recognising how rich
and varied Wales is with our cities,

51051267
04:53:51.208 --> 04:53:52.360
countryside and coast.

1506175019
04:53:52.361 --> 04:53:59.565
And that means a tailored approach
that reflects these different needs.

38878434
04:53:59.566 --> 04:54:04.108
This government has already
delivered significant achievements,

3461690613
04:54:04.110 --> 04:54:06.958
passing 50 acts in its first
parliamentary session.

2068718644
04:54:06.959 --> 04:54:12.971
And behind every piece of legislation
are real people and real lives.

2954756722
04:54:12.972 --> 04:54:17.457
Among them is the Employment Rights
Act, strengthening protections,

