including engineers, apprentices,

2807581398
05:05:21.848 --> 05:05:24.818
contractors, dockyard workers
and military personnel.

1776869062
05:05:24.819 --> 05:05:27.981
We are a proud part of the wider
Plymouth travel to work area,

3126933059
05:05:27.982 --> 05:05:31.241
and our connectivity across
the Tamar is essential to sustaining

1368748811
05:05:31.819 --> 05:05:34.525
that defence workforce
and unlocking regional growth.

2916659724
05:05:34.526 --> 05:05:36.631
I have consistently raised the importance

775232916
05:05:36.632 --> 05:05:38.337
of these crossings in this House,

2309256921
05:05:38.338 --> 05:05:40.444
and yet the crossings are still sometimes

3882593178
05:05:40.445 --> 05:05:42.448
treated as purely local infrastructure,

1164732885
05:05:42.450 --> 05:05:44.606
as investment into Davenport and long term

653348043
05:05:44.607 --> 05:05:46.511
defence capability continues to grow,

313142899
05:05:46.512 --> 05:05:49.026
the pressure on those
links will only grow too.

1882364487
05:05:49.027 --> 05:05:52.235
So as the government rightly
invest billions into strengthening

2943726477
05:05:52.236 --> 05:05:54.942
Britain's defence capability
and long term readiness,

2227521357
05:05:54.943 --> 05:05:57.349
and South East Cornwall
help sustain nationally

1102254715
05:05:57.350 --> 05:05:58.751
important defence activity,

3466548886
05:05:58.753 --> 05:06:02.113
our local community must feel
the benefits of that investment too.

1859742950
05:06:02.114 --> 05:06:05.774
We also recognise the reality that
energy security is national security.

3881735499
05:06:05.775 --> 05:06:08.282
Recent years have shown
the risks of overexposure

1218466362
05:06:08.283 --> 05:06:10.387
to volatile international energy markets.

3729033869
05:06:10.388 --> 05:06:13.421
Secure Home-grown clean energy,
strengthens resilience,

868109777
05:06:13.422 --> 05:06:15.426
supports economic stability and reduces

3250435955
05:06:15.427 --> 05:06:18.220
vulnerability to external shocks.

3000603370
05:06:18.221 --> 05:06:22.423
Climate resilience rightly forms part
of this government's understanding

3819301605
05:06:22.424 --> 05:06:25.926
of what defence readiness means
to communities like mine.

1468241154
05:06:25.927 --> 05:06:28.722
Extreme weather
and environmental instability

3261148588
05:06:28.723 --> 05:06:30.971
increasingly affect infrastructure,

1974131502
05:06:30.972 --> 05:06:33.929
supply chains and operational
capability across the world.

3751158519
05:06:33.929 --> 05:06:37.680
Preparing for those risks is part of
preparing Britain for our future.

2348644007
05:06:37.777 --> 05:06:41.370
And finally, defence readiness
in the modern world must

3759011519
05:06:41.371 --> 05:06:44.519
include cyber resilience
and digital capabilities.

2921756056
05:06:44.519 --> 05:06:48.076
Protecting critical infrastructure,
communication systems and national

1237134566
05:06:48.077 --> 05:06:51.125
networks is fundamental to
protecting our country itself,

2163251866
05:06:51.126 --> 05:06:54.278
because the future of defence
will depend not only on ships,

4145074574
05:06:54.279 --> 05:06:55.882
submarines and military assets,

721202599
05:06:55.883 --> 05:06:58.139
but also on secure
systems, skilled workers,

3228772343
05:06:58.140 --> 05:07:00.973
resilient infrastructure
and strong communities

2775203103
05:07:00.974 --> 05:07:02.277
like south east Cornwall.

2616746683
05:07:02.278 --> 05:07:05.821
When we talk about strengthening
Britain's defence capability,

3559067422
05:07:05.822 --> 05:07:09.283
we recognise the places and
the people helping sustain it every day.

2828346456
05:07:09.284 --> 05:07:12.678
Because defence readiness begins
long before a ship leaves port.

135945461
05:07:12.819 --> 05:07:15.625
It begins with resilient
infrastructure, secure energy,

4264131797
05:07:15.626 --> 05:07:19.972
strong digital capabilities
and communities like mine.

3725861930
05:07:19.973 --> 05:07:22.381
So I welcome this new era
of defence readiness.

2576385073
05:07:22.382 --> 05:07:26.269
South East Cornwall is proud to play its

1741212266
05:07:26.271 --> 05:07:28.326
part in supporting that national effort.

2020342295
05:07:28.327 --> 05:07:30.834
>> Adrian Ramsay thank
you, Madam Deputy Speaker,

4232601724
05:07:30.835 --> 05:07:34.586
and it's a pleasure to follow
the Member for South East Cornwall.

3216197264
05:07:34.587 --> 05:07:38.733
The first duty of any government
is to keep the public safe.

810447823
05:07:38.735 --> 05:07:41.644
This duty must shape everything
that we do in this House,

488257147
05:07:41.646 --> 05:07:43.954
and it must shape how
we think about defence.

3227545963
05:07:43.955 --> 05:07:48.420
There's no doubt that Britain today
faces profound defence challenges,

2622869293
05:07:48.421 --> 05:07:49.976
as we've heard in this debate,

4116250957
05:07:49.977 --> 05:07:53.369
from international instability
to cyber threats and increasing

2733939034
05:07:53.370 --> 05:07:55.476
pressure on our energy and supply chains.

458087343
05:07:55.477 --> 05:07:58.879
But if we are serious about defence,
then we must also recognise

3569582232
05:07:58.880 --> 05:08:03.771
that the types of threats
that we face are changing.

1989833003
05:08:03.772 --> 05:08:04.774
To debate security.

2514910441
05:08:04.775 --> 05:08:07.233
We must also look at whether
our most vulnerable

1636934006
05:08:07.233 --> 05:08:09.239
people are protected from extreme heat,

1676234659
05:08:09.240 --> 05:08:11.596
whether our communities
can cope with flooding

3127918191
05:08:11.597 --> 05:08:13.472
and whether we can secure food,

3847401772
05:08:13.473 --> 05:08:16.621
water and energy in
an increasingly unstable world.

2844533169
05:08:16.622 --> 05:08:19.322
Today, the Climate Change
Committee published

1401205712
05:08:19.323 --> 05:08:21.028
its report on climate adaptation,

2770858966
05:08:21.029 --> 05:08:24.373
and its warnings could not be clearer.

3635689784
05:08:24.374 --> 05:08:28.826
We are on a path to two
degrees of warming by 2050.

2282481400
05:08:28.827 --> 05:08:32.132
That means that in just
a couple of decades or so,

837456402
05:08:32.133 --> 05:08:34.926
9 in 10 of our homes will
be at risk of overheating.

3075536140
05:08:34.927 --> 05:08:38.233
Peak river flows may rise by 45%,

2174804084
05:08:38.235 --> 05:08:42.125
water supply shortfalls may
exceed 5,000,000,000l per day,

3179636248
05:08:42.126 --> 05:08:46.572
and 40 degree heat waves will become
the new normal across the UK,

2282278219
05:08:46.572 --> 05:08:51.169
potentially leading to
an additional 10,000

4257304281
05:08:51.170 --> 05:08:52.674
heat related deaths per year.

4198005531
05:08:52.675 --> 05:08:57.121
The committee is also clear that
without action warming of up to

2881953083
05:08:57.122 --> 05:09:00.975
four degrees by the end of this
century remains a possibility.

499148838
05:09:00.976 --> 05:09:03.975
Now four degrees of warming
would be catastrophic.

2986055214
05:09:03.976 --> 05:09:07.481
Temperatures in the UK nearing 50Â°C,

1891611807
05:09:07.482 --> 05:09:11.423
infrastructure pushed beyond what
it was ever designed to withstand,

305308697
05:09:11.424 --> 05:09:14.422
and profound consequences
for public health,

2357909961
05:09:14.423 --> 05:09:17.871
economic stability and social cohesion.

3806914001
05:09:17.872 --> 05:09:20.469
These are not distant projections.

1244028467
05:09:20.470 --> 05:09:23.727
Madam Deputy Speaker, my
constituents and yours are already

1867665819
05:09:23.728 --> 05:09:27.926
having to live with
the consequences of climate breakdown.

2648588818
05:09:27.927 --> 05:09:30.525
We see in the thousands of deaths caused

3037083939
05:09:30.526 --> 05:09:33.173
by the increasingly regular heat waves.

2784963119
05:09:33.174 --> 05:09:37.993
We see it in the communities
repeatedly devastated by flooding,

2296497071
05:09:37.994 --> 05:09:39.851
and we see it in rising food prices,

1170211513
05:09:39.852 --> 05:09:42.474
rising insurance costs
and growing pressures on

4058139024
05:09:42.475 --> 05:09:46.517
the services and systems that
people rely on every day.

1433262094
05:09:46.518 --> 05:09:48.525
None of this should come as a surprise.

3611957898
05:09:48.526 --> 05:09:51.483
Earlier this year, the government's
own Joint Intelligence

1505695066
05:09:51.483 --> 05:09:53.237
Committee warned that biodiversity

2894869305
05:09:53.827 --> 05:09:57.286
loss and ecosystem collapse pose
serious risks to national security,

1924058224
05:09:57.286 --> 05:09:59.331
threatening food and water supplies,

1198159183
05:09:59.332 --> 05:10:02.224
disruption to infrastructure
and supply chains,

2464325662
05:10:02.225 --> 05:10:04.380
increased flooding, risks to public health

3077975095
05:10:04.381 --> 05:10:07.226
and wider economic instability.

3878089396
05:10:07.227 --> 05:10:10.531
It also warned of the cascading
effects of displacement,

4003352183
05:10:10.532 --> 05:10:13.176
conflict and competition for resources.

3566169977
05:10:13.177 --> 05:10:15.684
Yet despite the scale
and seriousness of warnings

3568052253
05:10:15.685 --> 05:10:17.523
by the government's own advisers,

636434295
05:10:17.524 --> 05:10:20.825
and despite repeated calls
for parliamentary time,

1394569485
05:10:20.826 --> 05:10:24.391
this House has still not been
allowed a dedicated opportunity to

1439241042
05:10:24.392 --> 05:10:28.839
debate its findings or scrutinise
the government's response.

335131887
05:10:28.840 --> 05:10:34.355
Our children will have to live
with the consequences of inaction.

3238211435
05:10:34.356 --> 05:10:36.414
It would be a dereliction of duty to let

473087892
05:10:36.415 --> 05:10:38.269
political dramas around by elections

2596690835
05:10:38.269 --> 05:10:40.631
and leadership contests distract us from

4085351791
05:10:40.632 --> 05:10:44.226
this most fundamental responsibility.

3288912067
05:10:44.227 --> 05:10:47.177
The evidence is clear
and we're not without options.

4134993339
05:10:47.178 --> 05:10:50.573
Today's report sets out practical,

315779355
05:10:50.575 --> 05:10:52.929
costed solutions better
cooling for hospitals,

3191315592
05:10:52.930 --> 05:10:56.373
schools and care homes
so our most vulnerable

3932512596
05:10:56.374 --> 05:10:58.329
and are protected during extreme heat.

4084564273
05:10:58.833 --> 05:11:01.339
Stronger flood defences
and investment in natural

2535740810
05:11:01.822 --> 05:11:03.727
flood management for our communities.

4203581486
05:11:03.728 --> 05:11:07.227
A serious approach to water security.

4210146681
05:11:07.228 --> 05:11:10.437
So shortages do not become routine
support for British farmers.

3143604992
05:11:10.438 --> 05:11:14.427
So British food production remains
viable under changing conditions,

2188441360
05:11:14.428 --> 05:11:19.528
retrofitting homes to their fit for
a warmer climate and infrastructure

3290510023
05:11:19.529 --> 05:11:25.080
built to withstand climate impacts
rather than fail under them.

1118175736
05:11:25.081 --> 05:11:26.936
And the economics are equally clear.

1834766484
05:11:26.937 --> 05:11:30.237
The cost of action is
around 11 billion a year.

372329028
05:11:30.238 --> 05:11:36.322
The cost of inaction could rise to
between 60 and 260 billion annually.

1368109517
05:11:36.323 --> 05:11:37.980
So this must be a turning point.

71523785
05:11:37.981 --> 05:11:40.382
We can no longer treat climate adaptation

239833796
05:11:40.383 --> 05:11:43.880
as a secondary environmental issue.

692360635
05:11:43.881 --> 05:11:47.275
It is a matter of national defence.

1001194198
05:11:47.276 --> 05:11:49.081
It's a matter of economic security.

2394880084
05:11:49.082 --> 05:11:51.879
Above all, it's a matter
of protecting people.

1311548392
05:11:51.880 --> 05:11:54.679
But it needs to be far
higher up the agenda

522857570
05:11:54.680 --> 05:11:59.376
for government and for Parliament.

2641842094
05:11:59.376 --> 05:12:01.333
That's why I'm calling for a dedicated

1211406407
05:12:01.334 --> 05:12:03.289
climate protection unit in number ten,

1079762526
05:12:03.290 --> 05:12:06.299
with the sole purpose of working
across departments to fund

2750266782
05:12:06.300 --> 05:12:10.381
and drive forward
the recommendations in this report,

3447859196
05:12:10.382 --> 05:12:13.281
I'm also supporting
the King's Speech amendment G on

2355721427
05:12:13.282 --> 05:12:16.677
the threats that nature collapse
poses to national security.

939374751
05:12:16.678 --> 05:12:21.331
Because defence is not responding
after disaster strikes.

3031917268
05:12:21.823 --> 05:12:26.875
Defence is about reducing risks
before crisis becomes catastrophe.

3637101304
05:12:26.876 --> 05:12:29.893
If the first duty of government
is to keep people safe,

640567260
05:12:29.894 --> 05:12:34.237
then climate adaptation cannot sit
at the margins of the King's speech.

4258193701
05:12:34.238 --> 05:12:40.592
It must be placed firmly at its heart.

1594507467
05:12:40.593 --> 05:12:41.144
Thank you.

42009310
05:12:41.826 --> 05:12:42.779
>> Tim Roca thank.

1501673784
05:12:42.780 --> 05:12:44.284
>> You, Madam Deputy Speaker.

1310751543
05:12:44.823 --> 05:12:50.028
I've spoken in this chamber before
about defence and the urgency

2787177358
05:12:50.029 --> 05:12:52.888
of rearmament at some length,
and together with the hon.

3171798188
05:12:52.889 --> 05:12:56.148
Member for Tunbridge Wells and
the Field Marshal, Lord Richards,

2903011603
05:12:56.149 --> 05:12:58.784
I was proud to join them
in creating the all

142679255
05:12:58.785 --> 05:13:01.580
party parliamentary group on rearmament.

1842587402
05:13:01.581 --> 05:13:03.638
But before I turn to what the government

3942011030
05:13:03.639 --> 05:13:05.393
is doing around defence readiness,

3999807611
05:13:05.394 --> 05:13:06.798
I think it's worth pausing,

804467170
05:13:06.799 --> 05:13:11.628
as we always should, on how we got
here, because context always matters.

2517145463
05:13:11.629 --> 05:13:13.535
A century ago, the Member for Epping,

1152562020
05:13:13.536 --> 05:13:15.989
one who understood well
what it meant to watch

3784085533
05:13:15.990 --> 05:13:17.894
a nation sleep while danger gathered,

2289551012
05:13:17.896 --> 05:13:20.782
described a period of neglect
and lost opportunity

2876751749
05:13:20.783 --> 05:13:23.583
in defence as the years
the locust has eaten.

775510400
05:13:23.584 --> 05:13:26.328
Madam Deputy Speaker, I think we can apply

3199219444
05:13:26.329 --> 05:13:27.983
the same epitaph to the previous

1079584730
05:13:27.985 --> 05:13:32.486
government and coalition government
years of stewardship of defence.

2171962100
05:13:32.487 --> 05:13:35.126
The locusts were busy.

2531689194
05:13:35.128 --> 05:13:36.934
Armed forces pay cut in real terms.

4287772644
05:13:36.935 --> 05:13:42.128
In nine out of 14 years, housing
forces housing in such a state

1192487760
05:13:42.129 --> 05:13:47.528
of disrepair that complaints
reached a record 13,000

201136014
05:13:47.529 --> 05:13:49.536
in a single year, troop numbers fell to

2688871196
05:13:50.827 --> 05:13:52.983
the lowest level since the Napoleonic era.

351840164
05:13:52.983 --> 05:13:55.090
Frigates and destroyers cut by a quarter,

1599955048
05:13:55.090 --> 05:13:58.185
minehunters reduced by half and ground

478275402
05:13:58.186 --> 05:14:01.853
based air defence spending slashed by

4245018199
05:14:01.854 --> 05:14:03.660
70% in their final years in office,

1721622394
05:14:03.840 --> 05:14:08.144
and a defence industrial strategy
that sat on a shelf gathering dust,

2527326708
05:14:08.146 --> 05:14:12.080
dust, commitment on paper,
but nothing in practice.

3842534558
05:14:12.081 --> 05:14:15.885
They certainly were the years
the locusts have eaten and that is

777853066
05:14:15.886 --> 05:14:20.634
the inheritance the defence
frontbench had to contend with.

1592538986
05:14:20.635 --> 05:14:23.443
And I've spoken before about
the urgency of rearmament.

531789397
05:14:23.444 --> 05:14:26.635
As I say, I won't repeat myself,
but what I will say is I'm

920427942
05:14:26.636 --> 05:14:30.379
incredibly proud of
the government defence frontbench.

4253974993
05:14:30.380 --> 05:14:32.376
I believe it has brought coherence,

138147134
05:14:32.378 --> 05:14:35.034
great industry and a genuine
patriotic determination

928533186
05:14:35.035 --> 05:14:39.287
to sort out the mess it inherited
and it deserves to be recognised.

1342637464
05:14:39.289 --> 05:14:44.385
Yeah, I'm glad that the government
is investing over Â£270 billion

3666975706
05:14:44.386 --> 05:14:47.544
across defence this Parliament
not as an accountancy exercise,

1995408392
05:14:47.545 --> 05:14:50.152
but as a genuine strategic
commitment to rebuilding

803955889
05:14:50.153 --> 05:14:52.575
our national security from the ground up.

3901674313
05:14:52.576 --> 05:14:56.427
And I understand, as we
meet our commitments

1575719054
05:14:56.428 --> 05:14:59.456
that we made at The Hague NATO conference,

2580273594
05:14:59.457 --> 05:15:00.911
to reach 3.5% in the future,

28119468
05:15:00.912 --> 05:15:03.269
there will be difficult
discussions to be had,

3993703495
05:15:03.271 --> 05:15:06.782
just as there were difficult discussions
to be had about foreign aid.

4130046962
05:15:06.783 --> 05:15:09.191
But there is no magic
bullet when we're talking

3666501270
05:15:09.192 --> 05:15:11.045
about increasing defence expenditure

3122350407
05:15:11.046 --> 05:15:13.102
and pretending that one thing will solve

358687248
05:15:13.103 --> 05:15:14.858
the issue is simply not realistic.

1849573741
05:15:14.858 --> 05:15:18.720
In the two previous periods that this
country had to rearm significantly

731109442
05:15:18.721 --> 05:15:23.745
in the 1930s and the 1950s, it was
a combination of increased taxation,

2408852943
05:15:23.746 --> 05:15:25.850
increased borrowing and difficult choices

1137636221
05:15:25.851 --> 05:15:27.756
about public expenditure that did it.

1916107342
05:15:27.757 --> 05:15:29.914
So, you know, wishy washy words about just

1615884970
05:15:29.915 --> 05:15:32.679
cutting welfare will sort it all out.

2948727906
05:15:32.680 --> 05:15:34.587
I am not convinced by, and crucially,

989542745
05:15:34.588 --> 05:15:37.394
something else that this
government has understood over

1234543406
05:15:37.396 --> 05:15:40.004
the last one never grasped
is that defence spending

2251616595
05:15:40.005 --> 05:15:42.387
isn't just a cost, it's an investment.

2948828715
05:15:42.388 --> 05:15:43.742
It's an engine for growth.

670873775
05:15:43.743 --> 05:15:46.930
We spend Â£32 billion annually
with industry equivalent

1741606262
05:15:46.932 --> 05:15:51.084
to Â£ 460 for every person
living in this country.

908396584
05:15:51.085 --> 05:15:58.482
UK defence supports 463,000
high quality, well paying jobs,

1687754215
05:15:58.483 --> 05:16:00.290
one in every 60 jobs across the UK.

3561634582
05:16:00.291 --> 05:16:03.233
Well, I'm very happy to give one.

4242446580
05:16:03.235 --> 05:16:05.446
>> I'm very grateful
to you for giving way.

3615995560
05:16:05.447 --> 05:16:09.342
Would you agree with me that
where I come from, 96,000

1187891606
05:16:09.343 --> 05:16:13.180
jobs in the South West
come related defence.

905917413
05:16:13.182 --> 05:16:15.478
It's a huge sector for defence,

2344317029
05:16:15.479 --> 05:16:18.128
but key in my town to those jobs are SMEs,

2633472347
05:16:18.129 --> 05:16:19.582
small new sized enterprises.

2879339989
05:16:19.583 --> 05:16:22.430
And despite the welcome
changes with the office

3407584612
05:16:22.432 --> 05:16:28.281
for Promoting Small Business from the MoD,

3063016098
05:16:28.282 --> 05:16:31.290
the portals are still unnavigable
by many small businesses.

1227484102
05:16:31.291 --> 05:16:34.643
Does he agree with me that
the mod should do more to make these

861766216
05:16:34.644 --> 05:16:39.286
contracts available for our
small businesses and SMEs?

167247768
05:16:39.286 --> 05:16:39.587
Yeah.

1808168532
05:16:39.588 --> 05:16:41.192
>> Member for his intervention.

4229202045
05:16:41.193 --> 05:16:43.401
I was in Bristol recently
at the NAD group,

3829990338
05:16:43.402 --> 05:16:46.210
the Re the renamed Defence
Equipment and Support group,

313606090
05:16:46.211 --> 05:16:48.772
and I was glad to hear they
are doing more on SMEs

2077106834
05:16:48.773 --> 05:16:51.682
and maybe the frontbench will
comment more on that later,

1037241407
05:16:51.683 --> 05:16:54.392
but it is right to recognise
that SMEs are absolutely

499876704
05:16:54.393 --> 05:16:56.400
crucial and in his area of the country,

3547431073
05:16:56.401 --> 05:16:59.108
a really, really important
and these are livelihoods,

687731057
05:16:59.108 --> 05:17:01.265
communities and the kind of good, skilled,

1636432328
05:17:01.266 --> 05:17:03.222
unionised jobs that sit that this side

3616024034
05:17:03.223 --> 05:17:05.733
of the House has always stood for.

610269173
05:17:05.735 --> 05:17:09.592
I also want to acknowledge the other
work the government has done.

2153796501
05:17:09.593 --> 05:17:11.899
Last year, Â£1.5 billion
committed to building

288882391
05:17:11.900 --> 05:17:13.354
the factories of the future,

1451175379
05:17:13.355 --> 05:17:16.212
including the first energetics
factories in two decades,

2561026072
05:17:16.213 --> 05:17:20.344
creating over 1000 jobs in
our industrial heartlands.

1666174824
05:17:20.345 --> 05:17:22.953
The Â£8 billion deal with
Turkey sustaining a 20,000

1986175785
05:17:22.954 --> 05:17:24.657
strong workforce across Scotland,

3190708341
05:17:24.658 --> 05:17:28.068
Lancashire and Bristol, and
the type 26 frigate selected by Norway.

3996489632
05:17:28.069 --> 05:17:30.175
That was mentioned earlier in the debate.

3417799972
05:17:30.176 --> 05:17:32.983
Although I was disappointed
to see Sweden choose France

429903143
05:17:32.985 --> 05:17:35.142
over the UK in its frigate decision today,

4150300322
05:17:35.143 --> 05:17:38.153
but we'll just leave that to
the traditional UK French MoD.

2171227782
05:17:38.154 --> 05:17:40.340
But there is a genuine defence dividend,

284740063
05:17:40.342 --> 05:17:44.540
measured not in press releases
but in real jobs and real communities.

264455596
05:17:44.831 --> 05:17:46.837
The length and breadth of this country,

3631821427
05:17:46.838 --> 05:17:48.844
and turning briefly to something I hope

2105299526
05:17:48.845 --> 05:17:50.983
will receive the attention it deserves.

1318638227
05:17:50.983 --> 05:17:54.391
The Strategic Defence Review made
several important recommendations

2884136164
05:17:54.392 --> 05:17:56.986
on strengthening home
defence and resilience,

1012846231
05:17:56.987 --> 05:17:59.839
and rightly so in the context
of a whole of society

3810161997
05:17:59.840 --> 05:18:02.346
approach to national
security, which several hon.

2558721894
05:18:02.347 --> 05:18:04.084
Friends have talked about today.

1116911168
05:18:04.085 --> 05:18:07.937
The threats that we face are not
confined to the battlefield.

2257168193
05:18:07.938 --> 05:18:10.993
They reach into our infrastructure,
our supply chains,

3483794982
05:18:10.994 --> 05:18:12.948
our communities and resilience must be

818188306
05:18:12.950 --> 05:18:14.705
built across the whole of society,

2464740721
05:18:14.706 --> 05:18:17.915
not just within the wire fences
of our military establishments.

3198145175
05:18:17.916 --> 05:18:19.070
And with that in mind,

958775451
05:18:19.071 --> 05:18:21.830
I was reassured to hear
the Ministers at the beginning

525889694
05:18:21.831 --> 05:18:25.243
of the debate say that Ministers
are working hard and that we will,

1196315567
05:18:25.244 --> 05:18:27.501
in due course, see
a defence readiness Bill,

3628168495
05:18:27.501 --> 05:18:29.807
because the legal
and institutional framework

161428018
05:18:29.808 --> 05:18:31.361
for defence readiness matters.

2627488195
05:18:31.362 --> 05:18:34.549
And I think we all want to
see that bill come forward.

469919501
05:18:34.550 --> 05:18:36.857
So, Madam Deputy Speaker,
I am by temperament

306119296
05:18:36.858 --> 05:18:39.165
an impatient person when
it comes to defence,

3810379608
05:18:39.166 --> 05:18:42.232
as you'll be impatient for
me to finish the speech,

2313099448
05:18:42.233 --> 05:18:45.584
but the threats are not waiting
for us, and I am a fair person.

426288808
05:18:45.585 --> 05:18:48.095
And it is only fair to
say, certainly in my view,

1262712015
05:18:48.096 --> 05:18:50.001
that the government is doing serious,

522018320
05:18:50.001 --> 05:18:53.362
sustained work for the renewal
and rebuilding of our armed forces,

3864189060
05:18:53.363 --> 05:18:56.070
restoring our industrial
base and making Britain once

4108674308
05:18:56.071 --> 05:18:58.327
again a country capable
of defending itself.

2408569644
05:18:58.328 --> 05:19:00.736
And I certainly hope that
the years the locusts

1392282888
05:19:00.737 --> 05:19:05.393
have eaten are hopefully behind us.

371652131
05:19:05.394 --> 05:19:05.845
>> Yeah.

2622504844
05:19:05.846 --> 05:19:07.550
>> Martin Wrigley Deputy Speaker.

2936744383
05:19:07.551 --> 05:19:09.959
>> It's been a very
interesting set of debates.

1615854931
05:19:09.960 --> 05:19:13.483
>> Today and interesting
speeches from many people.

3881909059
05:19:13.483 --> 05:19:15.390
I, too, am fully behind the increased

2956818264
05:19:16.831 --> 05:19:18.887
and rapid increase in funds for defence,

887214631
05:19:18.888 --> 05:19:23.239
and I wish to add my thanks
to our serving personnel.

3292396248
05:19:23.240 --> 05:19:25.646
The defence readiness
actually requires a whole

1053006873
05:19:25.835 --> 05:19:27.989
society response and sovereign capability,

4293700839
05:19:27.990 --> 05:19:31.034
and across a wide range of
issues in our technologies,

1765843841
05:19:32.831 --> 05:19:35.084
defence, infrastructure,
housing regulation.

480726324
05:19:35.085 --> 05:19:37.084
The same pattern keeps appearing.

2410066591
05:19:37.085 --> 05:19:39.796
Services and systems
that are set up to serve

2607510160
05:19:39.797 --> 05:19:43.883
the public gradually drift
away from having purpose,

3031628412
05:19:43.884 --> 05:19:46.485
to simply extracting rents and our time

2626891109
05:19:46.486 --> 05:19:50.131
all wrapped up in a bureaucratic mess.

2608216499
05:19:50.132 --> 05:19:52.337
The overriding demand
for quarterly profits

3515252518
05:19:52.836 --> 05:19:54.941
and denial of early intervention instead,

1008972887
05:19:54.942 --> 05:19:57.148
rationing resources at
the point of maximum

2354508332
05:19:57.149 --> 05:20:00.172
need have driven perverse outcomes.

4192289492
05:20:00.173 --> 05:20:01.225
In strategic change.

379492069
05:20:01.226 --> 05:20:04.095
We are renting our entire
economy to ourselves.

216904348
05:20:04.096 --> 05:20:06.303
We are wasting it on
our own bureaucracies.

558496853
05:20:06.304 --> 05:20:09.796
Whilst too often the gains
are captured elsewhere,

4131122269
05:20:09.797 --> 05:20:13.235
we need to move back to something much

1898595400
05:20:13.236 --> 05:20:16.447
more fundamental an economy
and a set of systems that we build,

2418770516
05:20:17.835 --> 05:20:19.036
understand and control.

3771718569
05:20:19.037 --> 05:20:22.634
This means having real capability
on sovereign technology,

685684696
05:20:22.635 --> 05:20:24.987
on UK business and intellectual property,

33770311
05:20:24.988 --> 05:20:28.536
and a resilient defence and security.

2194584323
05:20:28.536 --> 05:20:29.840
But this is not abstract.

359326179
05:20:29.842 --> 05:20:34.451
It is directly connected to whether
this country is affordable,

2170498629
05:20:34.452 --> 05:20:36.509
liveable and works for the people in it.

599167149
05:20:36.791 --> 05:20:39.147
Ultimately, this is about
the social contract.

3283607731
05:20:39.148 --> 05:20:41.391
My constituents need to know that

4196032697
05:20:41.392 --> 05:20:43.795
the systems they rely on public services,

3479515540
05:20:43.796 --> 05:20:48.092
housing or business using buses
and trains have purpose to the people,

2158876392
05:20:48.093 --> 05:20:51.745
not just bottom lines to fill
that they are designed in their

1030066312
05:20:51.746 --> 05:20:54.637
interest and will continue
to work for them over time.

969477207
05:20:54.638 --> 05:20:59.638
And I want to use a single example,
the Palantir contract with the NHS,

1327537527
05:20:59.639 --> 05:21:04.190
because it highlights in one place
how we have got it all wrong.

3811458829
05:21:04.191 --> 05:21:08.095
We have a major national system
handling highly sensitive personal

4069658011
05:21:08.096 --> 05:21:11.206
data procured in a way where
the model is subscription based,

3952299461
05:21:11.207 --> 05:21:14.789
not delivery based, where the intellectual

4104706145
05:21:14.790 --> 05:21:16.233
property wrapped up in know

2702189448
05:21:16.233 --> 05:21:22.290
how much of which is built, does
not sit clearly with the public.

627743568
05:21:22.291 --> 05:21:25.943
Where we become dependent on
a single supplier over time.

2676458657
05:21:25.944 --> 05:21:30.286
That is not just a procurement
question, it's a question of control,

1652878830
05:21:30.287 --> 05:21:31.842
resilience and long term cost.

4012307914
05:21:31.843 --> 05:21:33.246
From a systems perspective,

915443130
05:21:33.247 --> 05:21:35.937
it creates lock in from
an economic perspective,

3424548863
05:21:35.938 --> 05:21:40.295
it allows value to flow out
rather than being built here.

2166016845
05:21:40.296 --> 05:21:43.154
And from a national perspective,
it raises the question,

1712773127
05:21:43.155 --> 05:21:45.891
what happens if that
capability is withdrawn,

711855563
05:21:45.892 --> 05:21:50.988
restricted, or simply becomes
too expensive to change?

2542095102
05:21:50.989 --> 05:21:55.081
We have British firms, British
engineers and a strong open

937016208
05:21:55.082 --> 05:21:58.351
source capability who could
deliver these systems.

137548515
05:21:58.352 --> 05:22:00.660
So the issue is not
capability, it is choice.

3976505619
05:22:00.793 --> 05:22:05.938
We cannot make the same mistake
with the new single patient record

4082592564
05:22:05.939 --> 05:22:09.498
specified in the forthcoming
health bill in the King's Speech.

3195371001
05:22:09.499 --> 05:22:12.606
That should be transformational,
allowing access to patients,

2790426397
05:22:13.836 --> 05:22:15.890
patients details wherever they originate

3738930516
05:22:15.891 --> 05:22:18.191
and must be a sovereign capability.

684556892
05:22:18.192 --> 05:22:18.492
Yeah.

797321524
05:22:18.493 --> 05:22:21.643
The same principle applies
to businesses more broadly.

1575197991
05:22:21.644 --> 05:22:26.250
Markets should reward value
creation, but too often now

929664957
05:22:26.251 --> 05:22:29.141
the incentive cause causes
value to be extracted.

2681715028
05:22:30.835 --> 05:22:33.089
Instead, whether through
monopoly positions,

3870382077
05:22:33.090 --> 05:22:35.750
weak regulation, or misaligned incentives.

611015739
05:22:35.751 --> 05:22:39.101
This is where the government has
a role not to replace markets,

1643195965
05:22:39.102 --> 05:22:42.541
but to make them work properly again.

3418026311
05:22:42.542 --> 05:22:46.285
In sector after sector, we see
systems that continue to function

250805701
05:22:46.286 --> 05:22:49.536
but no longer serve the people
they were designed for,

3087835148
05:22:49.536 --> 05:22:52.336
and it applies equally
to defence and security.

834580563
05:22:52.337 --> 05:22:56.188
Resilience is not just about
spending levels, it's about design.

1327060162
05:22:56.189 --> 05:22:59.641
It's about ensuring that we do
not build national capability

4057129923
05:22:59.642 --> 05:23:02.497
on systems that can
fail at a single point,

168255595
05:23:02.498 --> 05:23:06.637
whether that's a supply
chain, a digital platform,

1058174079
05:23:06.638 --> 05:23:08.796
or a dependency on external actors.

2893322644
05:23:08.797 --> 05:23:11.888
Sovereign capability is
not an abstract concept.

2356935943
05:23:11.889 --> 05:23:14.941
It's the practical ability
to continue operating

1429812676
05:23:14.942 --> 05:23:18.385
when conditions are difficult.

332656984
05:23:18.386 --> 05:23:21.244
It's the ability to serve our
country, our constituents,

2892043413
05:23:21.245 --> 05:23:23.551
through thick and thin,
whatever the weather.

38001447
05:23:23.552 --> 05:23:25.256
Madam Deputy Speaker, what links?

2792597569
05:23:25.257 --> 05:23:30.692
All of this is simple when incentives
drift, when cost control is lost,

1885136547
05:23:30.693 --> 05:23:34.741
when systems become extractive,
the societal contract begins to fail.

2502951898
05:23:34.742 --> 05:23:36.347
We have talent in this country.

2154175768
05:23:36.348 --> 05:23:37.551
We have the capability.

1796650054
05:23:37.552 --> 05:23:39.852
The question is whether
we choose to use it,

3035651773
05:23:39.853 --> 05:23:43.102
because in the end, I want
to see systems that work,

2821684950
05:23:43.103 --> 05:23:48.185
and I want to see a social
contract that people can trust.

274825347
05:23:48.186 --> 05:23:50.142
The King's Speech does not not address

4215144498
05:23:50.840 --> 05:23:52.592
sufficiently sovereign capability,

2230365871
05:23:52.593 --> 05:23:55.845
and it lacks the ambition
and the government needs to go

4185305561
05:23:55.846 --> 05:24:00.969
further and faster for us
to truly be defence ready.

3388680043
05:24:00.970 --> 05:24:04.192
>> Richard Baker thank
you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

4124590192
05:24:04.835 --> 05:24:06.941
Earlier this month, I joined the workers,

250740519
05:24:06.942 --> 05:24:11.053
the apprentices and management at
the metal yard in my constituency,

3147744146
05:24:11.054 --> 05:24:17.691
where they christened
the seahorse barge 85m long,

1924666865
05:24:17.692 --> 05:24:21.194
25m wide, weighing
approximately 1400 tonnes.

278746810
05:24:21.195 --> 05:24:23.099
Seahorse is an impressive achievement

2056711999
05:24:23.100 --> 05:24:25.207
and will play a critical role in enabling

3415227763
05:24:25.208 --> 05:24:30.590
the construction of the Royal Navy's
three fleet solid support ships.

2073753886
05:24:30.590 --> 05:24:32.548
The sun was shining on metal that day.

3940937305
05:24:32.549 --> 05:24:36.111
The fourth was sparkling and it was
fantastic to join with the workers

29224067
05:24:36.112 --> 05:24:40.451
who were rightly proud of
delivering this project on time,

130869735
05:24:40.452 --> 05:24:42.458
on Budget and particularly to hear from

1702629923
05:24:42.459 --> 05:24:44.944
the apprentices at
the yard about the skills

1463008562
05:24:44.945 --> 05:24:47.842
and experience they gained
from being involved

2580988918
05:24:47.843 --> 05:24:51.642
and now their hopes for
the future as well.

612675422
05:24:51.643 --> 05:24:53.651
A day of pride and joy for the workers.

515363663
05:24:53.839 --> 05:24:57.340
And what a contrast to my
first visit at the yard.

4127815067
05:24:57.340 --> 05:25:01.444
Only a few days after I was
elected to this place,

206076123
05:25:01.445 --> 05:25:04.647
then Harland and Wolff had
fallen into administration.

1070747698
05:25:04.648 --> 05:25:07.195
The future of the yard and its skilled

506683304
05:25:07.196 --> 05:25:09.101
workforce was under very real threat.

1820008078
05:25:09.102 --> 05:25:11.108
But it was Labour Ministers who stepped

128472350
05:25:11.108 --> 05:25:15.144
in and worked with the UK to save metal

2305858759
05:25:15.144 --> 05:25:19.196
and three other yards
across the United Kingdom,

457885108
05:25:19.197 --> 05:25:21.289
and metal had reaped the rewards.

893056025
05:25:21.290 --> 05:25:24.138
Where there was once
a bleak future for the yard.

2983560988
05:25:24.139 --> 05:25:29.093
Now we see investment and opportunity
in a community where too

116111930
05:25:29.094 --> 05:25:32.388
many people and too many
families are still struggling.

3509789154
05:25:32.389 --> 05:25:36.189
And since acquiring metal,

296387034
05:25:36.190 --> 05:25:38.697
Navantia has grown
the workforce from 180 to 260.

525834635
05:25:38.698 --> 05:25:43.787
It's now on recruitment drive
to fill a further 110 roles.

4176241795
05:25:43.789 --> 05:25:46.586
This includes recruiting
50 more apprentices to

1169086503
05:25:46.587 --> 05:25:48.894
join the existing 54
apprentices at the yard.

2987474621
05:25:48.894 --> 05:25:53.185
Brilliant opportunities for young people

414222928
05:25:53.186 --> 05:25:54.992
from the local area for the future.

3346539825
05:25:54.993 --> 05:25:57.394
And the UK has invested Â£27 million in

1527038534
05:25:57.394 --> 05:26:01.122
upgrading the yard and its facilities.

698916468
05:26:01.123 --> 05:26:04.132
This investment has turned
around the fortunes of the yard,

1944500579
05:26:04.133 --> 05:26:08.597
which has now won a further two
contracts for marine infrastructure,

3863354440
05:26:08.598 --> 05:26:11.356
which the workforce will
deliver in the coming months.

2454588642
05:26:11.357 --> 05:26:13.664
And the transformation
of the yard means it's

4007698429
05:26:13.665 --> 05:26:15.723
ready to play a key role in the defence,

2949068522
05:26:17.839 --> 05:26:22.239
in the delivery of defence
contracts for the future.

4281898275
05:26:22.240 --> 05:26:27.090
Metal is a living example of what
can be achieved through defence

1697868198
05:26:27.092 --> 05:26:30.548
investment as an engine for
growth and of course, growth.

3868116536
05:26:30.549 --> 05:26:35.148
Growing our economy is at
the heart of this King's speech

4246344776
05:26:35.149 --> 05:26:37.746
yesterday I was delighted
to hear my right hon.

2436695796
05:26:37.747 --> 05:26:42.106
Friend the Defence Secretary
set out the measure of this

795778564
05:26:42.107 --> 05:26:46.435
ambition in his speech to
the Good Growth Foundation.

1986529281
05:26:46.436 --> 05:26:49.295
He has made it clear our
increased defence spending will

3695051169
05:26:49.296 --> 05:26:52.640
bring investment into
the British defence sector.

2713368955
05:26:52.641 --> 05:26:54.495
Scotland shows the difference which.

3160993885
05:26:55.843 --> 05:26:58.101
This can make a Â£10
billion deal with Norway

1126252892
05:26:58.102 --> 05:27:00.632
for frigates to be built on the Clyde,

2015757115
05:27:00.633 --> 05:27:06.054
supporting 2000 jobs until
the end of the next decade,

3227085486
05:27:06.055 --> 05:27:08.754
and a further 2000 jobs
in the supply chain.

382782218
05:27:08.755 --> 05:27:11.845
How often we talked about
nostalgia for the great

89246205
05:27:11.846 --> 05:27:14.154
days of the Clyde
and fearing for its future.

552711565
05:27:14.155 --> 05:27:16.491
This government delivering contracts,

2959169695
05:27:16.492 --> 05:27:19.892
which makes that future
bright for Fife with

466955453
05:27:19.893 --> 05:27:24.471
the yard's methyl and also
at Rosyth, which my hon.

1831601798
05:27:24.472 --> 05:27:27.643
Friend the Member for Dunfermline
and a doughty champion.

1015068472
05:27:27.644 --> 05:27:35.143
For, as Ministers know, the Defence
Investment Plan will be vital

488865196
05:27:35.144 --> 05:27:39.800
for the future of our local area
and our defence businesses,

3591168641
05:27:39.801 --> 05:27:44.249
and I am as impatient as anybody
for the plan's publication.

1462393974
05:27:44.250 --> 05:27:49.989
But I also understand how important
it is to get the plan right and to

1444719692
05:27:49.990 --> 05:27:54.943
make sure it's ready with the right
strategy when it is published.

2286001138
05:27:54.944 --> 05:27:55.546
And my hon.

1866276948
05:27:55.547 --> 05:27:55.947
My hon.

3106912923
05:27:55.948 --> 05:28:00.450
Friend the the Secretary of
State is aware of my view that

1792384439
05:28:00.842 --> 05:28:04.300
a key part of getting that
plan right is securing

553391876
05:28:04.301 --> 05:28:09.349
work for methyl and for
Belfast through programmed

1809077314
05:28:09.350 --> 05:28:11.607
Euston to deliver new
dry docks for Faslane.

2445474429
05:28:11.839 --> 05:28:13.392
Because, Madam Deputy Speaker,

1969443841
05:28:13.393 --> 05:28:17.242
my experience of working
with the workforce,

3071115186
05:28:17.243 --> 05:28:19.801
with the management
and with the unions at methyl.

880102674
05:28:19.802 --> 05:28:23.493
Is that the case for
investment in British yards,

3299796017
05:28:23.494 --> 05:28:27.151
in British businesses and in
our workers is not only for

3044066011
05:28:27.152 --> 05:28:33.493
the benefits it brings to our
economies and our communities.

3270019941
05:28:33.494 --> 05:28:36.795
It is because the skills,
the capabilities and the experience

3137794299
05:28:36.796 --> 05:28:41.454
in our defence industry is
second to none across the world.

4124500855
05:28:41.455 --> 05:28:45.654
This is why it is the right
strategy for our economy,

1177730301
05:28:45.655 --> 05:28:48.243
for our armed forces.

95570686
05:28:48.244 --> 05:28:51.795
And at a time when we face
so much global uncertainty

3623644926
05:28:51.796 --> 05:28:53.551
for our national security as well,

843715348
05:28:53.552 --> 05:28:57.040
to take forward this strategy,
and I hope it's one

2966590689
05:28:57.041 --> 05:28:59.347
that the government will
continue and pursue.

2122460591
05:28:59.844 --> 05:29:01.698
>> Rebecca Smith thank you, speaker.

1241228468
05:29:01.700 --> 05:29:05.293
>> Now, we've heard plenty
this afternoon about the lack

835344020
05:29:05.294 --> 05:29:07.852
of a defence readiness bill
in this King's speech,

2327960214
05:29:07.853 --> 05:29:09.809
and we've heard lots about the yawning

272711894
05:29:09.810 --> 05:29:11.715
delay of the Defence Investment Plan,

537669261
05:29:11.715 --> 05:29:14.023
which has been rehearsed
over and over again.

3082218157
05:29:14.024 --> 05:29:17.135
But I just want to remind Ministers
of why this is important.

213051721
05:29:17.136 --> 05:29:21.445
It's important because SMEs right
across this country are waiting for

236383752
05:29:21.446 --> 05:29:25.097
this detail to be set out so that
they can plan for the future,

3684562968
05:29:25.098 --> 05:29:27.907
to provide the skills
and jobs that this country needs.

2286018268
05:29:27.908 --> 05:29:31.168
Now, we've heard already from
the Ministers that there have been

3642430108
05:29:31.169 --> 05:29:34.026
contracts awarded since this
government came into place,

1518414357
05:29:34.027 --> 05:29:37.137
but it's just not good enough
because it's not providing that

1096248375
05:29:37.138 --> 05:29:39.794
reassurance and security to
particularly these SMEs.

2830185525
05:29:39.795 --> 05:29:42.954
And whether that is constituents
of mine working in Portsmouth

1176797488
05:29:42.955 --> 05:29:45.110
or whether it's constituency businesses in

1803082305
05:29:45.111 --> 05:29:47.970
my South West Devon constituency
who are telling me that

2176441422
05:29:47.971 --> 05:29:50.379
they are waiting with
bated breath for the dip.

4157168153
05:29:50.380 --> 05:29:52.586
It is something that
is incredibly serious.

3017611322
05:29:52.587 --> 05:29:55.447
However, what I want to
focus on this afternoon

972512287
05:29:55.448 --> 05:29:57.455
is the two things Regulating for Growth

731298170
05:29:57.456 --> 05:30:01.045
Bill and also the challenge manufacturing

4148845055
05:30:01.046 --> 05:30:03.544
is facing around the steel industry now.

3789052861
05:30:03.545 --> 05:30:05.650
The King's Speech included the Regulating

2264305066
05:30:05.651 --> 05:30:07.356
for Growth Bill, you might argue.

523749252
05:30:07.357 --> 05:30:10.164
Madam Deputy Speaker, that's
actually quite a misnomer.

592352915
05:30:10.165 --> 05:30:13.373
Usually regulations have
the opposite effect and stifle growth.

1119436259
05:30:13.374 --> 05:30:16.083
However, I appreciate what
is trying to be done here,

2708595187
05:30:16.084 --> 05:30:18.793
and it's something that
I have long been calling for.

908010337
05:30:18.794 --> 05:30:22.304
With Plymouth named the centre for
Marine Autonomy by the government,

2260760869
05:30:22.304 --> 05:30:23.909
which is a welcome designation.

1452276184
05:30:23.910 --> 05:30:25.816
This means nothing if we can't change

3029684842
05:30:25.817 --> 05:30:28.072
the regulations that
enable these businesses

3070757119
05:30:28.072 --> 05:30:29.981
to do what they are setting out to do

3524831599
05:30:29.982 --> 05:30:31.887
and deliver for our defence industry,

992494566
05:30:31.888 --> 05:30:34.697
and I've raised this issue
time and time again in here.

55273276
05:30:34.698 --> 05:30:38.107
I've met with key stakeholders,
local businesses, industry experts,

3795664405
05:30:38.108 --> 05:30:41.566
the Marine Maritime Organisation
and spoken with relevant Ministers,

99202642
05:30:41.567 --> 05:30:43.876
and I know they have
been aware of this issue

2810425629
05:30:43.876 --> 05:30:45.632
for a considerable amount of time.

844692363
05:30:45.633 --> 05:30:49.247
But I have to say I am disappointed
with the speed at which things have

3128115386
05:30:49.248 --> 05:30:52.811
moved because at the end of the day,
marine autonomy waits for no man.

856696598
05:30:52.812 --> 05:30:55.521
It is progressing fastly
down the river, so to speak,

1214060971
05:30:55.522 --> 05:30:57.679
and we are not doing them any favours with

1097032097
05:30:57.680 --> 05:30:59.437
the amount of time this is taking.

1613504215
05:30:59.438 --> 05:31:02.848
It requires primary legislation,
which is why this bill is welcome.

3584891224
05:31:02.849 --> 05:31:05.507
But considering that
the government was able to push

4273428309
05:31:05.508 --> 05:31:07.965
through the two child
benefit cap being removed,

3898671166
05:31:07.965 --> 05:31:10.171
which was never programmed
into government,

2155865327
05:31:10.172 --> 05:31:12.177
I think it highlights their priorities.

2277368478
05:31:12.178 --> 05:31:14.635
That's why I tabled
a Marine Autonomous Maritime

244263760
05:31:14.636 --> 05:31:16.842
Vessels Regulation bill
in March this year,

1998371509
05:31:16.843 --> 05:31:19.200
because I was keen to
force this conversation,

553565072
05:31:19.201 --> 05:31:21.408
which seems to have had
the desired effect.

4150396223
05:31:21.409 --> 05:31:24.649
So I have to say, I'm going
to take some credit for this.

1338534423
05:31:24.650 --> 05:31:27.307
Regulating for Growth Bill
Madam Deputy Speaker Now,

1303573227
05:31:27.308 --> 05:31:30.820
I'm pleased to see that within
the government's write up of the Bill,

221180556
05:31:30.821 --> 05:31:33.879
as it stands already, there are
illustrations from overseas.

3581841210
05:31:33.880 --> 05:31:36.639
When I was recently at
Oceanology at the Excel Centre,

704636855
05:31:36.640 --> 05:31:40.439
I met with Canadians from Nova Scotia
who already have these regulations

810772492
05:31:40.440 --> 05:31:43.744
that we need here and which are
enabling equivalent marine

4096214793
05:31:43.745 --> 05:31:47.196
autonomy businesses to
literally about six weeks.

199778072
05:31:47.197 --> 05:31:50.358
It takes them to get the right
permissions to test and develop

2167145657
05:31:50.358 --> 05:31:53.418
and put this development of these
new vessels into practice.

2946411082
05:31:53.843 --> 05:31:56.400
Similarly, I met recently
with an American company

3983971469
05:31:56.401 --> 05:31:58.857
whose ambition for manufacture
of unmanned ships

1448871268
05:31:58.858 --> 05:32:01.465
would not yet be deliverable
in this country purely

3479711304
05:32:01.847 --> 05:32:03.853
because of our out of date regulations.

3543279322
05:32:03.854 --> 05:32:06.061
Now, local businesses,
many of whom I know,

478763278
05:32:06.062 --> 05:32:11.193
the Secretary of State even is familiar
with M zero USV, a pure ocean,

3159864863
05:32:11.194 --> 05:32:14.698
all cutting edge and all desperately
needing this legislation

1458042367
05:32:14.700 --> 05:32:17.055
to fully deliver on their
ambitious potential.

1937457232
05:32:17.057 --> 05:32:19.717
Now, a part of this is
the developing of test sites.

1244934073
05:32:19.718 --> 05:32:21.775
I believe that the coast off of Plymouth

626367949
05:32:21.776 --> 05:32:23.582
is the perfect place to pilot this.

841331330
05:32:23.583 --> 05:32:26.493
I don't think we need to wait
until it's something that's

3773197067
05:32:26.494 --> 05:32:28.802
ready for everyone to
have at the first time.

1655479644
05:32:28.803 --> 05:32:31.161
At the same time, I know
that Turnchapel Wharf

2130238649
05:32:31.161 --> 05:32:33.319
and the team behind Team Plymouth are keen

421215399
05:32:33.320 --> 05:32:35.428
to get going and I would be delighted for

155119452
05:32:35.429 --> 05:32:37.536
us to be that pilot if that were helpful.

3715997198
05:32:37.537 --> 05:32:39.956
So in terms of this bill, I simply call on

3539149872
05:32:39.957 --> 05:32:41.863
the government to make it a priority.

4073802959
05:32:41.864 --> 05:32:44.472
Let's see the Second Reading
soon after the Whitsun

2744734559
05:32:44.473 --> 05:32:46.330
recess so we can get moving on this.

2843864501
05:32:46.331 --> 05:32:49.843
And please, let's keep it agile
and flexible in its drafting to avoid

3160501340
05:32:49.844 --> 05:32:53.253
a repeat situation where regulations
can't keep up with technology.

1320942136
05:32:53.254 --> 05:32:55.247
Let's make sure this legislation is as

484586910
05:32:55.248 --> 05:32:57.649
good as it needs to be for the future.

4033984223
05:32:57.650 --> 05:32:59.003
Now, Madam Deputy Speaker,

247191235
05:32:59.004 --> 05:33:02.147
tomorrow sees the debate on
the steel nationalisation bill.

453036439
05:33:02.148 --> 05:33:03.853
But before that bill even begins,

2360909293
05:33:03.854 --> 05:33:06.813
we have another steel related
issue that has the potential

1972155877
05:33:06.814 --> 05:33:10.805
to significantly damage manufacturing
in the UK and by association,

3155310407
05:33:10.807 --> 05:33:11.959
our defence readiness.

2839473613
05:33:11.960 --> 05:33:15.102
The new UK steel regime kicks
in on the 1st of July.

262187688
05:33:15.103 --> 05:33:18.751
Now Plymouth is the home to
the Plymouth Manufacturing Group,

2237337045
05:33:18.753 --> 05:33:22.311
a cluster of manufacturing businesses
ranging from Alderman's tooling,

1121082078
05:33:22.312 --> 05:33:24.618
Lang and Potter, Olympus
and Plessey, Rittal,

3239853648
05:33:24.619 --> 05:33:27.900
CSM and Kawasaki Precision Machinery.

2807932170
05:33:27.901 --> 05:33:30.812
Now all of those businesses
have been part of a system in

1126998718
05:33:30.813 --> 05:33:33.672
Plymouth of manufacturing that
was set up after the war,

3492754926
05:33:33.673 --> 05:33:35.679
when the dockyard was seeing a decline.

3531349597
05:33:35.679 --> 05:33:37.485
Naturally, we've got this hub here,

1311862243
05:33:37.486 --> 05:33:40.346
but ultimately this this new
regime that is coming in on

615501280
05:33:40.347 --> 05:33:42.605
the 1st of July is already
seeing costs into

34380379
05:33:42.606 --> 05:33:45.012
the hundreds of thousands
for these businesses.

3232761036
05:33:45.013 --> 05:33:47.221
And in the case of one
of these businesses,

151462053
05:33:47.222 --> 05:33:50.159
at least Â£2 million
additional costs a year

3355312625
05:33:50.160 --> 05:33:52.065
simply because of these steel quotas.

3200755637
05:33:52.066 --> 05:33:54.273
Now, Madam Deputy
Speaker, I think you will

1297049077
05:33:54.274 --> 05:33:56.230
agree with me that whilst I understand

4109977656
05:33:56.231 --> 05:33:59.491
what the government is trying to
do to promote British industry,

3975586786
05:33:59.492 --> 05:34:02.100
if we are inadvertently
because I'm sure this isn't

4160221993
05:34:02.101 --> 05:34:04.304
deliberate impacting
British manufacturing,

1662021354
05:34:04.304 --> 05:34:07.515
where their supply chain can't
always be bought with, you know,

2393914204
05:34:07.516 --> 05:34:10.524
purely British Steel, we are
ultimately hindering the aims,

1809330101
05:34:10.525 --> 05:34:12.833
which I know the government
has to see growth

3844512674
05:34:12.834 --> 05:34:15.595
and to see jobs and to see
skills and manufacturing,

3357786851
05:34:15.596 --> 05:34:18.347
particularly around
the industrial strategy.

2594363855
05:34:18.348 --> 05:34:19.552
So I would just, again,

3284455033
05:34:19.553 --> 05:34:22.411
urge the Ministers here today
to listen to manufacturers

3019987353
05:34:22.411 --> 05:34:25.522
letters have gone to the Secretary
of State about this issue,

1863012057
05:34:25.843 --> 05:34:29.203
but it's vitally important that we
don't stick another hand behind

3348920324
05:34:29.204 --> 05:34:31.309
the backs of these manufacturing industry

1690077260
05:34:31.310 --> 05:34:32.914
professionals who want to help,

2402869325
05:34:32.915 --> 05:34:36.850
who want to make this difference, who
are passionate about what they do.

1242849601
05:34:36.851 --> 05:34:40.104
But if we start giving them
these additional costs on

2269358384
05:34:40.105 --> 05:34:43.402
top of the challenges they've
had around employment,

3350177532
05:34:43.403 --> 05:34:46.463
we're going to see the end of
manufacturing in this country.

587923172
05:34:46.464 --> 05:34:48.371
And I'm sure that is not what anybody

2180588887
05:34:48.372 --> 05:34:50.178
in this chamber today wants to see.

2366872738
05:34:50.179 --> 05:34:52.700
>> Sam Carling thank you,
Madam Deputy Speaker.

1894525833
05:34:52.701 --> 05:34:54.856
Today's debate theme is defence readiness,

13031700
05:34:54.857 --> 05:34:57.164
and I'm pleased that in
His Majesty's speech,

1149661092
05:34:57.165 --> 05:34:59.471
we heard the government's
clear commitment to

3290746244
05:34:59.472 --> 05:35:01.577
a sustained increase in defence spending.

972428451
05:35:01.578 --> 05:35:03.733
I also welcome the announcement of several

4293372534
05:35:03.735 --> 05:35:06.404
bills aimed at boosting national security.

3918887951
05:35:06.405 --> 05:35:08.460
Notably, the Tackling State Threats Bill

3642218516
05:35:08.461 --> 05:35:10.416
intended to create a tougher operating

335776358
05:35:10.417 --> 05:35:13.674
environment for foreign intelligence
services and their proxies.

836511782
05:35:13.675 --> 05:35:16.283
I also welcome the National
Security Bill to target

1960462441
05:35:16.284 --> 05:35:18.389
those inciting terrorism, be it Islamist,

772900852
05:35:18.390 --> 05:35:20.596
another religion, extreme
right wing or any

3364218604
05:35:20.597 --> 05:35:22.552
other form an extreme violence online.

3913078773
05:35:22.553 --> 05:35:25.598
We know many of those threats
are arising from overseas,

2180127865
05:35:25.599 --> 05:35:29.445
and their prevention is
a key part of our defence

1244507298
05:35:29.446 --> 05:35:32.053
and the establishment of
a defence housing service,

3103806915
05:35:32.054 --> 05:35:35.166
as laid out in the Armed Forces
Bill, will be of huge benefit

2295346687
05:35:35.167 --> 05:35:37.674
to the many military
families in my constituency.

2764887761
05:35:37.675 --> 05:35:39.883
We have to look after
the people who devote

4127026330
05:35:39.884 --> 05:35:42.298
their lives to serving our country.

3889716150
05:35:42.299 --> 05:35:44.506
On housing more broadly,
I'm pleased to see

1779042621
05:35:44.507 --> 05:35:46.612
the Commonhold and Leasehold Reform Bill.

3901706828
05:35:46.613 --> 05:35:49.774
Leasehold tenancies are a huge
problem for so many in my area,

4120994556
05:35:49.775 --> 05:35:52.936
and I look forward to a fairer
system that limits ground rent,

625074234
05:35:52.937 --> 05:35:55.093
as well as protecting my constituents from

3703614622
05:35:55.094 --> 05:35:57.149
being exploited by poor managing agents.

2156545466
05:35:57.150 --> 05:35:59.656
We need greater transparency
over service charges

1927506926
05:35:59.657 --> 05:36:02.114
and more powers for residents
to challenge them.

127511825
05:36:02.115 --> 05:36:04.522
I've also had constituents
approach me who have

1998121294
05:36:04.523 --> 05:36:06.780
been victims of domestic
abuse and have been

1696453776
05:36:06.781 --> 05:36:09.138
unable to remove their
abuser from their joint

1177946323
05:36:09.139 --> 05:36:11.346
social tenancy due to
a gap in legislation.

3259637155
05:36:11.347 --> 05:36:13.603
I am therefore delighted
that the government

451040930
05:36:13.604 --> 05:36:15.358
has listened to representations on

1715023825
05:36:15.358 --> 05:36:17.517
this and have set out plans for the Social

2755295557
05:36:17.518 --> 05:36:19.322
Housing Bill to address that issue.

1353729693
05:36:19.323 --> 05:36:21.682
That will be a real change
for my constituents

2591735026
05:36:21.683 --> 05:36:23.991
who have had to live in
fear and uncertainty,

2585516493
05:36:23.992 --> 05:36:26.197
and it ties into
the government's ambitions

4254748796
05:36:26.198 --> 05:36:28.405
to tackle violence
against women and girls.

475377164
05:36:28.406 --> 05:36:31.066
And on that note, there was
a serious issue I raised

2181488171
05:36:31.067 --> 05:36:33.273
during the debate on
the English Devolution

3504437802
05:36:33.274 --> 05:36:35.279
and Community Empowerment Act last year

2888607428
05:36:35.280 --> 05:36:37.235
around taxi and private hire vehicles,

3974688786
05:36:37.236 --> 05:36:39.643
where the ability of many
private hire vehicles

373136518
05:36:39.644 --> 05:36:41.249
to be licensed in any authority

3326590080
05:36:41.250 --> 05:36:43.307
in the country yet operate far away from

142574128
05:36:43.308 --> 05:36:45.062
the authority which licenses them,

2883809482
05:36:45.063 --> 05:36:47.870
is creating an environment
which allows shopping around

3819298189
05:36:47.871 --> 05:36:50.276
for lower standards
affecting passenger safety,

1143256576
05:36:50.277 --> 05:36:53.336
as well as driver security,
and penalising those drivers who

2079315317
05:36:53.337 --> 05:36:56.246
do the right thing and register
where they actually work.

536945505
05:36:56.247 --> 05:36:59.054
We've started to tackle this
issue through the national

4089564371
05:36:59.055 --> 05:37:01.713
minimum standards being
brought in through that act,

1244730347
05:37:01.714 --> 05:37:04.223
and I'm pleased to now see
in this King's speech,

904821916
05:37:04.224 --> 05:37:05.427
measures to go further,

1300994041
05:37:05.428 --> 05:37:07.885
the taxi and private hire
vehicle Bill announced

2681245926
05:37:07.886 --> 05:37:09.991
in His Majesty's speech will specifically

4102297492
05:37:09.992 --> 05:37:12.549
deliver on the recommendations
of the Casey Report

1099485878
05:37:12.550 --> 05:37:14.554
on child sexual exploitation and abuse,

3244567799
05:37:14.555 --> 05:37:17.112
such as clear licensing
requirements and stronger,

2589251927
05:37:17.113 --> 05:37:18.916
more consistent enforcement powers.

3035687541
05:37:18.917 --> 05:37:22.027
That will be a real positive for
both passengers and drivers.

1429284766
05:37:22.028 --> 05:37:24.336
I'm going to focus
the remainder of my speech

2252693683
05:37:24.337 --> 05:37:26.092
on the Regulating for Growth Bill,

2305392551
05:37:26.093 --> 05:37:28.549
something I hope will have
significant potential

3673216374
05:37:28.550 --> 05:37:30.705
to support British business and innovation

4116725170
05:37:30.706 --> 05:37:33.815
and make us much more competitive
on the international stage,

1602921933
05:37:33.816 --> 05:37:34.918
including in defence.

41881097
05:37:34.919 --> 05:37:38.580
I am pleased to see the government
explicitly referenced this bill being

2161052698
05:37:38.581 --> 05:37:42.040
used to enable better testing of
next generation defence technology.

3962121328
05:37:42.041 --> 05:37:43.946
Having a background in life sciences,

1953730537
05:37:43.947 --> 05:37:45.753
I'm keenly aware of the ever faster

1377444568
05:37:45.754 --> 05:37:48.812
progress our researchers are
making in developing new drugs,

28600595
05:37:48.813 --> 05:37:51.469
therapies and medical
technologies to fight disease.

2313399524
05:37:51.470 --> 05:37:54.479
British science is often world
leading and for good reason.

3598478745
05:37:54.480 --> 05:37:57.336
But translating conceptual
research into clinical trials

3231918716
05:37:57.337 --> 05:38:00.345
and eventually into products
and services is too difficult.

1275492229
05:38:00.346 --> 05:38:03.005
That problem is going to
increase as we move further

3367389913
05:38:03.006 --> 05:38:05.061
into the world of personalised medicine,

3303006827
05:38:05.062 --> 05:38:08.371
where we're using genetic data to
create hyper specific therapies

2748640200
05:38:08.372 --> 05:38:11.328
that will specifically target
individual patients cancers.

880040140
05:38:11.329 --> 05:38:14.187
This government led world first
regulations last July to

2774235177
05:38:14.188 --> 05:38:16.845
make access to these therapies
easier once approved,

570937712
05:38:16.846 --> 05:38:19.604
allowing them to be manufactured
closer to patients so

2696556064
05:38:19.605 --> 05:38:22.314
they can be delivered far
faster and save more lives.

3158899242
05:38:22.315 --> 05:38:24.572
So the appetite is there,
but the regulatory

504447251
05:38:24.572 --> 05:38:26.327
environment does need an overhaul.

1382275469
05:38:26.328 --> 05:38:28.685
That's not an attack on
our regulators either.

3577250094
05:38:28.686 --> 05:38:31.346
In my capacity as chair of
the all party group known

2222499563
05:38:31.347 --> 05:38:33.702
as the Parliamentary
and Scientific Committee,

3494617992
05:38:33.703 --> 05:38:35.658
the oldest APPG set up in 1939.

3319833356
05:38:35.659 --> 05:38:39.117
I regularly engage with research
scientists and professional bodies.

692524976
05:38:39.118 --> 05:38:41.475
We had a very well attended
discussion meeting

2562708645
05:38:41.476 --> 05:38:43.583
as early as recently as Monday this week,

427739597
05:38:43.584 --> 05:38:45.590
and they often express a lot of support

2660767696
05:38:45.592 --> 05:38:47.296
for our life sciences regulators,

2846405800
05:38:47.297 --> 05:38:50.158
most of which get it fully
back over off agenda and very

2601599568
05:38:50.159 --> 05:38:52.715
much want to be facilitators
rather than blockers.

3275717576
05:38:52.717 --> 05:38:55.976
But there's too much fragmentation
for that to work effectively,

1636161110
05:38:55.977 --> 05:38:58.451
to name just a few regulators.

3389477160
05:38:58.452 --> 05:39:01.309
We have the Medicines
and Healthcare Products Regulatory

2367927389
05:39:01.310 --> 05:39:03.415
Authority looking at safety and efficacy.

3020366075
05:39:03.416 --> 05:39:07.024
The National Institute of Care
Excellence examining cost effectiveness,

2342563382
05:39:07.025 --> 05:39:09.631
the Health and Safety
Executive examining hazardous

439656022
05:39:09.632 --> 05:39:11.986
substances and genetically
modified organisms.

2198685743
05:39:11.987 --> 05:39:14.744
The Human Tissue Authority
regulating human tissue use

2123609324
05:39:14.745 --> 05:39:17.902
the Health Regulation Agency
making assessments around ethics,

3957219735
05:39:17.903 --> 05:39:20.408
the Human Fertilisation
and Embryology Authority,

560533340
05:39:20.409 --> 05:39:23.469
which needs to sign off on some
stem cell research projects,

2977292669
05:39:23.470 --> 05:39:25.826
and the projects which
require animal studies,

3006610301
05:39:25.827 --> 05:39:29.490
need to go to the Animals in Science
Regulation unit in the Home Office.

2060001564
05:39:29.491 --> 05:39:31.045
That's not an exhaustive list,

2796701500
05:39:31.046 --> 05:39:33.203
and I haven't even touched on the plethora

1758348020
05:39:33.204 --> 05:39:36.666
of NHS bodies that have to give
approval for data sharing and usage.

1982973894
05:39:36.667 --> 05:39:39.024
Should research studies
need that, as many do,

573048328
05:39:39.025 --> 05:39:41.983
these are all looking at different
and important features.

1997026124
05:39:41.983 --> 05:39:44.090
But this is a crazy number of regulators.

3862722128
05:39:44.092 --> 05:39:45.947
It isn't that we need to deregulate.

2311307035
05:39:45.948 --> 05:39:48.907
Rather, we need to bring together
regulators to streamline

1249014845
05:39:48.908 --> 05:39:51.161
decisions without
compromising on standards.

268130281
05:39:51.162 --> 05:39:53.974
And I do hope the government
uses this bill to do that.

1192337381
05:39:53.975 --> 05:39:55.929
The individual regulators usually have

3061812303
05:39:55.929 --> 05:39:57.833
reasonable decision making timelines,

2900882910
05:39:57.834 --> 05:39:59.489
though some are prone to delays.

2884342984
05:39:59.490 --> 05:40:01.947
But in totality, having
to get so many decisions

4108583339
05:40:01.948 --> 05:40:04.304
slows down research
and innovation enormously,

2297705632
05:40:04.304 --> 05:40:06.510
particularly when
researchers have to apply

3974030745
05:40:06.511 --> 05:40:08.415
for clearance from them sequentially.

2421548162
05:40:08.416 --> 05:40:11.827
In most cases, though, this government
has taken the first steps to

751932983
05:40:11.828 --> 05:40:15.138
reduce that through a new combined
pathway between Nice and MHRA.

1312114084
05:40:15.139 --> 05:40:17.996
Regulators often also asked
for very similar information

3637360802
05:40:17.997 --> 05:40:20.302
in slightly different
formats and timetables.

2988428265
05:40:20.303 --> 05:40:23.311
That's wasting time and money
across industry and academia,

1494598297
05:40:23.312 --> 05:40:25.819
from knowledgeable people
who want to be cracking

2729883793
05:40:25.820 --> 05:40:27.524
on actually doing their research.

667321210
05:40:27.525 --> 05:40:30.335
So why can't we have a single
front door for approvals?

546305810
05:40:30.336 --> 05:40:33.093
There could be a unified
approvals application process

1163230437
05:40:33.094 --> 05:40:35.852
which collects all the relevant
information in one go,

772684464
05:40:35.853 --> 05:40:38.661
so researchers can submit one
application and then have

2855481220
05:40:38.661 --> 05:40:41.772
the regulators work out which
of them need to make decisions,

945826510
05:40:41.773 --> 05:40:43.729
ideally doing so in tandem rather than

558462228
05:40:43.730 --> 05:40:45.485
each waiting for the previous one.

668400989
05:40:45.486 --> 05:40:48.697
We could, of course, also look
to merge some of the regulators,

2169116666
05:40:48.697 --> 05:40:50.655
and I would not object to that either,

854896463
05:40:50.656 --> 05:40:52.561
provided we can keep their expertise.

3557311996
05:40:52.562 --> 05:40:55.670
So I'll be closely following how
that legislation progresses.

1067719062
05:40:55.671 --> 05:40:57.426
>> Claire Young you, Madam Deputy.

1758153252
05:40:57.427 --> 05:40:58.028
>> Speaker.

121808861
05:40:58.029 --> 05:40:59.233
>> It's a privilege to.

2111326350
05:40:59.233 --> 05:41:01.742
>> Speak in this debate
on defence and readiness.

2186268427
05:41:01.743 --> 05:41:04.851
Like others, I'm disappointed
with this government's delay in

3321253930
05:41:04.852 --> 05:41:07.809
bringing forward the long
promised Defence Readiness Bill,

1603546629
05:41:07.810 --> 05:41:10.268
both because of what that
means for the security

2914242749
05:41:10.269 --> 05:41:12.024
of our nation and the implications

255144521
05:41:12.025 --> 05:41:15.436
for the hundreds of my constituents
who work in the defence sector.

2809331243
05:41:15.437 --> 05:41:18.144
I want to talk, however,
about readiness more widely.

1350134650
05:41:18.146 --> 05:41:21.505
The government is right that energy
security is national security.

2140957787
05:41:21.506 --> 05:41:24.414
A country that cannot power
itself, cannot defend itself.

763864462
05:41:24.415 --> 05:41:27.072
I represent a constituency
that has the potential to

3460030746
05:41:27.073 --> 05:41:29.733
deliver a great deal of clean
power to support that.

2358176745
05:41:29.733 --> 05:41:32.742
However, this government is not
delivering on that promise.

987140393
05:41:32.743 --> 05:41:35.251
Ministers often speak of
a golden age of nuclear,

918049715
05:41:35.251 --> 05:41:36.606
and they named Sizewell C,

1827375938
05:41:36.607 --> 05:41:38.914
Hinkley Point C and Wylfa
I remind Ministers,

3565668915
05:41:38.915 --> 05:41:40.721
as I have done in previous debates,

2975394763
05:41:40.722 --> 05:41:43.832
that any honest list of that
Golden Age must include Oldbury.

4239372682
05:41:43.833 --> 05:41:45.487
Oldbury sits in my constituency.

1513202587
05:41:45.488 --> 05:41:47.394
It has a community that knows nuclear

3270993516
05:41:47.394 --> 05:41:49.501
and a site ready for the next generation.

1051911170
05:41:49.503 --> 05:41:51.560
But nuclear on the horizon does not help

196575026
05:41:51.561 --> 05:41:53.816
the constituents struggling
with their bill.

1972760485
05:41:53.817 --> 05:41:56.122
Today, energy prices are
crippling households

3819032734
05:41:56.123 --> 05:41:58.078
and the businesses that employ people.

1936916893
05:41:58.079 --> 05:42:00.860
In the past two years, my.

3271300066
05:42:00.861 --> 05:42:04.910
We've seen the loss of hundreds of
manufacturing jobs in my constituency

2105444641
05:42:04.911 --> 05:42:10.455
with the closure of the factory
and Billington steelworks.

3915106098
05:42:10.456 --> 05:42:13.209
Remaining businesses tell
me our energy prices

1680538440
05:42:13.210 --> 05:42:14.964
are deterring them from expanding.

506191559
05:42:14.965 --> 05:42:17.272
Decisions taken in
the last session have made

1223685900
05:42:17.273 --> 05:42:19.228
running a business harder, not easier,

2695044311
05:42:19.229 --> 05:42:21.136
and there is little sign in the bills

963914643
05:42:21.137 --> 05:42:23.305
proposed of the government changing

948791574
05:42:23.307 --> 05:42:26.567
that you cannot build resilience
in defence or in anything else.

668038645
05:42:26.568 --> 05:42:31.961
If you have hollowed out
the industrial base that sustains it.

511003653
05:42:31.962 --> 05:42:35.666
Without, local supply, chains will
be vulnerable to interference

1481879771
05:42:35.667 --> 05:42:39.265
in our energy grid and other
forms of parallel warfare.

2866426719
05:42:39.266 --> 05:42:43.253
More needs to be done
to ensure that we have

2418885106
05:42:43.254 --> 05:42:45.560
a skilled workforce to
support that industry.

2209621690
05:42:45.561 --> 05:42:47.867
Thornbury and Yate has
no dedicated technical

4008822771
05:42:47.868 --> 05:42:49.320
further education provision.

6747673
05:42:49.321 --> 05:42:52.458
Young people who want to train
as electricians, welders,

1140042761
05:42:52.459 --> 05:42:55.712
nuclear technicians,
wind turbine engineers.

1695947623
05:42:55.713 --> 05:42:57.417
It's a further education college.

1017808635
05:42:57.418 --> 05:42:59.073
You must travel out of the area,

678086274
05:42:59.075 --> 05:43:01.685
often by buses that do not
run when they need them,

102785323
05:43:01.686 --> 05:43:04.996
and the South West Aerospace
and defence cluster on our doorstep,

4126704419
05:43:04.997 --> 05:43:08.063
employing tens of thousands
in skilled, well-paid jobs,

2342315528
05:43:08.064 --> 05:43:11.557
stands ready to absorb local talent.

540550725
05:43:11.558 --> 05:43:13.614
We are not yet training the constituency

1550171355
05:43:13.615 --> 05:43:15.320
that sits between a nuclear site,

1248950399
05:43:15.321 --> 05:43:17.378
a tidal estuary and one of the country's

1111241628
05:43:17.379 --> 05:43:19.383
largest aerospace and defence clusters,

1291159996
05:43:19.384 --> 05:43:22.994
should be exactly the right place for
fresh technical skills provision.

1244734551
05:43:22.995 --> 05:43:26.206
Put the clean energy jobs of
the future in young people's hands

2297122562
05:43:26.207 --> 05:43:29.215
and let them tackle the challenge
from their own community.

3816387645
05:43:29.217 --> 05:43:32.808
Industry needs infrastructure
to support it too,

2149029577
05:43:32.809 --> 05:43:36.614
whether that's investing in
a permanent solution for the Severn,

1018635881
05:43:36.615 --> 05:43:40.567
the old Severn Bridge,

388611074
05:43:40.568 --> 05:43:43.562
which which at the moment is
not allowing HGVs over it,

2076236373
05:43:43.563 --> 05:43:46.355
having a massive impact on hauliers,

1452376774
05:43:46.356 --> 05:43:49.712
or whether that's investing in
redevelopment of Yate station.

919339644
05:43:49.713 --> 05:43:52.459
In what is a closing window of opportunity

486449254
05:43:52.460 --> 05:43:55.409
as the adjacent land has become available.

2896542142
05:43:55.410 --> 05:43:58.962
I've raised this to the Prime
Minister and I raise it again today,

1580805155
05:43:58.963 --> 05:44:03.113
and I would welcome a meeting
with the Rail Ministers.

271666381
05:44:03.114 --> 05:44:05.221
And we also need resilience in our public

1268996355
05:44:05.222 --> 05:44:10.259
services like education and health.

2427932909
05:44:10.260 --> 05:44:13.260
I've spoken a lot in this
House about send issues.

1844965581
05:44:13.261 --> 05:44:16.465
So I'll just I'll just say
now on health, on the NHS,

1884130286
05:44:16.465 --> 05:44:19.223
my constituents are not waiting
for structural reform.

2737110674
05:44:19.224 --> 05:44:22.134
They are waiting for a GP
appointment for an NHS dentist,

1997746741
05:44:22.135 --> 05:44:23.358
taking new patients,

2943157248
05:44:23.360 --> 05:44:26.621
and for elective procedures that
would let them go back to work.

2754559352
05:44:26.622 --> 05:44:30.215
Structural reform is necessary,
but it is not by itself sufficient.

806408268
05:44:30.217 --> 05:44:34.559
I urge Ministers to direct
the savings visibly to our constituents.

3682257670
05:44:34.560 --> 05:44:38.219
I will judge this government
by results in my constituency.

2543964989
05:44:38.220 --> 05:44:41.215
Can a young adult get a bus
to a technical college

3240901401
05:44:41.217 --> 05:44:43.762
and change a train for a clean energy job?

246028792
05:44:43.763 --> 05:44:46.070
Can a local business
afford the energy bills,

1244064541
05:44:46.071 --> 05:44:49.511
business rates and the tax
costs to hire people?

3886372479
05:44:49.512 --> 05:44:53.965
Can a constituent access the medical
care they need when they need it?

1741745120
05:44:53.967 --> 05:44:56.518
And can Oldbury be part of a golden age?

3461220712
05:44:56.519 --> 05:44:59.372
This government has promised?

1411637041
05:44:59.373 --> 05:45:02.631
Sadly, the government's proposals
in the King's Speech represent

2365578279
05:45:02.632 --> 05:45:05.718
more incrementalism at a moment
that calls for seriousness,

4161715368
05:45:05.719 --> 05:45:08.626
more fiddling around the edges
with consequences not just

2850014662
05:45:08.628 --> 05:45:11.447
for this government's
reputation for my constituents,

442595765
05:45:11.448 --> 05:45:13.956
living standards and
the security of the country.

336959545
05:45:14.858 --> 05:45:17.116
We're all sent here to
defend Amanda Martin.

1938463020
05:45:17.117 --> 05:45:18.922
>> Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

117887060
05:45:18.923 --> 05:45:21.514
It's always a privilege
to stand in this House

3871833075
05:45:21.515 --> 05:45:23.519
and represent the people of Portsmouth,

3823397314
05:45:23.521 --> 05:45:26.680
a proud naval city built on
service, innovation and hard work.

2677566119
05:45:26.682 --> 05:45:29.063
And as Portsmouth marks 100 years of city

4254344624
05:45:29.064 --> 05:45:31.410
status and a city that is bidding

661558438
05:45:31.411 --> 05:45:33.519
to become the first or the next and first

16525859
05:45:33.519 --> 05:45:35.225
ever southern UK City of culture,

1405489833
05:45:35.226 --> 05:45:38.085
there is a real sense of pride,
ambition and resilience.

601678126
05:45:38.820 --> 05:45:41.076
Defence readiness isn't
just about the hard,

1711131401
05:45:41.077 --> 05:45:43.011
shiny stuff, it's about everything.

14801762
05:45:43.012 --> 05:45:45.969
In Portsmouth, defence is not
abstract Westminster debate.

2444189206
05:45:45.970 --> 05:45:47.425
It's a part of our identity.

3022807277
05:45:47.426 --> 05:45:50.987
It's in our dockyards, it's in our
naval bases, our engineering firms,

4014103252
05:45:50.988 --> 05:45:53.818
our supply chains, our
communities and our homes.

1625417670
05:45:54.858 --> 05:45:57.467
Generations of people in
my city have helped defend

1193579328
05:45:57.468 --> 05:45:59.575
this country and continue to do so today.

3075618468
05:45:59.576 --> 05:46:02.233
But people in Portsmouth
also know what happens when

2808953500
05:46:02.235 --> 05:46:04.868
governments fail to back
British industry properly.

2800873365
05:46:04.869 --> 05:46:07.323
Under the Conservatives,
Britain and Portsmouth,

3671736215
05:46:07.325 --> 05:46:09.880
shipbuilding capacity was
absolutely hollowed out,

1423684868
05:46:09.881 --> 05:46:12.286
skills were lost
and opportunities were missed,

400612957
05:46:12.287 --> 05:46:15.259
and too many communities like
Portsmouth were left behind.

1762011099
05:46:15.260 --> 05:46:18.108
Despite the enormous
contribution that they have

2725950486
05:46:18.110 --> 05:46:20.367
made and can make to our
national community.

2707764116
05:46:20.858 --> 05:46:21.159
This.

2732479556
05:46:21.160 --> 05:46:24.219
This decline does not happen
overnight and reversing it will

440189539
05:46:24.220 --> 05:46:27.061
require long term commitment
and serious investment.

2847950053
05:46:27.062 --> 05:46:27.312
And.

1959754985
05:46:27.313 --> 05:46:28.415
Madam Deputy Speaker.

1147389383
05:46:28.861 --> 05:46:29.762
Tangible actions.

378806673
05:46:29.763 --> 05:46:33.223
That is why the second King's Speech
this Labour government matters.

2816980716
05:46:33.224 --> 05:46:36.028
Yes, we have delivered real
and lasting change for

3248934362
05:46:36.029 --> 05:46:38.587
our armed forces community
in the first two years,

1980940638
05:46:38.588 --> 05:46:41.447
with the largest pay rises for
armed forces in 22 years,

1554788199
05:46:41.448 --> 05:46:44.608
with 9 billion investment to
upgrade thousands of forces homes

2856900961
05:46:44.608 --> 05:46:47.568
to make them fit for service
personnel and their families.

3471509229
05:46:47.569 --> 05:46:47.969
Change.

3231860441
05:46:47.970 --> 05:46:49.224
I've seen it first hand.

760154520
05:46:49.225 --> 05:46:52.710
And this Madam Deputy Speaker,
alongside a housing officer,

1513141451
05:46:52.711 --> 05:46:56.564
every service family to improve
the processes for repairs and updated

2308172875
05:46:56.565 --> 05:46:58.922
rules that allow families
to decorate how they

1963116421
05:46:58.923 --> 05:47:01.472
wish and keep pets without
seeking permission,

232985564
05:47:01.473 --> 05:47:03.515
go some way to giving back.

2800629324
05:47:03.516 --> 05:47:06.623
We have established the Independent
Armed Forces Commissioner

3875607141
05:47:06.624 --> 05:47:09.631
with powers to investigate
general service welfare matters.

2204059398
05:47:09.632 --> 05:47:12.239
We've given new targeted
retention measures to keep

4207764117
05:47:12.240 --> 05:47:14.546
those with valuable
experience in the forces,

3986093937
05:47:14.547 --> 05:47:17.204
and we've expanded the early
years childcare funding

3838260901
05:47:17.205 --> 05:47:19.712
overseas to match the offer
available in England.

1659976991
05:47:19.713 --> 05:47:22.872
We've invested in cadets and we
continue to support specialist

1469648152
05:47:22.873 --> 05:47:26.030
mental health and homelessness
services, veterans and proudly.

663964440
05:47:26.031 --> 05:47:28.336
Madam Deputy Speaker,
through my persistence,

939717922
05:47:28.337 --> 05:47:30.945
I've secured an Operation
Valour Centre in my city.

4105505017
05:47:30.946 --> 05:47:33.508
A lot has been done,
but so much more is to do so.

851559106
05:47:33.509 --> 05:47:34.611
Madam Deputy Speaker.

3935853291
05:47:34.612 --> 05:47:34.862
Yes.

3278171794
05:47:35.858 --> 05:47:36.260
>> Hon.

3904417268
05:47:36.261 --> 05:47:38.117
Lady, for a very, very strong speech

1416051206
05:47:39.819 --> 05:47:41.825
and for for being a strong spokesperson

2917782263
05:47:41.826 --> 05:47:44.837
for for the Navy and for
